description: Amphid sensory organs are the sensory organs of nematodes.

name: neural rod
description: A solid rod of neurectoderm derived from the neural keel. The neural rod is roughly circular in cross section. Neural rod formation occurs during primary neurulation in teleosts. An intermediate stage in the development of the central nervous system present during the segmentation period; the neural rod is roughly cylindrical in shape, forms from the neural keel, and is not yet hollowed out into the neural tube.

name: neural fold hinge point
description: The median hinge point extends for the entire length of the neural tube, and the lateral hinge points do not form in the spinal cord region of the neural tube.

name: anterior neuropore
description: The neuropore at the anterior (rostral) end of the neural tube.

name: posterior neuropore
description: The neuropore at the posterior (caudal) end of the neural tube.

name: forebrain-midbrain boundary
description: An anatomical boundary that adjacent_to a forebrain and adjacent_to a midbrain.

name: hindbrain-spinal cord boundary
description: An anatomical boundary that adjacent_to a hindbrain and adjacent_to a spinal cord.

name: neuropore
description: A temporary opening leading from the central canal of the embryonic neural tube to the exterior.

name: lamina terminalis of neural tube
description: The anterior-most (rostral) portion of the wall of the neural tube, formed by closure of the anterior neuropore; the median strip of the anterior wall of the prosencephalon, which persists in a relatively unchanged state as the cerebral hemispheres grow out forward beyond the original anterior end of the prosencephalon.

name: eggshell
description: A product of the somatic follicle cell epithelium and a structure that supports the egg in a hostile environment, minimizing water loss whilst allowing gas exchanges essential for embryonic respiration.

name: metanephric ureteric bud
description: The portion of the ureteric bud tube that contributes to the morphogenesis of the metanephros.

name: ureter ureteric bud
description: The portion of the ureteric bud that contributes to the morphogenesis of the ureter. The ureter ureteric bud is the initial structure that forms the ureter.

name: tube lumen
description: A hole in a tube.

name: nipple sheath
description: A circular ingrowth of the epidermis around the region of the mammary sprout.

name: ectodermal placode
description: An ectodermal placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that is the primordium of many structures derived from the ectoderm

name: hair follicle placode
description: A bud-like thickening in the epidermis consisting of elongated keratinocytes, which at the distal end are in touch with numerous aggregated specialized dermal fibroblasts, the dermal condensate.

name: tooth placode
description: An tooth placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that will give rise to the tooth bud.
synonyms: ["dental anlage","dental placode","dental primordium","odontogenic placode","tooth anlage","tooth primordium"]

name: sebaceous gland placode
description: A sebaceous gland placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that will give rise to the sebaceous gland bud.

name: sweat gland placode
description: An sweat gland placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that will give rise to the sweat gland bud.

name: muscle structure
description: Muscle structures are contractile cells, tissues or organs that are found in multicellular organisms.

name: embryonic cement gland
description: A simple mucus-secreting structure that is positioned at the front of the embryo, attaches the newly hatched embryo to a support before the hatchling can swim well or feed, and marks the anterior-most dorsal ectoderm.

name: beak
description: The avian beak is an external anatomical structure, in the head region, that is adapted for feeding self and young, catching prey, probing, etc. It encompasses, but is not restricted to, the maxilla, mandible, maxillary ramaphotheca, mandibular ramaphotheca, nostril, nasal fossa, nasal bones, egg tooth and rictus. The beak, bill or rostrum is an external anatomical structure of birds which is used for eating and for grooming, manipulating objects, killing prey, probing for food, courtship and feeding young. .

name: descending thin limb
description: The descending thin limb is a part of the loop of Henle situated just after the proximal straight tubule (S3). It extends to the tip of the loop of Henle.
synonyms: ["descending thin limb of loop of Henle","loop of Henle descending thin limb","loop of Henle thin descending limb","pars descendens (tubulus attenuatus)","thin descending limb"]

name: renal connecting tubule
description: The connecting tubule is a tubular segment of the nephron; it connects the distal convoluted tubule to the collecting duct.

name: short descending thin limb
description: The short descending thin limb is the descending thin limb of a short nephron that has a squamous epithelial morphology.

name: long descending thin limb
description: The long descending limb starts in the inner stripe of the outer medulla and extends into the inner medulla.

name: early distal convoluted tubule
description: The early distal convoluted tubule contains DCT cells and is vasopressin-insensitive.

name: late distal convoluted tubule
description: The late distal convoluted tubule contains DCT cells and intercalated (IC) alpha and beta cells and is vasopressin-sensitive.

name: mesonephric epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a mesonephros.

name: metanephric tubule
description: A metanephric tubule is an epithelial tube that is part of the metanephros.

name: metanephric cap
description: The metanephric cap is formed by the condensation of metanephric mesenchymal cells surrounding the ureteric bud tip. Mesenchyme closely apposed to the tips of the buds is called cap mesenchyme; it will later go on to form nephrons etc.

name: metanephric epithelium
description: An epithelium is a tissue that covers the internal or external surfaces of an anatomical structure.

name: metanephric smooth muscle tissue
description: Any smooth muscle tissue that is part of a metanephros.

name: metanephric nephron
description: A metanephric nephron is the functional unit of the metanephros.

name: metanephric pyramid
description: Metanephric pyramids are the conical masses that constitute the renal medulla in a metanephros; they contain the loops of Henle and the medullary collecting ducts.

name: metanephric ascending thin limb
description: The metanephric ascending thin limb is a segment of a nephron tubule in the metanephros lying in the inner medulla that is permeable to ions but not to water and has a simple epithelium; active transepithelial solute transport is absent.

name: metanephric cortical collecting duct
description: The metanephric cortical collecting duct is the portion of the metanephric collecting duct that resides in the renal cortex.

name: metanephric descending thin limb
description: It extends to the tip of the metanephric loop of Henle.

name: metanephric distal convoluted tubule
description: The metanephric distal convoluted tubule is a portion of the metanephric nephron tubule that connects the metanephric loop of Henle to the collecting duct.

name: metanephric early distal convoluted tubule
description: The metanephric early distal convoluted tubule contains metanephric DCT cells and is vasopressin-insensitive.

name: metanephric glomerular mesangium
description: The metanephric glomerular mesangium is the thin membrane connective tissue composed of mesangial cells in the metanephros, which helps to support the capillary loops in a renal glomerulus.

name: metanephric late distal convoluted tubule
description: The metanephric late distal convoluted tubule contains metanephric DCT cells and intercalated (IC) alpha and beta cells and is vasopressin-sensitive.

name: metanephric long descending thin limb bend
description: The metanephric long descending thin limb bend is a part of the descending thin limb of a long nephron that lies beyond the prebend segment in the metanephros.

name: metanephric macula densa
description: The metanephric macula densa is an area of specialized cells in the distal tubule of the metanephros that makes contact with the vascular pole of the glomerulus.

name: metanephric prebend segment
description: The metanephric prebend segment is a part of the metanephric descending thin limb that lies before the bend and exhibits permeabilities characteristic of the ascending limb, especially negligible water permeability.

name: metanephric proximal convoluted tubule
description: The metanephric proximal convoluted tubule is the most proximal portion of the metanephric proximal tubule and extends from the metanephric glomerular capsule to the metanephric proximal straight tubule.

name: metanephric proximal straight tubule
description: The metanephric proximal straight tubule is the part of the metanephric descending limb that extends from the metanephric proximal convoluted tubule to the metanephric descending thin tubule.

name: metanephric S1
description: The S1 portion is the initial portion of the metanephric proximal convoluted tubule and is responsible for avid reabsorption of water and solutes.

name: metanephric thick ascending limb
description: At the macula densa, the thick ascending limb connects to the distal convoluted tubule.

name: metanephric distal tubule
description: The metanephric distal tubule is a metanephric nephron tubule that begins at the metanephric macula densa and extends to the metanephric connecting tubule.

name: metanephric loop of Henle
description: The metanephric loop of Henle is a metanephric nephron tubule that connects the proximal convoluted tubule to the distal convoluted tubule in the metanephros.

name: metanephric long nephron
description: Long nephrons are associated with juxtamedullary glomeruli and extend into the inner medulla in the metanephros.

name: metanephric glomerulus vasculature
description: The metanephric glomerulus vasculature is composed of the tubule structures that carry blood or lymph in the metanephric glomerulus.

name: metanephric nephron epithelium
description: The metanephric nephron epithelium is a tissue that covers the surface of a nephron in the metanephros.

name: metanephric glomerular epithelium
description: A metanephric glomerular visceral epithelial cell is a specialized epithelial cell that contains 'feet' that interdigitate with the 'feet' of other glomerular epithelial cells in the metanephros.

name: metanephric glomerular endothelium
description: The metanephric glomerular endothelium is an epithelial tissue that covers the internal surfaces of the glomerulus of the metanephros.

name: metanephric capsule
description: The metanephric capsule is the tough fibrous layer surrounding the metanephros, covered in a thick layer of perinephric adipose tissue. It provides some protection from trauma and damage.

name: metanephric short nephron
description: Short nephrons are associated with mid-cortical and superficial glomeruli, are situated entirely in the outer medulla, and have no thin ascending limb.

name: metanephric short descending thin limb
description: The metanephric short descending thin limb is the descending thin limb of a short nephron in the metanephros that has a squamous epithelial morphology.

name: metanephric glomerular capillary
description: This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts.

name: metanephric comma-shaped body
description: The metanephric comma-shaped body is the precursor structure to the metanephric S-shaped body that contributes to the morphogenesis of a nephron in the metanephros.

name: metanephric nephron tubule
description: A metanephric nephron tubule is an epithelial tube that is part of the metanephric nephron, the functional part of the metanephros.

name: metanephric renal vesicle
description: The renal vesicle is the primordial structure of the metanephric nephron epithelium, and is formed by the condensation of mesenchymal cells.

name: metanephric S-shaped body
description: The metanephric S-shaped body is the successor of the metanephric comma-shaped body that contributes to the morphogenesis of a nephron in the metanephros.

name: metanephric connecting tubule
description: The metanephric connecting tubule is a tubular segment of the metanephric nephron; it connects the distal convoluted tubule to the collecting duct in the metanephros.

name: metanephric proximal tubule
description: The metanephric proximal tubule is a metanephric nephron tubule that connects Bowman's capsule to the descending thin limb of the loop of Henle in the metanephros. It has a brush border epithelial morphology.

name: epithelial bud
description: A bud is a protrusion that forms from an epithelial sheet by localized folding.

name: epithelial cord
description: A cord of epithelial cells without a lumen and usually several cells thick.

name: open tracheal system
description: An open tracheal system is a respiratory system, a branched network of epithelial tubes that supplies oxygen to target tissues via spiracles. An example of this is found in Drosophila melanogaster.

name: reproductive structure
description: Any anatomical structure that is part of the reproductive system.

name: epithelial fold
description: An epithelial sheet bent on a linear axis.

name: parenchyma of central nervous system
description: The functional tissue of the central nervous system consisting of neurons and glial cells.
synonyms: ["central nervous system parenchyma","CNS parenchyma","parenchyma of central nervous system","parenchyma of CNS"]

name: pyramid of medulla oblongata
description: The anterior or ventral portion of the medulla oblongata is named the pyramid and lies between the anterior median fissure and the antero-lateral sulcus. Its upper end is slightly constricted, and between it and the pons the fibers of the abducent nerve emerge; a little below the pons it becomes enlarged and prominent, and finally tapers into the anterior funiculus of the medulla spinalis, with which, at first sight, it appears to be directly continuous.
synonyms: ["lobule VIII of Larsell","medullary pyramid","pyramid of medulla","pyramid of medulla oblongata","pyramis (medullae oblongatae)","pyramis bulbi","pyramis medullae oblongatae"]

name: vestigial structure
description: A remnant structure from earlier development or evolution.

name: pelvic spur
description: Pelvic spurs are the externally visible portion of the vestigial remnants of legs found on each side of the vent in primitive snakes, such as boas and pythons. The remnants of a pelvis and femur, which have no connection with the spine, simply 'float' in the muscle mass. The femur protrudes from the snake's body and is covered by a corneal spur, which resembles a claw. Males' spurs are generally longer and more pointed than females', and are used for clasping and tickling during courtship and mating, as well as combat with other males in some species

name: multi cell part structure
description: A structure consisting of multiple cell components but which is not itself a cell and does not have (complete) cells as a part.

name: ascending limb of loop of Henle
description: The distal part of the loop of Henle that is impermeable to water and actively pumps sodium out of the filtrate to generate the hypertonic interstitium that drives countercurrent exchange; it consists of an initial very thin segment lined by simple squamous epithelium followed by a distal thick segment lined by simple cuboidal epithelium.
synonyms: ["ascending limb","ascending limb of Henle's loop","loop of Henle ascending limb"]

name: papillary duct
description: The terminal portions of the medullary collecting ducts are the papillary ducts, which end at the renal papilla and empty into a minor calyx.
synonyms: ["papillary duct","papillary duct of kidney","renal papillary duct"]

name: renal interlobular vein
description: Any of the veins that parallel the interlobular arteries, receiving blood from the peritubular capillary plexus and empty into the arcuate veins

name: interstitial tissue
description: connective tissue between the cellular elements of a structure.

name: granulosa cell layer
description: A layer of the ovarian follicle that consists of granulosa cells.
synonyms: ["granulosa cell layer of ovarian follicle","membrana granulosa","membrana granulosa of ovarian follicle","ovary stratum granulosum","stratum granulosum of ovarian follicle"]

name: hepatic duct
description: Any portion of the ducts that carry bile from the liver to the common bile duct. This may include both intrahapetic components (parts of left and right hepatic ducts) and extrahapetic components (common hepatic duct, plus hilar portion).

name: abdomen element
description: An organ or element that is in the abdomen. Examples: spleen, intestine, kidney, abdominal mammary gland.

name: abdominal segment element
description: An organ or element that is part of the adbominal segment of the organism. This region can be further subdivided into the abdominal cavity and the pelvic region.

name: dorsal region element
description: An organ or element that part of the dorsum of the organism. Examples: spinal cord, vertebrae, muscles of back.

name: chest organ
description: An organ that is part of a chest.

name: tooth enamel organ
description: A circumscribed mass of ectodermal cells which bud off from the dental lamina; it becomes cup-shaped and develops on its internal face the ameloblast layer of cells that produces the enamel cap of a developing tooth.

name: trunk region element
description: An organ or element that part of the trunk region. The trunk region can be further subdividied into thoracic (including chest and thoracic cavity) and abdominal (including abdomen and pelbis) regions.

name: thoracic cavity element
description: An organ or element that is in the thoracic cavity. Examples: lung, heart, longus colli.

name: pelvic region element
description: An organ or element that is part of the pelvic region. Examples: reproductive organs (in some organisms), urinary bladder, bones of the pelvis.

name: thoracic segment organ
description: An organ that part of the thoracic segment region. This region can be further subdividied chest and thoracic cavity regions.

name: hair medulla
description: Innermost layer of the hair shaft.

name: renal medulla collecting duct
description: The portion of the collecting duct that resides in the renal medulla

name: obsolete cervical artery
description: An artery that is part of a uterine cervix.

name: deferent duct artery
description: An artery in males that provides blood to the vas deferens. The artery usually arises from the anterior trunk of the superior vesical artery. It accompanies the vas deferens into the testis, where it anastomoses with the testicular artery. In this way it also supplies blood to the testis and epididymis. A small branch supplies the ureter.
synonyms: ["arteria ductus deferentis","artery of ductus deferens","ductus deferens artery","vas deferens artery"]

name: ethmoidal artery
description: One of: anterior or posterior ethmoidal arteries.

name: thoracic vein
description: A vein that is part of a thorax.

name: deferent duct vein
description: A vein that is part of a vas deferens.

name: spleen germinal center
description: A germinal center that is part of the spleen. The spleen germinal center is located in a secondary B follicle in the white pulp of the spleen.
synonyms: ["germinal center of spleen","spleen follicle center","spleen GC","splenic germinal center"]

name: cervical mammary gland
description: A mammary gland that is part of a cervical region.

name: thoracic mammary gland
description: A lactiferous gland that is located in the thoracic region/breast.

name: distal straight tubule macula densa
description: A macula densa that is part of an ascending limb of loop of Henle.

name: trachea gland
description: a tubuloacinar seromucous gland that is located principally in the submucosa of the trachea. Excretory ducts from this gland pass through the lamina propria to the tracheal lumen.

name: larynx submucosa gland
description: A gland that is part of a larynx submucosa.

name: choroid plexus stroma
description: Stromal matrix surrounding blood vessels within the choroid plexus.

name: tonsil capsule
description: A capsule that is part of a tonsil.

name: right atrium valve
description: A valve that is part of a right atrium.

name: renal medulla interstitium
description: tissue surrounding the loop of Henle in the renal medulla.
synonyms: ["kidney medulla interstitium","renal medullary interstitial tissue","renal medullary interstitium"]

name: Leydig cell region of testis
description: The male gonad containing two functional parts: the SEMINIFEROUS TUBULES for the production and transport of male germ cells (SPERMATOGENESIS) and the interstitial compartment containing LEYDIG CELLS that produce ANDROGENS..
synonyms: ["interstitium of testis","interstitium of the testis","testis - interstitial","testis interstitial tissue","testis interstitium"]

name: outer renal medulla interstitium
description: A portion of interstitial tissue that is part of a outer medulla of kidney.

name: inner renal medulla interstitium
description: A portion of interstitial tissue that is part of a inner medulla of kidney.

name: kidney interstitium
description: The interstitial compartment of the kidney, comprising the extravascular intertubular spaces of the renal parenchyma, with their attendant cellular elements and extracellular substances, bounded on all sides by epithelial and vascular basement membranes.
synonyms: ["interstitial tissue of kidney","renal interstitial tissue","renal interstitium","renal stroma","stroma of kidney"]

name: optic eminence surface ectoderm
description: An external ectoderm that is part of a optic eminence.

name: midbrain subarachnoid space
description: A subarachnoid space that is part of a midbrain.

name: diencephalon subarachnoid space
description: A subarachnoid space that is part of a diencephalon.

name: hindbrain subarachnoid space
description: A subarachnoid space that is part of a hindbrain.

name: pancreas head parenchyma
description: A parenchyma that is part of a head of pancreas.

name: liver right lobe parenchyma
description: A parenchyma that is part of a right lobe of liver.

name: liver left lobe parenchyma
description: A parenchyma that is part of a left lobe of liver.

name: pancreas body parenchyma
description: A parenchyma that is part of a body of pancreas.

name: pancreas tail parenchyma
description: A parenchyma that is part of a tail of pancreas.

name: upper leg epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a hindlimb stylopod.

name: pedal digit epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a toe.

name: manual digit epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a finger.

name: upper arm epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a forelimb stylopod.

name: lower leg epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a lower leg.

name: medial-nasal process ectoderm
description: An ectoderm that is part of a medial nasal prominence.

name: optic eminence ectoderm
description: An ectoderm that is part of a optic eminence.

name: osseus labyrinth vestibule
description: A small, oval, bony chamber of the labyrinth. The vestibule contains the utricle and saccule, organs which are part of the balancing apparatus of the ear.
synonyms: ["bony labyrinth vestibule","inner ear vestibulum","osseous labyrinth vestibule","vestibule","vestibule of bony labyrinth"]

name: obsolete apical ectodermal ridge forelimb
description: A forelimb that is part of an apical ectodermal ridge.

name: obsolete apical ectodermal ridge hindlimb
description: A hindlimb that is part of an apical ectodermal ridge.

name: interventricular septum endocardium
description: An endocardium that is part of a interventricular septum.

name: lobar bronchus of right lung cranial lobe
synonyms: ["lobar bronchus of cranial lobe","right lung cranial lobe lobar bronchus","right superior lobar bronchus","right upper lobar bronchus","right upper lobe bronchus"]

name: lobar bronchus of right lung caudal lobe
description: A lobar bronchus that is part of a lower lobe of right lung.

name: bulbus cordis myocardium
description: A myocardium that is part of a bulbus cordis.

name: metanephric renal pelvis
description: A renal pelvis that is part of a metanephros.

name: stomatodeum gland
description: A gland that is part of a stomodeum.

name: yolk sac cavity
description: An anatomical cavity that is part of a yolk sac.

name: lesser sac cavity
description: An anatomical cavity that is part of a lesser sac.
synonyms: ["cavity of lesser sac","cavity of omental bursa","cavity of omental bursa viewed anatomically","lesser peritoneal sac","lesser sac cavity","omental bursa cavity"]

name: head mesenchyme
description: Portion of primordial embryonic connective tissue of the developing head, consisting of mesenchymal cells supported in interlaminar jelly, that derive mostly from the mesoderm and contribute to head connective tissue, bone and musculature in conjunction with cranial neural crest cells.

name: upper leg mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing hindlimb stylopod.

name: pedal digit mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing toe.

name: trunk mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing trunk.

name: manual digit mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing finger.

name: upper arm mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing forelimb stylopod.

name: lower leg mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing lower leg.

name: atrium cardiac jelly
description: A cardiac jelly that is part of an atrium.

name: ventricle cardiac jelly
description: A cardiac jelly that is part of a ventricle.

name: outflow tract cardiac jelly
description: A cardiac jelly that is part of a outflow tract.

name: renal cortex artery
description: An artery that supplies the renal cortex.

name: renal cortex vein
description: Artery that receives blood from the renal cortex

name: renal cortex interstitium
description: A compartment of the renal cortex situated between basement membranes of epithelia and vessels that contains two contiguous cellular networks in mutual contact, one formed by interstitial fibroblasts, the other by dendritic cells.

name: juxtamedullary cortex
description: The part of the renal cortex nearest to the medulla.
synonyms: ["inner cortex of kidney","inner renal cortex","juxtamedullary cortex of kidney"]

name: peritubular capillary
description: the tiny blood vessels that receive blood from the efferent arterioles of the glomerulus, and interact with superficial cortical nephrons allowing reabsorption and secretion between blood and the inner lumen of the nephron; peritubular capillaries are situated around the tubule and are at low pressure

name: nail bed
description: Region of skin beneath the nail plate.

name: dorsal skin of digit
synonyms: ["dorsal digit skin","skin of dorsal part of digit"]

name: dorsal skin of finger
description: A dorsal skin of digit that is part of a manual digit.
synonyms: ["dorsal finger skin","skin of dorsal part of finger","subdivision of skin of dorsal part of finger"]

name: dorsal skin of toe
description: A dorsal skin of digit that is part of a pedal digit.
synonyms: ["dorsal toe skin","skin of dorsal part of toe","subdivision of skin of dorsal part of toe"]

name: nail bed of finger
description: A nail bed that is part of a manual digit.

name: nail bed of toe
description: A nail bed that is part of a pedal digit.

name: ventricular system of central nervous system
description: A set of structures containing cerebrospinal fluid in the brain. It is continuous with the central canal of the spinal cord.
synonyms: ["CNS ventricular system","ventricular system","ventricular system of neuraxis"]

name: tela choroidea
description: A structure found in the walls of the ventricles of the brain, consisting of part of the meninges (pia mater in mammals) plus ependyma.

name: tela choroidea of midbrain cerebral aqueduct
description: Tela choroidea that lines the tectal ventricle.
synonyms: ["tela chorioidea tectal ventricle","tela choroidea of cerebral aqueduct","tela choroidea tectal ventricle"]

name: tela choroidea of fourth ventricle
description: Tela chorioidea that lines the fourth ventricle. The tela chorioidea of the fourth ventricle is the name applied to the triangular fold of pia mater which is carried upward between the cerebellum and the medulla oblongata. It consists of two layers, which are continuous with each other in front, and are more or less adherent throughout: The posterior layer covers the antero-inferior surface of the cerebellum. The anterior layer is applied to the structures which form the lower part of the roof of the ventricle, and is continuous inferiorly with the pia mater on the inferior peduncles and closed part of the medulla.
synonyms: ["choroid membrane","choroid membrane of fourth ventricle","tela chorioidea fourth ventricle","tela choroidea","tela choroidea fourth ventricle","tela choroidea of fourth ventricle","tela choroidea ventriculi quarti"]

name: tela choroidea of third ventricle
description: Tela chorioidea that lines the third ventricle. The part of the choroid plexus in relation to the body of the ventricle forms the vascular fringed margin of a triangular process of pia mater, named the tela chorioidea of the third ventricle, and projects from under cover of the lateral edge of the fornix. Blood is supplied by branches from the superior cerebellar artery.
synonyms: ["choroid membrane of third ventricle","tela chorioidea of third ventricle","tela chorioidea third ventricle","tela choroidea third ventricle","tela choroidea ventriculi tertii"]

name: tela choroidea of telencephalic ventricle
description: Tela chorioidea that lines the telencephalic ventricle.
synonyms: ["tela chorioidea of lateral ventricle","tela chorioidea of telencephalic ventricle","tela chorioidea telencephalic ventricle","tela choroidea (ventriculi lateralis)","tela choroidea of lateral ventricle","tela choroidea telencephalic ventricle"]

name: myelencephalon
description: The posterior part of the developing vertebrate hindbrain or the corresponding part of the adult brain composed of the medulla oblongata and a portion of the fourth ventricle; as well as the glossopharyngeal nerve (CN IX), vagus nerve (CN X), accessory nerve (CN XI), hypoglossal nerve (CN XII), and a portion of the vestibulocochlear nerve (CN VIII)..

name: embryonic tissue
description: A portion of tissue that is part of an embryo.

name: extraembryonic tissue
description: Portion of tissue that is contiguous with the embryo and is comprised of portions of tissue or cells that will not contribute to the embryo.

name: cerebellum lobe
description: A major subdivision of the cerebellum: anterior, posterior and flocculonodular
synonyms: ["cerebellar lobe","lobe of cerebellum","lobe parts of the cerebellar cortex"]

name: gonadal ridge
description: the elevation of thickened mesothelium and underlying mesenchyme found on the ventromedial border of the embryonic mesonephros in which the primordial germ cells become embedded, establishing it as the primordium of the testis or ovary

name: sex cord
description: Cordlike masses of epithelial tissue that invaginate from germinal epithelium of the gonad and give rise to seminiferous tubules and rete testes in the male, and primary ovarian follicles and rete ovarii in the female.

name: ovary sex cord
description: structures that develop from sex cords in the female. After further development they become the ovarian follicles.

name: testis sex cord
description: The testis cords are precursors to the rete testis. They play several different roles in the development of the male genitals.

name: skin of clitoris
description: A zone of skin that is part of a clitoris.

name: prepuce of clitoris
description: A retractable double-layered fold of skin and mucous membrane that covers the clitoral glans.
synonyms: ["clitoral hood","clitoral prepuce","clitoris prepuce","prepuce of female","prepuce of the clitoris","preputium clitoridis"]

name: male preputial gland
description: One of the sebaceous glands of the corona and neck of the glans penis.
synonyms: ["preputial gland","preputial gland of male","preputial gland of penis"]

name: female preputial gland
description: The paired, lobulated, modified sebaceous glands located on the side of the clitoris in female rodents; in contrast to the preputial glands in male rodents, clitoral glands are a minor source of olfactory stimuli contributing to sexual attractivity; unlike other sebaceous glands, they undergo progressive atrophy of the glandular portion with marked ductal ectasia as rodents age.

name: hypogastric nerve
description: The transition between the superior hypogastric plexus and the inferior hypogastric plexus.

name: submucous nerve plexus
description: the gangliated plexus of unmyelinated nerve fibers that ramify the stomach and intestinal submucosa

name: thyroid follicle
description: Discrete, cystlike units of the thyroid gland that are lined with cuboidal epithelium and are filled with a colloid substance, about 30 to each lobule.

name: blastema
description: A blastema is a mass of cells capable of growth and regeneration into organs or body parts. Historically blastema have been thought to be composed of undifferentiated pluripotent cells, but recent research indicates that in some organisms blastema may retain memory of tissue origin. Blastemata are typically found in the early stages of an organism's development such as in embryos, and in the regeneration of tissues, organs and bone. A regenerating tissue composed of a proliferative mass of undifferentiated progenitor cells from which new differentiated structures arise.

name: chorion-containing eggshell
description: An eggshell that contains chorion. An example of this is found in Drosophila melanogaster.

name: nephrostome
description: The nephrostome is the opening of the pronephros into the body cavity.

name: pronephric nephron
description: A pronephric nephron is the functional unit of the pronephros.

name: pronephric nephron tubule
description: The pronephric nephron tubule is an epithelial tube that is part of the pronephric nephron and connects the filtration unit (glomerulus or glomus) of the pronephros to the pronephric duct.

name: mammary placode
description: The mammary placode is a transient lens shaped structure that will give rise to the mammary bud proper.

name: mammary duct terminal end bud
description: A unique club-shaped epithelial structure that develops at the tip of the mammary duct at the onset of puberty under the action of circulating hormones.

name: alveolar primary septum
description: A primary alveolar septum is a specialized epithelium that surrounds the saccule as it forms.

name: alveolar secondary septum
description: A secondary alveolar septum is a specialized epithelium that subdivides the initial saccule.

name: endocardial endothelium
description: The endothelial lining of the endocardium.

name: pulmonary artery endothelium
description: An pulmonary artery endothelium is an epithelium that lines the pulmonary artery.

name: mesonephric collecting duct
description: The collecting duct is the final common path through which urine flows before entering the ureter and then emptying into the bladder.

name: mesonephric juxtaglomerular apparatus
description: The juxtaglomerular apparatus lies adjacent to the glomerulus and regulates kidney function by maintaining the blood flow to the kidney and the filtration rate.

name: mesonephric nephron
description: A nephron that is part of a mesonephros.

name: mesonephric mesenchyme
description: Mesonephric mesenchyme is the tissue made up of loosely connected mesenchymal cells in the mesonephros.

name: mesonephric macula densa
description: The mesonephric macula densa is an area of specialized cells in the distal tubule of the mesonephros that makes contact with the vascular pole of the glomerulus.

name: mesonephric glomerulus
description: The mesonephric glomerulus is a capillary tuft which forms a close network with the visceral epithelium (podocytes) and the mesangium to form the filtration barrier and is surrounded by Bowman's capsule in nephrons of the mature vertebrate kidney, or mesonephros.

name: mesonephric glomerulus vasculature
description: The mesonephric glomerulus vasculature is composed of the tubule structures that carry blood or lymph in the mesonephric glomerulus.

name: mesonephric glomerular epithelium
description: A mesonephric glomerular visceral epithelial cell is a specialized epithelial cell that contains 'feet' that interdigitate with the 'feet' of other glomerular epithelial cells in the mesonephros.

name: mesonephric comma-shaped body
description: The mesonephric comma-shaped body is the precursor structure to the mesonephric S-shaped body that contributes to the morphogenesis of a nephron in the mesonephros.

name: mesonephric nephron tubule
description: A mesonephric nephron tubule is an epithelial tube that is part of the mesonephric nephron, the functional part of the mesonephros.

name: mesonephric nephron epithelium
description: The mesonephric nephron epithelium is a tissue that covers the surface of a nephron in the mesonephros.

name: mesonephric renal vesicle
description: The renal vesicle is the primordial structure of the mesonephric nephron epithelium, and is formed by the condensation of mesenchymal cells.

name: mesonephric S-shaped body
description: The mesonephric S-shaped body is the successor of the mesonephric comma-shaped body that contributes to the morphogenesis of a nephron in the mesonephros.

name: mammary bud
description: A bulb of epithelial cells that forms from the mammary placode that develops into the mammary gland.

name: oral lamina propria
description: A lamina propria that is part of a mucosa of oral region.

name: chorioallantoic membrane
description: The chorioallantoic membrane is a vascular membrane found in eggs of some amniotes, such as birds and reptiles. It is formed by the fusion of the mesodermal layers of two developmental structures: the allantois and the chorion. Three different layers compose the chorioallantoic membrane; these are called the chorionic epithelium, the mesenchyme and the allantoic epithelium. Blood capillaries and sinuses are found between epithelial cells of the chorionic layer, allowing close contact (within 0.2 N<m) with air found in pores of the shell membrane of the egg. As a result, the chorioallantoic membrane allows exchange of gases, such as oxygen, to developing embryos. During embryonic development of birds, the chorioallantoic membrane also plays an essential role in bone formation by transporting calcium into the embryo from the eggshell. Chorioalloantoic membranes from developing chicken eggs are routinely used in biological and biomedical research to investigate development, angiogenesis, tumors, and to propagate and investigate viruses or helminths.

name: capillary layer of choroid
description: The capillary lamina of choroid or choriocapillaris is a layer of capillaries that is immediately adjacent to Bruch's membrane in the choroid.
synonyms: ["capillary lamina of choroid","capillary layer of choroid","inner layer of choroid proper"]

name: outflow tract of ventricle
description: A ventricular outflow tract is a portion of either the left ventricle or right ventricle of the heart through which blood passes in order to enter the great arteries. The right ventricular outflow tract (RVOT) is an infundibular extension of the ventricular cavity which connects to the pulmonary artery. The left ventricular outflow tract (LVOT), which connects to the aorta, is nearly indistinguishable from the rest of the ventricle.
synonyms: ["heart ventricle outflow tract","outflow part of ventricle","ventricular outflow tract"]

name: outflow tract aortic component
description: An outflow tract that is part of a aorta.

name: dorsal telencephalic commissure
description: A fiber tracts that connect the dorsal region of the two cerebral hemispheres and span the longitudinal fissure, including the corpus callosum and hippocampal commissure.

name: ventral commissure
description: The fiber tracts that connect the ventral region of the two cerebral hemispheres and span the longitudinal fissure, including the anterior and the habenular commissures.

name: malleus head
description: rounded portion of the malleus that articulates with the body of the incus.

name: cortical plate
description: The outer neural tube region in which post-mitotic neuroblasts migrate along radial glia to form the adult cortical layers.
synonyms: ["cerebral cortex cortical plate","CP","CxP","future cortical layers II-VI","neocortex cortical plate"]

name: peritoneal vaginal process
description: A peritoneal diverticulum in the embryonic lower anterior abdominal wall that traverses the inguinal canal. In the male it forms the tunica vaginalis testis and normally loses its connection with the peritoneal cavity; a persistent processus vaginalis in the female is known as the canal of Nuck.
synonyms: ["processus vaginalis","processus vaginalis peritoneus","saccus vaginalis","vaginal process of peritoneum"]

name: cerebellum vermis lobule VIIA
description: The folium vermis is a short, narrow, concealed band at the posterior extremity of the vermis, consisting apparently of a single folium, but in reality marked on its upper and under surfaces by secondary fissures. Laterally, it expands in either hemisphere into a considerable lobule, the superior semilunar lobule (lobulus semilunaris superior; postero-superior lobules), which occupies the posterior third of the upper surface of the hemisphere, and is bounded below by the horizontal sulcus. The superior semilunar lobules and the folium vermis form the lobus semilunaris.
synonyms: ["folium","folium of vermis of cerebellum","vermic lobule VIIA"]

name: cerebellum vermis lobule VIIB
synonyms: ["lobule VII B of vermis","neuraxis tuber","tuber of vermis of cerebellum","vermic lobule VIIb"]

name: ansiform lobule
description: A lobule comprising the greater part of the hemisphere of the cerebellum; its superior and inferior surfaces are separated by the horizontal fissure into major parts known as crus I (superior semilunar lobule) and crus II (inferior semilunar lobule).
synonyms: ["ansiform lobule of cerebellum","ansiform lobule of cerebellum [hVIIa]","lobuli semilunares cerebelli","lobulus ansiformis cerebelli","lobulus ansiformis cerebelli [h vii a]","semilunar lobules of cerebellum"]

name: paramedian lobule
description: The anterior portion of the posteroinferior lobule of the cerebellum, the posterior portion being the semilunar lobule inferior; the two are continuous with the tuber of the vermis.
synonyms: ["gracile lobule","hemispheric lobule VIIBii","lobule VIIIB (pyramis and biventral lobule, posterior part)","lobulus gracilis","lobulus paramedianus","lobulus paramedianus [hVIIb]","paramedian 1 (hVII)","paramedian lobule [h vii b]","paramedian lobule [HVIIB]","paramedian lobule [hVIIIb]"]

name: lobule simplex
synonyms: ["hemispheric lobule VI","lobule h VI of larsell","lobulus quadrangularis pars caudalis/posterior","lobulus quadrangularis pars inferoposterior","lobulus quadrangularis posterior","lobulus quadrangularis posterior cerebelli [H VI]","lobulus simplex","lobulus simplex cerebelli [h vi et vi]","posterior crescentic lobule of cerebellum","semilunar lobule-1 (posterior)","simple lobule","simple lobule of cerebellum","simple lobule of cerebellum [h VI and VI]","simplex","simplex (hVI)","simplex lobule"]

name: paraflocculus
synonyms: ["cerebellar tonsil","neuraxis paraflocculus","parafloccular lobule of cerebellum","paraflocculus of cerebellum","tonsil (HXI)","tonsilla"]

name: spermatic cord
description: The cord-like structure in males comprising the vas deferens and associated tissue that runs from the abdomen down to each testis.

name: spleen perifollicular zone
description: The compartment located between the marginal zone and the red pulp harboring scattered B and T lymphocytes.

name: malleus processus brevis
description: The projection extending from the base of the manubrium of the malleus which contacts the upper part of the tympanic membrane where the tympanic cavity makes a deep pocket (epitympanic pocket) surrounding the cartilaginous nodule.

name: malleus neck
description: The narrow contracted section of the malleus located between the head and the manubrium.

name: Rathke's pouch
description: A pouch of ectoderm that grows out from the upper surface of the embryonic stomodeum and gives rise to the anterior and intermediate lobes of the pituitary gland. In embryogenesis, Rathke's pouch is a depression in the roof of the developing mouth in front of the buccopharyngeal membrane. It gives rise to the anterior pituitary (adenohypophysis), a part of the endocrine system.

name: brain ependyma
description: the ependymal cell layer that lines the brain ventricles

name: ventricle of nervous system
description: A layer in the central nervous system that lines system of communicating cavities in the brain and spinal cord.

name: spinal cord ependyma
description: the ependymal cell layer that lines the spinal cord
synonyms: ["ependyma of central canal of spinal cord","spinal cord ependymal layer"]

name: inferior glossopharyngeal IX ganglion
description: The lower group of sensory neuron cell bodies associated with the glossopharyngeal nerve. It is situated in a depression in the lower border of the petrous portion of the temporal bone.
synonyms: ["extracraniale ganglion","ganglion inferius (nervus glossopharygeus)","ganglion inferius nervus glossopharyngei","ganglion of andersch","glossopharyngeal nerve inferior ganglion","glossopharyngeal nerve petrous ganglion","inferior ganglion of glossopharyngeal nerve","inferior glossopharyngeal ganglion","inferior glossopharyngeal ganglion of the glossopharyngeal (IX) nerve","ninth cranial nerve inferior ganglion"]

name: superior glossopharyngeal IX ganglion
description: The upper ganglion of the glossopharyngeal nerve. is situated in the upper part of the groove in which the glossopharyngeal nerve is lodged during its passage through the jugular foramen. It is very small, and is usually regarded as a detached portion of the inferior ganglion
synonyms: ["Ehrenritter's ganglion","ganglion superius (nervus glossopharyngeus)","ganglion superius nervus glossopharyngei","glossopharyngeal nerve jugular ganglion","glossopharyngeal nerve superior ganglion","intracranial ganglion","ninth cranial nerve superior ganglion","superior ganglion of glossopharyngeal nerve","superior glossopharyngeal ganglia","superior glossopharyngeal ganglion","superior glossopharyngeal ganglion of the glossopharyngeal (IX) nerve"]

name: vagus X ganglion
description: the group of sensory neuron cell bodies associated with the vagus nerve
synonyms: ["ganglion of vagus nerve","gX","right glossopharyngeal ganglion","vagal ganglion","vagus ganglion","vagus neural ganglion"]

name: inferior vagus X ganglion
description: the large group of sensory neuron cell bodies, anterior to the jugular vein, associated with the vagus nerve (tenth cranial nerve)
synonyms: ["ganglion inferius (nervus vagus)","ganglion inferius nervi vagi","ganglion inferius nervus vagi","ganglion nodosum","inferior ganglion of vagus","inferior ganglion of vagus nerve","inferior vagus X","nodose ganglion","tenth cranial nerve nodose ganglion","vagus nerve inferior ganglion","vagus nerve nodose ganglion"]

name: superior vagus X ganglion
description: the upper ganglion of the vagus nerve located at the jugular foramen
synonyms: ["ganglion superius (nervus vagus)","ganglion superius nervus vagi","superior ganglion of vagus","superior ganglion of vagus nerve","superior vagus ganglion","superior vagus X","tenth cranial nerve jugular ganglion","vagus nerve jugular ganglion","vagus nerve superior ganglion"]

name: olfactory lobe
description: The lobe at the anterior part of each cerebral hemisphere, responsible for olfactory functions.

name: hippocampus molecular layer
description: The most superficial stratum in the hippocampus. Here the perforant path fibers form synapses onto the distal, apical dendrites of pyramidal cells.
synonyms: ["hippocampal molecular layer","hippocampus stratum moleculare","molecular layer of hippocampus"]

name: hippocampus stratum lacunosum
description: A thin stratum in the hippocampus that is immediately deep to the molecular layer, and is superficial to the stratum radiatum.

name: hippocampus stratum oriens
description: Layer that is part of the CA fields of the hippocampus consisting of a narrow relatively cell free layer located deep to the pyramidal cell layer extending through areas CA1, CA2 and CA3. (adapted from Paxinos The rat central nervous system, 2nd ed, Academic Press, San Diego, 1995)
synonyms: ["oriens layer of hippocampus","oriens layer of the hippocampus","polymorphic layer of hippocampus","polymorphic layer of the hippocampus","stratum oriens","stratum oriens hippocampi"]

name: hippocampus stratum radiatum
description: The layer located immediately above the pyramidal cell layer in CA2 and CA1 and superficial to the stratum lucidum in CA3. Suprapyramidal region in which CA3 to CA3 associational connections and CA3 to CA1 Schaffer collateral connections are located.
synonyms: ["radiate layer of hippocampus","stratum radiatum","stratum radiatum hippocampi"]

name: spinal cord dorsal column
description: the wedge-shaped fiber bundle of white matter in the dorsomedial side of the spinal cord that is made up of the fasciculus gracilis and fasciculus cuneatus; it is part of the ascending posterior column-medial lemniscus pathway that is important for well-localized fine touch and conscious proprioception
synonyms: ["dorsal column","dorsal column of spinal cord","posterior column","spinal cord posterior column"]

name: spinal cord lateral column
description: the region of white matter of the spinal cord that is located between the dorsal and ventral spinal roots

name: spinal cord ventral column
description: the area of white matter of the spinal cord located on either side of the ventral (anterior) medial fissure

name: olfactory bulb external plexiform layer
description: Cytoarchitectural part of the olfactory bulb, lying superior to the mitral cell layer and inferior to the glomerular layer. The EPL is mostly neuropil composed almost entirely of mitral and tulfted cell dendrites and granule cell dendrites and their synaptic inputs.
synonyms: ["external plexiform layer","olfactory bulb main external plexiform layer"]

name: olfactory bulb glomerular layer
description: The glomerular layer is the most superficial layer, consisting of mitral cell dendritic arborizations (glomeruli), olfactory nerve fibers, and periglomerular cells. Periglomerular cells contact multiple mitral cell dendrites within the glomeruli and provide lateral inhibition of neighboring glomeruli while allowing excitation of a specific mitral cell dendritic tree. Each mitral cell is contacted by at least 1000 olfactory nerve fibers. Portion of tissue which is located in between the primary olfactory fiber layer and the external cellular layer of the olfactory bulb.
synonyms: ["glomerular layer","olfactory bulb main glomerulus","stratum glomerulosum bulbi olfactorii"]

name: olfactory bulb granule cell layer
description: The granule cell layer contains multiple small round neurons that lack axons. Long dendritic processes of the neurons reach the more superficial layers and inhibit mitral cells and tufted cells. Small distal processes make contacts with the exiting mitral cell axons.
synonyms: ["granule cell layer","olfactory bulb main granule cell layer"]

name: olfactory bulb subependymal zone
description: the region of mitotically active layer of cells surrounding the lateral brain ventricles that consists of migrating neuroblasts, astrocytes and transitory amplifying progenitor cells, that produce neurons that migrate to the olfactory bulb

name: dentate gyrus granule cell layer
description: Granule cell layer is also called the DG principal cell layer. This one of the three layers of dentate gyrus that lies deep to the molecular layer and is made of densely packed layer that is four to eight granule cells thick.
synonyms: ["DG granule cell layer","granular layer of dentate gyrus","stratum granulare gyri dentati"]

name: dorsal striatum
description: Dorsal components of the striatum comprising the caudate nucleus and the putamen, in species that have distinct nuclei; the caudoputamen in species which don't.

name: caudate-putamen
description: Regional part of telencephalon in some species, e.g., rodent, equivalent to the dorsal striatum (caudate nucleus and putamen). Unlike the dorsal striatum of primates, for example, the caudoputamen is not split into separate nuclei by the fibers of the internal capsule. Rather, the internal capsule splits into fiber bundles which course through the structure.

name: nasal cavity epithelium
description: An epithelium that lines the nasal cavity.

name: nasal cavity respiratory epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of the respiratory segment of the nasal mucosa.

name: olfactory segment of nasal mucosa
description: That portion of the nasal mucosa containing the sensory endings for olfaction; the organ of smell.
synonyms: ["olfactory area of nasal mucosa","olfactory mucosa","olfactory part of nasal mucosa","olfactory zone of nasal mucosa","pars olfactoria tunicae mucosae nasi"]

name: olfactory glomerulus
description: One of the small globular masses of dense neuropil in the olfactory bulb, containing the first synapse in the olfactory pathway.
synonyms: ["glomerulus of olfactory bulb","olfactory bulb glomerulus","olfactory glomeruli"]

name: photoreceptor array
description: An array of photoreceptors and any supporting cells found in an eye.

name: transparent eye structure
description: A transparent structure that is part of a visual sense organ, the function of which is to direct or focus light onto a photoreceptor array.

name: cortical layer I
description: The most superficial layer of the neocortex characterized by a paucity of cell bodies.
synonyms: ["cerebral cortex, layer 1","lamina molecularis isocorticis [lamina I]","layer 1 of neocortex","layer I of neocortex","molecular layer of cerebral cortex","molecular layer of isocortex [layer i]","molecular layer of neocortex","molecular layer of neocortex","neocortex layer 1","neocortex layer I","neocortex molecular layer","neocortex plexiform layer","plexiform layer of neocortex"]

name: cortical layer II
description: Layer of neocortex lying just deep to molecular layer characterized by numerous small cell bodies.
synonyms: ["cerebral cortex, layer 2","external granular layer of isocortex [layer II]","external granular layer of neocortex","external granule cell layer of neocortex","lamina granularis externa isocorticis [lamina ii]","layer II of neocortex","neocortex layer 2","neocortex layer II"]

name: cortical layer III
description: Layer of neocortex lying deep to the external granule cell layer defined cytoarchitecturally by numerous small pyramidal neurons.
synonyms: ["cerebral cortex, layer 3","external pyramidal cell layer","external pyramidal cell layer of neocortex","external pyramidal layer of isocortex [layer iii]","external pyramidal layer of neocortex","lamina pyramidalis externa isocorticis [lamina iii]","layer 3 of neocortex","layer III of neocortex","neocortex external pyramidal cell layer","neocortex layer 3","neocortex layer III"]

name: cortical layer IV
description: Layer of neocortex lying deep to the external pyramidal cell layer defined cytoarchitecturally by the presence of numerous small cells
synonyms: ["cerebral cortex, layer 4","internal granular layer of isocortex [layer iv]","internal granular layer of neocortex","internal granule cell layer of neocortex","lamina granularis interna isocorticis [lamina iv]","layer 4 of neocortex","layer IV of neocortex","neocortex internal granule cell layer","neocortex layer 4","neocortex layer IV","neocortical internal granule cell layer","neocortical layer IV"]

name: cortical layer V
description: Layer of neocortex lying deep to the internal granule cell layer (layer 4) defined cytoarchitecturally by the predominance of large pyramidal cell bodies
synonyms: ["betz' cells","cerebral cortex, layer 5","internal pyramidal cell layer of neocortex","internal pyramidal layer of isocortex [layer v]","internal pyramidal layer of neocortex","lamina pyramidalis interna isocorticis [lamina v]","layer 5 of neocortex","layer V of neocortex","neocortex internal pyramidal cell layer","neocortex layer 5","neocortex layer V","neocortical layer 5","neocortical layer V"]

name: cortical layer VI
description: Innermost layer of neocortex lying deep to the internal pyramidal cell layer defined cytoarchitecturally by cells of varying size.
synonyms: ["cerebral cortex, layer 6","lamina multiformis isocorticis [lamina vi]","layer VI of neocortex","multiform layer of isocortex [layer vi]","multiform layer of neocortex","multiform layer of neocortex","neocortex layer 6","neocortex layer VI","neocortex multiform layer","neocortical layer 6","neocortical layer VI","pleiomorphic layer of neocortex"]

name: carotid artery segment
description: One of: the common carotid artery, or its branches, the external and internal carotid arteries.

name: brain arachnoid mater
description: An arachnoid mater that surrounds a brain.
synonyms: ["arachnoidea mater cranialis","arachnoidea mater encephali","brain arachnoid matter","cranial arachnoid mater"]

name: female reproductive gland
description: A sex gland that is part of a female reproductive system.

name: male reproductive gland
description: A sex gland that is part of a male reproductive system.

name: telencephalon arachnoid mater
description: An arachnoid mater that is part of a telencephalon.

name: cerebral hemisphere gray matter
description: A gray matter that is part of a cerebral hemisphere.
synonyms: ["cerebral gray matter","cerebral grey matter","cerebral hemisphere grey matter"]

name: philtrum
description: the vertical groove found on the median line of the upper lip, extending to the nose

name: ventral striatum
description: A composite structure of the telencephalon that is defined in the striatopallidal system by connectivity and neurochemical staining. It includes the nucleus accumbens, the most ventral portions of the caudate nucleus and the putamen, the rostrolateral portion of the anterior perforated substance, the islands of Calleja and a rostral subcommissural portion of substantia innominata. The boundary between the ventral striatum and dorsal striatum is indistinct in sections stained for Nissl substance (Heimer-1995; adapted from Brain Info).

name: frontonasal suture
description: A suture between frontal and nasal bones

name: pararenal fat
description: The paranephric body (or paranephric fat or pararenal fat) is collection of adipose tissue located superficial to the renal fascia. The perirenal fat, or adipose capsule of kidney, is deep to the renal fascia but superficial to the renal capsule.

name: perirenal fat
description: The adipose capsule of kidney (or perinephric fat or perirenal fat) is a structure between the renal fascia and renal capsule, and may be regarded as a part of the latter. A different structure, the pararenal fat, is the adipose tissue superficial to the renal fascia.

name: sublingual ganglion
description: the small parasympathetic ganglion found anterior to the submandibular gland that provides postsynaptic fibers to the sublingual gland

name: circumventricular organ
description: Any of any of the secretory or sensory organs located in the brain region around or in relation to the ventricular system that are characterized by extensive vasculature and a lack of a normal blood brain barrier (BBB) and allow for the linkage between the central nervous system and peripheral blood flow.

name: alimentary part of gastrointestinal system
description: The part of the digestive system that excludes the hepatobiliary system.

name: cartilaginous otic capsule
description: A otic capsule endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: bony otic capsule
description: the cartilage or bony capsule surrounding the inner ear mechanism

name: optic fissure
description: Groove that is in the developing ventral optic cup and through which blood vessels pass to the enclosed mesenchyme. a ventral fissure in the developing optic cup through which blood vessels pass to the enclosed mesenchyme.
synonyms: ["choroid fissure - optic fissure","optic fissures","optic stalk fissure"]

name: spinocerebellar tract
description: This tract conveys interoceptive, proprioceptive, and exteroceptive information from the body's internal organs, and from the trunk, extremities, and neck region to the Cerebellum.

name: zone of polarizing activity
description: An area of mesenchymal cells that contains signals which instruct the developing limb or fin bud to form along the anterior/posterior axis.

name: zone of polarizing activity of pectoral appendage
description: A zone of polarizing activity that is part of a pectoral appendage bud mesenchyme.

name: zone of polarizing activity of pelvic appendage
description: A zone of polarizing activity that is part of a pelvic appendage bud mesenchyme.

name: forelimb bud
description: A limb bud that develops into a forelimb.
synonyms: ["anterior limb bud","limb bud - forelimb","upper limb bud"]

name: hindlimb bud
description: A limb bud that develops into a hindlimb.

name: pectoral appendage bud
description: A limb bud that develops into a forelimb or pectoral fin.

name: pelvic appendage bud
description: A limb bud that develops into a hindlimb or pelvic fin.

name: pectoral appendage apical ectodermal ridge
description: An apical ectodermal ridge that is part of a pectoral appendage bud.

name: pelvic appendage apical ectodermal ridge
description: An apical ectodermal ridge that is part of a pelvic appendage bud.

name: presumptive retinal pigmented epithelium
description: Portion of tissue that is the outer layer of the optic cup and will become the retinal pigmented epithelium.
synonyms: ["future retinal pigmented epithelium","future RPE","optic cup outer layer","outer layer optic cup","presumptive pigmented epithelia"]

name: presumptive neural retina
description: Portion of tissue that is the inner layer of the optic cup and will become the neural retina.
synonyms: ["future neural retina","future retinal neural layer","inner layer optic cup","optic cup inner layer","presumptive retinas"]

name: lens vesicle
description: Portion of tissue that gives rise to the lens.

name: corneal primordium
description: Portion of tissue that is part of the eye and gives rise to the mature, fully layered cornea.

name: vagal neural crest
description: Vagal neural crest is adjacent to the first seven somites gives rise to both ganglionic and ectomesenchymal derivatives.

name: dorsal pancreatic duct
description: A pancreatic duct that develops from the dorsal pancreatic bud.

name: ansa cervicalis
description: A loop of nerves that are part of the cervical plexus that lies superficial to the internal jugular vein in the carotid sheath. Branches from the ansa cervicalis innervate three of the four infrahyoid muscles, including the sternohyoid muscle, the sternothyroid muscle, and the omohyoid muscle.

name: anterior spinal artery
description: A blood vessel that supplies the anterior portion of the spinal cord. It arises from branches of the vertebral arteries and is supplied by the anterior segmental medullary arteries, including the artery of Adamkiewicz, and courses along the anterior aspect of the spinal cord.

name: aortic sac
description: The dilated structure that is lined by endothelial cells and located at the arterial pole of the heart just above (distal to) the truncus arteriosus in mammalian embryos; it is the primordial vascular channel from which the aortic arches (and eventually the dorsal aortae) arise; the aortic sac is homologous to the ventral aorta of gill-bearing vertebrates

name: obsolete peripheral part of autonomous nervous system
synonyms: ["autonomic division of peripheral nervous system","autonomic part of peripheral nervous system","divisio autonomica systematis nervosi peripherici","pars autonomica systematis nervosi peripherici","peripheral autonomic nervous system","peripheral part of autonomic nervous system"]

name: cervical region
synonyms: ["cervical region","neck subdivision","region of neck","subdivision of neck"]

name: upper part of cisterna chyli
description: A dilated sac at the lower end of the thoracic duct into which lymph from the intestinal trunk and two lumbar lymphatic trunks flow.
synonyms: ["atypical confluence of lymph trunks","chyle cistern","cistern of Pecquet","cisterna chyli"]

name: common hepatic artery
description: In anatomy, the common hepatic artery is a short blood vessel that supplies oxygenated blood to the liver, pylorus (a part of the stomach), duodenum (a part of the small intestine) and pancreas. It arises from the celiac artery and has the following branches:

name: conus medullaris
description: The conus medullaris is the terminal end of the spinal cord. It occurs near lumbar vertebral levels 1 (L1) and 2 (L2). After the spinal cord tapers out, the spinal nerves continue as dangling nerve roots called cauda equina. This terminal nerve root tail is referred to as the filum terminale. The upper end of the conus medullaris is usually not well defined.

name: coronary sinus
description: the short trunk that recieves most of the cardiac veins carrying the blood from the myocardium and delivers it to the right atrium, with the sinoatrial connection occurring between the inferior vena cava and the atrioventricular orifice

name: ductus arteriosus
description: A fetal blood vessel connecting the pulmonary artery with the descending aorta. In the developing fetus, the ductus arteriosus is a shunt connecting the pulmonary artery to the aortic arch. It allows most of the blood from the right ventricle to bypass the fetus' fluid-filled lungs, protecting the lungs from being overworked and allowing the left ventricle to strengthen. There are two other fetal shunts, the ductus venosus and the foramen ovale. the fetal vessel that connects the left pulmonary artery with the descending aorta; the ductus arteriosus normally regresses into a fibrous cord, the ligamentum arteriousum after birth

name: external intercostal muscle
description: An intercostal muscle that aids in quiet and forced inhalation via elevation of the ribs, and expanding the transverse dimensions of the thoracic cavity.

name: abdominal external oblique muscle
description: The lateral abdominal wall muscle that is the most superficial, immediately superficial to the internal oblique.
synonyms: ["abdominal external oblique muscle","external abdominal oblique muscle","external oblique","external oblique muscle","obliquus externus abdominis"]

name: filum terminale
description: A strand of fibrous tissue in the spinal cord consisting of the filum terminale internum and the filum terminale externum.
synonyms: ["filum terminale segment of pia mater","pars pialis fili terminalis","terminal filum"]

name: segment of pes
description: A segment of autopod that is part of a pes.
synonyms: ["foot region","foot subdivision","regio pedis","segment of foot","subdivision of foot"]

name: foramen rotundum
description: The foramen rotundum is a circular hole in the sphenoid bone that connects the middle cranial fossa and the pterygopalatine fossa.

name: greater omentum
description: The greater omentum (also the great omentum, omentum majus, gastrocolic omentum, epiploön, or, especially in animals, caul) is a large fold of peritoneum that hangs down from the stomach, and extends from the stomach to the posterior abdominal wall after associating with the transverse colon.

name: greater sac cavity
description: The cavity in the abdomen that is inside the peritoneum but outside of the lesser sac..
synonyms: ["cavity of greater sac","cavum peritonei","greater peritoneal cavity","greater sac lumen"]

name: segment of manus
description: A segment of autopod that is part of a manus.
synonyms: ["hand region","hand subdivision","regio manus","segment of hand","subdivision of hand"]

name: hepatic cord
description: A three-dimensional arrangement formed by plates of hepatocytes, usually one cell thick, that radiates from the center of the liver lobule; hepatic laminae are highly branched, irregular structures bordered by endothelial lined vascular spaces called hepatic sinusoids.

name: inferior mesenteric ganglion
description: A ganglion located near where the inferior mesenteric artery branches from the abdominal aorta.

name: abdominal internal oblique muscle
description: The lateral abdominal wall muscle that is deep to the external oblique and superficial to the transversus.
synonyms: ["abdominal internal oblique muscle","internal oblique","obliquus internus abdominis","obliquus internus abdominis muscle"]

name: interventricular groove
description: Either of the anterior and posterior grooves on the surface of the heart that lie over the interventricular septum and join at the apex.

name: jugular foramen
description: The jugular foramen is a large aperture in the base of the skull. It is located behind the carotid canal and is formed in front by the petrous portion of the temporal, and behind by the occipital; it is generally larger on the right than on the left side

name: left thymus lobe
description: A thymus lobe that is in the left side of a thymus.

name: left umbilical vein
description: An umbilical vein that is in the left side of a multicellular organism.

name: left vitelline vein
description: A vitelline vein that is in the left side of a multicellular organism.

name: levator scapulae muscle
description: An axial muscle that originates in the cervical vertebraae inserts on the scapula.

name: lower back
description: Subdivision of abdominal segment of trunk which in humans is demarcated from the front of the abdomen by the posterior surface of the anterior layer of the thoracolumbar fascia and the anterior surface of the lumbar vertebral column; together with the front of the abdomen, it constitutes the abdomen.
synonyms: ["abdominal back","back of abdomen","dorsum of abdomen","lower back","lumbar part of back","lumbar region","lumbar region of back","posterior part of abdomen","regio lumbalis"]

name: subcapsular sinus of lymph node
description: A space between the capsule and the cortex which allows the free movement of lymphatic fluid and so contains a sparsity of lymphocytes. It is continuous with the similar lymph sinuses that flank the trabeculae.

name: median sacral artery
description: The median sacral artery (or middle sacral artery) is a small vessel, which arises from the back of the aorta, a little above its bifurcation. It descends in the middle line in front of the fourth and fifth lumbar vertebræ, the sacrum and coccyx, and ends in the glomus coccygeum (coccygeal gland). From it, minute branches are said to pass to the posterior surface of the rectum. On the last lumbar vertebra it anastomoses with the lumbar branch of the iliolumbar artery; in front of the sacrum it anastomoses with the lateral sacral arteries, and sends offsets into the anterior sacral foramina. It is crossed by the left common iliac vein, and is accompanied by a pair of venæ comitantes; these unite to form a single vessel, which opens into the left common iliac vein.

name: obturator nerve
description: The obturator nerve arises from the ventral divisions of the second, third, and fourth lumbar nerves; the branch from the third is the largest, while that from the second is often very small.

name: platysma
description: The platysma is a pharyngeal arch 2 muscle and a superficial facial muscle that participates in oral/pharyngeal behaviors and is innervated by the cervical branch of the facial nerve. It attaches to the mandible and it attaches to the skin of the head, neck, and thoracic region where it is found superficial to the clavicle. Burrows et al. (2011) argue that in hylobatids (and, presumably, other primates) the platysma in the region of the modiolus represents both the cervicale and myoides muscles.

name: right thymus lobe
description: A thymus lobe that is in the right side of a thymus.

name: right umbilical vein
description: An umbilical vein that is in the right side of a multicellular organism.

name: right vitelline vein
description: A vitelline vein that is in the right side of a multicellular organism.

name: sacral region
description: A subdivision of an organism along the anterior-posterior axis in the pelvic region immediately posterior to the lumbar region and anterior to the caudal region. Sometimes an intermediate region is defined between the sacral and caudal.
synonyms: ["back of pelvis","pelvic back","posterior part of pelvis","regio sacralis","sacral part of pelvis"]

name: sigmoid sinus
description: A portion of the lateral venous sinus, bulging prominently into the mastoid cavity, that serves as a principal conduit by which blood leaves the cranium. The sigmoid is drained by the internal jugular vein

name: spinal nerve trunk
description: trunk part of spinal nerve, where dorsal and ventral roots meet to form the spinal nerve, before branching off to dorsal and ventral rami.
synonyms: ["spinal nerve (trunk)","spinal neural trunk","trunk of spinal nerve"]

name: stomach fundus epithelium
description: A simple columnar epithelium that is part of a fundus of stomach.
synonyms: ["epithelium of fundus of stomach","gastric epithelium of fundus","gastric fundus epithelium"]

name: sulcus limitans of neural tube
description: A longitudinal groove in the neural tube wall that divides the neural tube into dorsal (alar) and ventral (basal) halves (dorsal receives input from sensory neurons, ventral effects motor functions); stretches from the mesencephalon caudad.
synonyms: ["neural tube lateral wall sulcus limitans","sulcus limitans"]

name: superior mesenteric ganglion
description: A ganglion in the upper part of the superior mesenteric plexus that is the synapsing point for one of the pre- and post-synaptic nerves of the sympathetic division of the autonomous nervous system.

name: superior orbital fissure
description: The orbital fissure that is situated superiorly between the greater wing and the lesser wing of the sphenoid bone

name: tentorial sinus
description: An unpaired venous dural sinus that receives blood from the superior cerebellar veins and inferior sagittal sinus and drains into the confluence of sinuses.

name: thymus lobe
description: Either of the two lateral lobes that constitute the thymus.

name: tricuspid valve leaflet
description: A valve leaflet that is part of a tricuspid valve.
synonyms: ["leaflet of tricuspid valve","tricuspid valve leaflet","tricuspid valve leaflets","tricuspid valvular leaflet"]

name: valve of inferior vena cava
description: the semicircular fold of endocardium located on the right atrium at the point of attachment of the inferior vena cava; during development this valve helps direct the flow of oxygen-rich blood through the right atrium into the left cardiac atrium via the foramen ovale (preventing blood flowing into the right ventricle)

name: venous dural sinus
description: A venous channel found between layers of dura mater in the brain. Receives blood from internal and external veins of the brain, receive cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) from the subarachnoid space, and ultimately empty into the internal jugular vein.
synonyms: ["cranial dural venous sinus","dural sinus","dural vein","dural venous sinus","venous dural","venous dural sinus"]

name: vitelline vein
description: the paired veins that carry blood from the yolk sac back to the embryo

name: superior mesenteric plexus
description: The superior mesenteric plexus is a continuation of the lower part of the celiac plexus, receiving a branch from the junction of the right vagus nerve with the plexus. It surrounds the superior mesenteric artery, accompanies it into the mesentery, and divides into a number of secondary plexuses, which are distributed to all the parts supplied by the artery, viz. , pancreatic branches to the pancreas; intestinal branches to the small intestine; and ileocolic, right colic, and middle colic branches, which supply the corresponding parts of the great intestine. The nerves composing this plexus are white in color and firm in texture; in the upper part of the plexus close to the origin of the superior mesenteric artery is the superior mesenteric ganglion.

name: anterior interventricular sulcus
description: The ventricles of the heart are separated by two grooves, one of which, the anterior longitudinal sulcus (or anterior interventricular sulcus), is situated on the sternocostal surface of the heart, close to its left margin. The other groove separating the ventricles is the posterior interventricular sulcus.

name: posterior interventricular sulcus
description: The ventricles are separated by two grooves, one of which, the anterior longitudinal sulcus, is situated on the sternocostal surface of the heart, close to its left margin, the other posterior longitudinal sulcus (posterior interventricular sulcus, inferior interventricular groove), on the diaphragmatic surface near the right margin. In it run the posterior interventricular artery and middle cardiac vein.
synonyms: ["diaphragmatic interventricular groove","inferior interventricular groove","posterior interventricular groove"]

name: glossopharyngeal neural crest
description: Cranial neural crest which gives rise to the glossopharyngeal ganglion.

name: hyaloid vessel
description: A blood vessel that is associated with the lens. In mammals, this is transient and normally nourishes the retina, immature lens and primary vitreous of the developing eye.

name: hyoid muscle
description: One of a group of muscles used in mastication and swallowing. These muscles are attached to the hyoid bone, which is suspended in the neck and forms the base of the tongue and larynx. The muscles are divided into suprahyoid (superior) or infrahyoid (inferior) groups relative to the bone.

name: neural tube lateral wall
description: Portion of tissue on the side of the lumen of the neural tube.

name: primitive heart tube
description: Multi-tissue structure that arises from the heart rudiment and will become the heart tube.

name: rhombomere 1
description: Hindbrain segment or neuromere 1.

name: rhombomere floor plate
synonyms: ["floor plate hindbrain","floor plate rhombomere region","rhombencephalon floor plate"]

name: rhombomere lateral wall
description: A neural tube lateral wall that is part of a rhombomere.

name: rhombomere roof plate
