This is usually the visible layer for most mammals and contains most of the pigmentation.

name: strand of zigzag hair
description: A truncal hair that has two or more sharp bends with diameter constrictions at the bends, and contain one air cell in the medulla.

name: strand of duvet hair
description: A strand of hair from the fine underhair of the coat

name: brille
description: A layer of transparent, immovable disc-shaped skin or scale covering the eyes of some animals for protection, especially in animals without eyelids. The brille has evolved from a fusion of the upper and lower eyelids.

name: clasper
description: A male anatomical structure found some groups of animals, used in mating. Male cartilaginous fish have claspers formed from the posterior portion of their pelvic fin which serve as intromittent organs used to channel semen into the female's cloaca during mating. The act of mating in some fish including sharks usually includes one of the claspers raised to allow water into the siphon through a specific orifice. The clasper is then inserted into the vagina, where it opens like an umbrella to anchor its position. The siphon then begins to contract expelling water and sperm. Male chimaeras have cephalic claspers on their heads, which are thought to aid in holding the female during mating

name: cephalic clasper
description: A mace-like spiny-headed rod found on the mid-dorsal surface of heads of male Holocephali. Thought to aid in holding the female during copulation.

name: pelvic fin clasper
description: The rod-like extension of the medial portion of the pelvic fin in male Elasmobranchii and Holocephali. Claspers are used as intromittent organs (not in clasping), the grooves on their facing surfaces together forming a tube for the transmission of sperm when the claspers are held together. The anterior proximal opening is called the apopyle, the posterior distal opening the rhipidion

name: tail electric organ
description: An electric organ that is part of a tail.

name: head electric organ
description: An electric organ that is part of a head.

name: electroreceptor organ
description: An organ that is capable of detecting electrical stimulus

name: replacement element
description: Skeletal element that forms as a replacement or substitution of another element or tissue.

name: microcirculatory vessel
description: A vessel of the microcirculature, lying between the arterioles and venules; includes capillaries (blood and lymphatic), metarterioles and arteriovenous anastomoses.

name: fibularis tertius
description: A muscle located in the lower limb that arises from the lower third of the anterior surface of the fibula; from the lower part of the interosseous membrane; and from an intermuscular septum between it and the peroneus brevis and inserted into the dorsal surface of the base of the metatarsal bone of the 5th digit. It is innervated by the deep fibular nerve. Its action is that of weak dorsiflexion of the ankle joint and to evert the foot at the ankle joint.
synonyms: ["musculus peroneus tertius","peroneus digiti quinti","peroneus tertius","peroneus tertius","peroneus tertius muscle"]

name: fibularis brevis
description: The peroneus brevis muscle (or fibularis brevis) lies under cover of the peroneus longus, and is a shorter and smaller muscle.
synonyms: ["musculus peroneus brevis","peronaeus brevis","peroneus brevis","peroneus brevis muscle"]

name: cavity of bone organ
description: An organ cavity that surrounded_by a bone.

name: metanephros induced blastemal cells
synonyms: ["induced blastemal cells","nephrogenic interstitium of nephrogenic zone"]

name: primitive nephron
description: An epithelial tube that is fated to become a nephron.

name: metanephros cortex
description: The metanephric cortex is the outer region of the metanephros.

name: primitive mesonephric nephron
description: Anatomical cluster which give rise to mature mesonephric nephrons. Zebrafish continously generate new mesonephric nephrons.

name: primitive metanephric nephron
description: A primitive nephron that is part of a metanephros.

name: mesonephric nephron progenitor
description: Cluster of cells comprising a portion of tissue which gives rise to new mesonephric nephrons. The cluster contains self-renewing stem cells.

name: paired limb/fin segment
description: An appendage segment that is part of a limb/fin.

name: tarsus pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a tarsal bone.

name: tarsus cartilage element
description: A cartilaginous condensation that has the potential to develop into a tarsal bone.

name: acropodial skeleton
description: The subdivision of the skeleton that consists of all the skeletal elements at the distalmost end of the autopodium - i.e. the bones of the digits or their cartilaginous precursors.
synonyms: ["acropodial skeleton","acropodium skeleton","set of phalanges","skeletal parts of acropodial region"]

name: metacarpus skeleton
description: The metacarpus is the intermediate part of the manus skeleton that is located between the phalanges (bones of the fingers) distally and the carpus which forms the connection to the forearm. The metacarpus consists of metacarpal bones. The metacarpals form a transverse arch to which the rigid row of distal carpal bones are fixed. The peripheral metacarpals (those of the thumb and little finger) form the sides of the cup of the palmar gutter and as they are brought together they deepen this concavity. The index metacarpal is the most firmly fixed, while the thumb metacarpal articulates with the trapezium and acts independently from the others. The middle metacarpals are tightly united to the carpus by intrinsic interlocking bone elements at their bases. The ring metacarpal forms a transitional element of the semi-independent last metacarpal..
synonyms: ["anterior metapodial skeleton","metacarpal bones","metacarpal skeleton","metacarpals [I-V]","metacarpals set","ossa metacarpalia [I-V]","ossa metacarpi [I-V]","set of metacarpal bones","set of metacarpals","set of metacarpals [I-V]","skeleton of metacarpus"]

name: metatarsus skeleton
description: Limb segment that consists of the long bones of the pes. The metatarsals are analogous to the metacarpal bones of the manus.
synonyms: ["metatarsal bones set","metatarsal skeleton","metatarsals [I-V]","ossa metatarsalia [I-V]","ossa metatarsi[I-V]","posterior metapodial skeleton","set of metatarsal bones","set of metatarsals [I-V]","skeleton of metatarsus"]

name: metapodial skeleton
description: Subdivision of skeleton that corresponds to metapodium region, between acropodial skeleton and mesopdoial skeleton.
synonyms: ["metacarpal/metatarsal skeleton","metapodial skeleton","metapodium skeleton","skeletal parts of metapodium","skeleton of metapodium"]

name: pedal digit 1 metatarsal pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pedal digit metatarsal pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a pedal digit 1 mesenchyme.
synonyms: ["hind limb digit 1 metatarsal pre-cartilage condensation","pedal digit I metatarsal pre-cartilage condensation","toe 1 metatarsal pre-cartilage condensation"]

description: A pedal digit metatarsal pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a pedal digit 2 mesenchyme.

description: A pedal digit metatarsal pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a pedal digit 3 mesenchyme.

description: A pedal digit metatarsal pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a pedal digit 4 mesenchyme.

description: A pedal digit metatarsal pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a pedal digit 5 mesenchyme.
synonyms: ["hind limb digit 5 metatarsal pre-cartilage condensation","pedal digit V metatarsal pre-cartilage condensation","toe 5 metatarsal pre-cartilage condensation"]

description: A pedal digit metatarsal cartilage condensation that is part of a pedal digit 1 mesenchyme.

description: A pedal digit metatarsal cartilage element that is part of a pedal digit 2 mesenchyme.
synonyms: ["hind limb digit 2 metatarsal cartilage condensation","pedal digit II metatarsal cartilage element","toe 2 metatarsal cartilage element"]

name: pedal digit 3 metatarsal cartilage element
description: A pedal digit metatarsal cartilage element that is part of a pedal digit 3 mesenchyme.
synonyms: ["hind limb digit 3 metatarsal cartilage condensation","pedal digit III metatarsal cartilage element","toe 3 metatarsal cartilage element"]

name: pedal digit 4 metatarsal cartilage element
description: A pedal digit metatarsal cartilage element that is part of a pedal digit 4 mesenchyme.
synonyms: ["hind limb digit 4 metatarsal cartilage condensation","pedal digit IV metatarsal cartilage element","toe 4 metatarsal cartilage element"]

name: pedal digit 5 metatarsal cartilage element
description: A pedal digit metatarsal cartilage element that is part of a pedal digit 5 mesenchyme.
synonyms: ["hind limb digit 5 metatarsal cartilage element","pedal digit V metatarsal cartilage element","toe 5 metatarsal cartilage element"]

name: pedal digit 1 mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing pedal digit 1.
synonyms: ["hind limb digit 1 mesenchyme","pedal digit I mesenchyme"]

name: manual digit 1 mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing manual digit 1.
synonyms: ["fore limb digit 1 mesenchyme","manual digit I mesenchyme"]

name: manual digit 1 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation
description: A manual digit metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a manual digit 1 mesenchyme.
synonyms: ["finger 1 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation","fore limb digit 1 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation","manual digit I metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation","metacarpal 1 pre-cartilage condensation"]

description: A manual digit metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a manual digit 2 mesenchyme.
synonyms: ["finger 2 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation","fore limb digit 2 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation","manual digit II metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation","metacarpal 2 pre-cartilage condensation"]

name: manual digit 3 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation
description: A manual digit metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a manual digit 3 mesenchyme.
synonyms: ["finger 3 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation","fore limb digit 3 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation","manual digit III metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation","metacarpal 3 pre-cartilage condensation"]

description: A manual digit metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a manual digit 4 mesenchyme.
synonyms: ["finger 4 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation","fore limb digit 4 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation","manual digit IV metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation","metacarpal 4 pre-cartilage condensation"]

name: manual digit 5 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation
description: A manual digit metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation that is part of a manual digit 5 mesenchyme.
synonyms: ["finger 5 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation","fore limb digit 5 metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation","manual digit V metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation","metacarpal 5 pre-cartilage condensation"]

name: manual digit 1 metacarpus cartilage element
description: A manual digit metacarpus cartilage element that is part of a manual digit 1 mesenchyme.

name: skeleton of manual acropodium
description: The subdivision of the skeleton that consists of all the skeletal elements at the distalmost end of the manual autopodium - i.e. the bones of the hands or their cartilaginous precursors.
synonyms: ["all phalanges in forelimb autopod","anterior acropodium skeleton","fore acropodium skeleton","hand digit skeleton","manual digit skeleton","manual phalanges","phalanges of hand","phalanges of manus","set of manual phalanges","set of phalanges of hand","set of phalanges of manus"]

name: manual digit 1 epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a manual digit 1.
synonyms: ["fore limb digit 1 epithelium","manual digit I epithelium"]

description: An epithelium that is part of a pedal digit 1.
synonyms: ["hind limb digit 1 epithelium","pedal digit I epithelium"]

name: mesenchyme of tarsal region
description: Mesenchyme of the carpal region that contributes to the tarsal skeleton.

name: skeleton of pedal acropodium
description: The subdivision of the skeleton that consists of all the skeletal elements at the distalmost end of the pedal autopodium - i.e. the bones of the foot or their cartilaginous precursors.
synonyms: ["all phalanges in hindlimb autopod","foot digit skeleton","hind acropodium skeleton","pedal phalanges","phalanges of foot","phalanges of pes","posterior acropodium skeleton","set of pedal phalanges","set of phalanges of foot","set of phalanges of pes"]

name: manual digit metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation
synonyms: ["fore limb digit metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation","metacarpal bone pre-cartilage condensation","metacarpal pre-cartilage condensation","metacarpus pre-cartilage condensation"]

name: manual digit metacarpus cartilage element
synonyms: ["finger metacarpus cartilage element","fore limb digit metacarpus cartilage element","metacarpal cartilage element","metacarpus cartilage element"]

name: digit mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme of the digit region.

name: forelimb zeugopod skeleton
description: The collection of all skeletal elements in an forelimb zeugopod region.
synonyms: ["antebrachial skeleton","antebrachium skeleton","anterior zeugopodium skeleton","fore epipodium skeleton","forearm skeleton","skeleton of forearm"]

name: parenchyma of quadrate lobe of liver
description: A liver parenchyma that is part of a quadrate lobe of liver.
synonyms: ["liver right quadrate lobe parenchyma","parenchyma of quadrate lobe"]

name: parenchyma of caudate lobe of liver
description: A liver parenchyma that is part of a caudate lobe of liver.
synonyms: ["liver right caudate lobe parenchyma","parenchyma of caudate lobe"]

name: appendage girdle complex
description: An organism subdivision that includes both an appendage and its associated girdle region. Note that this includes both the skeletal elements and associated tissues (integument, muscle, etc).
synonyms: ["appendage complex","appendage-girdle complex","appendage/girdle complex","girdle plus limb or fin"]

name: pectoral complex
description: Appendage girdle complex that when present, encompasses the pectoral appendicular skeleton and the pectoral girdle.
synonyms: ["pectoral appendage/girdle complex","pectoral girdle plus anterior limb or fin","pectoral girdle plus pectoral limb or fin"]

name: pelvic complex
description: Appendage girdle complex that when present, encompasses the pelvic appendicular skeleton and the pelvic girdle.
synonyms: ["pelvic appendage/girdle complex","pelvic girdle plus pelvic limb or fin","pelvic girdle plus posterior limb or fin"]

name: pectoral fin skeleton
description: Paired fin skeleton that consists of the supporting endochondral proximal and distal radials and the dermal fins rays or lepidotrichia. The pectoral fin skeleton is located in the thoracic region of the body and articulates with the scapula and coracoid.

name: pelvic fin skeleton
description: Paired fin skeleton located in the abdominal position that consists of supporting endochondral radialsB and dermal fin rays or lepidotrichia.

name: limb skeleton subdivision
description: Skeletal subdivision that is a segment of the limb skeleton.

name: paired fin skeleton
description: The collection of all skeletal elements in a single paired fin.

name: iliac cartilage element
description: A iliac endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: pubic cartilage element
description: A pubic endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: girdle skeleton
description: The subdivision of the skeleton of either the pectoral or pelvic girdle.

name: hindlimb zeugopod skeleton
description: Subdivision of skeleton consisting of all skeletal elements in an hindlimb zeugopod region. Typically consists of the tibia and the fibula.
synonyms: ["crural skeleton","crus skeleton","hindlimb zygopod skeleton","posterior zeugopodium skeleton","skeleton cruris"]

name: distal tarsal bone
description: There are three cuneiform bones in the human foot: the medial cuneiform the intermediate cuneiform also known as the middle the lateral cuneiform. They are located between the navicular bone and the first, second and third metatarsal bones and are medial to the cuboid bone.
synonyms: ["cuneiform bone","distal tarsal","distal tarsal bone","os cuneiform","os cuneiforme"]

name: accessory bone
description: A bone which does not occur frequently in the body but is still present in a significantly large number of organisms

name: os vesalianum pedis
description: An accessory bone located proximal to the base of the fifth metatarsal. Its prevalence has been reported to be from 0.1% to 1.0%. This bone is found within the peroneus brevis tendon and is considered to be asymptomatic in the majority of people

name: lateral tubercle of talus
description: An accessory bone tubercle which if present lies posterior to the talus
synonyms: ["accessory talus","os trigonum","os trigonum of talus","tuberculum laterale (talus)"]

name: accessory navicular bone
description: An accessory bone of the pes that occasionally develops abnormally in front of the ankle towards the inside of the pes. This bone may be present in approximately 2.5% of the general population and is usually asymptomatic

name: sutural bone
description: A piece of bone that is located within a suture in the cranium.

name: sphenoid lesser wing pre-cartilage condensation
description: A orbitosphenoid endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: alisphenoid pre-cartilage condensation
description: A alisphenoid endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: alisphenoid cartilage element
description: A alisphenoid endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: distal tarsal bone 4
description: Endochondral tarsal bone articulating with centralia and metatarsal 4.

name: distal tarsal bone 5
description: Endochondral tarsal bone articulating with centralia and metatarsal 5.

name: distal carpal bone 5
description: endochondral carpal bone similar to distal carpal 4, but lost in most reptiles and mammals.

name: bone of appendage girdle complex
description: A bone that is part of an appendage girdle complex (i.e. any bone in a limb, fin or girdle).

name: bone of pectoral complex
description: A bone that is part of a pectoral complex. Examples: scapula, manus phalanx, any carpal bone, any bone of the pectoral fin.

name: bone of pelvic complex
description: A bone that is part of a pelvic complex. Examples: pubis, ischium, fot phalanx, any tarsal bone, any bone of the pelvic fin or girdle.

name: meningeal cluster
description: The collection of all meningeal layers that line a central nervous system.

name: sacral vertebra pre-cartilage condensation
description: A sacral vertebra endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: sacral vertebra cartilage element
description: A sacral vertebra endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.
synonyms: ["sacral vertebral cartilage condensation","sacral vertebral cartilage condensation group"]

name: iliac blade
description: The extension of the ilium above the level of the acetabulum. Attachment site for both hindlimb and caudal musculature. Medially is the site of attachment of the sacral ribs, where these exist.
synonyms: ["a. ossis ilii","ala of ilium","ala ossis ilii","ilium ala","wing of ilium","wing of the ilium"]

name: body of ilium
description: The body of ilium enters into the formation of the acetabulum, of which it forms rather less than two-fifths. Its external surface is partly articular, partly non-articular; the articular segment forms part of the lunate surface of the acetabulum, the non-articular portion contributes to the acetabular fossa. The internal surface of the body is part of the wall of the lesser pelvis and gives origin to some fibers of the Obturator internus. Below, it is continuous with the pelvic surfaces of the ischium and pubis, only a faint line indicating the place of union.

name: lymph node follicle
description: A lymphoid follicle that is part of a lymph node.

name: middle pharyngeal constrictor
description: The middle pharyngeal constrictor is a fanshaped muscle, smaller than the Inferior pharyngeal constrictor muscle.
synonyms: ["middle constrictor","middle constrictor of pharynx","middle constrictor pharyngeus","musculus constrictor pharyngis medius"]

name: prefrontal bone
description: A bone separating the lacrimal and frontal bones in many tetrapod skulls

name: squamous part of temporal bone primordium
exoccipital cartilage element
description: A exoccipital endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: lymph node secondary follicle
description: A secondary follicle that is located in a lymph node

name: germinal center
description: A collection of activated B cells at the center of a secondary follicle, formed after B cells become activated and migrate to the center.
synonyms: ["central zone of follice","light zone of follicle","reaction center of follicle"]

name: secondary follicle corona
description: The part of the secondary follicle that surrounds the germinal center.
synonyms: ["dark zone of follicle","inactive zone of follicle","peripheral zone of follicle"]

name: spleen follicular dendritic cell network
description: The enmeshed group of antigen presenting cells with extensive dendritic processes in the spleen B cell follicle that present antigen to B cells during an immune response
synonyms: ["FDC network","FDCN","spleen FDC network","splenic follicular dendritic cell network"]

name: rib 8
description: The eighth rib counting from the top of the rib cage down. Note that members of this class are not necessarily homologous.

name: subdivision of organism along appendicular axis
description: A major subdivision of an organism that divides an organism along an axis perpedicular to the main body anterior-posterior axis. In vertebrates, this is typically a fin or limb segment. In insects, this includes segments of appendages such as antennae, as well as segments of the insect leg.

name: equine distal sesamoid
description: lies on the palmar aspect of the coffin joint between the second phalanx and third phalanx. articulates closely with the distal phalanx, to which it is connected by the impar ligament of the navicular bone. The impar ligament is very strong and permits relatively little motion between the navicular bone and the distal phalanx.

name: supraglenoid tubercle
description: The supraglenoid tubercle is a region of the scapula to which the long head of the biceps brachii muscle attaches.

name: calcaneum pre-cartilage condensation
description: A calcaneum endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: calcaneum cartilage element
description: A calcaneum endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: clavicle cartilage element
description: A cartilaginous condensation that has the potential to develop into a clavicle.

name: clavicle pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a clavicle.

name: radius pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a radius bone.

name: ulna pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a ulna.

name: radius-ulna cartilage element
description: A radius-ulna endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: tibia cartilage element
description: A cartilaginous condensation that has the potential to develop into a tibia.

name: tibia pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a tibia.

name: fibula cartilage element
description: A cartilaginous condensation that has the potential to develop into a fibula.

name: fibula pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a fibula.

name: capitulum of humerus
description: A smooth, rounded eminence on the lateral portion of the articular surface of the humerus. It articulates with the cupshaped depression on the head of the radius, and is limited to the front and lower part of the bone.

name: skin of front of neck
description: A skin of neck that is part of a throat.
synonyms: ["skin of anterior neck","skin of anterior part of neck","skin of anterior portion of neck","skin of throat"]

name: skin of forelimb wing
description: A zone of skin that is part of a forelimb wing.

name: patagium
description: A membranous extension of skin that forms the wing material in animals such as bats. It typically comprises a number of patagial segments, stretching from the side of the body between the forelimb digits and sometimes the hindlimbs.

name: propatagium
description: In bats and pterosaurs, thin web of skin that extends from the shoulder to the wrist anterior to the upper arm and forearm, and is fixed on the neck or skull.

name: dactylopatagium
description: An interdigital region that is part of a patagium.

name: dactylopatagium brevis
description: A dactylopatagium that is connected_to a manual digit 1 and connected_to a manual digit 2.

name: dactylopatagium minus
description: A dactylopatagium that is connected_to a manual digit 2 and connected_to a manual digit 3.

name: dactylopatagium medius
description: A dactylopatagium that is connected_to a manual digit 3 and connected_to a manual digit 4.

name: dactylopatagium major
description: A dactylopatagium that is connected_to a manual digit 4 and connected_to a manual digit 5.

name: plagiopatagium
description: A flight membrane running between the body and the limb or digits.

name: uropropatagium
description: The membrane that is stretches between the legs of bats, used for flight, and in the case of insect-eating bats, for catching prey.

name: calcar
description: A spur of cartilage arising from inner side of ankle and running along part of outer interfemoral membrane in bats

name: tusk
description: A calcareous tooth that is elongated and protrudes from the mouth.

name: gular fold
description: A transverse fold of skin across the throat (Peters 1964).

name: limb cartilage element
description: A skeletal element that is part of a limb and composed of cartilage tissue.

name: limb bone pre-cartilage condensation
description: A skeletal element that is part of a limb and composed of pre-cartilage tissue.

name: forelimb cartilage element
description: A cartilaginous condensation that has the potential to develop into a forelimb bone.

name: forelimb bone pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a forelimb bone.

name: hindlimb cartilage element
description: A cartilaginous condensation that has the potential to develop into a hindlimb bone.

name: hindlimb pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a hindlimb bone.

name: tragus
description: A small pointed eminence of the external ear, situated in front of the concha, and projecting backward over the meatus.

name: obsolete seta
description: A hair-like unicellular external process of the body wall or any derivative of the latter; a hair; a bristle.

name: ectethmoid
description: either of two lateral parts of the ethmoid bone that form part of the anterior wall of the orbit

name: pelvic complex muscle
description: Muscles of the pelvic girdle, hindlimb or pelvic fin.

name: pectoral complex muscle
description: A muscle of a pectoral girdle, pectoral fin or anterior limb.

name: mesethmoid element
description: An endochondral element of the nasal capsule that forms septum between nasal capsules and usually remains unossified in mammals

name: median external naris
description: Am unpaired external naris that lies in the midline of the head.

name: sequential hermaphroditic organism
description: Hermaphroditic organism that produces gametes first of one sex, and then later of the other sex.

name: gastralium
description: Dermal element that arises via intramembranous ossification and are developmentally distinct from true ribs that articulate with the vertebral column.

name: synchronous hermaphroditic organism
description: Hermaphroditic organism that produces both male and female gametes at the same time.

name: tarsometatarsus cartilage element
description: A cartilaginous condensation that has the potential to develop into a tarsometatarsus.

name: tarsometatarsus pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a tarsometatarsus.

name: tibiotarsus cartilage element
description: A cartilaginous condensation that has the potential to develop into a tibiotarsus.

name: tibiotarsus pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a tibiotarsus.

name: clavicle bone primordium
description: A primordium that develops into a clavicle bone.

name: parafibula
description: third bone of the lower leg, normally restricted to the area of the knee, in multuberculates, monotremes and some therians

name: paraglossale
description: An arrowhead-shaped bone in the avian hyoid apparatus which forms the base of the tongue

name: opisthotic
description: Posterior ossification of the otic capsule.

name: ossicle
description: Skeletal element that is often isolated, small, and variable in composition.

name: subdivision of skeleton
description: Anatomical cluster consisting of the skeletal elements (i.e. bone elements, cartilage elements, cartilage condensations) that are part of an individual subdivision of the organism. Excludes joints.

name: vertebral element
description: Skeletal element that forms around the notochord and is part of the vertebral column.

name: median thyrohyoid ligament
description: The middle thicker part of the thyrohyoid membrane is termed the median thyrohyoid ligament (middle hyothyroid ligament, middle thyrohyoid ligament), its lateral thinner portions are pierced by the superior laryngeal vessels and the internal branch of the superior laryngeal nerve. Its anterior surface is in relation with the Thyreohyoideus, Sternohyoideus, and Omohyoideus, and with the body of the hyoid bone

name: lateral thyrohyoid ligament
description: The lateral thyrohyoid ligament (lateral hyothyroid ligament) is a round elastic cord, which forms the posterior border of the hyothyroid membrane and passes between the tip of the superior cornu of the thyroid cartilage and the extremity of the greater cornu of the hyoid bone. The recurrent laryngeal nerve typical lies lateral to this ligament

name: thyroepiglotticus muscle
description: fibers of the thyroarytenoid muscle that continue to the margin of the epiglottis; it closes the inlet to the larynx.
synonyms: ["pars thyroepiglottica (musculus thyroarytenoideus)","pars thyroepiglottica musculus thyroarytenoidei","thyro-epiglottic part of thyro-arytenoid","thyroepiglottic","thyroepiglottic muscle","thyroepiglotticus","thyroepiglottus","thyroepiglottus muscle"]

name: cricopharyngeus muscle
description: The cricopharyngeus is a pharyngeal arch 4/6 muscle that participates in oral/pharyngeal behaviors and is innervated by the pharyngeal plexus and the recurrent laryngeal n. (from Vagus, CN X), and is an integral part of the pharyngeal tube, and attaches to the cricoid cartilage and the midline raphe. It acts as a sphincter between the pharynx and esophagus.
synonyms: ["cricopharyngeal part","cricopharyngeal part of inferior constrictor pharyngeus","cricopharyngeal part of inferior pharyngeal constrictor","cricopharyngeal part of inferior pharyngeal constrictor muscle","cricopharyngeus","cricopharyngeus portion of the inferior pharyngeal constrictor","musculus cricopharyngeus","pars cricopharyngea (musculus constrictor pharyngis inferior)","pars cricopharyngea musculus constrictoris pharyngis inferioris"]

name: intermandibularis
description: Is a mandibular muscle that develops into the ventral intermandibularis anterior and posterior muscles.

name: crico-arytenoid muscle
description: Cricoarytenoid muscles are muscles that connect the cricoid cartilage and arytenoid cartilage. More specifically, it can refer to: Posterior cricoarytenoid muscle Lateral cricoarytenoid muscle

name: orbicularis oris muscle
description: The orbicularis oris is a superficial facial muscle with fibers that encircle the opening of the oral cavity that attaches to the maxilla, mandible, skin and modiolus, and that participates in oral/pharyngeal behaviors, and is innervated by the facial nerve (CN VII).

name: thyropharyngeus muscle
synonyms: ["musculus thyropharyngeus","pars thyropharyngea (musculus constrictor pharyngis inferior)","pars thyropharyngea musculus constrictoris pharyngis inferioris","thyropharyngeal part of inferior constrictor pharyngeus","thyropharyngeal part of inferior constrictor pharyngeus muscle","thyropharyngeal part of inferior pharyngeal constrictor","thyropharyngeus"]

name: salpingopharyngeus muscle
description: The salpingopharyngeus muscle arises from the inferior part of the cartilage of the pharyngotympanic tube (Eustachian tube) in the nasal cavity; it passes downward and blends with the posterior fasciculus of the palatopharyngeus muscle. The salpingopharyngeus is known to raise the pharynx and larynx during deglutition (swallowing) and laterally draws the pharyngeal walls up. In addition, it opens the pharyngeal orifice of the pharyngotympanic tube during swallowing. This allows for the equalization of pressure between the auditory canal and the pharynx. The salpingopharyngeus is innervated by the vagus nerve (CN X) via the pharyngeal plexus.

name: muscle of digastric group
description: Either of the two muscles that comprise the digastric group (anterior or posterior).

name: anterior digastric muscle
description: The anterior digastric is a pharyngeal arch I muscle that participates in oral/pharygeal behaviors and is innervated by the nerve to mylohyoid (a branch of the third division of the trigeminal nerve), is attached to the mandible and to the hyoid apparatus, and it is superficial to mylohyoid muscle.
synonyms: ["anterior belly of digastric","anterior belly of digastric muscle","anterior digastric","anterior digastric muscle","digastric, anterior","digastricus anterior","digastricus anterior belly","digastricus, venter rostralis","venter anterior (musculus digastricus)","venter posterior musculus digastrici anterior"]

name: posterior digastric muscle
description: The posterior digastric is a pharyngeal arch II muscle that participates in oral pharyngeal behavior, is innervated by the digastric branch of facial nerve and attaches to the posterior cranial base and the hyoid apparatus. It is found superficial to the mylohyoid muscle.
synonyms: ["digastric, posterior","digastricus posterior","digastricus posterior belly","digastricus, venter caudalis","m. digastricus posterior","posterior belly of digastric","posterior belly of digastric muscle","posterior digastric muscle","venter posterior musculus digastrici"]

name: jugulohyoideus muscle
description: runs from the processus jugularis to the os stylohyoideum; innervated with the ramus jugulohyoideus from the nervus facialis

name: occipitofrontalis muscle
description: The occipitofrontalis or epicranius is a muscle which covers parts of the skull. It consists of two parts or bellies: The occipital belly, near the occipital bone, and the frontal belly, near the frontal bone.

name: occipitalis
description: A belly of the occipitofrontalis muscle that is near the occipital bone
synonyms: ["occipital belly of occipitofrontalis","occipital part of occipitofrontalis","venter occipitalis (musculus occipitofrontalis)","venter transversa musculi occipitofrontalis occipitalis","venter transversa musculus occipitofrontalis occipitalis"]

name: cleidooccipital muscle
description: A muscle organ that attaches_to a clavicle and attaches_to a occipital bone.

name: sternooccipital muscle
description: A muscle organ that has_muscle_insertion a occipital bone and has_muscle_origin a sternum.

name: styloauricular muscle
description: An occasional small muscle extending from the root of the styloid process to the cartilage of the meatus of the ear

name: interscutular muscle
description: A muscle that attaches to the base of the ear and to the middle of the skull

name: frontalis muscle belly
description: A belly of the occipitofrontalis muscle that is near the frontal bone
synonyms: ["frontal belly of occipitofrontalis","frontal part of occipitofrontalis","frontalis","frontalis muscke","orbito-temporo-auricularis","venter frontalis (musculus occipitofrontalis)","venter frontalis musculus occipitofrontalis"]

name: nasalis muscle
description: The nasalis (compressor naris) is a sphincter-like muscle of the nose whose function is to compress the nasal cartilage. It consists of two parts, transverse and alar: The transverse part arises from the maxilla, above and lateral to the incisive fossa; its fibers proceed upward and medially, expanding into a thin aponeurosis which is continuous on the bridge of the nose with that of the muscle of the opposite side, and with the aponeurosis of the Procerus. The alar part is attached at one end to the greater alar cartilage, and at the other to the integument at the point of the nose. Other sources divide it into 'Compressor nasalis' and 'Dilator nasalis'.

name: ceratohyoideus muscle
description: The ceratohyoideus is a muscle of Pharyngeal Arch III that participates in oral/pharyngeal behaviors and is innervated by the glossopharyngeal n. , and attaches to the ceratohyal part of the hyoid apparatus and also to a non-ceratohyal part of the hyoid apparatus.

name: pterygopharyngeal part of superior pharyngeal constrictor
synonyms: ["pars pterygopharyngea (musculus constrictor pharyngis superior)","pars pterygopharyngea musculus constrictoris pharyngis superioris","pterygopharyngeal part of superior constrictor pharyngeus"]

name: arytenoid muscle
description: A single muscle, filling up the posterior concave surfaces of the arytenoid cartilages. It arises from the posterior surface and lateral border of one arytenoid cartilage, and is inserted into the corresponding parts of the opposite cartilage. It consists of oblique and transverse parts.

name: craniocervical muscle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of either the head or the neck.

name: transverospinalis pre-muscle mass
description: A pre-muscle condensation that will develop into a transverospinalis muscle.

name: transversospinales muscle
description: The transversospinal muscles are a group of muscles of the human back. Their combined action is rotation and extension of the vertebral column. They include: semispinalis, spanning 4-6 vertebral segments semispinalis dorsi semispinalis cervicis semispinalis capitis multifidus, spanning 2-4 vertebral segments rotatores, spanning 1-2 vertebral segments rotatores cervicis rotatores thoracis rotatores lumborum

name: coronoid process of ulna
description: A a triangular eminence projecting forward from the proximal epiphysis of the ulna.
synonyms: ["coronoid process","coronoid process of the ulna","processus coronoideus","ulnar coronoid process"]

name: deep part of masseter muscle
synonyms: ["deep layer of masseter","deep part of masseter","masseter, deep","masseter, profundus","pars profunda (musculus masseter)","pars profunda musculus masseterica","pars profunda of masseter muscle"]

name: articular cartilage of joint
description: A thin layer of cartilage, usually hyaline, on the articular surface of bones in synovial joints.

name: articular cartilage element
description: Cartilage of the lower jaw that give rise to a portion of the anguloarticular compound bone.

name: pharyngeal arch cartilage
description: A cartilage element that is part of a splanchnocranium.

name: endocardium of auricle
description: An endocardium that is part of a atrium auricular region.

name: endocardium of left auricle
description: An endocardium that is part of a left atrium auricular region.
synonyms: ["left atrium auricular region endocardium","left auricle endocardium"]

name: endocardium of right auricle
description: An endocardium that is part of a right atrium auricular region.

name: brachioradialis
description: Brachioradialis is a muscle of the forearm that acts to flex the forearm at the elbow. It is also capable of both pronation and supination, depending on the position of the forearm. It is attached to the distal styloid process of the radius by way of the brachioradialis tendon, and to the lateral supracondylar ridge of the humerus.

name: flexor pollicis brevis muscle
description: The flexor pollicis brevis is a muscle in the hand that flexes the thumb. It is one of three thenar muscles. It has both a superficial part and a deep part.

name: spinalis muscle
description: The spinalis is the portion of the erector spinae, a bundle of muscles and tendons, located nearest to the spine. It is divided into three parts..

name: spinalis capitis muscle
description: Origin: spines of upper thoracic and lower cervical vertebrae; insertion: occipital bone; innervation: spinal nerves; action, extends head.

name: pyramidalis
description: The pyramidalis is a small and triangular muscle, anterior to the Rectus abdominis, and contained in the rectus sheath.

name: semispinalis muscle
description: A transversospinalis muscle of the human body.

name: flexor hallucis brevis muscle
description: A muscle that originates from the cuboid bone and divides into two portions, which are inserted into the medial and lateral sides of the base of the first phalanx of the great toe, a sesamoid bone being present in each tendon at its insertion.
synonyms: ["flexor hallucis brevis","flexor hallucis brevis muscle","m.flexor hallucis brevis"]

name: extrinsic extensor muscle of manus
description: The extrinsic extensor muscles of the hand are located in the back of the forearm and have long tendons connecting them to bones in the hand, where they exert their action.

name: aryepiglotticus muscle
description: The aryepiglotticus is a muscle of the larynx running in the aryepiglottic fold from the arytenoid cartilage to the epiglottis.
synonyms: ["ary-epiglottic part of oblique arytenoid","aryepiglottic","aryepiglottic muscle","aryepiglotticus","aryepiglottus","aryepiglottus muscle","pars aryepiglottica (musculus arytenoideus obliquus)","pars aryepiglottica musculus arytenoidei obliqui"]

name: obturator muscle
description: One of: obturator externus or obturator internus

name: obturator internus
description: The obturator internus muscle originates on the medial surface of the obturator membrane, the ischium near the membrane, and the rim of the pubis. It exits the pelvic cavity through the lesser sciatic foramen. The obturator internus is situated partly within the lesser pelvis, and partly at the back of the hip-joint. It functions to help laterally rotate extended thigh and abduct flexed thigh, as well as to steady the femoral head in the acetabulum.

name: uterovesical pouch
description: The peritoneum over the rectum and the bladder is continued over the intestinal surface and fundus of the uterus on to its vesical surface, which it covers as far as the junction of the body and cervix uteri, and then to the bladder, forming here a second, but shallower, pouch, the vesicouterine excavation (or uterovesical pouch). The vesicouterine excavation is close to the anterior fornix of the vagina.

name: thoracic vertebra 8
description: The eighth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down. Note that members of this class are not necessarily homologous.

name: perilymphatic channel
description: A channel containing perilymph passing through the temporal bone, connecting the scala tympani of the cochlea to the subarachnoid space.

name: endolymphatic space
description: endolymph-filled space contained by the membranous labyrinth.

name: angular bone
description: Dermal bone that is located posterior to the dentary and lateral to the articular and retroarticular bones of the lower jaw. The angular forms the outer dermal sheet of the posterior part of the lower jaw. The angular bears a portion of the mandibular sensory canal. The angular is a paired bone.

name: palatoquadrate arch
description: The dorsal portion of the first pharyngeal arch, comprising the upper jaw.

name: ligament of knee joint
description: A ligament that is part of a knee joint.

name: skeleton of right pelvic girdle
description: A skeleton of pelvic girdle that is part of a right pelvic girdle region.

name: skeleton of left pelvic girdle
description: A skeleton of pelvic girdle that is part of a left pelvic girdle region.

name: right pelvic girdle region
description: A pelvic girdle region that is in the right side of a multicellular organism.

name: left pelvic girdle region
description: A pelvic girdle region that is in the left side of a multicellular organism.

name: vertebra cartilage element
description: The cartilaginous form of a vertebral element, a skeletal element that forms around the notochord and is part of the vertebral column.

name: vertebra pre-cartilage condensation
description: The pre-cartilaginous form of a vertebral element, a skeletal element that forms around the notochord and is part of the vertebral column.

name: lacrimal nerve
description: The lacrimal nerve is the smallest of the three branches of the ophthalmic division of the trigeminal nerve.

name: epiphysis of fifth metacarpal bone
description: An epiphysis that is part of a metacarpal bone of digit 5.

name: cruciate ligament of atlas
description: A cruciate ligament in the neck forming part of the atlanto-axial joint. It consists of the transverse ligament of the atlas, along with additional fibers above and below.
synonyms: ["cruciate ligament of dens","cruciform ligament of atlas","cruciform ligament of dens","ligamentum cruciforme atlantis"]

name: synovial joint of pelvic girdle
description: A synovial joint that is part of a pelvic girdle region.

name: synovial joint of pectoral girdle
description: A synovial joint that is part of a pectoral girdle region.

name: humeroulnar joint
description: The humeroulnar joint, is part of the elbow-joint or the Olecron Joint, between the ulna and humerus bones is the simple hinge-joint, which allows for movements of flexion, extension and circumduction. The Humero-Ulnar Joint is the junction of trochlear notch of the ulna and the trochlea of the humerus. Owing to the obliquity of the trochlea of the humerus, this movement does not take place in the antero-posterior plane of the body of the humerus. When the forearm is extended and supinated, the axis of the arm and forearm are not in the same line; the arm forms an obtuse angle with the forearm. During flexion, however, the forearm and the hand tend to approach the middle line of the body, and thus enable the hand to be easily carried to the face. The accurate adaptation of the trochlea of the humerus, with its prominences and depressions, to the semilunar notch of the ulna, prevents any lateral movement. Flexion is produced by the action of the Biceps brachii and Brachialis, assisted by the Brachioradialis, with a tiny contribution from the muscles arising from the medial epicondyle of the humerus. Extension is produced by the Triceps brachii and AnconC&us, with a tiny contribution from the muscles arising from the lateral epicondyle of the humerus, such as the Extensor digitorum communis.

name: humeroradial joint
description: A hinge joint between the head of the radius and the capitulum of the humerus.

name: tibiofibular joint
description: A joint that connects the tibia and the fibula.

name: inferior tibiofibular joint
description: The inferior tibiofibular articulation (tibiofibular syndesmosis) is formed by the rough, convex surface of the medial side of the lower end of the fibula, and a rough concave surface on the lateral side of the tibia. Below, to the extent of about 4 mm. these surfaces are smooth, and covered with cartilage, which is continuous with that of the ankle-joint. The ligaments are: Anterior ligament of the lateral malleolus, Posterior ligament of the lateral malleolus, Inferior transverse ligament of the tibiofibular syndesmosis, Interosseous ligament

name: superior tibiofibular joint
description: The superior tibiofibular articulation is an arthrodial joint between the lateral condyle of the tibia and the head of the fibula. The contiguous surfaces of the bones present flat, oval facets covered with cartilage and connected together by an articular capsule and by anterior and posterior ligaments. When the term 'tibiofibular articulation' is used without a modifier, it refers to the superior, and not the inferior tibiofibular articulation.

name: tarsometatarsal joint
description: The tarsometatarsal articulations are arthrodial joints in the pes.

name: carpometacarpal joint
description: The carpometacarpal joints (CMC) are joints in the wrist that articulates the distal row of carpal bones and the proximal bases of the metacarpal bones.

name: laryngeal joint
description: A skeletal joint that connects a laryngeal cartilage.

name: cricothyroid joint
description: The cricoarytenoid articulation (or joint) is a joint connecting the cricoid cartilage and the thyroid cartilage.

name: cricoarytenoid joint
description: The cricoarytenoid articulation (or joint) is a joint connecting the cricoid cartilage and the arytenoid cartilage.

name: stifle joint
description: A complex joint in the hind limbs of quadruped mammals such as the sheep, horse or dog. It is the equivalent joint to the human knee. It is often the largest synovial joint in the body.

name: xiphisternal joint
description: The xiphisternal joint (or xiphisternal synchondrosis) is a location near the bottom of the sternum, where the body of the sternum and the xiphoid process.

name: intermetacarpal joint
description: A skeletal joint that connects two adjacent metacarpals.

name: intercarpal joint
description: A skeletal joint that connects two carpal bones.

name: intermetatarsal joint
description: A joint that connects two adjacent metatarsals

name: nonsynovial joint
description: Joint in which the articulating bones or cartilages are connected by ligaments or fibrocartilage without an intervening synovial cavity. Examples: sagittal suture, inferior tibiofibular syndesmosis, costochondral joint, pubic symphysis.

name: intervertebral cartilage
description: A cartilage element that lies between two successive vertebral centra.

name: ligament of vertebral column
description: ligament that joins successive centra. Important in controlling the stiffness of the vertebral column when it flexes.

name: axial skeletal system
description: Subdivision of the skeletal system which consists of the axial skeleton plus associated joints.

name: postcranial axial skeletal system
description: Subdivision of the skeletal system which consists of the postcranial axial skeleton plus associated joints.

name: synovial limb joint
description: Any synovial joint that is part of a (free) limb.

name: superficial part of masseter muscle
synonyms: ["masseter, superficial","pars profunda musculus masseterica superficialis","pars superficialis (musculus masseter)","pars superficialis of masseter muscle","superficial layer of masseter","superficial part of masseter"]

name: appendicular ossicle
description: Ossicle that is part of the appendicular skeleton.

name: axial ossicle
description: Ossicle that is part of the axial skeleton.
synonyms: ["ossicle of axial skeleton","ossicle of postcranial-axial skeleton"]

name: upper urinary tract
description: Subdivision of urinary system which consists of the kidney and the ureters.

name: adductor muscle
description: A muscle capable of adduction. Adduction is a movement which brings a part of the anatomy closer to the middle sagittal plane of the body. It is opposed to abduction.

name: silk gland
description: Any of the glands in silk-spinning insects and spiders that secrete a protein liquid that hardens into silk on exposure to air.

name: Verson's gland
description: A gland found in the larvae of lepidoptera. Each gland is made of three cells: the secretory cell, the reservoir cell and the canal cell.

name: submucosal gland
description: Gland of the lamina epithelialis mucosae which perforate the lamina muscularis, with their adenomeres located in the submucosal connective tissue.

name: Marshall's gland
description: A paired hollow organ in the genito-urinary apparatus of Raja (and probably other skates and rays) whose cavity is fluid filled.

name: pharyngeal arch derived gill
description: A gill that develops_from a pharyngeal gill precursor.

name: jaw depressor muscle
description: A muscle whose action is to depress the lower jaw.

name: dorsal hyoid arch skeleton
synonyms: ["dorsal hyoid arch","dorsal pharyngeal arch 2 skeleton","dorsal visceral arch 2"]

name: ventral hyoid arch skeleton
synonyms: ["ventral hyoid arch","ventral pharyngeal arch 2 skeleton","ventral visceral arch 2"]

name: gular region
description: Surface structure that extends from the chin covering pharynx and larynx.

name: Sylvian cistern
description: The subarachnoid space associated with the lateral cerebral sulcus (Sylvian fissure); contains the M1 segment of the middle cerebral artery and the origin of lenticulostriate arteries, and proximal parts of the middle cerebral artery

name: facial skeleton
description: Subdivision of skull that consists of the facial bones.

name: cuneiform cartilage
description: The cuneiform cartilages of the larynx are two small, elongated pieces of yellow elastic cartilage, placed one on either side, in the aryepiglottic fold, where they give rise to small whitish elevations on the surface of the mucous membrane, just in front of the arytenoid cartilages.

name: primary subdivision of skull
description: The skull can be divided into two: the neurocranium and the facial skeleton

name: primary subdivision of cranial skeletal system
nasal suture
description: A suture joining a nasal bone to another bone.

name: spheno-occipital synchondrosis
description: The cartilaginous junction between the basisphenoid and basioccipital bones of the mammalian skull

name: supraoccipital cartilage element
description: A cartilaginous condensation that has the potential to develop into a supraoccipital bone.

name: supraoccipital pre-cartilage condensation
description: A pre-cartilage condensation that has the potential to develop into a supraoccipital bone.

name: neurocranium bone
description: A bone that is part of a neurocranium.

name: crico-esophageal tendon
description: Longitudinal fibers of the esophagus that attaches to the posterior aspect of the cricoid cartilage of the larynx

name: septomaxilla bone
description: Paired, intramembranous bones located within the nasal capsules and embedded in the nasal cartilages; it is pierced by the ductus nasolacrimalis.

name: postfrontal bone
description: A bone behind and above the orbit of which it commonly forms part of the border that is present in many vertebrates and corresponds to the postorbital process of the frontal bone of various birds and mammals

name: postorbital bone
description: The postorbital is one of the bones in vertebrate skulls which forms a portion of the dermal skull roof and, sometimes, a ring about the orbit. Generally, it is located behind the postfrontal and posteriorly to the orbital fenestra. In some vertebrates, the postorbital is fused with the postfrontal to create a postorbitofrontal.

name: quadrate-articular joint
description: A skeletal joint that connects quadrate and articular bones.

name: joint connecting upper and lower jaws
description: Synovial joint that articulates bones of upper and lower jaw.

name: retrorubral area of midbrain reticular nucleus
description: The term retrorubral area of the midbrain reticular nucleus refers to a region of the rat brain caudal and dorsal to the ventral tegmental area. It is one of three parts of the midbrain reticular nucleus; the other two are the magnocellular part of the midbrain reticular nucleus and the parvicellular part of the midbrain reticular nucleus (Swanson-2004). BrainInfo distinguishes between the Retrorubral area of the midbrain reticular formation and the retrorubral nucleus.
synonyms: ["A8","midbrain reticular nucleus, retrorubral area","retrorubal field","retrorubral area"]

name: anterior division of bed nuclei of stria terminalis
description: One of two divisions of the nuclei of stria terminalis based on topology, connectivity and multiple stains in the rat ( Swanson-2004 ) and the mouse ( Dong-2004 ). The other division consists of the posterior nuclei of stria terminalis. The anterior division includes the anterolateral area of stria terminalis, anteromedial area of stria terminalis, oval nucleus of stria terminalis, juxtacapsular nucleus of stria terminalis, rhomboid nucleus of stria terminalis, dorsomedial nucleus of stria terminalis, fusiform nucleus of stria terminalis, ventral nucleus of stria terminalis, and the magnocellular nucleus of stria terminalis
synonyms: ["anterior division","anterior nuclei of stria terminalis","bed nuclei of the stria terminalis, anterior division"]

name: fusiform nucleus of stria terminalis
synonyms: ["bed nuclei of the stria terminalis, anterior division, fusiform nucleus","fusiform nucleus"]

name: oval nucleus of stria terminalis
synonyms: ["bed nuclei of the stria terminalis, anterior division, oval nucleus","oval nucleus"]

name: posterior division of bed nuclei of stria terminalis
description: One of two divisions of the nuclei of stria terminalis based on topology, connectivity and multiple stains in the rat ( Swanson-2004 ) and the mouse ( Dong-2004 ). The other division consists of the anterior nuclei of stria terminalis. The posterior division includes the principal nucleus of stria terminalis, interfascicular nucleus of stria terminalis, transverse nucleus of stria terminalis, premedullary nucleus of stria terminalis, dorsal nucleus of stria terminalis, the strial extension of stria terminalis, and the cell sparse zone of stria terminalis.
synonyms: ["bed nuclei of the stria terminalis, posterior division","posterior division","posterior nuclei of stria terminalis"]

name: principal nucleus of stria terminalis
synonyms: ["bed nuclei of the stria terminalis, posterior division, principal nucleus","principal nucleus"]

name: transverse nucleus of stria terminalis
synonyms: ["bed nuclei of the stria terminalis, posterior division, transverse nucleus","transverse nucleus"]

name: corpus spongiosum of penis
description: Corpus spongiosum (also known as corpus cavernosum urethrae in older texts) is the mass of spongy tissue surrounding the male urethra within the penis.

name: epithelium of crypt of Lieberkuhn
description: An epithelium that is part of a crypt of Lieberkuhn.

name: gastrointestinal sphincter
description: A sphincter muscle that is part of the gastrointestinal system

name: Krause's gland
description: small, mucous accessory lacrimal glands that are found underneath the eyelid where the upper and lower conjuctivae meet. Their ducts unite into a rather long sinus which open into the fornix conjunctiva. There are approximately forty Krause glands in the region of the upper eyelid, and around 6 to 8 in the region of the lower lid. The function of these glands are to produce tears which are secreted onto the surface of the conjuctiva

name: ventral tubercle of humerus
description: The greater tubercle of the humerus is situated lateral to the head of the humerus and posteriolateral to the lesser tubercle. Its upper surface is rounded and marked by three flat impressions. the highest of these gives ('superior facet') insertion to the Supraspinatus the middle ('middle facet') to the Infraspinatus. the lowest one ('inferior facet'), and the body of the bone for about 2.5 cm. below it, to the Teres minor. The lateral surface of the greater tubercle is convex, rough, and continuous with the lateral surface of the body. Between the greater tubercle and the lesser tubercle is the intertubercular sulcus (bicipital groove).
synonyms: ["greater tubercle","greater tubercle of humerus","greater tuberosity of humerus","tuberculum majus","tuberculum majus humeri"]

name: lesser tubercle of humerus
description: The lesser tubercle of the humerus, although smaller, is more prominent than the greater tubercle: it is situated in front, and is directed medially and anteriorly. Above and in front it presents an impression for the insertion of the tendon of the Subscapularis.

name: lamina propria of large intestine
description: A lamina propria that is part of a large intestine.
synonyms: ["lamina propria of mucosa of large intestine","large intestinal lamina propria","large intestine lamina propria"]

name: lunule of nail
description: A crescent-shaped whitish area of the bed of a fingernail or toenail. The lunula is the visible part of the nail matrix (i.e. the root of the nail).

name: ophthalmic vein
description: Ophthalmic veins are veins which drain the eye. More specifically, they can refer to: Superior ophthalmic vein Inferior ophthalmic vein

name: superior ophthalmic vein
description: The superior ophthalmic vein begins at the inner angle of the orbit in a vein named the nasofrontal which communicates anteriorly with the angular vein; it pursues the same course as the ophthalmic artery, and receives tributaries corresponding to the branches of that vessel. Forming a short single trunk, it passes between the two heads of the Rectus lateralis and through the medial part of the superior orbital fissure, and ends in the cavernous sinus. The ethmoidal veins drain into the superior ophthalmic vein. Vorticose veins also drain into the superior ophthalmic vein.

name: inferior ophthalmic vein
description: The inferior ophthalmic vein begins in a venous net-work at the forepart of the floor and medial wall of the orbit; it receives some vorticose veins and other veins from the Rectus inferior, Obliquus inferior, lacrimal sac and eyelids, runs backward in the lower part of the orbit and divides into two branches. One of these passes through the inferior orbital fissure and joins the pterygoid venous plexus, while the other enters the cranium through the superior orbital fissure and ends in the cavernous sinus, either by a separate opening, or more frequently in common with the superior ophthalmic vein.

name: ophthalmic plexus
description: An autonomic plexus, entering the orbit in company with the ophthalmic artery, derived from the internal carotid plexus.

name: inferior parathyroid epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a inferior parathyroid gland.

name: superior parathyroid epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a superior parathyroid gland.

name: parathyroid epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a parathyroid gland.

name: muscle layer of large intestine
description: A muscle layer that is part of a large intestine.
synonyms: ["muscular coat of large intestine","muscular layer of large intestine","muscularis externa of large intestine","tunica muscularis intestini crassi"]

name: prostatic utricle
description: A small indentation located in the prostatic urethra, at the apex of the urethral crest, on the seminal colliculus (verumontanum), laterally flanked by openings of the ejaculatory ducts.
synonyms: ["sinus pocularis","uterus masculinus","utricle of prostate","utriculus of prostate","vagina masculina"]

name: sacrococcygeal symphysis
description: The sacrococcygeal symphysis (sacrococcygeal articulation, articulation of the sacrum and coccyx) is an amphiarthrodial joint, formed between the oval surface at the apex of the sacrum, and the base of the coccyx. It is a slightly moveable joint which is frequently, partially or completely, obliterated in old age, homologous with the joints between the bodies of the vertebrae.

name: muscle layer of small intestine
description: A muscle layer that is part of a small intestine.
synonyms: ["muscular coat of small intestine","muscular layer of small intestine","muscularis externa of small intestine","small intestine muscularis propria","tunica muscularis (intestinum tenue)","tunica muscularis intestini tenuis"]

name: urachus epithelium
description: An epithelium that is part of a urachus.

name: urachus mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing urachus.

name: rectovesical pouch
description: Between the rectum and the bladder the peritoneal cavity forms, in the male, a pouch, the rectovesical excavation (or rectovesical pouch), the bottom of which is slightly below the level of the upper ends of the vesiculae seminalesbi. e. , about 7.5 cm. from the orifice of the anus. its lowest part membranous partition called Rectoprostatic fascia. The corresponding structure in women is the rectouterine pouch.

name: carpometacarpus
description: The carpometacarpus is the fusion of the carpal and metacarpal bone, essentially a single fused bone between the wrist and the knuckles. It is a smallish bone in most birds, generally flattened and with a large hole in the middle. In flightless birds, however, its shape may be slightly different, or it might be absent entirely.

name: hinge joint
description: A joint that allows motion around an axis.

name: iliocostalis lumborum
description: The iliocostalis lumborum (iliocostalis muscle; sacrolumbalis muscle) is inserted, by six or seven flattened tendons, into the inferior borders of the angles of the lower six or seven ribs.

name: root of vagus nerve
description: A root of cranial nerve that is part of a vagus nerve.
synonyms: ["rootlet of vagus nerve","rX","vagal root","vagus nerve root","vagus root"]

name: nucleus of midbrain tectum
description: A neural nucleus that is part of a midbrain tectum.

name: central nervous system cell part cluster
description: A multi cell part structure that is part of a central nervous system.

name: organ system subdivision
description: A subdivision of an anatomical system.

name: spinalis cervicis muscle
description: Origin: spinous processes of seventh cervical and sometimes two upper thoracic vertebrae; insertion: spinous processes of axis and sometimes of second to fourth cervical vertebrae; innervation: branches of cervical; action: extends vertebral column.

name: longissimus lumborum muscle
description: Lumbar muscle that extends and rotates the vertebral column.

name: mastoid process of temporal bone
description: The mastoid process is a conical prominence projecting from the undersurface of the mastoid portion of the temporal bone. It is located just behind the external acoustic meatus, and lateral to the styloid process. Its size and form vary somewhat; it is larger in the male than in the female. This process serves for the attachment of the posterior belly of the digastric, sternocleidomastoid, splenius capitis, and longissimus capitis muscles. The word is derived from the Greek 'masto-', alluding to its resemblance to the breast.

name: ora serrata of retina
description: The ora serrata is the serrated junction between the retina and the ciliary body. This junction marks the transition from the simple non-photosensitive area of the retina to the complex, multi-layered photosensitive region. In animals in which the region does not have a serrated appearance, it is called the ora ciliaris retinae.

name: synovial membrane of synovial tendon sheath
description: Synovial sac which surrounds parts of one or more tendons. Examples: synovial tendon sheath of manual digit 2, radial bursa.

name: fibrous membrane of synovial tendon sheath
deep fascia
description: Deep fascia (or 'investing fascia') is a layer of fascia which can surround individual muscles, and divide groups of muscles into compartments. This is the dense fibrous connective tissue that interpenetrates and surrounds the muscles, bones, nerves and blood vessels of the body. It provides connection and communication in the form of aponeuroses, ligaments, tendons, retinacula, joint capsules, and septa. The deep fasciae envelop all bone; cartilage, and blood vessels and become specialized in muscles and nerves. The high density of collagen fibers is what gives the deep fascia its strength and integrity. The amount of elastin fiber determines how much extensibility and resilience it will have.

name: visceral fascia
description: Fascia that suspends a visceral organ.

name: mesethmoid bone
description: An ossified mesethmoid element

name: ethmoid region
description: The most anterior region of the braincase. Provides structural support for peripheral olfactory organ.

name: ethmoid cartilage
description: Region between capsules formed by anterior tips of neurocranial trabeculae.

name: perpendicular plate of ethmoid
description: The perpendicular plate of the ethmoid bone (vertical plate) is a thin, flattened lamina, polygonal in form, which descends from the under surface of the cribriform plate, and assists in forming the septum of the nose; it is generally deflected a little to one or other side. The anterior border articulates with the spine of the frontal bone and the crest of the nasal bones. The posterior border articulates by its upper half with the sphenoidal crest, by its lower with the vomer. The inferior border is thicker than the posterior, and serves for the attachment of the septal cartilage of the nose. The surfaces of the plate are smooth, except above, where numerous grooves and canals are seen; these lead from the medial foramina on the cribriform plate and lodge filaments of the olfactory nerves.
synonyms: ["lamina perpendicularis (os ethmoidale)","lamina perpendicularis of ethmoid bone","perpendicular plate"]

name: infra-orbital canal of maxilla
description: A canal through the maxilla that is connects the infra-orbital groove and foramen and is the conduit for the passage of the infraorbital nerve and artery.

name: procoracoid element
description: Endochondral element of pectoral girdle, positioned posterior to the clavicle and anterior to the coracoid.

name: appendicular skeletal system
description: Subdivision of the skeletal system which consists of the appendicular skeleton plus associated joints.

name: autopod bone
description: A bone that is part of a autopod region. Note that this incudes the carpal and tarsal bones.

name: levator claviculae muscle
description: A skeletal muscle in the posterior triangle of the neck. It originates on the transverse processes of the upper cervical vertebrae and is inserted in the lateral half of the clavicle

name: scent gland
description: Scent glands are exocrine glands found in most mammals. They produce semi-viscous secretions which contain pheromones and other semiochemical compounds. These odor-messengers indicate information such as status, territory marking, mood, and sexual power. The odor may be subliminal-not consciously detectable. Though it is not their primary function, the salivary glands may also function as scent glands in some animals.

name: Eimer's organ
description: A sensory organ in which the epidermis is modified to form bulbous papillae. The organs are formed from a stack of epidermal cells, which is innervated by nerve processes from myelinated fibers in the dermis, which form terminal swellings just below the outer keratinized layer of epidermis. They contain a Merkel cell-neurite complex in the epidermis and a lamellated corpuscle in the dermal connective tissue.

name: rhinarium
description: Moist, hairless, crenelated area around nostrils of some mammals

name: femoral gland
description: A gland arranged along a row on the underside of the hindlimb in some lizards

name: femoral pore
description: Femoral pores are a part of a holocrine secretory gland found on the inside of the thighs of certain lizards and amphisbaenians which releases pheromones to attract mates or mark territory. In certain species only the male has these pores and in other species, both sexes have them, with the males being larger. Femoral pores appear as a series of pits or holes within a row of scales on the ventral portion of the animal's thigh.

name: carpometacarpal joint of digit 1
description: A carpometacarpal joint that connects to metacarpal 1.
synonyms: ["carpometacarpal joint of digit I","carpometacarpal joint of pollex","carpometacarpal joint of thumb"]

name: quadratojugal bone
description: The quadratojugal is a small jaw bone that is present in most amphibians, reptiles, and birds, but has been lost in mammals. It is connected to the jugal as well as other bones, though these may vary with species. The quadratojugal bone is a small bone between the cheek and otic notch (Lecointre 380). Squamates (lizards and snakes) lack a quadratojugal bone (Schwenk 193).

name: sublingua
description: A secondary tongue located below the primary tongue in prosimian primates and some primitive mammals. This structure does not have taste buds or salivary glands

name: dorsal trunk
description: The part of the trunk that is in the dorsum.
synonyms: ["back of trunk","dorsal part of trunk","dorsum of trunk","trunk back"]

name: caudal-sacral region of vertebral column
description: Subdivision of vertebral column that is posterior to the sacral region and anterior to the caudal region.

name: nail of manual digit 1
description: A nail that is part of a manual digit 1.
synonyms: ["claw of digit 1 of fore-paw","nail of manual digit I","nail of thumb","nail plate of thumb","thumb nail"]

name: nail of manual digit 2
description: A nail that is part of a manual digit 2.
synonyms: ["claw of digit 2 of fore-paw","index finger nail","nail of index finger","nail of manual digit II","nail of second finger","nail plate of index finger"]

name: nail of manual digit 3
description: A nail that is part of a manual digit 3.
synonyms: ["claw of digit 3 of fore-paw","middle finger nail","nail of manual digit III","nail of middle finger","nail of third finger","nail plate of middle finger"]

name: nail of manual digit 4
description: A nail that is part of a manual digit 4.
synonyms: ["claw of digit 4 of fore-paw","nail of fourth finger","nail of manual digit IV","nail of ring finger","nail plate of ring finger","ring finger nail"]

name: nail of manual digit 5
description: A nail that is part of a manual digit 5.
synonyms: ["claw of digit 5 of fore-paw","little finger nail","nail of fifth finger","nail of manual digit V","nail plate of little finger"]

name: nail of pedal digit 1
description: A nail that is part of a pedal digit 1.
synonyms: ["big toe nail","claw of digit 1 of hind-paw","nail of big toe","nail of great toe","nail of pedal digit I","nail plate of big toe"]

name: nail of pedal digit 2
description: A nail that is part of a pedal digit 2.
synonyms: ["claw of digit 2 of hind-paw","nail of pedal digit II","nail of second toe","nail plate of second toe","second toe nail"]

name: nail of pedal digit 3
description: A nail that is part of a pedal digit 3.
synonyms: ["claw of digit 3 of hind-paw","nail of pedal digit III","nail of third toe","nail plate of third toe","third toe nail"]

name: nail of pedal digit 4
description: A nail that is part of a pedal digit 4.
synonyms: ["claw of digit 4 of hind-paw","fourth toe nail","nail of fourth toe","nail of pedal digit IV","nail plate of fourth toe"]

name: nail of pedal digit 5
description: A nail that is part of a pedal digit 5.
synonyms: ["claw of digit 5 of hind-paw","little toe nail","nail of fifth toe","nail of little toe","nail of pedal digit V","nail plate of little toe"]

name: epoophoron
description: A remnant of the Mesonephric duct that can be found next to the ovary and fallopian tube.

name: rostral organ
description: A putative electroreceptor organ located in the medial rostral cavity in the ethmoid portion of the chondrocranium of Coelacanths. It is surrounded by an insulating layer of adipose tissue and innervated by the superficial ophthalmic nerve.

name: stomochord
description: A flexible, unpaired, hollow tube found in hemichordates that arises in embryonic development as an outpocketing from the roof of the embryonic gut anterior to the pharynx. In adults, they extend dorsally from the pharynx into the probiscis, and serve to communicate with the oral cavity.

name: pharyngobasilar fascia
description: The pharyngeal aponeurosis (or pharyngobasilar fascia, or fibrous coat), is situated between the mucous and muscular layers. It is thick above where the muscular fibers are wanting, and is firmly connected to the basilar portion of the occipital and the petrous portions of the temporal bones. As it descends it diminishes in thickness, and is gradually lost. It is strengthened posteriorly by a strong fibrous band, which is attached above to the pharyngeal spine on the under surface of the basilar portion of the occipital bone, and passes downward, forming a median raphe, which gives attachment to the Constrictores pharyngis.

name: submucosa of uterine tube
description: The submucous layer of the wall of the uterine tube.
synonyms: ["submucosa of fallopian tube","tela submucosa tubae uterinae"]

name: white matter of telencephalon
description: A partion of white matter that is part of a telencephalon. This can be further subdivided in some species, for example, into hemisphere white matter and the corpus callosum.
synonyms: ["predominantly white regional part of telencephalon","telencephalic tract/commissure","telencephalic white matter"]

name: gray matter of telencephalon
description: A portion of gray matter that is part of a telencephalon.

name: tunicate tunic
description: Outer covering of an animal typically consisting primarily of cellulose (tunicin) in addition to varying amounts of water, protein and carbohydrates. The tunicate is a characteristic feature of Tunicata

name: tunicate postabdomen
description: Basalmost subdivision of a tunicate containing the heart and reproductive organs

name: superficial part of temporalis
description: The superficial temporalis muscle is a separable part of the temporalis muscle that attaches to the temporalis fascia
synonyms: ["anterior temporal","temporal muscle anterolateral part","temporales","temporalis anterior head","temporalis pars anterior","temporalis pars superficialis"]

name: deep part of temporalis
description: The deep temporalis muscle is a separable part of the temporalis muscle that that attaches to the bony wall of the braincase and is deep to the superficial temporalis.
synonyms: ["medial temporal","posterior temporal","temporal muscle posterior part","temporalis bbHauptmassebb","temporalis lamina profunda","temporalis pars posterior","temporalis pars profunda","temporalis posterior head"]

name: suprazygomatic part of temporalis
description: The suprazygomatic part of the temporalis muscle is a separable part of the deep temporalis that attaches to the superior surface of the temporal root of the zygomatic arch.

name: pars reflexa of masseter
