name: middle phalanx of digit 3
description: A middle phalanx that is part of a digit 3.
synonyms: ["3rd digit intermediate phalanx","3rd digit middle phalanx","3rd digit of intermediate phalanx","3rd digit of middle phalanx","digit 3 intermediate phalanx","digit 3 middle phalanx","intermediate phalanx of 3rd digit","intermediate phalanx of digit 3","intermediate phalanx of third digit","middle phalanx of 3rd digit","middle phalanx of digit III","middle phalanx of middle digit","middle phalanx of third digit","third digit intermediate phalanx","third digit middle phalanx","third middle phalanx"]

name: middle phalanx of digit 4
description: A middle phalanx that is part of a digit 4.
synonyms: ["4th digit intermediate phalanx","4th digit middle phalanx","4th digit of intermediate phalanx","4th digit of middle phalanx","digit 4 intermediate phalanx","digit 4 middle phalanx","fourth digit intermediate phalanx","fourth digit middle phalanx","fourth middle phalanx","intermediate phalanx of 4th digit","intermediate phalanx of digit 4","intermediate phalanx of fourth digit","middle phalanx of 4th digit","middle phalanx of digit IV","middle phalanx of fourth digit","middle phalanx of ring digit"]

name: middle phalanx of digit 5
description: A middle phalanx that is part of a digit 5.
synonyms: ["5th digit intermediate phalanx","5th digit middle phalanx","5th digit of intermediate phalanx","5th digit of middle phalanx","digit 5 intermediate phalanx","digit 5 middle phalanx","fifth digit intermediate phalanx","fifth digit middle phalanx","fifth middle phalanx","intermediate phalanx of 5th digit","intermediate phalanx of digit 5","intermediate phalanx of fifth digit","middle phalanx of 5th digit","middle phalanx of digit V","middle phalanx of fifth digit","middle phalanx of little digit"]

name: proximal phalanx of digit 1
description: A proximal phalanx that is part of a autopod digit 1.
synonyms: ["digit I P1","digit I-1","first proximal phalanx of autopod","proximal phalanx of digit I","proximal phalanx of first digit of autopod"]

name: proximal phalanx of digit 2
description: A proximal phalanx that is part of a autopod digit 2.
synonyms: ["2nd digit of autopod proximal phalanx","2nd digit proximal phalanx","autopod digit 2 proximal phalanx","digit II-1","digit IU P1","proximal phalanx of 2nd digit","proximal phalanx of 2nd digit of autopod","proximal phalanx of digit II","proximal phalanx of index digit","proximal phalanx of second digit","proximal phalanx of second digit of autopod","second digit proximal phalanx","second proximal phalanx of autopod"]

name: proximal phalanx of digit 3
description: A proximal phalanx that is part of a autopod digit 3.
synonyms: ["3rd digit of autopod proximal phalanx","3rd digit proximal phalanx","autopod digit 3 proximal phalanx","digit III P1","digit III-1","proximal phalanx of 3rd digit","proximal phalanx of 3rd digit of autopod","proximal phalanx of digit III","proximal phalanx of middle digit","proximal phalanx of third digit","proximal phalanx of third digit of autopod","third digit proximal phalanx","third proximal phalanx of autopod"]

name: proximal phalanx of digit 4
description: A proximal phalanx that is part of a autopod digit 4.
synonyms: ["4th digit of autopod proximal phalanx","4th digit proximal phalanx","autopod digit 4 proximal phalanx","digit IV P1","digit IV-1","fourth digit proximal phalanx","fourth proximal phalanx of autopod","proximal phalanx of 4th digit","proximal phalanx of 4th digit of autopod","proximal phalanx of digit IV","proximal phalanx of fourth digit","proximal phalanx of fourth digit of autopod","proximal phalanx of ring digit"]

name: proximal phalanx of digit 5
description: A proximal phalanx that is part of a autopod digit 5.
synonyms: ["5th digit of autopod proximal phalanx","5th digit proximal phalanx","autopod digit 5 proximal phalanx","digit V P1","digit V-1","fifth digit proximal phalanx","fifth proximal phalanx of autopod","proximal phalanx of 5th digit","proximal phalanx of 5th digit of autopod","proximal phalanx of digit V","proximal phalanx of fifth digit","proximal phalanx of fifth digit of autopod","proximal phalanx of little digit"]

name: distal interphalangeal joint of digit 3
description: A distal inter-phalangeal joint that is part of the 3rd digit.

name: distal interphalangeal joint of pedal digit 3
description: A distal inter-phalangeal joint that is part of the 3rd pedal digit.
synonyms: ["distal interphalangeal joint of pedal digit III","distal interphalangeal joint of third digit of foot","distal interphalangeal joint of third toe"]

name: distal interphalangeal joint of manual digit 3
description: A distal inter-phalangeal joint that is part of the 3rd manual digit.
synonyms: ["distal interphalangeal joint of manual digit III","distal interphalangeal joint of middle finger"]

name: distal sesamoid impar ligament
description: A short wide fibrous structure that attaches proximally to the navicular (distal sesamoid) and distally to the palmar margin of the flexor surface of the distal phalanx
synonyms: ["distal sesamoidean impar ligament","DSIL","impar ligament of distal equine limb"]

name: lamina of omasum
description: A muscular sheet of the omasum wall consisting of two lateral layers and an intermediate layer of smooth muscle covered with non-glandular stratified squamous epithelium

name: anterodorsal nucleus of medial geniculate body
dorsolateral oculomotor nucleus
synonyms: ["dorsolateral nucleus of oculomotor nuclear complex","nucleus dorsalis nervi oculomotorii","oculomotor nerve dorsolateral nucleus"]

name: oculomotor division of oculomotor nuclear complex
description: A division of oculomotor nuclear complex that exists in organisms with electric organs which is responsible for eye movements.

name: electromotor division of oculomotor nuclear complex
description: A division of oculomotor nuclear complex that exists in organisms with electric organs which has axons terminating in the electric organs.

name: limb of internal capsule of telencephalon
synonyms: ["internal capsule subdivision","limb of internal capsule","subdivision of internal capsule"]

name: anterior limb of internal capsule
description: Portion of internal capsule lying between the lenticular nucleus and the head of the caudate nucleus.
synonyms: ["capsula interna, pars anterior","crus anterius capsulae internae"]

name: posterior limb of internal capsule
description: Portion of internal capsule lying between the globus pallidus and the thalamus (Nolte, The Human Brain, 6th ed., 2009, pg 409, modified by MM)
synonyms: ["capsula interna, pars posterior","crus posterius capsulae internae"]

name: extreme capsule
description: Thin band of fibers separating the claustrum from the insular cortex

name: lenticular fasciculus
description: The lenticular fasciculus is a tract connecting the globus pallidus to the Thalamic fasciculus. The thalamic fasciculus (composed of the lenticular fasciculus and ansa lenticularis) runs into the Thalamus. It connects the globus pallidus to the thalamus.
synonyms: ["dorsal division of ansa lenticularis","fasciculus lenticularis","fasciculus lenticularis [h2]","forel's field h2","lenticular fasciculus","lenticular fasciculus","lenticular fasciculus [h2]","lenticular fasciculus of diencephalon","lenticular fasciculus of telencephalon","tegmental area h2"]

name: white matter lamina of cerebral hemisphere
medullary lamina of thalamus
description: Medullary laminae of thalamus are layers of myelinated fibres that appear on cross sections of the thalamus. They also are commonly referred to as laminae medullares thalami or medullary layers of thalamus. The specific layers are: Lamina medullaris lateralis (external medullary lamina) - separates ventral and lateral thalamus from the subthalamus and thalamic reticular nucleus; Lamina medullaris medialis (internal medullary lamina) - positioned between the dorsomedial and ventral nuclei of thalamus, encloses the intralaminar nuclei (centromedian nucleus, paracentral, and central lateral)

name: external medullary lamina of thalamus
description: A medullary lamina that separates ventral and lateral thalamus from the subthalamus and thalamic reticular nucleus.
synonyms: ["external medullary lamina","lamella medullaris externa","lamina medullaris externa","lamina medullaris externa thalami","lamina medullaris lateralis","lamina medullaris lateralis thalami","lamina medullaris thalami externa"]

name: periamygdaloid cortex
description: Is located ventral to the basal nucleus and has three subdivisions: the periamygdaloid cortex, the medial division, and the sulcal division.

name: subdivision of spinal cord central canal
description: A subdivision of the central canal of the spinal cord along its anterior-posterior axis. This is typically subdivided into cervical, thoracic, lumbar and sacral segments
synonyms: ["regional part of spinal cord central canal"]

name: precommissural fornix of forebrain
description: Part of fornix extending from the body that curves ventrally rostral to the crossing of the anterior commissure ending in the septal nuclei

name: white matter lamina of cerebellum
description: The white laminae of cerebellum is subdivision of the cerebellar cortex comprised of myelinated axons lying deep to the granule cell layer of the cerebellar cortex.
synonyms: ["lamina alba of cerebellar cortex","laminae albae of cerebellar cortex","white lamina of cerebellum","white laminae of cerebellum"]

name: thoracic division of spinal cord central canal
description: Part of spinal cord central canal contained in the thoracic spinal cord. It is continuous rostrally with the cervical spinal cord central canal and caudally with the lumbar spinal cord central canal.

name: cervical division of cord spinal central canal
description: Part of central canal contained within the cervical spinal cord. It is continuous caudally with the thoracic spinal cord central canal and rostrally with the fourth ventricle of the brain via the obex

name: lumbar division of spinal cord central canal
description: Part of central canal lying within the lumbar spinal cord. It is continuous rostrally with the central canal of the thoracic spinal cord and caudally with the central canal of the sacral spinal cord.

name: frontomarginal sulcus
description: A superficial feature of the human frontal lobe; it is located at the rostral margin of the orbital surface of the lobe (Ono-90). (NN)

name: sacral division of spinal cord central canal
description: Part of spinal cord central canal contained in the sacral spinal cord. It is continuous rostrally with the spinal cord central canal of the lumbar cord.

name: pyramidal layer of CA1
description: CA1 part of stratum pyramidale hippocampi
synonyms: ["CA1 part of stratum pyramidale hippocampi","CA1 stratum pyramidale hippocampi","field CA1, pyramidal layer","stratum pyramidale of CA1","stratum pyramidale of the CA1 field"]

name: pyramidal layer of CA2
description: Part of pyramidal cell layer in area CA2, lying superficial to the CA2 stratum oriens, and deep to the stratum radiatum of CA2, continuous with the pyramidal cell layers of CA1 and CA3
synonyms: ["CA2 part of stratum pyramidale hippocampi","CA2 stratum pyramidale hippocampi","field CA2, pyramidal layer","stratum pyramidale of CA2","stratum pyramidale of the CA2 field"]

name: pyramidal layer of CA3
description: A layer of hippocampal field that is part of a hippocampus pyramidal layer and is part of a CA3 field of hippocampus.
synonyms: ["CA3 part of stratum pyramidale hippocampi","CA3 stratum pyramidale hippocampi","field CA3, pyramidal layer","stratum pyramidale of CA3","stratum pyramidale of the CA3 field"]

name: CA2 stratum oriens
description: Part of stratum oriens lying in area CA2 deep to the CA2 pyramidal cell layer and continuous with stratum oriens of area CA2 and bounded by the dentate gyrus hilus.
synonyms: ["CA2 part of stratum oriens","CA2 stratum oriens","oriens layer of CA2 field","stratum oriens of the CA2 field"]

name: CA1 stratum oriens
description: Part of stratum oriens lying in area CA1, superficial to the alveus of CA1 and deep to the pyramidal cell layer of CA1. It is continuous with the stratum oriens of CA2 and bounded by the subiculum
synonyms: ["CA1 part of stratum oriens","CA1 stratum oriens","oriens layer of CA1 field","stratum oriens of the CA1 field"]

name: CA3 stratum oriens
description: Part of stratum oriens lying in area CA3 deep to the CA3 pyramidal cell layer and continuous with stratum oriens of area CA2 and bounded by the dentate gyrus hilus.
synonyms: ["CA3 part of stratum oriens","CA3 stratum oriens","oriens layer of CA3 field","stratum oriens of the CA3 field"]

name: CA1 stratum radiatum
description: Part of stratum radiatum lying in area CA1, superficial to the CA1 pyramidal cell layer and deep to the CA1 stratum lucidum-moleculare, continuous with the stratum radiatum of CA2 and bounded by the subiculum. It contains the Schaffer collateral projection from CA3.
synonyms: ["CA1 part of stratum radiatum","CA1 stratum radiatum","radiate layer of CA1 field","stratum radiatum of the CA1 field"]

name: CA2 stratum radiatum
description: Part of stratum radiatum in area CA2, lying superficial to the pyramidal cell layer and deep to CA2 stratum lacunosum-moleculare, continuous with the stratum radiatum of CA1 and CA3.
synonyms: ["CA2 part of stratum radiatum","CA2 stratum radiatum","radiate layer of CA2 field","stratum radiatum of the CA2 field"]

name: CA3 stratum radiatum
description: Part of stratum radiatum in area CA3, lying superficial to the stratum lucidum and deep to CA3 stratum lacunosum-moleculare.
synonyms: ["CA3 part of stratum radiatum","CA3 stratum radiatum","radiate layer of CA3 field","stratum radiatum of the CA3 field"]

name: CA1 stratum lacunosum moleculare
description: Part of stratum lacunosum-moleculare lying in area CA1, superficial to CA1 stratum radiatum and bounded by the pial surface, continuous with stratum lacunosum-moleculare of CA2 and the subiculum stratum moleculare
synonyms: ["CA1 part of stratum lacunosum moleculare","CA1 stratum lacunosum moleculare","lacunar-molecular layer of CA1 field","stratum lacunosum moleculare of the CA1 field"]

name: CA2 stratum lacunosum moleculare
description: Part of stratum lacunosum-moleculare lying in area CA2, superficial to the CA2 stratum radiatum, that is continuous with the stratum lacunosum-moleculare in areas CA3 and CA1
synonyms: ["CA2 part of stratum lacunosum moleculare","CA2 stratum lacunosum moleculare","lacunar-molecular layer of CA2 field","stratum lacunosum moleculare of the CA2 field"]

name: CA3 stratum lacunosum moleculare
description: Part of stratum lacunosum-moleculare in area CA3. It is bounded by the stratum lacunosum-moleculare of CA2 and CA1. It is bounded superficially by the pial surface and deep by the CA3 stratum radiatum. It is continuous with the stratum lacunosum-moleculare of CA2.
synonyms: ["CA3 part of stratum lacunosum moleculare","CA3 stratum lacunosum moleculare","lacunar-molecular layer of CA3 field","stratum lacunosum moleculare of the CA3 field"]

name: CA3 stratum lucidum
description: A layer of hippocampal field that is part of a CA3 field of hippocampus and is part of a hippocampus stratum lucidum.
synonyms: ["CA3 stratum lucidum","stratum lucidum of the CA3 field"]

name: layer of hippocampal field
description: A subdivision of a layer of the hippocampus (e.g. stratum moleculare) covering all or port of a hippocampal field (e.g. CA1).

name: dorsal tegmental nucleus pars dorsalis
description: Part of dorsal tegmental nucleus characterized by round, small cells that are lightly stained in Nissl preparations.

name: dorsal tegmental nucleus pars ventralis
description: Cytoarchitectural part of the dorsal tegmental nucleus based on cell size. The pars ventralis is characterized by medium sized oval or triangular cells that stain darkly in NIssl stains.

name: CA1 alveus
description: CA1 portion of the alveus

name: CA3 alveus
description: Part of alveus lying within hippocampal sector CA3

name: anterior nucleus of hypothalamus anterior part
anterior nucleus of hypothalamus central part
anterior nucleus of hypothalamus posterior part
anterior nucleus of hypothalamus dorsal part
paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus descending division - medial parvicellular part, ventral zone
synonyms: ["paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus descending division - medial parvicellular part, ventral zone","PVHmpv"]

name: paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus descending division - dorsal parvicellular part
synonyms: ["paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus descending division - dorsal parvicellular part","PVHdp"]

name: paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus descending division - lateral parvicellular part
synonyms: ["paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus descending division - lateral parvicellular part","PVHlp"]

name: paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus descending division - forniceal part
synonyms: ["paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus descending division - forniceal part","PVHf"]

name: paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus magnocellular division - anterior magnocellular part

name: fundus striati
description: The ventral portion of the dorsal striatum, linking the caudate nucleus and the putamen anteriorly (adapted from Wikipedia)

name: thoracic spinal cord lateral horn
description: A spinal cord lateral horn that is part of a thoracic spinal cord.

name: thoracic spinal cord dorsal horn
description: A dorsal horn of spinal cord that is part of a thoracic spinal cord.

name: thoracic spinal cord ventral horn
description: A ventral horn of spinal cord that is part of a thoracic spinal cord.

name: apex of thoracic spinal cord dorsal horn
synonyms: ["apex of thoracic spinal cord dorsal horn"]

name: substantia gelatinosa of thoracic spinal cord dorsal horn
description: Substantia gelatinosa of thoracic spinal cord posterior horn

name: cervical spinal cord gray matter
description: A gray matter of spinal cord that is part of a cervical spinal cord.

name: cervical spinal cord white matter
description: A white matter of spinal cord that is part of a cervical spinal cord.

name: accessory nerve root
description: A nerve root that is part of a accessory XI nerve.

name: dorsal nerve root of thoracic spinal cord
synonyms: ["dorsal nerve root of thoracic spinal cord"]

name: ventral nerve root of thoracic spinal cord
synonyms: ["ventral nerve root of thoracic spinal cord"]

name: cervical spinal cord lateral horn
description: A spinal cord lateral horn that is part of a cervical spinal cord.

name: cervical spinal cord dorsal horn
description: A dorsal horn of spinal cord that is part of a cervical spinal cord.

name: cervical spinal cord ventral horn
description: A ventral horn of spinal cord that is part of a cervical spinal cord.

name: apex of cervical spinal cord dorsal horn

name: substantia gelatinosa of cervical spinal cord dorsal horn

name: vestibular fissure of the cochlear canal
terminal part of the cochlear canal
ventral gray commissure of spinal cord
synonyms: ["anterior grey commissure of spinal cord","commissura grisea anterior medullae spinalis","spinal cord anterior gray commissure","ventral grey commissure of spinal cord"]

name: dorsal gray commissure of spinal cord
description: the part of the gray commissure in the spinal central gray posterior to the central canal of the spinal cord
synonyms: ["commissura grisea posterior medullae spinalis","dorsal gray commissure","dorsal grey commissure of spinal cord","posterior grey commissure of spinal cord","spinal cord posterior gray commissure"]

name: apex of lumbar spinal cord dorsal horn
synonyms: ["apex of lumbar spinal cord dorsal horn"]

name: substantia gelatinosa of lumbar spinal cord dorsal horn
description: A substantia gelatinosa that is part of a lumbar spinal cord dorsal horn.
synonyms: ["substantia gelatinosa of lumbar spinal cord dorsal horn"]

name: ventral nerve root of cervical spinal cord
description: A ventral root of spinal cord that overlaps a cervical spinal cord.
synonyms: ["ventral nerve root of cervical spinal cord"]

name: dorsal nerve root of cervical spinal cord
description: A dorsal root of spinal cord that overlaps a cervical spinal cord.
synonyms: ["dorsal nerve root of cervical spinal cord"]

name: thoracic spinal cord gray matter
description: A gray matter of spinal cord that is part of a thoracic spinal cord.

name: thoracic spinal cord white matter
description: A white matter of spinal cord that is part of a thoracic spinal cord.

name: lumbar spinal cord dorsal horn
description: A dorsal horn of spinal cord that is part of a lumbar spinal cord.

name: frontal sulcus
description: A sulcus of brain that is part of a frontal cortex.

name: occipital gyrus
description: A gyrus that is part of a occipital lobe.

name: terminal nerve root
description: A nerve root that extends_fibers_into a terminal nerve.
synonyms: ["cranial nerve 0 root","root of terminal nerve","terminal nerve root"]

name: vestibulocerebellum
description: A phylogenetic subdivision of the cerebellum, the oldest part, which regulates balance and eye movements. It receives vestibular input from both the semicircular canals and from the vestibular nuclei, and sends fibres back to the medial and lateral vestibular nuclei. It also receives visual input from the superior colliculi and from the visual cortex (the latter via the pontine nuclei, forming a cortico-ponto-cerebellar pathway). Lesions of the vestibulocerebellum cause disturbances of balance and gait.

name: spinocerebellum
description: A phylogenetic subdivision of the cerebellum, the intermediate part, which regulates body and limb movements. It receives proprioception input from the dorsal columns of the spinal cord (including the spinocerebellar tract) and the trigeminal nerve, as well as from visual and auditory systems. It sends fibres to deep cerebellar nuclei which in turn project to both the cerebral cortex and the brain stem, thus providing modulation of descending motor systems.

name: cerebrocerebellum
description: The part of the cerebellar cortex that receives input from the cerebral cortex via axons from the pontine relay nuclei.

name: nucleus H of ventral tegmentum
description: A nucleus present in the ventral tegmentum of squalomorph sharks.

name: nucleus K of ventral tegmentum
description: A nucleus present in the ventral tegmentum of skates.

name: hemisphere part of cerebellar anterior lobe
description: A multi-tissue structure that is part of a anterior lobe of cerebellum and is part of a cerebellar hemisphere.
synonyms: ["hemisphere of anterior lobe","hemisphere of anterior lobe of cerebellum","hemispherium lobus anterior"]

name: hemisphere part of cerebellar posterior lobe
description: A multi-tissue structure that is part of a cerebellar hemisphere and is part of a posterior lobe of cerebellum.
synonyms: ["hemisphere of posterior lobe","hemisphere of posterior lobe of cerebellum","hemispherium lobus posterior"]

name: white matter of medulla oblongata
description: A white matter that is part of a medulla oblongata.
synonyms: ["substantia alba medullae oblongatae","white matter of medulla","white substance of medulla"]

name: dorsal hypothalamic nucleus
description: A nerve cell nucleus situated in the dorsal portion of the intermediate hypothalamic region.

name: nucleus preopticus
description: The nucleus preopticus (NPO) of the hypothalamus of common carp, is a homolog of the paraventricular nucleus of mammals.

name: periventricular nucleus of hypothalamus
description: A small nucleus at the base of the hypothalamus, adjacent to the arcuate nucleus.

name: distal interphalangeal joint of manual digit 2
synonyms: ["distal interphalangeal joint of index finger","distal interphalangeal joint of manual digit II"]

name: distal interphalangeal joint of manual digit 4
synonyms: ["distal interphalangeal joint of manual digit IV","distal interphalangeal joint of ring finger"]

name: distal interphalangeal joint of manural digit 5
synonyms: ["distal interphalangeal joint of little finger","distal interphalangeal joint of manural digit V"]

name: distal interphalangeal joint of pedal digit 2
synonyms: ["distal interphalangeal joint of pedal digit II","distal interphalangeal joint of second digit of foot","distal interphalangeal joint of second toe"]

name: distal interphalangeal joint of pedal digit 4
synonyms: ["distal interphalangeal joint of fourth digit of foot","distal interphalangeal joint of fourth toe","distal interphalangeal joint of pedal digit IV"]

name: distal interphalangeal joint of pedal digit 5
synonyms: ["distal interphalangeal joint of fifth digit of foot","distal interphalangeal joint of fifth toe","distal interphalangeal joint of little toe","distal interphalangeal joint of pedal digit V"]

name: distal interphalangeal joint of digit 2
description: A distal interphalangeal joint that is part of a digit 2.

name: distal interphalangeal joint of digit 4
description: A distal interphalangeal joint that is part of a digit 4.

name: distal interphalangeal joint of digit 5
description: A distal interphalangeal joint that is part of a digit 5.

name: tooth whorl
description: A spirally arranged cluster of teeth

name: parasymphisial tooth whorl
description: A tooth whorl located at or near the mandibular symphysis.

name: Helicoprion tooth whorl
description: A tooth whorl found in extinct holocephalids, in which the teeth in the center of the spiral are smallest and oldest, probably occupying the entire mandibular arch.

name: pterygoid plexus
description: The pterygoid plexus is a venous plexus of considerable size, and is situated between the temporalis muscle and lateral pterygoid muscle, and partly between the two pterygoid muscles.
synonyms: ["plexus venosus pterygoideus","pterygoid venous plexus","pterygoid venous plexus"]

name: angular vein
description: The angular vein formed by the junction of the frontal vein and supraorbital vein, runs obliquely downward, on the side of the root of the nose, to the level of the lower margin of the orbit, where it becomes the anterior facial vein. It receives the external nasal veins of the ala nasi, and communicates with the superior ophthalmic vein through the nasofrontal vein, thus establishing an important anastomosis between the anterior facial vein and the cavernous sinus.

name: temporal sulcus
description: Any of three grooves in the temporal lobe including the inferior, middle, and superior temporal sulci.

name: middle temporal sulcus
description: A groove or cleft that divides the outer surface of the temporal lobe running in the same direction but at a lower level to the superior temporal sulcus.

name: left gastric vein
description: The Left gastric vein (or coronary vein) carries blood low in Oxygen, tributaries derived from both surfaces of the stomach; it runs from right to left along the lesser curvature of the stomach, between the two layers of the lesser omentum, to the esophageal opening of the stomach, where it receives some esophageal veins. It then turns backward and passes from left to right behind the omental bursa and drains into the portal vein. Esophageal and paraesophageal varices are primarily supplied by the left gastric vein and typically drain into the azygos/hemiazygos venous system.

name: right gastric vein
description: The right gastric vein, also known as the pyloric vein, drains blood from the lesser curvature of the stomach into the hepatic portal vein. It is part of the portal circulation.

name: superficial epigastric vein
description: The superficial epigastric vein is a vein which travels with the superficial epigastric artery. It joins the accessory saphenous vein near the fossa ovalis.

name: posterior auricular artery
description: The posterior auricular artery is a small artery and arises from the external carotid artery, above the Digastric muscle and Stylohyoid muscle, opposite the apex of the styloid process. It ascends posteriorly beneath the parotid gland, along the styloid process of the temporal bone, between the cartilage of the ear and the mastoid process of the temporal bone along the lateral side of the head. The posterior auricular artery supplies blood to the scalp posterior to the auricle and to the auricle itself.

name: deep auricular artery
description: The deep auricular artery often arises in common with the anterior tympanic artery. It ascends in the substance of the parotid gland, behind the temporomandibular articulation, pierces the cartilaginous or bony wall of the external acoustic meatus, and supplies its cuticular lining and the outer surface of the tympanic membrane. It gives a branch to the temporomandibular joint.

name: anterior choroidal artery
description: The anterior choroidal artery originates from the internal carotid artery, though it also rarely arises from the middle cerebral artery.

name: extraembryonic venous system
description: A venous system that overlaps a umbilical cord and is part of a entire extraembryonic component.

name: extraembryonic vascular system
description: A vascular system that overlaps a umbilical cord and is part of a entire extraembryonic component.

name: frontonasal process epithelium
description: A epithelium that is part of a frontonasal prominence.

name: anal membrane ectodermal component
description: A unilaminar epithelium that develops_from a ectoderm and is part of a anal region.

name: pleuroperitoneal canal lumen
description: A anatomical space that is enclosed by a pleuroperitoneal canal.

name: median lingual swelling epithelium
description: A epithelium that is part of a median lingual swelling.

name: hyoplastron
description: A paired plastron element that is in the anterior part of the plastron, anterior to the hypoplastron, posterior to the epiplastron and adjacent to the median entoplastron.

name: costal plate of carapace
description: One of a series of plates on each side of the carapace, forming two rows between the peripheral plates and the median neural plates.

name: carapace primordium
description: A primordium that gives rise to a carapace.

name: carapacial ridge
description: A longitidunial ridge on the lateral aspect of the flank that appears in the late pharyngula stage of chelonians. It forms the leading edge of the laterally expanding carapacial primordium.

name: carapacial ridge mesenchyme
description: A mesenchyme that is part of a carapacial ridge.

name: carapacial ridge ectoderm
description: A epithelium that is part of a carapacial ridge.

name: interlobular duct
description: A duct that is located between lobules, within the thin connective tissue septa that separate lobules. All interlobular ducts are excretory.

name: mucous acinus
description: The secretory unit of a mucous gland. The acinar portion is composed of mucous secreting cells.

name: intralobular duct
description: A duct that is located within a lobule, with no more connective tissue intervening between ducts and secretory units (i.e., acini or tubules) than between adjacent secretory units. Intercalated and striated ducts are intralobular

name: interlobar duct
description: A duct that is located between lobes, within conspicuous, thick connective tissue septa that separate lobes. All interlobar ducts are excretory.

name: intercalated duct
description: A small duct which drains individual secretory units. These are usually inconspicuous, lined by a simple epithelium consisting of low cuboidal cells.

name: intercalated duct of pancreas
description: A intercalated duct that is part of a pancreas.

name: intercalated duct of salivary gland
description: The tiny tubules with a very thin epithelial layer in the salivary glands running from the salivary acini into the striated duct.

name: striated duct of salivary gland
description: gland duct which connects an intercalated duct to an interlobular duct in a salivary gland.

name: osteon
description: A circular structural unit of bone tissue. It consists of a central hole, the Haversian canal through which blood vessels run, surrounded by concentric rings, called lamellae.

name: haversian canal
description: Haversian canals are a series of tubes around narrow channels formed by lamellae. This is the region of bone called compact bone. Osteons are arranged in parallel to the long axis of the bone. The Haversian canals surround blood vessels and nerve cells throughout the bone and communicate with osteocytes in lacunae (spaces within the dense bone matrix that contain the living bone cells) through canaliculi. This unique arrangement is conducive to mineral salt deposits and storage which gives bone tissue its strength.

name: compound cell cluster organ
description: An anatomical structure consisting of multiple cell cluster organs, that has a largely bona-fide boundary and that does not contain portions of tissue.

name: dorsal ventricular ridge of pallium
description: A large expansion of the lateral wall of the telencephalon, located in the pallium. Found in reptiles and birds

name: allocortex
description: One of two types of cerebral cortex defined on the basis of cytoarchitecture and fetal development. The other is neocortex. Allocortex does not pass through a prenatal phase of six-layered structure and has three or four layers in the mature brain ( Schiebler-1999 ). Allocortex has three subtypes: paleocortex, archicortex and periallocortex. This definition differs from that in some older sources, which excluded the olfactory bulb and the accessory olfactory bulb ( Carpenter-1983 ).

name: paleocortex
description: Part of the allocortex defined on the basis of cytoarchitecture. The other two are archicortex and periallocortex. It consists of very thin, primitive cortex with few clearly defined layers. It is distinguished ontogenetically by the fact that it does not develop through a cortical plate. It includes the olfactory bulb, accessory olfactory bulb, olfactory tubercle, septum, prepyriform area and periamygdalar area ( Stephan-1975 ). (adapted from Brain Info)

name: periallocortex
description: Agranular cortical structures located next to the allocortex.

name: medial pallium
description: Subdivision of pallium that is located is the medial position in vertebrates with an evaginated brain and in the distal position in vertebrates with an everted brain.
synonyms: ["lateral zone of dorsal telencephalon","medial zone of dorsal telencephalic area","medial zone of dorsal telencephalon","MP"]

name: dorsal pallium
description: Subdivision of pallium that is located dorsally.
synonyms: ["area dorsalis telencephali, zona dorsalis","dorsal zone of dorsal telencephalic area","dorsal zone of dorsal telencephalon","DP"]

name: lateral pallium
description: Subdivision of pallium that is located laterally.
synonyms: ["area dorsalis telencephali, zona lateralis","lateral zone of D","lateral zone of dorsal telencephalic area","LP"]

name: central nucleus of pallium
description: A nucleus located in the dorsal pallium that is present in sharks, skates and rays and extends at some levels to the midline..

name: P1 area of pallium (Myxiniformes)
description: Most superficial of the areas of the pallium in the enlarged evaginated telencephalon of hagfishes.

name: P2 area of pallium (Myxiniformes)
description: Area directly deep to the P1 area of pallium in hagfishes.

name: P3 area of pallium (Myxiniformes)
description: Area directly deep to the P2 area of pallium in hagfishes.

name: P4 area of pallium (Myxiniformes)
description: Area directly deep to the P3 area of pallium in hagfishes.

name: P5 area of pallium (Myxiniformes)
description: Most deep of the areas of the pallium in the enlarged evaginated telencephalon of hagfishes.

name: Wulst
description: A nuclear complex in the avian telecephalon dorsal to the DVR. The Wulst has telencephalic circuitry similar to the DVR.

name: entopallium
description: The major telecephalic thalamorecipient zone of the tectofugal visual system in Aves.

name: gustatory nucleus
description: The gustatory nucleus is the enlarged rostral portion of the solitary nucleus, which receives taste afferents from the glossopharyngeal nerve and the intermediate nerve ( Carpenter-1983 ).

name: spinal trigeminal tract
description: Brainstem tract formed by the central processes of first-order, trigeminal ganglion neurons that extends from the caudal medulla to the midpons. This tract conveys nociceptive and thermal information from the face to second-order neurons in the spinal nucleus of the trigeminal complex.

name: fused metapodial bones 2-4
description: An element formed from the fusion of metapodium bones 2, 3 and 4 (i.e. either metatarsals 2-4 or metacarpals 3-4).

name: fused metatarsal bones 2-4
description: An element formed from the fusion of metapodium bones 2, 3 and 4 in the pedal autopod.

name: anatomical line along groove
description: Anatomical line that delineates a furrow or depression in an organ or tissue.

name: crus of diaphragm
description: The domain of the diaphragm that is located dorsally and attaches to the vertebrae and surrounds the esophagus and aorta.

name: right crus of diaphragm
description: A crus of diaphragm that is in_the_right_side_of a diaphragm.
synonyms: ["crus dextrum (Diaphragma)","crus dextrum diaphragmatis","external sphincter of esophagus","right crus of diaphragm","right crus of lumbar part of diaphragm"]

name: left crus of diaphragm
description: A crus of diaphragm that is in_the_left_side_of a diaphragm.
synonyms: ["crus sinistrum (Diaphragma)","crus sinistrum diaphragmatis","left crus of diaphragm","left crus of lumbar part of diaphragm"]

name: superior palpebral vein
description: A blood vessel that drains from from an upper eyelid.

name: palpebral vein
description: A blood vessel that drains from from an eyelid.

name: palpebral artery
description: An artery that supplies blood to an eyelid.

name: lateral palpebral artery
description: The lateral palpebral arteries are small arteries which supply the eyelid.

name: medial palpebral artery
description: The medial palpebral arteries (internal palpebral arteries) are arteries of the head. They are two in number, superior and inferior, arise from the ophthalmic, opposite the pulley of the Obliquus superior.

name: prosomere
description: A neuromere that is part of the presumptive forebrain

name: midbrain neuromere
description: A neuromere that is part of the presumptive midbrain
synonyms: ["mesomere","mesomere of nervous system","midbrain segment","neuromere of mesomere group","segment of midbrain"]

name: spinal neuromere
description: A neuromere that is part of the presumptive spinal cord

name: cell group
description: A group of cells that may not be contained within macroscopic anatomical boundaries, e.g., A9 dopaminergic cell group; massa intercalata of the amygdala (CUMBO)

name: liver reticuloendothelial system
description: A reticuloendothelial system that is part of a liver.

name: palatine aponeurosis
description: Attached to the posterior border of the hard palate is a thin, firm fibrous lamella called the palatine aponeurosis, which supports the muscles and gives strength to the soft palate. It is thicker above than below, where it becomes very thin and difficult to define. Laterally it is continuous with the pharyngeal aponeurosis. It serves as the insertion for the Tensor veli palatini and Levator veli palatini, and the origin for the Musculus uvulae, Palatopharyngeus, and Palatoglossus. It provides support for the soft palate.

name: cloacal muscle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a cloaca.

name: transverse cloacal muscle
description: a very prominent superficial muscle and with its almost transverse course it forms the boundary between the abdomen and the tail.

name: levator cloacae
description: a long narrow muscle arising from the underside of feather bulge of the lateral rectrices, inserting near the midline of the cloacal tubercle - phallus.
synonyms: ["m. retractor phalli caudalis","musculus levator cloacae","musculus retractor phalli caudalis"]

name: extraembryonic umbilical vein
description: Extraembryonic part of the vein passing through the umbilical cord to the fetus and returning the purified and nutrient blood from the placenta.

name: left extraembryonic umbilical vein
description: A extraembryonic umbilical vein that is in_the_left_side_of a multicellular organism.

name: right extraembryonic umbilical vein
description: A extraembryonic umbilical vein that is in_the_right_side_of a multicellular organism.

name: lingual septum
description: The lingual septum consists of a vertical layer of fibrous tissue, extending throughout the entire length of the median plane of the tongue, though not quite reaching the dorsum. It is thicker behind than in front, and occasionally contains a small fibrocartilage, about 6 mm. in length. It is well displayed by making a vertical section across the organ.

name: musculature of forelimb stylopod
description: Any collection of muscles that is part of the forelimb stylopod region.

name: musculature of pelvic complex
description: Any collection of muscles that is part of a pelvic complex. The pelvic complex comprises the pelvic girdle and the associated limb or fin.

name: musculature of pectoral complex
description: Any collection of muscles that is part of a pectoral complex. The pectoral complex comprises the pectoral girdle and the associated limb or fin.

name: pectoral appendage muscle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a pectoral appendage (forelimb or pectoral fin).

name: pelvic appendage muscle
description: Any muscle organ that is part of a pelvic appendage (hindlimb or pelvic fin).

name: common tendinous ring
description: A ring of fibrous tissue surrounding the optic nerve at its entrance at the apex of the orbit.
synonyms: ["anulus of Zinn","anulus tendineus communis","common annular tendon","common anular tendon"]

name: hypobranchial group muscle
description: A jaw muscle that arises from trunk somites and is innervated by spinal nerves.

name: clavotrapezius muscle
description: The most anterior of the trapezius muscles, found in felids, it is also the largest. Its fibers run obliquely to the ventral surface. Its origin is the superior nuchal line and median dorsal line and its insertion is the clavicle. Its action is to draw the clavicle dorsally and towards the head.

name: acromiotrapezius muscle
description: Acromiotrapezius is the middle trapezius muscle. It covers the dorsal and lateral surfaces of the scapula. Its origin is the neural spines of the cervical vertebrae and its insertion is in the metacromion process and fascia of the clavotrapezius. Its action is to draw the scapula to the dorsal, and hold the two scapula together.

name: spinotrapezius muscle
description: Spinotrapezius, also called thoracic trapezius, is the most posterior of the three trapezius muscles. It is triangular shaped. Posterior to the acromiotrapezius and overlaps latissimus dorsi on the front. Its origin is the neural spines of the thoracic vertebrae and its insertion is the scapular fascia. Its action is to draw the scapula to the dorsal and caudal regions.

name: nuchal line attachment site
description: Any of the four curved lines on the external surface of the occipital bone that serves as an attachment site for a muscle.

name: highest nuchal line attachment site
description: Of the nuchal lines, the upper, often faintly marked, is named the highest nuchal line, but is sometimes referred to as the Mempin Line, and to it the galea aponeurotica is attached.

name: superior nuchal line attachment site
description: Of the nuchal lines, the one below the highest nuchal line is the superior nuchal line. To it is attached the Occipitalis muscle, the Splenius capitis muscle, the trapezius muscle, and the Sternocleidomastoid muscle.

name: median nuchal line attachment site
description: Of the nuchal lines, the one that runs from the external occipital protuberance a ridge or crest is the median nuchal line, often faintly marked, descends to the foramen magnum, and affords attachment to the ligamentum nuchae.

name: inferior nuchal line attachment site
description: Of the nuchal lines, the one running from the middle of the median line is the inferior nuchal line. Attached are the Obliquus capitis superior muscle, Rectus capitis posterior major muscle, and Rectus capitis posterior minor muscle.

name: pectoantebrachialis
description: The most superficial of pectoral muscles, found in some mammals

name: xiphihumeralis
description: The most deep of pectoral muscles, found in some mammals

name: supracoracoideus muscle
description: A muscle that is important to the body support of limbed reptiles, underlies the front part of the pectoral muscle, arises from the coracoid, and passes to the underpart of the humerus

name: puboischiofemoralis muscle
description: A dorsal muscle of lower tetrapods.

name: vastus intermedius
description: The Vastus intermedius (Cruraeus) arises from the front and lateral surfaces of the body of the femur in its upper two-thirds, sitting under Rectus Femoris and from the lower part of the lateral intermuscular septum. Its fibers end in a superficial aponeurosis, which forms the deep part of the Quadriceps femoris tendon. The Vastus medialis and Vastus intermedius appear to be inseparably united, but when the Rectus femoris has been reflected a narrow interval will be observed extending upward from the medial border of the patella between the two muscles, and the separation may be continued as far as the lower part of the intertrochanteric line, where, however, the two muscles are frequently continuous.

name: tendon of quadriceps femoris
synonyms: ["common tendon of quadriceps femoris","quadriceps femoris tendon","quadriceps tendon"]

name: hemotrichorial placental membrane
description: A placental membrane that consists of three trophoblast cell layers.

name: hemomonochorial placental membrane
description: A placental membrane that consists of a single layer of syncytiotrophoblast at term.

name: chorda tendinea of left ventricle
description: Chorda tendinea which is attached to the leaflet of mitral valve and is continuous with the endocardium of papillary muscle of left ventricle.

name: chorda tendinea of right ventricle
description: Chorda tendinea which is attached to the leaflet of tricuspid valve and is continuous with the endocardium of papillary muscle of right ventricle.

name: commissural leaflet of mitral valve
description: Leaflet of mitral valve which is attached to the commissural chorda tendinea of left ventricle.

name: anterior leaflet of mitral valve
description: Leaflet of mitral valve which is attached to the anterior head of the posterior papillary muscle of left ventricle through the chorda tendinea of the left ventricle.
synonyms: ["anterior cusp of mitral valve","anterior leaflet","anterior mitral leaflet","anteromedial leaflet","anteromedial leaflet of mitral valve","aortic leaflet of mitral valve","aortic leaflet of the left-sided mitral valve","cuspis anterior valvae atrioventricularis sinistri","greater leaflet of mitral valve","septal leaflet of mitral valve"]

name: posterior leaflet of mitral valve
description: Leaflet of mitral valve which is attached to the posterior head of the lateral papillary muscle of left ventricle through the chorda tendinea of the left ventricle.
synonyms: ["cuspis posterior (valva mitralis)","cuspis posterior valvae atrioventricularis sinistri","mural leaflet of mitral valve","posterior cusp of mitral valve","posterior mitral leaflet","posterolateral leaflet of mitral valve","smaller leaflet of mitral valve","ventricular leaflet of mitral valve"]

name: cysticercus stage
description: The larval form of any of the Taenia tapeworms.

name: zoea stage
description: A crustacean larval stage characterised by the use of the thoracic appendages for swimming.

name: crustacean post-larval stage
description: A crustacean larval stage characterised by the use of abdominal appendages (pleopods) for propulsion.

name: megalopa stage
description: The crustacean post-larval stage of a crab

name: copepodite stage
description: A development stage of copepods which follows the nauplius stage. It is segmented with more than 3 pairs of appendages

name: glaucothoe stage
description: A developmental stage in a hermit crab that has completed the swimming larval stages.

name: trochophore stage
description: A larval stage of a trochozoan in which the organism is in free-swimming planktonic form with several bands of cilia.

name: veliger stage
description: The characteristic larval stage of the gastropod, bivalve and scaphopod taxonomic classes. It is produced following either the embryonic or trochophore larval stage of development

name: caterpillar stage

name: iliotibialis muscle
description: A muscle in amphibians that connects originates in the ilium and inserts in the tibia.

name: left hemisphere of cerebellum
description: A cerebellar hemisphere that is in_the_left_side_of a cerebellum.

name: right hemisphere of cerebellum
description: A cerebellar hemisphere that is in_the_right_side_of a cerebellum.

name: brainstem white matter
description: White matter that is part of a brainstem.

name: skeletal muscle organ
description: A muscle organ that consists of skeletal muscle tissue ensheathed in epimysium, that develops from myotome and that is innervated by some somatic motor neuron. Skeletal muscles are typically attached (via a tendon) to a bone but there are exceptions (e.g. intrinsic tongue muscles).

name: somatic muscle
description: A muscle structure of invertebrates whose origin and insertion sites are in basal side of the epidermis or structures derived from it. The simplest somatic muscles consist of a single cell and associated extracellular structures.

name: transversely striated somatic muscle
description: A somatic muscle that consists of one or more somatic muscle myotubes and any associated extracellular structures.

name: obliquely striated somatic muscle
description: A somatic muscle that consists of one or more obliquely striated muscle cells and any associated extracellular structures.

name: lamina terminalis of ischium
description: In those cases in which the interilial region is broadly expanded and the pubis is extremely reduced, the anterior margin of the ischium forms an expanded area.

name: anterolateral ligament of knee
description: A ligament on the lateral aspect of the human knee, anterior to the fibular collateral ligament.
synonyms: ["(mid-third) lateral capsular ligament","ALL","anterolateral ligament","capsulo-osseous layer of the iliotibial band","ligament of Segond"]

name: primordial vasculature
description: A portion of tissue that will develop into vasculature.

name: intersegmental pulmonary vein
description: A vein receiving blood from adjacent bronchopulmonary segments; it emerges from the inferior margin of a segment to become a tributary of a branch of a pulmonary vein.
synonyms: ["infrasegmental part of pulmonary vein","intersegmental part of pulmonary vein","partes intersegmentales venarum pulmonum"]

name: intersomitic vessel
description: One of the primary blood vessel sprouts that originate from the dorsal aorta and posterior cardinal vein and align dorsoventrally at the myotomal boundaries between somites.
synonyms: ["intersegmental vessel","intersegmental vessels","intersomitic blood vessel","intersomitic vessels","segmental vessel"]

name: cerebellopontine angle
description: Junction between the cerebellum and the pons.

name: ventral pallium
description: The pallial region located next to the pallium-subpallium boundary.

name: haemolymphatic fluid-testis barrier
description: A barrier between the blood or haemolymphatic fluid and the testes.

name: genu of facial nerve
description: The bend in the facial nerve at the lateral end of the internal acoustic meatus.

name: velar vocal fold
description: On of a pair of medial protrusions of the intra-pharyngeal ostium (an oval opening within the soft palate that connects the oral and nasal portions of the pharynx), used in vocalization in Koalas.

name: pouch sphincter
description: A sphincter muscle that is part of a pouch. The pouch sphincter serves to keep the young from falling out.

name: perivascular space
description: The space between a blood vessel and the pia mater.

name: periungual skin
description: A zone of skin adjacent to a nail or claw.

name: cerebral cortex marginal layer
description: developing superficial cortical layer located just under the pia matter, develops from the marginal layer of the neural tube and becomes cortical layer I
synonyms: ["cortical marginal layer","cortical marginal zone","future cortical layer I","marginal zone","MZ","MZ"]

name: proisocortex

name: lamina terminalis of cerebral hemisphere
description: The remnant of the lamina terminalis in the developed brain.

name: obsolete neocortical column
description: A group of neurons in the cortex of the brain which can be successively penetrated by a probe inserted perpendicularly to the cortical surface, and which have nearly identical receptive fields.

name: scolex
description: The anterior organ of a tapeworm used for attachment to the host intestine.

name: right outer canthus
description: A outer canthus that is in_the_right_side_of a head.

name: left outer canthus

name: anatomical line between outer canthi
description: An anatomical line of the face that connects the two outer (lateral) canthi of the eye. The length of this line is known as the outer canthal distance.
synonyms: ["inter lateral canthal line","inter outer canthal line"]

name: anterior internodal tract
description: Internodal tract which consists of the atrial and atrial septal branches.

description: The tapering portion of the gall bladder that narrows to form the neck and cystic duct.

name: falciform fat
description: A large fat pad that is located at the base of the abdominal wall, in the falciform ligament of the liver.

name: mesenteric fat pad

name: Harderian gland duct
description: A duct that is part of a Harderian gland. opens into the conjunctival sac at the base of the nictitating membrane.
synonyms: ["duct of Harder's gland","duct of Harderian gland"]

name: gland of ocular region
description: A gland that is typically found in or near the orbital region, in or around either the medial or lateral canthi, and is typically associated with secretions onto the eyeball or associated ducts. Includes the Harderian, nictitans and lacrimal glands.

name: medial gland of ocular region
description: A gland that is located in the ocular region, nearer the inner canthi. Typically associated with or part of the nictitating membrane, when present

name: lateral gland of orbital region
description: A gland that is located in or around the ocular region, nearer the outer canthi.

name: conjunctival space
description: A anatomical space that is enclosed by a conjunctiva.
synonyms: ["cavity of conjunctival sac","conjunctival sac cavity","subconjunctival space"]

name: terminal branch of ophthalmic artery
description: The two terminal branches of the ophthalmic artery in humans are the dorsal nasal artery and the supratrochlear artery

name: zygomatico-orbital artery
description: The middle temporal artery occasionally gives off a zygomatico-orbital branch, which runs along the upper border of the zygomatic arch, between the two layers of the temporal fascia, to the lateral angle of the orbit. This branch, which may arise directly from the superficial temporal artery, supplies the Orbicularis oculi, and anastomoses with the lacrimal and palpebral branches of the ophthalmic artery.

name: ophthalmotemporal branch of external ophthalmic artery
supraorbital artery
description: The supraorbital artery is an artery of the head. It springs from the ophthalmic artery as that vessel is crossing over to the medial side of the optic nerve.

name: inferior branch of oculomotor nerve
description: The inferior branch of the oculomotor nerve or the inferior division, the larger, divides into three branches. One passes beneath the optic nerve to the medial rectus. Another, to the inferior rectus. The third and longest runs forward between the inferior recti and lateralis to the inferior oblique. From the last a short thick branch is given off to the lower part of the ciliary ganglion, and forms its short root. All these branches enter the muscles on their ocular surfaces, with the exception of the nerve to the inferior oblique, which enters the muscle at its posterior border.
synonyms: ["inferior ramus of oculomotor nerve","oculomotor nerve inferior division","ramus inferior (nervus oculomotorius [III])","ramus inferior nervi oculomotorii","ramus inferior nervus oculomotorii"]

name: superior branch of oculomotor nerve
description: The superior branch of the oculomotor nerve or the superior division, the smaller, passes medialward over the optic nerve. It supplies the Superior rectus and Levator palpebrae superioris.
synonyms: ["oculomotor nerve superior division","ramus superior (nervus oculomotorius [III])","ramus superior nervi oculomotorii","ramus superior nervus oculomotorii","superior ramus of oculomotor nerve"]

name: multi-unit eye
description: An eye consisting of multiple light-sensing organs

name: tapetum
description: Light reflecting layer found in a variety of different types of eye.

name: nauplius eye
description: An eye that consists of a cluster of three or four median eyes that form a single structural unit but are separated from one another by pigment layers

name: uterine spiral artery
description: A corkscrew-like artery in premenstrual or progestational endometrium; uterine spiral arteries play a vital role in supplying nutrients to the placenta and fetus, and are thus remodeled into highly dilated inelastic vessels by the action of invading trophoblast (physiological change)

name: endometrial blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a endometrium.

name: helicine branch of uterine artery
description: The helicine branches of uterine artery (or helicine arterioles, or spiral arteries) are small arteries which temporarily supply the endometrium of the uterus during the luteal phase of the menstrual cycle. In histology, identifying the presence of these arteries is one of the most useful techniques in identifying the phase of the cycle.
synonyms: ["arcuate artery of uterus","helicine artery of uterus","rami helicini uterinae"]

name: helicine artery of penis
description: The helicine arteries of penis are arteries in the penis. They are found in the corpora cavernosa penis. They are involved in the process of erection.

name: helicine artery
description: Either the helicine artery of the penis or the helicine artery of the uterus

name: somite border
description: A region of somite adjacent to presomitic mesoderm.

name: somite boundary epithelium
description: Epithelium located in the intersomitic region.

name: neck of talus
description: The neck of talus is directed forward and medialward, and comprises the constricted portion of the bone between the body and the oval head. Its upper and medial surfaces are rough, for the attachment of ligaments; its lateral surface is concave and is continuous below with the deep groove for the interosseous talocalcaneal ligament.

name: neck of tooth
description: The slightly constricted part of a tooth, between the crown and the root.
synonyms: ["cervix dentis","cervix of tooth","collumn dentis","dental neck","tooth neck"]

name: perineural vascular plexus
description: The capillary bed that initially surrounds the relative avascular brain and spinal cord; the perineural vascular plexus (PNVP) is the precursor to the blood brain barrier formed by angioblasts which migrate away from somites and is recruited to surround the neural tube in response to VEGF; vascularization of the brain and spinal cord occurs via angiogenesis as sprouting vessels from the PNVP invade the neuroepithelium and grow inward toward the ventricular lumen.

name: lymph heart
description: A circulatory organ that is reponsible for pumping lymph throughout the body.

name: non-connected functional system
description: An anatomical group whose component structures share a common function.

name: glandular system
description: A non-connected functional system that is composed primarily of a gland.

name: lateral structure
description: Any structure that is placed on one side of the left-right axis of a bilaterian.

name: barnacle cement gland
description: Typical barnacles, common name of the sedentary crustacean marine animals constituting the subclass Cirripedia, attach to the substrate by means of an exceedingly adhesive cement, produced by a cement gland, and secrete a shell, or carapace, of calcareous (limestone) plates, around themselves.

name: arcuate ligament
description: A ligament that is part of a diaphragm.

name: median arcuate ligament
description: The median arcuate ligament is a ligament under the diaphragm that connects the right and left crura of diaphragm.

name: middle nasal meatus
description: The middle meatus is a nasal opening or canal situated between the middle and inferior conchae, and extends from the anterior to the posterior end of the latter. The lateral wall of this meatus can be satisfactorily studied only after the removal of the middle concha. On it is a curved fissure, the hiatus semilunaris, limited below by the edge of the uncinate process of the ethmoid and above by an elevation named the bulla ethmoidalis; the middle ethmoidal cells are contained within this bulla and open on or near to it. Through the hiatus semilunaris the meatus communicates with a curved passage termed the infundibulum, which communicates in front with the anterior ethmoidal cells and in rather more than fifty percent of skulls is continued upward as the frontonasal duct into the frontal air-sinus; when this continuity fails, the frontonasal duct opens directly into the anterior part of the meatus. Below the bulla ethmoidalis and hidden by the uncinate process of the ethmoid is the opening of the maxillary sinus (ostium maxillare); an accessory opening is frequently present above the posterior part of the inferior nasal concha.

name: inferior nasal meatus
description: The inferior meatus, the largest of the three meatuses of the nose, is the space between the inferior concha and the floor of the nasal cavity. It extends almost the entire length of the lateral wall of the nose, is broader in front than behind, and presents anteriorly the lower orifice of the nasolacrimal canal.

name: ventral nasal meatus
description: The ventral nasal meatus is found between the ventral nasal concha and the dorsal surface of the hard palate.It connects the nasal vestibule with the nasopharynx. Rostrally it is narrow at the nasal vestibule and widens caudally towards the nasopharyngeal meatus. The ventral nasal meatus is the main passage for air. Apart from olfaction, the nasal cavity functions to warm the inhaled air as it passes through the meatuses over the vascular beds of the mucosa. The air is humidified by the vaporization of tears and serous nasal secretion. The air is cleaned throughout the scattered mucous glands. These glands secrete mucous through the nasal cavity and the mucous serves to trap the large particles that come into contact with it. PPP Clinically in the horse the ventral nasal meatus is the main passage through which a stomach tube can be passed to the pharynx and oesophagus and then to the stomach. This kind of a tube is commonly used when drenching a horse for colic, as well as having many other veterinary applications. The tube has to pass through the ventral nasal meatus to the nasopharyngeal meatus and the caudal nares to reach the pharynx and oesophagus. If the tube is accidentally passed into the dorsal or middle nasal meatuses it would pass to the ethmotubinates and cause massive haemorrhage.

name: dorsal nasal meatus
description: The dosal nasal meatus is a narrow passage bounded dorsally by the roof of the nasal cavity and ventrally by the dorsal concha. It terminates caudally at the junction of the inner plate of the frontal bone with the cribiform plate and lateral mass of the ethmoid bone. It is the shortest and shallowest of the three meatuses.

name: interventricular foramen intermedium
description: A anatomical conduit that is part of a ventricular septum intermedium.

name: atrial foramen intermedium
description: A anatomical conduit that is part of a atrial septum intermedium.

name: peristaltic circulatory vessel
description: A vessel down which passes a wave of muscular contraction, that forces the flow of haemolymphatic fluid.

name: circulatory organ
description: A hollow, muscular organ, which, by contracting rhythmically, contributes to the circulation of lymph, blood or analogs. Examples: a chambered vertebrate heart; the tubular peristaltic heart of ascidians; the dorsal vessel of an insect; the lymoh heart of a reptile.

name: accessory circulatory organ
description: A circulatory organ that is not responsible for primary circulation.

name: nematode pharynx
description: The feeding organ, a neuro-muscular pump in the head of the animal, used to ingest food, bacteria suspended in liquid, filter them out, grind them up and transport posteriorly into the instestine.

name: nucleus of dorsal thalamus
description: A nucleus of brain that is part of a dorsal thalamus.

name: nucleus of ventral thalamus
description: A nucleus of brain that is part of a ventral thalamus.

name: pineal complex
description: A cluster in the epithalamus that consists of the pineal body and any associated structures, such as the parapineal gland or the parietal organ. The complex is poorly developed in mammals.

name: lower part of vagina
description: The lower third of the vagina.
synonyms: ["caudal vagina","perineal part of vagina","vagina lower part"]

name: accessory olfactory bulb granule cell layer
synonyms: ["accessory olfactory bulb, granular layer","AOB, granular layer"]

name: septal olfactory organ
description: A spatially segregated cluster of sensory cells in the nasal cavity.

name: septal organ of Masera
description: A small island of olfactory neuroepithelium lying bilaterally at the ventral base of the nasal septum near the entrance of the nasopharynx.

name: bifurcation of trachea
description: This is the point at which the trachea splits into two (left and right) principal bronchi. It is located in the region of the fourth to sixth intercostal space, though this varies with species and with respiratory phase. This position closely associates the bifurcation with the heart base. The thickened median crest initiating the bifurcation is called the tracheal carina .

name: digit skin
description: A zone of skin that is part of a digit.

name: coat hair follicle
description: A hair follicle that is part of a coat of hair.

name: pancreas left lobe
description: A pancreatic lobule that is in_the_left_side_of a exocrine pancreas.

name: pancreas right lobe
description: A pancreatic lobule that is in_the_right_side_of a exocrine pancreas.

name: respiratory system basement membrane
description: A basement membrane of epithelium that is part of a respiratory system.

name: saphenous artery
description: A branch of the descending genicular artery, the last branch (most distal) of the femoral, the saphenous is also variable. It usually lies between the sartorius and the garcilis muscles and supplies their distal ends. The artery accompanies the saphenous nerve. It usually supplies the skin on the medial and proximal part of the leg. The artery may continue to join, in varying degrees, the dorsalis pedis artery and plantaris pedis arteries.

name: urethra mesenchymal layer
description: A mesenchyme that is part of a urethra.

name: ureteral valve
description: A valve that is part of a ureter.

name: hilar portion of hepatic duct
description: The segment of either hepatic duct located in the hilum of the liver.

name: levator auris longus muscle
description: Muscle organ located on the dorsal surface of the head innervated by the facial nerve

name: accessory olfactory bulb mitral cell layer
blood vessel external elastic membrane
description: A thin layer of fibrous tissue capable of stretching and contracting. It is part of the tunica media of the blood vessels.

name: anterior lingual gland duct
description: A duct that is part of a anterior lingual gland.

name: subcutaneous lymph node
description: A lymph node that is part of a hypodermis.

name: pancreatic fat pad
description: A fat pad that is part of a pancreas.

name: mediastinal fat pad
description: A fat pad that is part of a mediastinum.

name: splenic lymph node
description: The splenic lymph nodes (or pancreaticolienal) accompany the lienal (splenic) artery, and are situated in relation to the posterior surface and upper border of the pancreas; one or two members of this group are found in the gastrolienal ligament. Their afferents are derived from the stomach, spleen, and pancreas, their efferents join the celiac group of preaortic glands.

name: tracheobronchial lymph node
description: A lymph node located near the bifurcation of the trachea.
synonyms: ["nodus tracheobronchiale lymphaticus","tracheobronchal lymph node","tracheobronchal node","tracheobronchial node"]

name: axilla skin
description: A zone of skin that is part of a axilla.

name: nose skin
description: A zone of skin that is part of a external nose.
synonyms: ["external nasal skin","skin of external nose","skin of nose"]

name: axillary fat pad
description: A fat pad that is part of a axilla.

name: scrotum skin
description: A zone of skin that is part of a scrotum.

name: proper hepatic artery
description: The hepatic artery proper (also proper hepatic artery), arises from the common hepatic artery and runs alongside the portal vein and the common bile duct to form the portal triad. The hepatic artery proper gives off a small supraduodenal artery to the duodenal bulb. Then the right gastric artery comes off and runs to the left along the lesser curvature of the stomach to meet the left gastric artery, which is a branch of the celiac trunk. It subsequently gives off the cystic artery, which feeds the gallbladder, before bifurcating into the right and left hepatic arteries. Of note, the right and left hepatic arteries may demonstrate variant anatomy. A replaced right hepatic artery may arise from the superior mesenteric artery (SMA) and a replaced left hepatic artery may arise from the left gastric artery.

name: left hepatic artery
description: A hepatic artery that is part of a left lobe of liver.
synonyms: ["left branch of hepatic artery","left part of hepatic artery proper","ramus sinister (arteria hepatica propria)"]

name: right hepatic artery
description: A hepatic artery that is part of a right lobe of liver.
synonyms: ["ramus dexter (arteria hepatica propria)","right branch of hepatic artery proper","right part of hepatic artery proper"]

name: epidermis of metapodial pad
description: A zone of skin that is part of a metapodial pad.

name: choledocho-duodenal junction
description: hat part of the duodenal wall traversed by the ductus choledochus, ductus pancreaticus, and ampulla.

name: sural nerve
description: The sural nerve (short saphenous nerve), formed by the junction of the medial sural cutaneous with the peroneal anastomotic branch of the lateral sural cutaneous nerve, passes downward near the lateral margin of the tendo calcaneus, lying close to the small saphenous vein, to the interval between the lateral malleolus and the calcaneus. It runs forward below the lateral malleolus, and is continued as the lateral dorsal cutaneous nerve along the lateral side of the foot and little toe (via a dorsal digital nerve), communicating on the dorsum of the foot with the intermediate dorsal cutaneous nerve, a branch of the superficial peroneal. In the leg, its branches communicate with those of the posterior femoral cutaneous.

name: body of corpus callosum
description: An area within the corpus callosum, a white matter structure within the cleft that separates the left and right cerebral hemispheres in the mammalian brain, between the genu (anterior region) and the splenium (posterior region).

name: frontal gyrus
description: A gyrus that is part of a frontal cortex.

name: genu of corpus callosum
description: Part of corpus callosum comprising the \"kneelike\" anterior bend (adapted from Nolte, The Human Brain, 6th ed., 2009 pg 664)

name: rostrum of corpus callosum
description: The part of the corpus callosum that projects posteriorly and inferiorly from the anteriormost genu.

name: sagittal sinus
description: Either the inferior or superior sagittal sinus

name: splenium of the corpus callosum
description: The posterior end of the corpus callosum. It overlaps the tela chorioidea of the third ventricle and the mid-brain, and ends in a thick, convex, free border.

name: anal canal epithelium
description: A epithelium that is part of a anal canal.

name: smooth muscle tissue layer of ejaculatory duct
description: A smooth muscle tissue that is part of a ejaculatory duct.

name: inferior tarsal muscle
description: A smooth muscle tissue that is part of a inferior eyelid tarsus.

name: mixed stratified cuboidal and columnar epithelium
description: Multilaminar epithelium, which consists of more than one layer of cuboidal and columnar cells, only one layer of which is in contact with a basement membrane. Examples: epithelium of wall of pancreatic duct, epithelium of wall of duct of salivary gland.

name: dense regular elastic tissue
description: Regular connective tissue, which consists of fibroblasts and of intercellular matrix, which contains elastic fiber bundles oriented predominantly in definable directions.
synonyms: ["dense elastic connective tissue","dense regular elastic connective tissue"]

name: epithelium of duct of salivary gland
description: A epithelium that is part of a duct of salivary gland.
synonyms: ["epithelium of salivary duct","salivary duct epithelium","salivary ductal epithelium"]

name: smooth muscle layer in fatty layer of subcutaneous tissue
description: A smooth muscle tissue that is part of a hypodermis.
synonyms: ["muscle layer in fatty layer of subcutaneous tissue","stratum musculosum panniculi adiposi telae subcutaneae"]

name: duct of olfactory gland
description: A duct that is part of a olfactory gland.

name: acinus of olfactory gland
description: A acinus that is part of a olfactory gland.
synonyms: ["acinar part of olfactory gland","olfactory gland acinus"]

name: respiratory segment of nasal mucosa
description: The portion of the nasal mucosa that is part of the respiratory system.
synonyms: ["pars respiratoria tunicae mucosae nasi","respiratory zone of nasal mucosa"]

name: upper respiratory conduit
description: Any anatomical conduit which is part of the upper respiratory tract

name: olfactory apparatus chamber
description: An anatomical chamber that is part of the olfactory apparatus, consisting of cavity walls (nasal epithelium and mucosal layers) and the space bounded anteriorly by the nares and posteriorly by the choanae, when these structures are present.

name: autopod skin
description: A zone of skin that is part of a autopod region.

name: digit connective tissue
description: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a digit.

name: induseum griseum
description: Thin layer of cortex lying on the dorsal surface of the corpus callosum. It has been debated whether it is more related to the hippocampus or the olfactory bulb (Shipley et al., Olfactory System In Paxinos The Rat Nervous System, 2nd ed)

name: left lung lobar bronchus epithelium
description: A epithelium that is part of a lobar bronchus of left lung.

name: right lung lobar bronchus epitheium
description: A epithelium that is part of a lobar bronchus of right lung.

name: liver blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a liver.

name: taenia tectum of brain
description: A continuation ventrally of the supracallosal gyrus beyond the rostrum of the corpus callosum. It is demonstrated histologically by Nissl stain. In the human ( Anthoney-1994 ) and the macaque ( Paxinos-2004 ) it lies on the rostral surface of the lamina terminalis and is considered identical to or part of the paraterminal gyrus. In the rat ( Swanson-1998 ) and the mouse ( Paxinos-2001 ) it is located similarly in relation to the supracallosal gyrus, however, it is a more prominent layered structure that extends rostrally on the medial surface overlying the anterior olfactory nucleus. It is considered part of the olfactory areas (rodent) of the cerebral cortex. In rodents it consists of two parts, the dorsal tenia tecta and the ventral tenia tecta. Note that some authors use the term 'tenia tecta' or 'taenia tecta' as a synonym for the lateral longitudinal stria ( Riley-1943 ).

name: ear epithelium
description: A epithelium that is part of a ear.

name: eye epithelium
description: A epithelium that is part of a camera-type eye.

name: middle ear epithelium
description: A epithelium that is part of a middle ear.

name: outer ear epithelium
description: A epithelium that is part of a external ear.

name: foregut epithelium
description: A epithelium that is part of a foregut.

name: duodenum lamina propria
description: A lamina propria that is part of a duodenum.
synonyms: ["duodenal lamina propria","lamina propria mucosae of duodenum","lamina propria of duodenum"]

name: incisor dental pulp
description: A dental pulp that is part of a incisor tooth.

name: incisor dental lamina
description: A dental lamina that is part of a incisor tooth.

name: incisor enamel organ
description: A tooth enamel organ that is part of a incisor tooth.

name: incisor mesenchyme
description: A odontogenic mesenchyme that is part of a incisor tooth.

name: upper left incisor tooth
description: A upper jaw incisor that is in_the_left_side_of a dentition.

name: incisor tusk
description: An incisor tooth that protrudes beyond the mouth.

name: canine tusk
description: An cuspid tooth that protrudes beyond the mouth.

name: narwhal tusk
description: A upper jaw incisor that protrudes prominently from the mouth as a single median tusk, found in narwhals.

name: dental pulp of median incisor tusk
description: A dental pulp that is part of a narwhal tusk.

name: interpedicular line
description: An anatomical line that connects two successive vertebral pedicles. The length of this line is known as the interpedicular distance.

name: ventral ectodermal ridge
description: A thickening of the surface ectoderm on the ventral side of the embryonic tail which resembles the apical ectodermal ridge of the limb bud.

name: parotid lymph node
description: A lymph node found near the parotid gland.

name: hepatic lymph node
description: Any of the lymph nodes adjacent to the stomach and duodenum.
synonyms: ["hepatic node","lymphoglandulae hepaticae","lymphoglandulæ hepaticæ","nodi lymphoidei hepatici","portal lymph node"]

name: gastric lymph node
description: A lymph node along the left gastric artery or greater omentum.

name: pancreaticosplenic lymph node
description: lymph nodes of the pancreatic tail and spleen, receiving afferents from both organs plus the greater curvature of the stomach; they drain to the celiac lymph nodes.

name: lymph node of epiploic foramen
