synonyms: ["lymph node of anterior border of epiploic foramen","lymph node of anterior border of omental foramen","node of anterior border of epiploic foramen","node of anterior border of omental foramen","nodus foraminalis","nodus lymphoideus foraminalis"]

name: retropharyngeal lymph node
description: The retropharyngeal lymph nodes, from one to three in number, lie in the buccopharyngeal fascia, behind the upper part of the pharynx and in front of the arch of the atlas, being separated, however, from the latter by the Longus capitis. Their afferents drain the nasal cavities, the nasal part of the pharynx, and the auditory tubes. Their efferents pass to the superior deep cervical glands. They are in the retropharyngeal space.

name: lymph node of head
description: A lymph node that is part of a head.

name: facial lymph node
description: Any of the lymph nodes that are part of a face.

name: mandibular lymph node
description: The mandibular lymph node is a lymph node found near the jaw.

name: heel skin
description: A zone of skin that is part of a heel.

name: heel
description: The part of the foot that is the projection of the calcaneus.

name: pelvic lymph node
description: Any lymph node within the abdominal pelvic region.

name: common iliac lymph node
description: The external iliac lymph nodes, from eight to ten in number, lie along the external iliac vessels. They are arranged in three groups, one on the lateral, another on the medial, and a third on the anterior aspect of the vessels; the third group is, however, sometimes absent. Their principal afferents are derived from the inguinal lymph nodes, the deep lymphatics of the abdominal wall below the umbilicus and of the adductor region of the thigh, and the lymphatics from the glans penis vel clitoridis, the membranous urethra, the prostate, the fundus of the urinary bladder, the cervix uteri, and upper part of the vagina.

name: internal iliac lymph node
description: The internal iliac lymph nodes (or hypogastric) surround the internal iliac artery and its branches (the hypogastric vessels), and receive the lymphatics corresponding to the distribution of the branches of it, i. e. , they receive lymphatics from all the pelvic viscera, from the deeper parts of the perineum, including the membranous and cavernous portions of the urethra, and from the buttock and back of the thigh. It does not receive lymph from the ovary, testis, or superior half of the rectum; the gonads drain to the paraaortic lymph nodes, while the superior half of the rectum drains to the pararectal lymph nodes.

name: root of nail
description: The part of the nail plate that extends into the dermis (nail matrix)

name: proximal deep inguinal lymph node
description: One of the deep inguinal lymph nodes located in or adjacent to the femoral canal; sometimes mistaken for a femoral hernia when enlarged.
synonyms: ["nodus inguinales profundi proximalis","nodus lymphoideus inguinales profundi proximalis","proximal deep inguinal node","proximal inguinal lymph node","rosenmuller's gland","rosenmuller's node"]

name: superficial lymph node
description: A lymph node that is located close to the surface.

name: deep lymph node
description: A lymph node that is located deeper within the organism, further from the surface.

name: obsolete tonsillar lymph node
description: The term tonsillar node can be inaccurate or ambiguous

name: obsolete genital lymph node
description: The term tonsillar node can be inaccurate or ambiguous

name: superficial parotid lymph node
description: A parotid lymph node that is located superficially.

name: sciatic lymph node
description: A lymph node that is medial to the gluteus superficialis m., caudal to gluteus medius m. and sciatic nerve lymph node

name: ileocolic lymph node
description: One of the lymph nodes that form a chain around the ileocolic artery.

name: paraaortic lymph node
description: The paraaortic lymph nodes (also known as para-aortic, periaortic, and peri-aortic) are a group of lymph nodes that lie in front of the lumbar vertebral bodies near the aorta. These lymph nodes receive drainage from the lower gastrointestinal tract and the pelvic organs.
synonyms: ["lateral aortic lymph node","lateral aortic node","para-aortic lymph node"]

name: mastoid lymph node
description: The mastoid lymph nodes (retroauricular lymph nodes, posterior auricular glands), usually two in number, are situated on the mastoid insertion of the Sternocleidomastoideus, beneath the Auricularis posterior. Their afferent vessels drain the posterior part of the temporoparietal region, the upper part of the cranial surface of the auricula or pinna, and the back of the external acoustic meatus; their efferents pass to the superior deep cervical glands.
synonyms: ["mastoid node","postauricular lymph node","retro-auricular lymph node","retro-auricular node"]

name: deep parotid lymph node
description: The deep parotid lymph nodes are lymph nodes found below the parotid gland. The afferents of the subparotid glands drain the nasal part of the pharynx and the posterior parts of the nasal cavities. Their efferents pass to the superior deep cervical glands.

name: anterior auricular lymph node
description: The preauricular deep parotid lymph nodes (anterior auricular glands or preauricular glands), from one to three in number, lie immediately in front of the tragus. Their afferents drain the lateral surface of the auricula and the skin of the adjacent part of the temporal region; their efferents pass to the superior deep cervical glands.
synonyms: ["pre-auricular lymph node","pre-auricular node","preauricular lymph node","preauricular node"]

name: infra-auricular lymph node
description: The infra-auricular deep parotid lymph nodes are a group of lymph nodes found underneath the ear.
synonyms: ["infra-auricular deep node","infra-auricular deep parotid lymph node","infra-auricular deep parotid node","infra-auricular node"]

name: submental lymph node
description: The submental lymph nodes (or suprahyoid) are situated between the anterior bellies of the Digastrici. Their afferents drain the central portions of the lower lip and floor of the mouth and the apex of the tongue. Their efferents pass partly to the submandibular lymph nodes and partly to a gland of the deep cervical group situated on the internal jugular vein at the level of the cricoid cartilage.

name: lymph node of lower limb
description: A lymph node that is part of a hindlimb.

name: lymph node of upper limb
description: A lymph node that is part of a forelimb.

name: infrapatellar fat pad
description: The infrapatellar fat pad, also known as Hoffa's fat pad, is a cylindrical piece of fat that is situated under and behind the patella bone within the knee.

name: thoracic wall
description: The thoracic wall (or chest wall) is the boundary of the thoracic cavity. The bony portion is known as the thoracic cage. However, the wall also includes muscle, skin, and fascia.

name: cervical vertebral arch joint
description: A vertebral arch joint that is part of a cervical region of vertebral column.
synonyms: ["cervical facet joint","joint of cervical vertebral arch","joint of cervical vertebral articular process","zygapophyseal joint of cervical vertebrae","zygapophysial joint of cervical vertebrae"]

name: pulmonary capillary
description: A capillary that is part of a lung.

name: corona of glans penis
description: The circumference of the base of the glans forms a rounded projecting border, the corona of the glans penis, overhanging a deep retroglandular sulcus, behind which is the neck of the penis.

name: male breast
description: A breast that is part of a male organism.

name: central part of body of bony vertebral centrum
anterior chest
description: Subdivision of thorax which is anterior to the plane of the posterior boundary of the middle mediastinum.

name: nasion
description: The intersection of the frontal and two nasal bones of the human skull. Its manifestation on the visible surface of the face is a distinctly depressed area directly between the eyes, just superior to the bridge of the nose.

name: compact bone of long bone
description: A compact bone tissue that is part of a bone tissue of long bone.

name: compact bone of diaphysis
description: A compact bone tissue that is part of a diaphysis.

name: epiphyseal plate of radius
description: A epiphyseal plate that is part of a radius bone.

name: proximal interphalangeal joint of little finger
palmar branch of median nerve
description: The palmar branch of the median nerve is a branch of the median nerve which arises at the lower part of the forearm and innervates skin of proximal central palm and thenar eminence.
synonyms: ["median nerve palmar branch","palmar branch of anterior interosseous nerve","palmar cutaneous branch of median nerve","ramus palmaris (nervus medianus)","ramus palmaris nervus interossei antebrachii anterior"]

name: chest wall
description: Subdivision of thorax which includes all structures from the skin to the costal pleura. Examples: There is only one chest wall.

name: glabella region of bone
description: A zone of the frontal bone that connects the supraorbital rirdges.

name: median palatine suture
description: the line of junction between the horizontal parts of the palatine bones that extends from both sides of the skull to form the posterior part of the hard palate.
synonyms: ["median palatine suture of skull","middle palatine suture of skull","midpalatal suture of skull"]

name: hair of head
description: A strand of hair that is part of a head.

name: hair of trunk
description: A strand of hair that is part of a trunk.

name: upper secondary premolar tooth
synonyms: ["maxillary secondary premolar tooth","upper permanent premolar tooth"]

name: lower secondary premolar tooth
synonyms: ["lower permanent premolar tooth","mandibular secondary premolar tooth"]

name: upper central secondary incisor tooth
synonyms: ["maxillary central permanent incisor tooth","maxillary central secondary incisor tooth","upper central permanent incisor tooth"]

name: upper lateral secondary incisor tooth
synonyms: ["maxillary lateral secondary incisor tooth","upper lateral permanent incisor tooth"]

name: esophageal hiatus
description: A hole in the diaphragm through which the esophagus passes

name: posterior pole of lens
description: the central point on the posterior surface of the lens.

name: periorbital skin
description: A zone of skin in the periorbital region of the face.

name: dorsum of nose
description: The midline prominence of the nose, extending from the nasal root to the tip.

name: antihelix
description: On the pinna, a curved prominence of cartilage, parallel with and in front of the helix, is called the antihelix, also known as the anthelix; this divides above into two crura, the crura antihelicis, between which is a triangular depression, the fossa triangularis.

name: antitragus
description: The antitragus is a feature of human ear anatomy. It is a small tubercle that points anteriorly. It is separated from the tragus by the intertragic notch.

name: skin of forehead
description: A zone of skin that is part of a forehead.

name: primary incisor tooth
description: A incisor tooth that is part of a primary dentition.

name: zygomatic process of maxilla
description: The zygomatic process of the maxilla (malar process) is a rough triangular eminence, situated at the angle of separation of the anterior, zygomatic, and orbital surfaces. In front it forms part of the anterior surface. Behind it is concave, and forms part of the infratemporal fossa. Above it is rough and serrated for articulation with the zygomatic bone. Below it presents the prominent arched border which marks the division between the anterior and infratemporal surfaces.
synonyms: ["malar process","malar process of maxilla","processus zygomaticus (maxilla)","processus zygomaticus maxillae","zygomaticoorbital process of maxilla"]

name: liver stroma
description: A stroma that is part of a liver.

name: capsule of liver
description: A collagenous capsule covering the external surface of the liver.
synonyms: ["capsula fibrosa perivascularis","fibrous capsule of liver","glisson's capsule","hepatic capsule","tunica fibrosa (hepar)","tunica fibrosa hepatis"]

name: bronchial lymph node
description: A lymph node that is part of a bronchus.

name: dental plaque
description: A soft, thin film of food debris, mucin, and dead epithelial cells deposited on the teeth, providing the medium for the growth of various bacteria. The main inorganic components are calcium and phosphorus, with small amounts of magnesium, potassium, and sodium; the organic matrix consists of polysaccharides, proteins, carbohydrates, lipids, and other components. Plaque plays an important etiologic role in the development of dental caries and periodontal and gingival diseases and provides the base for the development of materia alba; calcified plaque forms dental calculus.

name: posterior fornix of vagina
description: The vaginal fornix that is behind the cervix. It is close to the recto-uterine pouch.
synonyms: ["pars posterior fornicis vaginae","posterior fornix","posterior part of fornix of vagina"]

name: anterior fornix of vagina
description: The vaginal fornix that is front of the cervix. It is close to the vesico-uterine pouch.
synonyms: ["anterior fornix","anterior part of fornix of vagina","pars anterior fornicis vaginae"]

name: auditory system
description: is the sensory system for the sense of hearing.

name: vertebral centrum element
description: Skeletal element that functionally replaces the notochord.

name: foramen spinosum of sphenoid bone
description: A foramen in the sphenoid bone through which the middle meningeal artery, middle meningeal vein, and the meningeal branch of the mandibular nerve pass.

name: palmaris longus muscle
description: The palmaris longus is seen as a small tendon between the flexor carpi radialis and the flexor carpi ulnaris, although it is not always present. The muscle is absent in about 14 percent of the population, however this varies greatly with ethnicity. Absence of palmaris does not have any known effect on grip strength. Palmaris longus can be palpated by touching the pads of the fifth and first fingers and flexing the wrist. The tendon, if present, will be very visible.

name: epicondyle of humerus
description: A epicondyle that is part of a humerus.

name: intestinal-cloacal junction
description: The juncture where the intestine empties into the cloaca.

name: esophageal-pneumatic duct sphincter
description: Sphincter at the junction of the esophagus and pneumatic duct.

name: muscularis mucosa of fundus of urinary bladder
description: A muscularis mucosa that is part of a fundus of urinary bladder.

name: muscularis mucosae of fundus of stomach
description: A muscularis mucosa that is part of a fundus of stomach.

name: stomach fundus lumen
description: A anatomical space that is enclosed by a fundus of stomach.
synonyms: ["cavity of fundus of stomach","lumen of fundus of stomach","lumen of stomach fundus"]

name: umbilical ring
description: A dense fibrous ring surrounding the umbilicus at birth. At about the sixth week of embryological development, the midgut herniates through the umbilical ring; four weeks later it returns to the abdominal cavity and rotates around the superior mesenteric artery.

name: Mullerian tubercle
description: An elevation on the wall of the embryonic urogenital sinus where the Müllerian ducts enter.

name: cavity of right ventricle
description: Luminal space of the right ventricle of the heart.

name: epithelium of male urethra
description: A epithelium that is part of a male urethra.

name: lamina propria of fundus of stomach
description: A lamina propria that is part of a mucosa of fundus of stomach.
synonyms: ["lamina propria mucosae of fundus of stomach"]

name: lumen of duodenum
description: A anatomical space that is part of a duodenum.

name: cavity of left atrium
description: luminal space of the left atrium of the heart.

name: cavity of left ventricle
description: luminal space of the left ventricle of the heart.

name: muscular layer of prostatic urethra
description: A muscular coat that is part of a prostatic urethra.
synonyms: ["muscle layer of prostatic part of urethra","muscle layer of prostatic urethra","muscle layer of prostatic urethra","muscular coat of prostatic urethra"]

name: lamina propria of prostatic urethra
description: A lamina propria that is part of a prostatic urethra.
synonyms: ["lamina propria of prostatic part of urethra","lamina propria of prostatic urethra"]

name: lumen of jejunum
description: A anatomical space that is part of a jejunum.

name: muscularis mucosae of jejunum
description: A muscularis mucosa that is part of a jejunum.

name: epithelium of female urethra
description: A epithelium that is part of a female urethra.

name: cavity of right atrium
description: luminal space of the right atrium of the heart.

name: muscle layer of spongiose part of urethra
description: A muscular coat that is part of a spongiose part of urethra.
synonyms: ["muscle layer of penile urethra","muscle layer of penile urethra","muscle layer of spongy urethra","muscular coat of spongy urethra","muscular layer of spongy urethra","tunica muscularis urethrae spongiosa"]

name: frontal lobe
description: Frontal lobe is the anterior-most of five lobes of the cerebral hemisphere. It is bounded by the central sulcus on its posterior border and by the longitudinal cerebral fissure on its medial border.

name: lobe of cerebral hemisphere
description: Subdivision of telencephalon which is one of a number of subdivisions of each hemisphere separated by both real landmarks (sulci and fissures) and arbitrary boundaries.
synonyms: ["cerebral hemisphere lobe","cerebral lobe","lobe of cerebral cortex","lobe parts of cerebral cortex","lobi cerebri"]

name: white matter of frontal lobe
description: A white matter of cerebral lobe that is part of a frontal lobe.

name: cortex of cerebral lobe
description: Grey matter neocortex region of a lobe of the cerebral hemisphere.
synonyms: ["cortex of cerebral hemisphere lobe","cortex of lobe of cerebral hemisphere"]

name: parietal cortex
description: Gray matter of the parietal region of the neocortex, located in the parietal lobe of gyrencephalic animals. It is continuous anteriorly with the frontal cortex, posteriorly with the occipital cortex and medially with the insular cortex and with the temporal cortex on the posterior/inferior border.
synonyms: ["cortex of parietal lobe","parietal lobe cortex","parietal neocortex"]

name: white matter of parietal lobe
description: A white matter of cerebral lobe that is part of a parietal lobe.

name: white matter of temporal lobe
description: A white matter of cerebral lobe that is part of a temporal lobe.

name: white matter of occipital lobe
description: A white matter of cerebral lobe that is part of a occipital lobe.

name: white matter of limbic lobe
description: A white matter of cerebral lobe that is part of a limbic lobe.

name: temporal cortex
description: Gray matter of the temporal region of the neocortex, located in the temporal lobe in gyrencephalic animals
synonyms: ["cortex of temporal lobe","temporal lobe cortex","temporal neocortex"]

name: occipital cortex
synonyms: ["cortex of occipital lobe","occipital lobe cortex","occipital neocortex"]

name: pharyngeal ectoderm
description: The external part of the developing pharynx that is made of ectoderm. During vertebrate development, pockets form in pharyngeal ectoderm between the pharyngeal arches.

name: central nervous system gray matter layer
description: A layer of of the central nervous system that is part of gray matter.
synonyms: ["CNS gray matter layer","CNS grey matter layer","gray matter layer of neuraxis","grey matter layer","grey matter layer of neuraxis"]

name: central nervous system white matter layer
description: A layer of of the central nervous system that is composed of white matter.
synonyms: ["CNS white matter layer","white matter layer","white matter layer of neuraxis"]

name: subdivision of spinal cord ventral column
phlegm
description: mucus produced in the respiratory tract.

name: respiratory system mucus
description: Any mucus produced by a mucosae of the respiratory system. This includes the mucus produced in the nasal cavity (nasal mucus) and mucus produced in the respiratory tract (phlegm).

name: white matter of midbrain
description: A white matter that is part of the midbrain.

name: stria of telencephalon
description: A stria of neuraxis that is part of a telencephalon.

name: superficial cerebral vein
description: The superficial cerebral veins are a group of veins in the head. This group includes the superior cerebral veins.

name: deep cerebral vein
description: The deep cerebral veins are a group of veins in the head. This group includes the superior thalamostriate vein.

name: cerebral blood vessel
description: A blood vessel that is part of a cerebellum.

name: pit
description: An roughly circular indentation in a surface.

name: statoconial membrane
description: An acellular membrane in the vestibular labyrinth that is composed of the otoconial layer, gelatinous layer, and a subcupular meshwork.

name: subcupular meshwork of statoconial membrane
description: An acellular membrane in the inner ear that is part of the statoconial membrane and consists of long branching filaments cross-bridged to one another. The filaments are continuous with those of the otolithic membrane on one side and with the surface of the epithelium on the other.

name: lamina of gray matter of spinal cord
obsolete lamina II of gray matter of spinal cord
lamina III of gray matter of spinal cord
synonyms: ["lamina spinale III","rexed lamina III","spinal lamina III"]

name: lamina IV of gray matter of spinal cord
synonyms: ["lamina spinale IV","rexed lamina IV","spinal lamina IV"]

name: lamina V of gray matter of spinal cord
description: Spinal lamina V is a lamina of the spinal cord. It is also known as the neck of the posterior horn.

name: lamina VI of gray matter of spinal cord
description: Spinal lamina VI is a lamina of the spinal cord. It is also known as the base of the posterior horn.

name: lamina VII of gray matter of spinal cord
lamina VIII of gray matter of spinal cord
lamina IX of gray matter of spinal cord
nucleus proprius of spinal cord
description: The Nucleus proprius is a layer of the spinal cord adjacent to the substantia gelatinosa. Nucleus proprius constitutes the bulk of the dorsal horn and receives inputs from the dorsal root ganglions that carry sensory information, such as light touch, as well as pain and temperature information. Cells in this nucleus project to deeper laminae of the spinal cord, to the posterior column nuclei, and to other supraspinal relay centers including the midbrain, thalamus, and hypothalamus. Rexed laminae III, IV, and V make up the nucleus propius Nucleus proprius (NP), along with nucleus dorsalis (ND) are involved in sensing fine touch and proprioception.

name: auditory hillocks, pharyngeal arch 1 derived
description: A collection of protruberances derived from pharyngeal arch 1 that develop into the tragus, crus of the helix, and helix.

name: auditory hillocks, pharyngeal arch 2 derived
description: A collection of protruberances derived from pharyngeal arch 2 that develop into the concha, antihelix and antitragus.

name: Y-shaped fibrocartilage skeleton of ventral pouch
description: A Y-shaped fibrocartilage structure that lies in the substance of the muscular ventral pouch of rorqual whales.

name: lunge feeding organ
description: A fibrous capsule located between the jaws of rorqual whales that contains a gelatinous substance and papillae bearing mechanorecaptors.

name: lunge feeding vibrissa
description: A vibrissa on the lower jaw of rorqual whales that is hypothesized to form part of the lung feeding system.

name: stem of Y-shaped fibrocartilage skeleton of ventral pouch
branch of Y-shaped fibrocartilage skeleton of ventral pouch
neurovascular bundle
description: A body structure consisting of nerves traveling together with arteries, veins, and/or lymphatics.

name: actinopterygian frontal-parietal joint
description: Fibrous joint connecting the actinopterygian frontal bone to the actinopterygian parietal bone.

name: parvocellular reticular nucleus
description: The parvocellular reticular nucleus is part of the brain located dorsolateral to the nucleus reticularis pontis caudalis. The dorsal portion of the reticular nucleus has been shown to innervate the mesencephalic trigeminal nucleus and its surrounding area. Also, it projects to the facial nucleus, hypoglossal nucleus and parabrachial nucleus along with parts of the caudal parvocellular reticular formation. This nucleus is also involved in expiration with a part of the gigantocellular nucleus.
synonyms: ["nucleus reticularis parvocellularis","parvicellular reticular nucleus","parvocellular reticular nucleus"]

name: premotor cortex
description: The premotor cortex is an area of motor cortex lying within the frontal lobe of the brain. It extends 3 mm anterior to the primary motor cortex, near the Sylvian fissure, before narrowing to approximately 1 mm near the medial longitudinal fissure, which serves as the posterior border for the prefrontal cortex. The premotor cortex is largely equivalent to Brodmann area 6. Activity within this region is critical to the sensory guidance of movement and control of proximal and trunk muscles of the body.

name: supplemental motor cortex
description: The supplementary motor area (SMA) is a part of the sensorimotor cerebral cortex (perirolandic, i.e. on each side of the Rolando or central sulcus). It was included, on purely cytoarchitectonic arguments, in area 6 of Brodmann and the Vogts. It is located on the medial face of the hemisphere, just in front of primary motor cortex. This is an element that appeared late in evolution, in monkeys, linked to the appearance of a true medial pallidum.

name: lateral periolivary nucleus
description: Lateral component of the periolivary nucleus

name: subparafascicular nucleus
description: The term subparafascicular nucleus refers to a cell group located ventral to the parafascicular nucleus in the thalamus. Identified by internal structure, it is present in the human ( Mai-1997 ), the macaque ( Paxinos-2009a ), the rat ( Swanson-1998 ), and the mouse ( Hof-2000 ).

name: lateral paragigantocellular nucleus
synonyms: ["lateral paragigantocellular reticular nucleus","paragigantocellular nucleus, lateral part"]

name: dorsal paragigantocellular nucleus
synonyms: ["dorsal paragigantocellular reticular nucleus","paragigantocellular nucleus, dorsal part","posterior paragigantocellular reticular nucleus"]

name: paramedian medullary reticular complex
synonyms: ["paramedian group (medullary reticular formation)","paramedian medullary reticular group"]

name: dorsal paramedian reticular nucleus
description: Small nucleus in the brainstem of human, located adjacent and medial to the nucleus prepositus in the dorsal medulla, described in several atlases of human brain stem. In transverse sections, it is oval with its long axis aligned with the dorsal border of the brainstem. It begins at about the same A-P level as the nucleus prepositus, just rostral to the hypoglossal nucleus. It includes calretinin immunoreactive large cells with oval or polygonal cell bodies. Cells are not immunoreactive for either calbindin or parvalbumin, but a few fibers immunoreactive to each protein are found within its central region. Cells in PMD are also immunoreactive to nNOS, and immunoreactivity to a neurofilament protein shows many labeled cells and fibers. According to Baizer et al., no equivalent structure was observed in the cat, rat, mouse or monkey atlas although they did not look at the brains of the great apes.
synonyms: ["dorsal paramedian nuclei of raphe","dorsal paramedian nucleus","posterior paramedian nucleus"]

name: paratrigeminal nucleus
description: The term paratrigeminal nucleus refers to a group of cells located lateral to the spinal trigeminal tract of the medulla and medial to the spinocerebellar tracts at the level of the spinal trigeminal nucleus. The cells, identified by Nissl stain, are partially embedded in the adjacent tracts; their distribution varies by species. The paratrigeminal nucleus may represent an extension of the lateral cervical nucleus into the medulla ( Swanson-2004 ). It is found in the human ( Carpenter-1983 ), the macaque ( Paxinos-2009a ), the rat ( Swanson-2004 ) and the mouse ( Paxinos-2001 ). In the functional model of central nervous system organization it is classified as part of the subcortical somatosensory system ( Swanson-2004 )

name: lateral nucleus of trapezoid body
description: One of two potential parts of the trapezoid nucleus. Separated by an indistinct boundary, the other is the medial trapezoid nucleus ( Crosby-1962 ). The existence of the trapezoid nucleus in the human is disputed ( Bazwinsky-2003 )

name: retroambiguus nucleus
description: The term retroambiguus nucleus refers to a group of neurons in the medulla at the caudal end of the nucleus ambiguus, from which the cranial part of the accessory nerve originates ( Crosby-1962 ).

name: obsolete subparabrachial nucleus
description: A cell group located ventral to the brachium conjunctivum in the general area where the medial and lateral parabrachial nuclei abut, shifting to the slightly more lateral position rostrally.

name: nucleus of phrenic nerve
description: neuron cell bodies located in the more medial portions of the anterior horn at cervical levels C3-C7 that innervate the diaphragm via the phrenic nerve.

name: renal fascia
description: A fascial pouch derived from extraperitoneal connective tissue that contains the kidneys, the suprarenal glands, the renal vessels and perirenal fat

name: skin scent gland
description: A scent gland that is part of the skin

name: interdigital gland
description: A skin gland found in the interdigital region of some mammals

name: dorsal part of optic cup
description: The dorsal region of the optic cup that gives rise to the dorsal part of the retina.
synonyms: ["dorsal optic cup","dorsal region of optic cup"]

name: ventral part of optic cup
description: The ventral region of the optic cup that gives rise to the ventral part of the retina.
synonyms: ["ventral optic cup","ventral region of optic cup"]

name: digit 6
description: A digit that is part of a digit 6 plus metapodial segment.

name: digit 7
description: A digit that is part of a digit 7 plus metapodial segment.

name: digit 8
description: A digit that is part of a digit 8 plus metapodial segment.

name: digit 6 plus metapodial segment
description: A subdivision of the autopod consisting of digit 6 plus the region incorporating a single metapodial element. These segments are typically repeated along the pre-axiom to post-axial axis.
synonyms: ["digit 6","digit 6 ( phalanges plus metapodial) plus soft tissue","digit 6 digitopodial subdivision","digit 6 ray","digit VI plus metapodial segment"]

name: digit 7 plus metapodial segment
description: A subdivision of the autopod consisting of digit 7 plus the region incorporating a single metapodial element. These segments are typically repeated along the pre-axiom to post-axial axis.
synonyms: ["digit 7","digit 7 ( phalanges plus metapodial) plus soft tissue","digit 7 digitopodial subdivision","digit 7 ray","digit VII plus metapodial segment"]

name: digit 8 plus metapodial segment
description: A subdivision of the autopod consisting of digit 8 plus the region incorporating a single metapodial element. These segments are typically repeated along the pre-axiom to post-axial axis.
synonyms: ["digit 8","digit 8 ( phalanges plus metapodial) plus soft tissue","digit 8 digitopodial subdivision","digit 8 ray","digit VIII plus metapodial segment"]

name: digit 6 digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of digit 6 plus the associated metapodial element.

name: digit 7 digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of digit 7 plus the associated metapodial element.

name: digit 8 digitopodial skeleton
description: A subdivision of the skeleton of the autopod consisting of the phalanges of digit 8 plus the associated metapodial element.

name: future central nervous system
description: Primordium that develops into the central nervous system

name: future nervous system
description: Primordium that develops into the nervous system

name: craniopharyngeal canal
description: The craniopharyngeal canal, is an anatomical feature sometimes found in the sphenoid bone opening to the sella turcica. It is a canal (a passage or channel) sometimes found extending from the anterior part of the fossa hypophyseos of the sphenoid bone to the under surface of the skull, and marks the original position of Rathke's pouch; while at the junction of the septum of the nose with the palate traces of the stomodeal end are occasionally present.

name: intertarsal-type crurotarsal joint
description: An ankle joint that passes between the astragalus and calcaneum.

name: ovarian fossa
description: A shallow depression on the lateral wall of the pelvis, wherein the ovary lies. This fossa has the following boundaries: superiorly: by the external iliac vessels anteriorly and inferiorly: by the broad ligament of the uterus posteriorly: by the ureter and internal iliac vessels

name: shoulder joint
description: The joint that is formed by the union of the humerus, the scapula (or shoulder blade), and the clavicle (or collarbone). Commonly thought of as a single joint, the shoulder is actually made up of two separate joints - the glenohumeral and acromioclavicular joints

name: epithelium of terminal part of digestive tract
description: Epithelium lining the distalmost portion of the digestive tract.

name: muscle tissue of terminal part of digestive tract
description: Any muscle tissue of the distalmost portion of the digestive tract.

name: entire extraembryonic component
description: The part of the conceptus that may be lost before birth or will be discarded at birth, or when the embryo becomes an independent organism.

name: transitional anatomical structure
description: An embryonic anatomical entity that will turn into one or more other anatomical entities, perhaps with other anatomical entities, later in development.

name: periosteum of long bone
description: A periosteum that is part of a long bone.

name: frenulum of upper lip
description: A frenulum of lip that is part of a upper lip.
synonyms: ["f. labii superioris","frenulum labii superioris","upper lip frenulum"]

name: frenulum of lower lip
description: A frenulum of lip that is part of a lower lip.

name: lamina lucida
synonyms: ["electron-lucent layer of basal lamina of connective tissue","lamina rara"]

name: vermilion
description: The zone of the skin that surrounds a lip and is colored red due to thin epithelium and presence of eleidin
synonyms: ["vermilion border","vermilion border of lip","vermilion of lip"]

name: upper vermilion
description: A vermilion that is part of a upper lip.
synonyms: ["vermilion border of upper lip","vermilion of upper lip"]

name: lower vermilion
description: A vermilion that is part of a lower lip.
synonyms: ["vermilion border of lower lip","vermilion of lower lip"]

name: descending trunk of arch of aorta
synonyms: ["descending aortic arch","descending limb of arch of aorta","descending trunk of aortic arch"]

name: preductal region of aortic arch
description: Area of aorta proximal to the ductus arteriosus.

name: postductal region of aortic arch
description: Area of aorta distal to the ductus arteriosus.

name: juxtaductal region of aortic arch
description: Area of aorta at the area of insertion to the ductus arteriosus.

name: mucus body coating
description: A coating of mucus that is produced by the skin and covers all or most of the body of an animal.

name: mucus cocoon
description: A mucous covering produced nocturnally by some fish that is used to envelope the whole animal.

name: metaphysis of fibula
description: A metaphysis that is part of a fibula.

name: lingual cusp of tooth
description: A medially (towards the tongue)) raised feature found on crown of a tooth.

name: ridge of tooth
description: A linear flat evelation on a tooth.

name: transverse ridge of tooth
description: Triangular ridges facing each other and crossing at transverse angle, forming a transverse ridge on posterior teeth.
synonyms: ["crista transversalis (corona dentis)","crista transversalis dentis","crista transversalis of tooth","transverse ridge of crown of tooth"]

name: triangular ridge of tooth
synonyms: ["crista triangularis (corona dentis)","crista triangularis dentis","crista triangularis of tooth","triangular ridge of crown of tooth"]

name: oblique ridge of tooth
synonyms: ["crista obliqua (corona dentis)","crista obliqua dentis","oblique ridge of crown of tooth"]

name: marginal ridge of tooth
synonyms: ["crista marginalis (dentis)","crista marginalis dentis","crista marginalis of tooth"]

name: flexor cruris lateralis pars accessoria muscle
synonyms: ["M. flexor cruris lateralis pars accessoria","pars accessoria of M. flexor cruris lateralis"]

name: exoccipital-atlas joint
description: A synovial joint that connects a vertebral bone 1 and connects a exoccipital bone.

name: lumen of hemipenial sheath
description: A anatomical space that is enclosed by a hemipenal sheath.

name: hemipenial mucuous gland
description: A gland within the hemipenial sheath that provides lubrication for the hemipenis.

name: hemipenial holocrine gland
description: A holocrine gland that is part of a hemipenis.
synonyms: ["holocrine gland of hemipenis","holoctine gland of hemipenis sheath"]

name: skin bony tubercle
description: A bony structure embedded in skin, roughly equivalent to osteoderms.

name: dorsal cloacal gland
description: Cloacal gland in female salamanders that secrete into the dorsal walls of the cloaca, anterior and / or posterior to the spermathecae or near the spermathecal common tube

name: hemipenis keratinized epithelium
description: A keratinized stratified squamous epithelium that is part of a hemipenis.

name: incisive process of premaxilla
description: A small protuberence on the lingual surface of the premaxilla, immediately posterior to the teeth.

name: placentome of cotyledonary placenta
description: An anatomical group consisting of a placental caruncle and a placental cotyldeon, a placental unit in some mammals such as ruminants.

name: placental caruncle
description: An oval or round thickening in the uterine mucosa resulting from proliferation of subepithelial connective tissue, in the maternal side of the placentome.

name: intertarsal sesamoid
description: A sesamoid element that is part of a tarsal skeleton.

name: upper primary premolar tooth
synonyms: ["maxillary primary premolar tooth","upper deciduous premolar tooth"]

name: lower primary premolar tooth
synonyms: ["lower deciduous premolar tooth","mandibular primary premolar tooth"]

name: cingulum of tooth
description: The portion of the teeth, occurring on the lingual or palatal aspects, that forms a convex protuberance at the cervical third of the anatomic crown. It represents the lingual or palatal developmental lobe of these teeth.

name: cingulum of upper incisor tooth
synonyms: ["cingulum of maxillary incisor tooth","upper incisor tooth cingulum"]

name: cingulum of lower incisor tooth
synonyms: ["cingulum of mandibular incisor tooth","lower incisor tooth cingulum"]

name: cingulum of upper canine tooth
synonyms: ["cingulum of maxillary canine tooth","upper canine tooth cingulum"]

name: cingulum of lower canine tooth
synonyms: ["cingulum of mandibular canine tooth","lower canine tooth cingulum"]

name: cingulum of lower jaw molar
description: A ridge that girdles the base of a lower molar tooth

name: cingulum of upper jaw molar
description: A ridge that girdles the base of a upper molar tooth

name: vomerine dentition
description: A set of teeth in which each tooth that attaches to a vomer.

name: afferent spiracular artery
description: A section of a pharyngeal arch artery that carries blood away from the spiracle.

name: efferent spiracular artery
description: A section of a pharyngeal arch artery that drains the spiracle.

name: extensor pollicis brevis muscle
description: The Extensor pollicis brevis lies on the medial side of, and is closely connected with, the Abductor pollicis longus.

name: spine appendage of head
description: A spine appendage that is part of a head.

name: cephalic spine
description: One of the spines, probably denticle derivatives, occurring singly or in pairs just behind the orbit on the cheek area in some fossil sharks. May have occurred only in males and may have served to hold the female during copulation, e.g. in the Jurassic genera Hybodus, Asteracanthus and Acrodus.

name: prepelvic clasper
description: A supplemental clasper in Holocephali, in front of the pelvic fin

name: pseudoclasper
description: one or more pairs of stiff ossified lobes or prongs found in the tip of the intromittent organ of Bythitoidei

name: pterygopodial gland
description: A gland of uncertain function at the base of the clasper in skates and rays, occupying the position of the siphon of other Elasmobranchii.

name: transverse folds of rectum
description: Houston's valves (or transverse folds of rectum) are semi-lunar transverse folds of the rectal wall that protrude into the anal canal. Their use seems to be to support the weight of fecal matter, and prevent its urging toward the anus, which would produce a strong urge to defecate. Although the term rectum means straight, these transverse folds overlap each other during the empty state of the intestine to such an extent that, as Houston remarked, they require considerable maneuvering to conduct an instrument along the canal, as often occurs in sigmoidoscopy and colonoscopy. These folds are about 12 mm. in width and are composed of the circular muscle coat of the rectum. They are usually three in number; sometimes a fourth is found, and occasionally only two are present. One is situated near the commencement of the rectum, on the right side. A second extends inward from the left side of the tube, opposite the middle of the sacrum. A third, the largest and most constant, projects backward from the forepart of the rectum, opposite the fundus of the urinary bladder. When a fourth is present, it is situated nearly 2.5 cm above the anus on the left and posterior wall of the tube.
synonyms: ["Houston's valve (middle of three)","Kohlrausch's fold (middle of three)","plicae transversae recti","set of transverse folds of rectum","transverse folds of rectum"]

name: rectal valve
description: A thin diaphragm located in the posterior fifth of the intestine of some Centrolophidae, e.g. Seriolella punctata, Schedophilus huttoni and Psenes pellucidus, or in others a sphincter-like constriction, e.g. Seriolella brama. A deep purple fluid was confined to the valve in S. punctata, but was found throughout the intestine in the other two species referred to. The fluid might be used to void a coloured cloud to distract or deter a predator.

name: swim bladder gas gland
description: A structure with numerous blood vessels (retia mirabilia) in the gas bladder that secretes gases from the blood.

name: mormyromast organ
description: An innervated group of cells in a round capsule at the end of a jelly-filled tube opening to the skin surface of Gymnarchidae and Mormyridae.

name: pineal corpora arenacea
description: A calcified structure of brain that is part of a pineal body.

name: choroid plexus corpora arenacea
description: A calcified structure of brain that is part of a choroid plexus.

name: xenarthrale
description: A supplementary intervertebral articulation found in xenarthrans characterized by two sets of zygapophyseal facets in the postdiaphragmatic vertebrae, one medial and one lateral to the met apophysis

name: marginal venous sinus
description: A paired dural venous sinus at the rim of the foramen magnum.

name: primitive marginal sinus
description: The primitive marginal sinuses (PMS) are embryonic sinuses forming the later superior sagittal sinus.

name: sinus of von Szily
description: A circular gap in the iris near the pupil between the layers of the optic cup (von Szily, 1902)
synonyms: ["marginal sinus (v. Szily)","marginal sinus of von Szily"]

name: meningeal branch of spinal nerve
description: Branch of spinal nerve that innervates the structures of the vertebral column.
synonyms: ["ramus meningeus nervorum spinales","recurrent meningeal branch of spinal nerve","sinuvertebral branch of spinal nerve"]

name: communicating branch of spinal nerve
description: Rami communicans (plural rami communicantes) is the term used for a nerve which connects two other nerves. When used without further definition, it almost always refers to a communicating branch between a spinal nerve and the sympathetic trunk. More specifically, it usually refers to one of the following: Gray ramus communicans White ramus communicans

name: external thoracic vein
description: extension of the long thoracic vein that collects blood from the mammary glands

name: internal mammary vein
description: One of two veins running parallel to their corresponding internal mammary arteries that unite forming one vessel. These veins drain the chest wall into the innominate vein.

name: prevertebral muscle of neck
description: A prevertebral muscle that is part of a neck.

name: ventral body wall
description: The ventral part of the body wall

name: dorsal body wall
description: The dorsal part of the body wall

name: developing mesenchymal structure
description: A mesenchyme-derived anatomical entity undergoing a transtion to become another structure.

name: salivary gland primordium
description: A primordium that has the potential to develop into a saliva-secreting gland.

name: intermaxillary gland (sensu Osteolepiformes)
description: A gland lodged in a fossa formed mainly of dermal bones, situated wholly in front of the nasal capsules of Osteolepiformes.

name: intermaxillary salivary gland
description: A gland located at the pre-nasal area being divided anteriorly by the ascendent processes of the intermaxillary bone.

name: buccal gland
description: Any of the small racemose mucous glands in the mucous membrane lining the cheeks

name: bony part of cervical vertebral arch
description: A bony part of vertebral arch that is part of a cervical vertebral arch.
synonyms: ["bony part of arch of cervical vertebra"]

name: bony part of vertebral arch of first sacral vertebra
description: A bony part of vertebral arch that is part of a sacral vertebra 1.
synonyms: ["bony part of vertebral arch of first sacral segment"]

name: abdominal viscera
description: A viscus that is part of a abdomen.
synonyms: ["abdominal viscera","abdominal viscera set","set of abdominal viscera"]

name: internal surface of cranial base
description: internal (endosteal) surface of the base of skull

name: thenar eminence
description: A raised fleshy area on the palm of the hand near the base of the thumb.

name: hypothenar eminence
description: Hypothenar refers to a group of three muscles of the palm that control the motion of the little finger. The three muscles are: Abductor digiti minimi Flexor digiti minimi Opponens digiti minimi

name: raphe of scrotum
description: A ridge of tissue that extends along the midline of the scrotum.

name: lower primary incisor tooth
description: A primary incisor tooth that is part of a lower jaw region.
synonyms: ["lower deciduous incisor tooth","primary lower incisor tooth"]

name: withers
description: The ridge between the shoulder blades of a four-legged mammal.

name: proximal mesopodial endochondral element
description: A mesopodial endochondral element that is in the most proximal part of the mesopodial skeleton, connected to the zeugopodial skeleton.

name: proximal mesopodial cartilage element
description: A proximal mesopodial endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: distal mesopodial endochondral element
description: An endochondral element in the distal portion of the mesopodial skeleton, between the central mesopodial skeleton and the metapodial skeleton

name: distal mesopodial cartilage element
description: A distal mesopodial endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

name: distal mesopodial pre-cartilage condensation
description: A distal mesopodial endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.

name: distal mesopodial bone
description: A distal mesopodial endochondral element that is composed primarily of a bone tissue.

name: posterior fascicle of palatopharyngeus
description: The thinner portion of the muscle of the palatopharyngeal arch, originating in the region of the midline where its fibers interdigitate with the contralateral partner, then passing posterior to the levator veli palatini muscle to join the longitudinal layer of pharyngeal musculature; acts as a sort of sphincter, reducing the caliber of the isthmus of fauces at the palatopharyngeal arch.
synonyms: ["fasciculus posterior (musculus palatopharyngeus)","fasciculus posterior musculus palatopharyngei","musculus sphincter palatopharyngeus","palatopharyngeal sphincter","velopharyngeal sphincter"]

name: parafoveal part of retina
description: The intermediate belt surrounding the fovea centralis

name: perifoveal part of retina
description: The outermost region surrounding the fovea centralis

name: foveola of retina
description: A region of the fovea centralis that lies in the center of the fovea and contains only cone cells, and a cone-shaped zone of Müller cells

name: superior auricular muscle
description: The superior auricular muscle, the largest of the three auriculares muscles, is also thin and fan-shaped. Its fibers arise from the galea aponeurotica, and converge to be inserted by a thin, flattened tendon into the upper part of the cranial surface of the auricula.

name: anterior auricular muscle
description: The anterior auricular muscle, the smallest of the three auriculares muscles, is thin and fan-shaped, and its fibers are pale and indistinct. It arises from the lateral edge of the galea aponeurotica, and its fibers converge to be inserted into a projection on the front of the helix.

name: posterior auricular muscle
description: The posterior auricular muscle consists of two or three fleshy fasciculi, which arise from the mastoid portion of the temporal bone by short aponeurotic fibers. They are inserted into the lower part of the cranial surface of the concha.

name: muscle layer of rectum
description: A muscle layer that is part of the rectum
synonyms: ["muscular coat of rectum","muscularis externa of rectum","rectal muscularis propria","tunica muscularis (rectum)","tunica muscularis recti"]

name: rectum smooth muscle tissue
description: Any portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of the rectum
synonyms: ["rectal smooth muscle tissue","rectum smooth muscle","smooth muscle of rectum"]

name: left kidney interstitium
description: A kidney interstitium that is part of a left kidney.

name: right kidney interstitium
description: A kidney interstitium that is part of a right kidney.

name: left renal pelvis
description: A renal pelvis that is part of a left ureter.
synonyms: ["pelvis of left ureter","renal pelvis of left kidney"]

name: right renal pelvis
description: A renal pelvis that is part of a right ureter.
synonyms: ["pelvis of right kidney","pelvis of right ureter"]

name: left renal cortex interstitium
description: A renal cortex interstitium that is part of a left kidney.

name: right renal cortex interstitium
description: A renal cortex interstitium that is part of a right kidney.

name: left renal medulla interstitium
description: A renal medulla interstitium that is part of a left kidney.

name: right renal medulla interstitium
description: A renal medulla interstitium that is part of a right kidney.

name: periovarian fat pad
description: The encapsulated adipose tissue associated with the ovaries.

name: tail fat pad
description: Encapsulated adipose tissue that is part of a tail.

name: monotreme bill
description: An elongated snout found in monotremes.

name: rugal fold of scrotum
description: A folded ridge of skin that is part of a scrotum superficial to the dartos muscle
synonyms: ["folded ridge of skin of scrotum","scrotal rugae"]

name: maxillary fenestra
description: A fenestra or hole which pierces the maxilla anterior to the antorbital fenestra.

name: premaxillary fenestra
description: A fenestra that is part of a premaxilla.

name: mammary lobe
description: A cluster of mammary gland lobules. In humans this is a distinct lobe and located in the breast region.

name: anterior perforated substance
description: Regional part of telencephalon lying on the basal surface and bounded by the olfactory trigone rostrally, the diagonal band medially and caudally and the prepiriform cortex laterally. It is characterized by many perforations caused by small blood vessels entering the gray matter (Meyer et al., J. Comp. Neurol 284: 405, 1989).
synonyms: ["anterior perforated area","anterior perforated space","olfactory area (mai)","substantia perforata anterior"]

name: caudal vertebra endochondral element
description: Any vertebra endochondral element that is part of the caudal region of the vertebral column (tail or coccyx).

name: transverse process of cervical vertebra
description: A transverse process that is part of a cervical vertebra

name: cervical rib
description: A rib that is attached to a cervical vertebra.

name: lumbar rib
description: A rib that is attached to a lumbar vertebra.

name: transverse process of lumbar vertebra
description: A transverse process that is part of a lumbar vertebra

name: ampullary gland secretion
description: A bodily secretion that produced_by a ampullary gland.

name: skin of lower lip
description: A zone of skin that is part of a lower lip.

name: skin of upper lip
description: A zone of skin that is part of a upper lip.

name: pars flaccida of tympanic membrane
description: A small, triangular, flaccid portion of the tympanic membrane, or eardrum, lying above the malleolar folds, attached directly to the petrous bone at the notch of Rivinus.
synonyms: ["pars flaccida (membrana tympanica)","pars flaccida membranae tympanicae","Shrapnell's membrane"]

name: ligament of middle ear
description: A ligament that is part of a middle ear.

name: posterior incudal ligament
description: A fold of mucous membrane that runs from the fossa incudus to the incus.

name: malleal ligament
description: A skeletal ligament that attaches to the malleus.

name: lateral malleal ligament
description: A malleal ligament that extends from the bony margin of the notch of Rivinus to the neck of the malleus.

name: superior malleal ligament
description: A malleal ligament that extends from the tempen tympani to the head of the malleus.

name: anterior malleal ligament
description: A malleal ligament that extends from the anterior tympanic wall to the anterior process of the malleus.

name: annular ligament of stapes
description: A ring of fibrous tissue that connects the base of the stapes to the oval window of the inner ear.
synonyms: ["annular ligament","annular ligament of base of stapes","annular stapedial ligament","ligamentum anulare stapedis"]

name: pulmonary part of lymphatic system
description: An organ system subdivision that is the part of the lymphoid system that includes the pulmonary lymphatic vessels.

name: pulmonary lymphatic vessel
description: A lymphatic vessel that is part of a lung.

name: renin-angiotensin system
description: A system consisting of renin, angiotensin-converting enzyme, and angiotensin II. Renin, an enzyme produced in the kidney, acts on angiotensinogen, an alpha-2 globulin produced by the liver, forming angiotensin I. The converting enzyme contained in the lung acts on angiotensin I in the plasma converting it to angiotensin II, the most powerful directly pressor substance known. It causes contraction of the arteriolar smooth muscle and has other indirect actions mediated through the adrenal cortex.

name: femoral canal
description: The compartment of the femoral sheath that contains efferent lymphatic vessels and a lymph node embedded in a small amount of areolar tissue. It is conical in shape and is about 2 cm long. The femoral canal is bordered: Anteriorly by the inguinal ligament Posteriorly by the pectineal ligament Medially by the lacunar ligament Laterally by the femoral vein It contains the lymph nodes of Cloquet or Rosenmuller. It should not be confused with the nearby adductor canal.

name: labyrinthine artery
description: A long slender branch of the anterior inferior cerebellar artery (85%-100% cases) or basilar artery (<15% cases), arises from near the middle of the artery; it accompanies the vestibulocochlear nerve through the internal acoustic meatus, and is distributed to the internal ear.
synonyms: ["arteria auditiva interna","arteria labyrinthi","artery of inner ear","internal auditory artery"]

name: axillary sweat gland
description: A sweat gland that is part of a axilla.
synonyms: ["axillary apocrine sweat gland","sweat gland of axilla"]

name: gland of Zeis
description: Glands of Zeis are unilobar sebaceous glands located on the margin of the eyelid. The glands of Zeis service the eyelash. These glands produce an oily substance that is issued through the excretory ducts of the sebaceous lobule into the middle portion of the hair follicle.
synonyms: ["ciliary sebaceous gland of eyelid","gland of Zeis","gland of Zeiss","Zeis gland"]

name: stroma of pancreas
description: A stroma that is part of a pancreas.

name: capsule of pancreas
description: A capsule that divides the parenchyma of the pancreas into lobes and lobules

name: nucleus of Bischoff
description: A midline nucleus of the dorsal motor column found in animals with a prominent tail, including alligator, some birds, kangaroo, rat, shrew, great anteater.

name: dorsal column-medial lemniscus pathway
description: A sensory tract originating in the spinal cord responsible for transmitting fine touch, vibration and conscious proprioceptive information from the body to the cerebral cortex. The components include the fasciculus gracilis and fasciculus cuneatus.

name: dorsal column nucleus
description: A nucleus that contain secondary neurons of the dorsal column-medial lemniscus pathway, which carries fine touch and proprioceptive information from the body to the brain. Examples: gracile nucleus, cuneat nucleus, nucleus of Bishoff.

name: rhombomere boundary
description: A boundary delimiting a rhombomere.

name: panniculus carnosus muscle
description: The skeletal muscle layer in the superficial fascia deep to the panniculus adiposus

name: prime adult stage
description: A life cycle stage that starts at completion of development and growth of the sexually mature adult animal, and ends before senescence.

name: palatine bone horizontal plate
description: The part of the palatine bone that forms the posterior part (approximately one third) of the bony palate.(Stedmans)
synonyms: ["horizontal plate of palatine bone","lamina horizontalis","lamina horizontalis (os palatinum)","lamina horizontalis ossis palatini"]

name: thymic artery
description: A vein that supplies blood to the thymus.

name: superficial cervical thymus
description: A cervical thymus that is located directly beneath the skin.

name: deep cervical thymus
description: A cervical thymus that is located deep in the ventral cervical region, superficial to hyoid, sternomastoid, and depressor neck muscles.

name: thyroid vein
description: A vein that drains a thyroid gland.

name: cervical thymic artery
description: An artery that supplies a cervical thymus.

name: meningeal vein
description: One of the veins draining a meninix.

name: internal pudendal vein
description: Accompanying vein of internal pudendal artery.

name: external pudendal vein
description: One of the veins of the pelvis which drain into the great saphenous vein.

name: jejunal artery
description: A branch of the superior mesenteric artery that supplies the jejunum.

name: lacrimal vein
description: A vein that drains a lacrimal gland.

name: submucosa of digestive tract
description: Any portion of submucosa that lines the digestive tract.

name: layer of muscle tissue
description: Any organ component layer that consists of muscle tissue.

name: muscular coat of digestive tract
description: A muscular coat that is part of a digestive tract.

name: dorsal zone of medial entorhinal cortex
ventral zone of medial entorhinal cortex
dorsal lateral ganglionic eminence
description: The dorsal region of the lateral ganglionic eminence. The cells in this area give rise to embryonic interneuron precursors that will migrate tangentially to the olfactory bulb.

name: anterior root of zygomatic arch
description: The anterior or rostral end of the zygomatic arch, which includes the temporal process of the zygomatic bone, but also including some of the body of the zygomatic bone. It may also include the zygomatico-temporal suture and the most rostral portion of the zygomatic process of the temporal bone.

name: third phalanx
description: The third phalangeal bone in a digit ray.

name: atlantal spinal nerve foramen
description: Foramen housing the root of the spinal nerve seen in the neural arch of the first vertebrae (atlas). (see Edwards 1976)

name: type 1 adrenal tissue
description: Adrenal tissue dispersed in clusters, found in periphery and center of adrenal gland in turtles (Yadav, 2008).

name: type 2 adrenal tissue
description: Adrenal tissue aggregated in a dorsal layer covering internal cords, found in lepidosaur adrenal glands. Islets of adrenal tissue found on ventral surface of gland (barely present in squamates). See Yadav, 2008.

name: type 3 adrenal tissue
description: Adrenal tissue found in archosaurs - tissue arranged in bands, alternating with interrenal cords (Yadav, 2008)

name: type 4 adrenal tissue
description: In mammals, adrenal tissue has a cortex and medulla creating a composite adrenal gland (Kardong 2012)

name: apex of paracone
description: The highest elevation of the paracone on a molariform tooth.

name: caniniform region
description: The anterior region of the maxillary tooth row, if that tooth row contains teeth that are substantially over the premaxillary teeth (see Laurin and Reisz 1995)

name: postcingulum of deciduous premolar 5
description: A postcingulum found on deciduous premolar 5

name: posthypocrista of deciduous premolar 5
description: A posthypocrista found on deciduous premolar 5

name: egg tooth
description: A protuberence or true tooth that is used during hatching to break the eggshell.

name: calcareous egg tooth
description: Tooth used to break the eggshell, that is shed soon after hatching. In lepidosaurs, a true tooth that is shed soon after hatching.

name: epidermal egg tooth
description: Epidermal outgrowth that facilitates breaking of the eggshell in archosaurs and monotremes.

name: hypoconid
description: The labial most of three cusps on the talonoid (posterior) end of lower molariform teeth. (modified from http://animaldiversity.ummz.umich.edu/collections/mammal_anatomy/cheek_teeth_structure/)

name: lower deciduous premolar 5
description: Fifth premolar (counting anteroposteriorly ) in the lower jaw.

name: lower molar 3
description: Third molar (counting anteroposteriorly) in the lower jaw.

name: lower pharyngobranchial toothplate
description: Pharyngeal toothplate of the lower jaw region; typically associated with ceratobranchial 5 element.

name: lower premolar 1
description: First premolar (counting anteroposteriorly ) in the lower jaw.

name: lower premolar 2
description: Second premolar (counting anteroposteriorly ) in the lower jaw.

name: molar 1 posteroloph
description: Posteroloph found on the first molar tooth.

name: premolar 1 hypoconoid
description: Hypoconid found on the first premolar tooth.

name: paracone
description: The anterior cusp along the labial margin seen in the molar or premolar teeth of mammals. (modified from http://animaldiversity.ummz.umich.edu/collections/mammal_anatomy/cheek_teeth_structure/)

name: paracristid
description: A crest running along the labial margin of molarifomr teeth of mammals. (modified from http://animaldiversity.ummz.umich.edu/collections/mammal_anatomy/cheek_teeth_structure/)

name: postcingulum
description: A shelf like ridge on the posterior (distal) outside edge of the upper molariform teeth. (modified from http://animaldiversity.ummz.umich.edu/collections/mammal_anatomy/cheek_teeth_structure/)

name: posteroloph
description: A shelf like ridge on the outside of the upper molariform teeth. (modified from http://animaldiversity.ummz.umich.edu/collections/mammal_anatomy/cheek_teeth_structure/)

name: posthypocrista
description: A crest on the hypoconid of molariform teeth. (modified from http://animaldiversity.ummz.umich.edu/collections/mammal_anatomy/cheek_teeth_structure/)

name: precingulum
description: A shelf like ridge on the proximal (mesial) outside edge of the upper molariform teeth. (modified from http://animaldiversity.ummz.umich.edu/collections/mammal_anatomy/cheek_teeth_structure/)

name: premolar 1
description: First premolar (counting anteroposteriorly) in the jaw.

name: preprotocrista
description: An enamel ridge joining the protocone and the paracone on the occlusal surface of a maxillary molar.

name: replacement tooth
description: Tooth (often obscured from view) in a 'waiting' position that will replace an existing tooth (i.e. a tooth that is well visible in the jaw)

name: resorption pit
description: A pit formed in an existing functional tooth, causing resorption of the surrounding dentine and periodontal tissues. (modified from LeBlanc and Reisz 2013, see figures 8, 10 for more details)

name: stylocone
description: Cusp found on a platform that is buccaal and mesial to the meta and paracones. Modified from Kermack 1967. Molar evolution in Mesozoic mammals

name: mandibular symphyseal tooth
description: Tooth of the lower jaw that is adjacent to the mandibular symphysis

name: upper canine 1
description: first canine (counting anteroposteriorly) in the upper jaw.

name: upper deciduous premolar 5
description: Fifth premolar (counting anteroposteriorly ) in the upper jaw.

name: upper molar 1
description: first molar (counting anteroposteriorly) in the upper jaw.

name: adrenal tissue
description: Tissue that is part of some adrenal gland

name: post-axial region of pectoral appendage
description: Anatomical region lying to the posteiror or ventral side of the metapterygial axis.

name: bicipital surface
description: region of the humerus associated with the biceps attachment areas

name: bulge
description: expanded and swollen region of a surface that is otherwise relatively flat

name: keel
description: Ridge shaped projection, similar to the keel of a boat

name: caudal melanophore spot
description: distinct colored area on the caudal region of an organism, similar in shape to a spot, i.e. circular.

name: central figure of scute
description: Anatomical structure consisting of a pattern of ridges on an osteoderm.

name: cephalic dermal scale
description: A dermal scale that is found in the head region

name: obsolete cervical rib
description: Rib attached to the cervical vertebrae.

name: cheek scale
description: A scale part of the cheek scale row.

name: cheek scale row
description: A row of scales foudn in the cheek region of the head of an organism.

name: choanal groove
description: grooves on the palatine bone which denote the passage of the choana or internal naris

name: clasper plate
description: Pelvic clasper organs that have been modified into a flattened structure

name: cuboid facet of calcaneum
description: Facet on the anterior surface of the calcaneus (as called calcaneum) for the articulation of the cuboid bone

name: dorsal osteoderm
description: Osteoderm found on the dorsal surface of an organisms.

name: entocarotid fossa
description: A depression on the lateral surface of the braincase posterior to the Vidian canal (Conrad 2008)

name: extramural oviduct
description: Section of the oviduct external to the uterine wall.

name: flexor sesamoid
description: A sesamoid bone located near or in the flexor musculature of a joint.

name: foramen for glossopharyngeal nerve
description: Foramen that allows the passge of the glossopharyngeal nerve (cranial nerve IX).

name: fourth phalanx
description: fourth most proximal phalanx in manual or pedal digits.

name: hyoid articular area
description: Area on the otic capsule for the articulation of the hyoid

name: hypochordal radial
description: Caudal fin radial element located ventral to the notochord

name: caudal fin radial element
description: Radial element that is part of the caudal fin.

name: ilioischiadic foramen
description: Situated just caudal to the acetabulum, the foramen is bound dorsally by the illium and ventrally by the ischium. The foramen transmitts the ischiadic nerves and vessels (Baumel et al. 1993)

name: incisura fossa
description: The condyloid fossa on the cranial aspect of the Atlas my be perforated (foramen fossa) or have an open dorsal notch (Incisura fossa) in which the apex of the dens rides. (From Baumel et al. 1993)

name: interpterygoid region
description: The region on the palate corresponding to the location of the pterygoid bone, if present and between the palatine bones and the parasphenoid if not.

name: interpterygoid vacuity
description: Open space between on the palate between the pteryogoid bone and the parasphenoid

name: intraramal joint
description: A joint in the lower jaw that enhances kinesis and for swallowing prey. Allows enhanced mobility and intraramal bending to increase gape.

name: jugal bar
description: elongate bar consisting of fused quadratojugal and jugal and connecting the maxilla to the quadrate

name: labial cartilage
description: Distinct cartilage around the jaws of elasmobranchs

name: lateral condyle of quadrate
description: Condyle on the lateral side of the quadrate

name: lateral dorsal aorta canal
description: One of the branches of the dorsal aorta, after it enters the aortic canal

name: maxillary shank
description: The triangular shaped posterior fold at the angle of the mouth. From Chakrabarty 2006

name: medial condyle of quadrate
description: The medialmost condyle on the distal region of the quadrate, in contact with the pterygoid.

name: medial cotyla
description: The medialmost of the cotyla of the lower jaw, for articulation with the cranium.

name: metotic fissure
description: An embryonic fissure between the otic capsule and the arches which develop into the occipital bones. The fissure may persist into adulthood. It is also referred to as the 'lateral otic fissure' The metotic fissure opens into the vestibular fontanelle, if the fontanelle is present. (Johanson et al. (2003)). Otherwise it opens to the metotic foramen.

name: midbody melanophore spot
description: distinct colored area on the midbody region of an organism, similar in shape to a spot, i.e. circular.

name: nasal process of premaxilla
description: A bony projection of the premaxilla that extends cadually and separates the nasal bones.

name: nuchal hump
description: Dorsal swelling on the head. Found in cichlid fish. Often only in males and during breeding season, but not exclusively so.

name: oviduct mucosal fold
description: The wall of the fallopian tube includes an elaborately folded mucosa (endosalpinx) surrounded by a muscularis (myosalpinx). The mucosa is lined by a ciliated columnar epithelium with secretory cells, and is folded out into the lumen so that an ovum in the lumen will always be close to the cilia for transport to the uterus.

name: parastyle
description: An anterior cusp on the stylar shelf of the tooth

name: stylar shelf
description: The stylar shelf is an an expansion of the cingulum; it often bears small cusps (each with its own name...).

name: parietal notch
description: A pronounced notch or cavity in the lateral face of the parietal.

name: pharyngeal apophysis
description: Ventral process on the neurocranium for the articulation of upper pharyngeal bones. It is variably composed of the parasphenoid, basioccipital, and prootic depending on the species. From: Greenwood, PH (1978). A review of the pharyngeal hypophysis and its significance in the classification of African cichlid fishes. Bull. Br. Mus. Nat. Hist. (Zool.) 33: 297-323.

name: precerebral fontanelle
description: The lack of chondrification of the anterior wall of the cranial cavity in front of the pineal foramen.....(Hanken and Hall)

name: prismatic cartilage
description: cartilage arranged into tesserae, blocks of calcified cartilage that fit together as tiles on a floor form a mosaic. Found only in chondrichthyans. Reference: A. Peter Klimley. 2013. The Biology of Sharks and Rays. University of Chicago Press.

name: quadrate condyle
description: The convex articular surface on the qudrate, part of the craniomandibular joint.

name: recessus vena jugularis
description: As defined here, this refers to a depression on the lateral surface of the braincase posterior to the Vidian canal as opposed to the carotid fossa...(Conrad 2008)

name: rictal bristle
description: Rictal bristles project from the beak of many insect-eating birds, including flycatchers, nightjars and even the American Robin. They are believed to provide protection for the bird's eyes as it consumes its wriggly prey. The bristles may also provide tactile feedback, like the whiskers on a dog or cat. from http://www.birds.cornell.edu/AllAboutBirds/studying/feathers/feathers/document_view

name: rostral entotympanic element
description: An entotympanic that arises in forward part of tympanic floor. It may be intimately fused witA cartilage of tube during development(MacPhee (1981: 62)) in contrast to a caudal entotympanic arising in the rear tympanic floor. From O'Leary et al. 2012

name: spina externa
description: A median bony point projecting from the anterior and ventral margin of the sternum of a bird. From http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/spina%20externa

name: subolfactory process
description: The ventral portion of the frontals which forms part of the lateral wall of the braincase. Modified from Lee and Caldwell 1998

name: suborbital foramen
description: Foramen located below the orbit and forming a passageway for nerves (eg fifth cranial nerve)

name: suborbital shelf
description: On the neurocranium, a horizontal plate arising on the ventral junction of the orbital wall and basal plate on each side which extends from the nasal capsule to the otic capsule; it forms the floor of the orbit.

name: supracondylar tubercle
description: Anatomical projection on the distal region of the femur or humerus and close to the condyles.

name: obsolete supracoracoid nerve foramen
description: Opening for the supracoracoid nerve in the supracoracoid.

name: suprameatal foramen
description: Foramen in the temporal bone, adjacent to the base of the zygomatic process.

name: supratemporal process
description: Process of the parietal

name: supratendinal bridge
description: ossified bridge over a tendon; Particularly, the bridge over the extensor canal at the distal end of the tibiotarsus of certain birds. The presence of the bridge and the position of the canal opening relative to the condyles may have phylogenetic significance. Ericson (1997). http://palaeos.com/vertebrates/glossary/glossarySq.html

name: processus ventralis of thoracic vertebra
description: The crest is present on the ventral side of the bodies of the thoracic vertebra (modified from Baumel et al. 1993)
synonyms: ["hypapophysis, crista ventralis corporis, crista ventralis, processus latus","processus ventralis"]

name: processus ventrolateralis of thoracic vertebra
description: Ventrolaerally oriented, paired projections atttached to the ventrolateral border of the body of certain thoracic vertebra; the ventrolateral crest flank the crista ventralis on each side. From Baumel et al. 1993

name: upper lateral line
description: dorsal sensory canal line in fish, dorsal to ventral lateral lane

name: ventral lateral line
description: ventral sensory canal line in fish, ventral to dorsal lateral lane

name: ventral supracondylar tubercle
description: tubercle on the distal humerus for the origin of the Lig. collaterale ventral of the elbow joint. Modified from Baumel et al. 1993

name: dorsal supracondylar tubercle
description: tubercle on the dorsal border of the distal humerus, a short distance from the dorsal epicondyle, for the origin of the m extensor carpe radialis modifeid from Baumel et al. 1993

name: vidian canal
description: canal for the vidian nerve

name: sallet
description: A unit of the tectoral membrane that is shaped like string of flat, pearls. Modified from Manley, Fey and Popper 2008

name: molar tooth 1
description: The molar tooth of the upper or lower jaw that is phylogenetically number 1

name: molar tooth 3
description: The molar tooth of the upper or lower jaw that is phylogenetically number 3

name: crustacean larval stage
description: The larval stage of a crustacean, the stages of which are separated my moults. Typically this goes through a nauplius - zoea - post-larval cycle.

name: metacestode
description: The larval (metacestode) stage of the tapeworm Echinococcus multilocularis.

name: second instar larva
description: Instar: a stage in the life of an arthropod (as an insect) between two successive molts.

name: metacercaria
description: A tailless encysted late larva of a trematode parasite that is usually the form which is infective for the definitive host.

name: cestode
description: Any of a class (Cestoda) of bilaterally symmetrical flatworms parasitic especially in the intestines of vertebrates.

name: cercaria
description: A usually tadpole-shaped larval trematode worm that develops in a molluscan host from a redia.

name: interoceptor
description: A sensory receptor that detects stimulus within the body. Examples of stimuli that would be detected by interoceptors include blood pressure and blood oxygen level.

name: chemoreceptor
description: A sensory receptor that detects chemical stimulus within the body.

name: arterial baroreceptor
description: Arterial baroreceptors are stretch receptors that are stimulated by distortion of the arterial wall when pressure changes.

name: low-pressure baroreceptor
description: found in large systemic veins, in pulmonary vessels, and in the walls of the right atrium and ventricles of the heart (the atrial volume receptors).

name: vein baroreceptor
description: A baroreceptor that located_in a vein.

name: cardiac baroreceptor
description: A baroreceptor that located_in a heart.

name: pulmonary baroreceptor
description: A baroreceptor that located_in a pulmonary vascular system.

name: posterior superior alveolar artery
