description: Innermost layer of dorsolateral prefrontal cortex lying deep to the internal pyramidal cell layer 5. It is cytoarchitectonically defined in the DLPFC by cells of varying sizes. DLPFC layer 6a is characterized by more neurons and layer 6b has comparatively more glia.

name: entire surface of organism
description: Anatomical surface, which is the external surface of the whole body. Examples: There is only one body surface.

name: infraclavicular lymph node
description: A lymph node located in the area below the clavicle.
synonyms: ["deltopectoral lymph node","deltopectoral node","infraclavicular node","nodus lymphaticus infraclavicularis axillae"]

name: posterior surface of prostate
description: The flattened aspect of the prostate with a slight furrow facing the rectum and anus.
synonyms: ["facies posterior (prostatae)","facies posterior prostatae","posterior surface of prostate gland"]

name: infraclavicular region
description: The region below the clavicle.

name: right ear
description: The organ of hearing located on the right side of the head.

name: abdominal part of esophagus
description: Clinical esophageal segment composed of smooth muscle. It corresponds to the inferior part of the lower third topographic segment of the esophagus.
synonyms: ["abdominal esophagus","abdominal part of oesophagus","pars abdominalis (oesophagus)","pars abdominalis oesophageae","T11 part of esophagus"]

name: sigmoid artery
description: The sigmoid arteries, two or three in number, run obliquely downward and to the left behind the peritoneum and in front of the Psoas major, ureter, and internal spermatic vessels. Their branches supply the lower part of the descending colon, the iliac colon, and the sigmoid or pelvic colon; anastomosing above with the left colic, and below with the superior hemorrhoidal artery.

name: calcarine artery
description: An artery that branches from the medial occipital artery that aligns with the calcarine sulcus.
synonyms: ["calcarine branch of medial occipital artery","ramus calcarinus (arteria occipitalis medialis)"]

name: plantar metatarsal artery
description: The plantar metatarsal arteries (digital branches) are four in number, and run forward between the metatarsal bones and in contact with the Interossei. Each divides into a pair of plantar digital arteries which supply the adjacent sides of the toes. Near their points of division each sends upward an anterior perforating branch to join the corresponding dorsal metatarsal artery. The first plantar metatarsal artery (arteria princeps hallucis) springs from the junction between the lateral plantar and deep plantar arteries and sends a digital branch to the medial side of the first toe. The digital branch for the lateral side of the fifth toe arise from the lateral plantar artery near the base of the fifth metatarsal bone.

name: superficial lymphatic vessel
description: The tubules that carry lymph throughout the body that are just beneath the surface of the skin.

name: gastrocolic ligament
description: A major portion of the greater omentum between the stomach and the transverse colon.

name: occipital lymph node
description: A lymph node located in the back of the head adjacent to the trapezius muscle.

name: deep fibular nerve
description: A branch of the common peroneal nerve. It innervates the ankle and toes.

name: paracolic gutter
description: The paracolic gutters (paracolic sulci, paracolic recesses) are spaces between the colon and the abdominal wall. There are two paracolic gutters: The right lateral paracolic gutter. The left lateral paracolic gutter. These gutters are clinically important because they allow a passage for infectious fluids from different compartments of the abdomen. For example; fluid from an infected appendix can track up the right paracolic gutter to the hepatorenal recess.

name: basal zone of heart
description: The superior portion of the heart located opposite to the apical portion. It is formed mainly by the left atrium.
synonyms: ["anatomical base of heart","base of heart","basis cordis"]

name: thoracic part of esophagus
description: Zone of esophagus located in the thorax.
synonyms: ["pars thoracica (oesophagus)","pars thoracica oesophageae","thoracic esophagus","thoracic part of oesophagus"]

name: parasternal lymph node
description: Any of the lymph nodes of the breast located under the ribcage, near the sternum.

name: anterior temporal artery
description: A branch of the middle cerebral artery that supplies blood to the anterior part of the temporal lobe.

name: tonsillar fossa
description: Between the plica triangularis and the surface of the palatine tonsils is a space known as the tonsillar fossa (or tonsillar sinus); in many cases, however, this sinus is obliterated by its walls becoming adherent.

name: superficial middle cerebral vein
description: A vein that runs along the fissure of Sylvius to the cavernous sinus on the lateral surface of the brain and connects to the superior sagittal and transverse sinuses.

name: medial circumflex femoral vein
description: A circumflex femoral vein that accompanies the medial circumflex femoral artery.

name: branch of internal carotid artery
synonyms: ["internal carotid arterial subdivision","subdivision of internal carotid artery"]

name: anal sinus
description: Furrows, with pouchlike recesses at the lower end, separating the rectal columns.

name: posterior external jugular vein
description: A vein that drains the superficial muscles and integument of the upper back portion of the neck into the external jugular vein.

name: left subcostal vein
description: A vein that extends along the bottom of the twelfth rib on the left side of the body.

name: mons pubis
description: A structure composed of adipose tissue lying above the pubic bone of adult women, anterior to the symphysis pubis. The mons pubis forms the anterior portion of the vulva, and limits the perineal region proximally and anteriorly.

name: neck of gallbladder
description: The narrowest portion of the gallbladder and distal to the cystic duct.

name: roof of nasopharynx
synonyms: ["nasopharynx roof","pharyngeal fornix","roof of nasal part of pharynx","superior nasopharynx","superior wall of nasopharynx","vault of pharynx"]

name: superior thoracic artery
description: The superior thoracic artery (highest thoracic artery) is a small vessel normally arising from the first division of the axillary artery, but may arise from the thoracoacromial artery, itself a branch of the second division of the axillary artery. Running forward and medialward along the upper border of the pectoralis minor, the superior thoracic artery passes between it and the pectoralis major to the side of the chest. It supplies branches to the first and second intercostal spaces as well as to the superior portion of serratus anterior. It anastomoses with the internal mammary and intercostal arteries.

name: epigastrium
description: The upper central region of the abdomen between the costal margins and the subcostal plane.

name: supraclavicular lymph node
description: A lymph node which is located above the clavicle.

name: axillary tail of breast
description: An extension of the tissue of the breast which extends into the axilla.
synonyms: ["axillary process","axillary tail","axillary tail of Spence","processus axillaris (glandula mammaria)","tail of Spence"]

name: left ear
description: The organ of hearing located on the left side of the head.

name: tuberculum sellae
description: An elevated zone of the sella turcica behind the chiasmatic groove.

name: inferolateral surface of prostate
description: The aspect of the prostate facing the pelvic diaphragm and pubis.
synonyms: ["facies inferolaterales (prostatae)","facies inferolateralis prostatae","inferolateral surface of prostate gland"]

name: prostatic capsule
description: The membrane the surrounds the prostate gland.

name: anterior median fissure of spinal cord
description: A fissure in the midline of the anterior surface of the spinal cord.
synonyms: ["fissura mediana anterior medullae spinalis","ventral median fissure of spinal cord"]

name: right common iliac artery
synonyms: ["trunk of right common iliac arterial tree"]

name: upper outer quadrant of breast
description: The quarter of the breast which is superior and lateral.

name: base of prostate
description: The uppermost part of the prostate gland adjacent to the bladder wall.

name: sphenoparietal sinus
description: The cavernous sinus receives the superior ophthalmic vein through the superior orbital fissure, some of the cerebral veins, and also the small sphenoparietal sinus, which courses along the under surface of the small wing of the sphenoid.

name: posterior lobe of prostate
description: The prostate gland lobe that is located on the posterior side of the organ.
synonyms: ["posterior lobe of prostate gland","posterior peripheral zone"]

name: lower outer quadrant of breast
description: The quarter of the breast which is inferior and lateral.

name: anterior surface of kidney
description: The aspect of the kidney facing the abdominal cavity.

name: retroperitoneal lymph node
description: A lymph node located in the retroperitoneal space.

name: small cardiac vein
description: A vein running parallel to the right coronary artery in the coronary sulcus that drains into the right extremity of the coronary sinus.

name: transverse fold of rectum
description: One of the semi-lunar transverse folds of the rectal wall that protrude into the anal canal.

name: branch of anterior cerebral artery
description: An arterial branch arising from the anterior cerebral artery. It includes the callosomarginal artery, frontopolar artery, medial orbitofrontal artery, pericallosal artery, and recurrent artery of Heubner.

name: cystic vein
description: A blood vessel carrying deoxygenated blood from the gallbladder and the cystic duct into the right branch of the portal vein.

name: branch of external carotid artery
synonyms: ["external carotid arterial subdivision","subdivision of external carotid artery"]

name: hypophysial artery
description: An artery that supplies the pituitary gland.

name: superior hypophysial artery
description: The superior hypophysial artery is an artery supplying the pars tuberalis,the infundibulum of the pituitary gland and the median eminence. It is a branch of the posterior communicating artery which branches from the internal carotid artery in the circle of Willis..

name: left inguinal part of abdomen
synonyms: ["left iliac fossa viewed surgically","left iliac region","left inguinal region"]

name: diaphragma sellae
description: The diaphragma sellae or sellar diaphragm is the circular fold of dura mater that almost completely roofs the fossa hypophyseos in the sphenoid bone of the skull. It retains the pituitary gland in the fossa hypophyseos, with only the infundibulum of the pituitary gland passing through it.

name: anterior longitudinal ligament
description: A ligament running the length of the anterior surface of the spinal column and thereby interconnects all the vertebral bodies.

name: circumflex branch of left coronary artery
description: Branch of left coronary artery which runs perpendicular to the anterior interventricular branch of the left coronary artery on the left side of the interventricular sulcus and supplies the left side of the heart.
synonyms: ["circumflex coronary artery","left circumflex branch of left coronary artery","ramus circumflexus (arteria coronaria sinistra)"]

name: falx cerebelli
description: A small triangular process of dura matter beginning at the internal occipital crest just beneath the tentorium and projecting forward.

name: mediastinal pleura
description: The parietal pleura that lines the mediastinum.
synonyms: ["mediastinal part of parietal pleura","pars mediastinalis (pleurae)","pars mediastinalis pleurae parietalis"]

name: right suprarenal vein
description: A vein that drains blood from the right adrenal gland into the inferior vena cava.

name: mucoid tissue
description: Loose connective tissue, the intercellular matrix of which consists predominantly of mucoid ground substance. Examples: Mucoid tissue of umbilical cord, mucoid tissue of vitreous body, mucoid tissue of nucleus pulposus.

name: apex of prostate
description: The lowest part of the prostate gland adjacent to the superior fascia of the urogenital diaphragm.

name: urogenital diaphragm
description: muscular components of the deep perineal pouch.

name: cervical part of esophagus
description: Clinical esophageal segment composed of skeletal muscle. It corresponds to the superior part of the upper third topographic segment of the esophagus.
synonyms: ["cervical esophagus","cervical part of oesophagus","pars cervicalis (oesophagus)","pars cervicalis oesophageae","pars colli oesophageae"]

name: anterior parietal artery
description: The artery that delivers blood to the anterior portion of the parietal lobe.

name: endometrial cavity
description: A space inside the uterus lined by a layer of mucus membranes called the endometrium.
synonyms: ["cavity of body of uterus","endometrial cavity","endometrial lumen","intrauterine cavity"]

name: costodiaphragmatic recess
description: The angled junction where the diaphragm meets the chest wall.

name: right subcostal vein
description: A vein that extends along the bottom of the twelfth rib on the right side of the body.

name: lower inner quadrant of breast
description: The quarter of the breast which is inferior and medial.

name: surface of prostate
description: The external portion of the prostate including the anterior, inferolateral, lateral and posterior surfaces.

name: left suprarenal vein
description: A vein that drains blood from the left adrenal gland into the left renal artery.

name: inferior hypophysial artery
description: The inferior hypophysial artery is an artery supplying the pituitary gland. It is a branch of the cavernous carotid artery (internal carotid artery).

name: hilum of lymph node
description: The concave side of the lymph node.

name: gastrophrenic ligament
description: the portion of the greater omentum that extends from the greater curvature of the stomach to the inferior surface of the diaphragm

name: unencapsulated tactile receptor
description: Free nerve endings are widely distributed throughout the body, and are found as branches of unmyelinated, or lightly myelinated fibres grouped in bundles beneath the epithelium. As they penetrate the epithelium, they lose their myelin, and branch among the epithelial cells. Branches of one nerve may cover a wide area and overlap the territories of other nerves. The free nerve endings detect pain, touch, pressure and temperature, and are associated with C fibres.

name: right inguinal part of abdomen
synonyms: ["right iliac fossa viewed surgically","right iliac region","right inguinal region"]

name: anterior mediastinal lymph node
description: A lymph node located in the superior mediastinum that collects lymph from the thymus, the pericardium, and the right side of the heart.

name: anterior surface of prostate
description: The aspect of the prostate facing the pubic symphysis.
synonyms: ["anterior surface of prostate gland","facies anterior (prostatae)","facies anterior prostatae"]

name: superficial fibular nerve
description: A branch of the common fibular nerve that innervates the fibularis longus and brevis muscles, and via branches innervates parts of the dorsal part of the pes.

name: left common iliac artery
synonyms: ["trunk of left common iliac arterial tree"]

name: basal vein
description: The basal vein is formed at the anterior perforated substance by the union of (a) a small anterior cerebral vein which accompanies the anterior cerebral artery and supplies the medial surface of the frontal lobe by the fronto-basal vein. (b) the deep middle cerebral vein (deep Sylvian vein), which receives tributaries from the insula and neighboring gyri, and runs in the lower part of the lateral cerebral fissure, and (c) the inferior striate veins, which leave the corpus striatum through the anterior perforated substance. The basal vein passes backward around the cerebral peduncle, and ends in the internal cerebral vein; it receives tributaries from the interpeduncular fossa, the inferior horn of the lateral ventricle, the hippocampal gyrus, and the mid-brain.

name: deep middle cerebral vein
description: The blood vessel that receives deoxygenated blood from the insula and gyri and drains into the basal vein of Rosenthal deep in the lateral sulcus.

name: body of gallbladder
description: The middle portion of the gallbladder which is distal to the gallbladder neck and proximal to the gallbladder fundus.

name: esophageal artery
description: Any of several arteries that arise from the aorta and supply blood to the esophagus.

name: upper inner quadrant of breast
description: The quarter of the breast which is superior and medial.

name: deep lymphatic vessel
description: The tubules that carry lymph throughout the body that are in the interior of the body or limbs.

name: posterior ciliary vein
description: The outer layer of the choroid (lamina vasculosa) consists, in part, of the larger branches of the short ciliary arteries which run forward between the veins, before they bend inward to end in the capillaries, but is formed principally of veins, named, from their arrangement, the vorticose veins. They converge to four or five equidistant trunks, which pierce the sclera about midway between the sclero-corneal junction and the entrance of the optic nerve. They drain uveal tract.

name: vasculature of integument
description: The part of the circulatory system that lies within the subcutaneous tissue layers close to the surface of the skin.

name: superficial vein
description: Any of the veins carrying deoxygenated blood from the subcutaneous tissue layers.

name: deep vasculature
description: The part of the circulatory system that lies deep beneath the subcutaneous tissue layers away from the surface of the skin.

name: deep vein
description: A blood vessel carrying deoxygenated blood far beneath the skin usually accompanying an artery.

name: left cardiac chamber
description: Any chamber of the left side of the heart

name: right cardiac chamber
description: Any chamber of the right side of the heart

name: obsolete fascia dentata
description: OBSOLETE: The fascia dentata is the earliest stage of the hippocampal circuit. Its primary input is the perforant path from the superficial layers of entorhinal cortex. Its principal neurons are tiny granule cells which give rise to unmyelinated axons called the mossy fibers which project to the hilus and CA3. The fascia dentata of the rat contains approximately 1,000,000 granule cells. It receives feedback connections from mossy cells in the hilus at distant levels in the septal and temporal directions. The fascia dentata and the hilus together make up the dentate gyrus. As with all regions of the hippocampus, the dentate gyrus also receives GABAergic and cholinergic input from the medial septum and the diagonal band of Broca.

name: styliform element
description: An unjointed, rod-like bony or cartilaginous structures that extend from distal limb joints in tetrapods.

name: magnocellular superficial pretectal nucleus
description: A nucleus that is part of the superficial pretectum and is characterized by large widely scattered cells.

name: parvocellular superficial pretectal nucleus
description: A nucleus that is part of the superficial pretectum and is characterized by small cells.

name: caudal pretectal nucleus
description: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the superficial pretectum and is rostrally contiguous with the magnocellular superficial pretectal nucleus. Cells of the caudal pretectal nucleus are slightly smaller and less orderly around a central neuropil than those of the magnocellular superficial pretectal nucleus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

name: central pretectal nucleus
description: Any nucleus found in the central pretectum.

name: accessory pretectal nucleus
description: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the central pretectum and lies dorsolateral to the caudal pretectal nucleus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

name: superficial pretectal nucleus
description: Any nucleus found in the superficial pretectum.

name: periventricular pretectal nucleus
description: A nucleus medial to the central pretectal nucleus in the periventricular zone.

name: nucleus praetectalis profundus
description: A neural nucleus of the pretectal region that lies lateral to the posterior commissure and gives rise to widespread projections.

name: nucleus lentiformis mesencephali (Aves)
description: A pretectal nucleus in Aves that receives heavy retinal input and is hypothesized to be homologous to the nucleus of the optic tract of Mammals.

name: subpretectal complex of Aves
description: A nuclear complex in the ventral pretectal region.

name: accessory optic system
description: Subdivision of visual system that processes movements of images across retina and regulates the movement of eyes to keep the image stable.

name: circular nucleus of antherior hypothalamic nucleus
description: A group of cells located in the central part of the anterior hypothalamic nucleus in the anterior hypothalamic region of the rat ( Swanson-2004 ) and the mouse ( Paxinos-2001 ). Functionally it belongs to the magnocellular neuroendocrine cell groups of the subcortical motor system ( Swanson-2004 )

name: profundal placode
description: An embryonic structure positioned halfway between the prospective eye and ear, adjacent to the future midbrain-hindbrain boundary. The profundal and the trigeminal ganglia are separate distally but fused at their proximal end as they condense around NF stage 24.
synonyms: ["ophthalmic lobe of trigeminal placode","ophthalmic lobe of trigeminal placode complex","ophthalmic placode","profundus placode"]

name: maxillomandibular placode
synonyms: ["maxillomandibular lobe of trigeminal placode complex","trigeminal placode"]

name: profundal part of trigeminal ganglion complex
maxillomandibular part of trigeminal ganglion complex
collar nerve cord
description: A nerve tract found in marine worms that is located in the collar body region (three body regions in marine worms: proboscis, collar (extending into tentacle-fringed arms) and trunk)

name: enteropneust proboscis
description: Anteriormost of the three body regions of an enteropneust.

name: enteropneust collar
description: Middle of the three body regions of an enteropneust.

name: enteropneust trunk
description: Posteriormost of the three body regions of an enteropneust.

name: cartilage of external acoustic meatus
synonyms: ["cartilage of acoustic meatus","cartilage of auditory canal","cartilago meatus acustici","external acoustic meatus cartilage"]

name: accessory nerve cord of dorsal region
description: Any longitudinally extending condensed cluster of neurons and processes that runs along the dorsal mid-line of the animal that is not the most prominent nerve cord.

name: dura mater lymph vessel
description: Any lymph vessel that is located in the dura mater of the brain.

name: outer root sheath companion layer
description: the innermost layer of the outer root sheath.

name: hair canal
description: Tubular connection between the epidermal surface and the most distal part of the inner root sheath. Contains the hair shaft.

name: hair peg
description: Column of keratinocytes growing into the dermis during embryonic hair follicle development. The concave proximal end starts to encase the dermal condensate, the future dermal papilla.

name: nasal turbinal
description: A skeletal element of the ethmoid region with complex morphology that are lined with mucuous membranes involved in either olfaction or air conditioning.

name: peripharyngeal space
description: The space filled with loose areolar tissue surrounding the pharynx; it is divided into two major divisions, the parapharyngeal space and the retropharyngeal space.

name: parapharyngeal space
description: The portion of the peripharyngeal space limited by the lateral wall of the pharynx, the cervical vertebrae and medial pterygoid muscle.

name: retropharyngeal space
description: The portion of the peripharyngeal space that is located posterior to the pharynx.

name: quadrant of breast
description: The part of the breast that is bordered by the intermammary line and a perpendicular line bisecting the nipple.

name: ocular adnexa
description: The parts of the orbital region that are outside of the the eyeball, including the lacrimal apparatus, the extraocular muscles and the eyelids, eyelashes, eyebrows and the conjunctiva

name: middle vesical artery
description: The middle vesical artery, usually a branch of the superior vesical artery, is distributed to the fundus of the bladder and the seminal vesicles.

name: laryngeal nerve
description: Any nerve that innervates the larynx.

name: anterior superior alveolar nerve
description: The anterior superior alveolar branch (anterior superior dental branch), of considerable size, is given off from the maxillary nerve just before its exit from the infraorbital foramen; it descends in a canal in the anterior wall of the maxillary sinus, and divides into branches which supply the incisor and canine teeth. It communicates with the middle superior alveolar branch, and gives off a nasal branch, which passes through a minute canal in the lateral wall of the inferior meatus, and supplies the mucous membrane of the anterior part of the inferior meatus and the floor of the nasal cavity, communicating with the nasal branches from the sphenopalatine ganglion.

name: posterior auricular nerve
description: A branch of the facial nerve that innervates the posterior auricular and intrinsic muscles of the auricle and, through its occipital branch, innervates the occipital belly of the occipitofrontal muscle.

name: nerve innervating pinna
description: Any nerve that innervates the pinna.

name: nerve of penis
description: Any nerve that innervates the penis.

name: nerve of clitoris
description: Any nerve that innervates the clitoris.

name: fibular nerve
description: Any nerve that innervates the fibularis. Includes the common fibular nerve, and its branches

name: paraumbilical vein
description: The small superficial veins that arise from the cutaneous veins, and run from the umbilicus along the round ligament of the liver; these terminate as accessory portal veins in the liver.

name: deep facial vein
description: The anterior facial vein receives a branch of considerable size, the deep facial vein, from the pterygoid venous plexus.

name: parotid vein
synonyms: ["anterior parotid vein","parotid branch of facial vein"]

name: anterior facial vein
description: A vein that represents a continuation of the angular vein and lies behind the facial artery.

name: secondary yolk sac cavity
synonyms: ["cavity of definitive yolk sac","cavity of secondary yolk sac","definitive yolk sac cavity","secondary yolk sac cavity","secondary yolk sac cavity","secondary yolk sac space"]

name: primary yolk sac cavity
synonyms: ["cavity of primary yolk sac","primary yolk sac cavity","primary yolk sac space"]

name: capillary plexus
description: A network of capillaries.

name: capillary network of liver
synonyms: ["capillary plexus of liver","hepatic capillary network","hepatic capillary plexus"]

name: peritubular capillary plexus of kidney
synonyms: ["peritubular capillary network of kidney","peritubular capillary plexus"]

name: subsegmental lymph node
description: The lymph nodes around the subsegmental bronchi.

name: median lobe of prostate
description: The upper, smaller part of the prostate between the ejaculatory ducts and the urethra.
synonyms: ["Albarran's gland","cranial part of prostate","lobus medius prostatae","middle lobe of prostate","pars proximalis (prostata)","pars proximalis prostatae","proximal part of prostate","proximal part of prostate gland"]

name: coccygeal nerve plexus
description: The coccygeal plexus is a plexus of nerves near the coccyx bone.

name: inferior mesenteric nerve plexus
description: The inferior mesenteric plexus is derived chiefly from the aortic plexus. It surrounds the inferior mesenteric artery, and divides into a number of secondary plexuses, which are distributed to all the parts supplied by the artery, viz. , the left colic and sigmoid plexuses, which supply the descending and sigmoid parts of the colon; and the superior hemorrhoidal plexus, which supplies the rectum and joins in the pelvis with branches from the pelvic plexuses.
synonyms: ["inferior mesenteric plexus","plexus mesentericus inferior","plexus nervosus mesentericus inferior"]

name: abdominal nerve plexus
description: The abdominal aortic plexus (aortic plexus) is formed by branches derived, on either side, from the celiac plexus and ganglia, and receives filaments from some of the lumbar ganglia. It is situated upon the sides and front of the aorta, between the origins of the superior and inferior mesenteric arteries. From this plexus arise part of the spermatic, the inferior mesenteric, and the hypogastric plexuses; it also distributes filaments to the inferior vena cava.
synonyms: ["abdominal aortic nerve plexus","abdominal aortic plexus","plexus aorticus abdominalis","plexus aortique abdominal@fr","plexus nervosus aorticus abdominalis","preaortic nerve plexus"]

name: thoracic aortic plexus
description: The thoracic aortic plexus is a sympathetic plexus in the region of the thoracic aorta.
synonyms: ["plexus aorticus thoracicus","plexus aortique thoracique@fr","plexus nervosus aorticus thoracicus","thoracic aortic nerve plexus"]

name: submandibular region
description: The region between the mandible and the hyoid bone that contains the submandibular and sublingual glands, suprahyoid muscles, submandibular ganglion, and lingual artery.

name: accessory ciliary ganglion
description: A parasympathetic ganglion located on the short ciliary nerve differentiated from the main ciliary ganglion by virtue of the fact that it had no root derived directly from the inferior trunk of the oculomotor nerve and it never attaches to this nerve

name: ganglion of ciliary nerve
description: Any parasympathetic ganglion that extends fibers into the short ciliary nerve. Includes both the main and acccessory ciliary ganglia

name: seminal clot
description: A portion of semen in a coagulated state.

name: telencephalic song nucleus HVC
description: A nucleus in the brain of songbirds located in the caudal nidopallium, projecting to the song motor pathway via the robust nucleus of the arcopallium and to the Anterior Forebrain Pathway via the basal ganglia nucleus Area X.
synonyms: ["HVC","HVC (avian brain region)","pars caudalis (HVc)","telencephalic song nucleus HVC"]

name: alveus of CA2 field
description: Part of alveus lying within hippocampal sector CA2

name: extrapyramidal tract system
description: A neural network located in the brain that is part of the motor system involved in the coordination of movement that is distinct from the pyramidal tract.

name: future mouth
description: The primordial mouth region of the developing head.

name: muscle layer of sigmoid colon
description: A muscle layer that is part of the sigmoid colon
synonyms: ["muscularis externa of sigmoid colon","muscularis propria of sigmoid colon","sigmoid colon muscularis propria"]

name: Hensen stripe
description: The dark, nonstriated, V-shaped band (ridge) found on the underside of the tectorial membrane in the basal region of the cochlea, from which fine gelatinous trabeculae extend to fix the TM to the border cells, i.e. cells directly adjacent to the inner phalangeal cells.

name: area X of basal ganglion
description: A nucleus in the basal ganglion of songbirds.

name: robust nucleus of arcopallium
description: A specialized nucleus within the intermediate archistriatum of songbirds, required for and active during the production of learned song.

name: pericardial fat
description: The sum of epicardial and paracardial fat deposits.

name: paracardial fat
description: Fat deposits in the mediastinum outside the parietal pericardium .

name: visceral fat
description: Any fat deposit surrounding a visceral organ.

name: abdominopelvic cavity
description: The part of the ventral body cavity that is within the abdominal segment of the trunk, which encompasses the abdomen proper plus pelvic cavity.

name: peritoneal sac
description: A serous sac that is the aggregate of the peritoneum and the peritoneal cavity, located in the abdominal cavity.

name: left adrenal gland cortex
description: the thick outer layer of the adrenal gland that is in the left side of the abdomen
synonyms: ["cortex of left adrenal gland","cortex of left suprarenal gland","left adrenal cortex"]

name: left adrenal gland medulla
description: the adrenal gland medulla that is in the left side of the abdomen
synonyms: ["left adrenal medulla","medulla of left adrenal gland","medulla of left suprarenal gland"]

name: right adrenal gland cortex
description: the thick outer layer of the adrenal gland that is in the right side of the abdomen
synonyms: ["cortex of right adrenal gland","cortex of right suprarenal gland","right adrenal cortex"]

name: right adrenal gland medulla
description: the adrenal gland medulla that is in the right side of the abdomen
synonyms: ["medulla of right adrenal gland","medulla of right suprarenal gland","right adrenal medulla"]

name: right gastroepiploic artery
description: Artery that runs from right to left along the greater curvature of the stomach, between the layers of the greater omentum, anastomosing with the left gastroepiploic branch of the splenic artery.
synonyms: ["arteria gastro-omentalis dextra","arteria gastroepiploica dextra","arteria gastroomentalis dextra","right gastro-epiploic artery","right gastro-omental artery","right gastroomental artery"]

name: left gastroepiploic artery
description: Artery that runs from left to right along the greater curvature of the stomach, between the layers of the greater omentum, and anastomoses with the right gastroepiploic.
synonyms: ["arteria gastro-omentalis sinistra","arteria gastroepiploica sinistra","arteria gastroomentalis sinistra","left gastro-epiploic artery","left gastro-omental artery","left gastroomental artery","left inferior gastric artery"]

name: costal diaphragm
description: The domain of the diaphragm that is a thin domed sheet of muscle composed of a radial array of myofibers extending laterally from the ribs and medially to a central tendon.

name: caval sphincter
description: A striated muscle sphincter that is an extension of the diaphragm and surrounds the vena cava.

name: lower esophagus muscularis layer
synonyms: ["lower esophagus muscularis propria","muscle coat of lower esophagus"]

name: apical region of left ventricle
description: Region around the apex of the cardiac left ventricle located at the bottom of the left ventricle inferior to both the mitral and aortic valve.

name: esophagogastric junction mucosa
description: mucosa from the lowest portion of the esophagus, just proximal to the stomach.

name: esophagogastric junction submucosa
description: submucosa from the lowest portion of the esophagus, just proximal to the stomach.

name: esophagogastric junction muscularis mucosa
description: muscularis mucosa from the lowest portion of the esophagus, just proximal to the stomach.

name: esophagogastric junction muscularis propria
description: muscularis propria from the lowest portion of the esophagus, just proximal to the stomach.

name: extensor digitorum brevis manus
description: An accessory extensor muscle of the hand found in some humans and other animals.
synonyms: ["extensor brevis digitorum manus","extensor digitorum brevis manus muscle"]

name: enthesis
description: The connective tissue between tendon and bone insertion sites, which acts to transmit tensile load from soft tissues to bone. They may be of the dense fibrous connective tissue or fibrocartilage type; fibrous entheses attach directly to bone or periosteum primarily via fibrous tissue, and fibrocartilaginous entheses attach to bone through a transitional layer of fibrocartilage from the fibrous tendon tissue the sites where tendons or ligaments insert into the bone. Recurring stress or inflammatory autoimmune disease can cause inflammation or occasionally fibrosis and calcification of the enthesis.

name: infraorbital margin
description: The infraorbital margin is the lower margin of the orbita.

name: orbital margin
description: the mostly sharp edge of the orbital opening that is the peripheral border of the base of the pyramidal orbit.

name: infraorbital bridge
description: A ridge of bone connecting left and right orbital margins located beneath the eye sockets.

name: primary somatosensory area barrel field layer 5
primary somatosensory area barrel field layer 1
primary somatosensory area barrel field layer 2/3
primary somatosensory area barrel field layer 6b
primary somatosensory area barrel field layer 6a
primary somatosensory area barrel field layer 4
subchondral region of epiphysis
description: The bone region of the epiphysis that provides underlying mechanical and physiological support for the cartilage of joint articular surfaces.

name: frontomaxillary suture
description: A suture between the frontal bone and the frontal process of the maxilla

name: zygomaticomaxillary suture
description: A suture between the zygomatic bone and the zygomatic process of the maxilla.

name: ethmoidomaxillary suture
description: A suture between the orbital surface of the body of the maxilla with the orbital plate of the ethmoid bone.

name: sphenomaxillary suture
description: an inconstant suture between the pterygoid process of the sphenoid bone and the body of the maxilla.

name: lacrimomaxillary suture
description: A suture between the lacrimal bone and the maxilla.

name: maxillary-premaxillary suture
description: A suture between the maxilla and premaxilla.

name: intraculminate fissure of cerebellum
description: A fissure that divides the culmen lobule (lobules IV and V)

name: radiation of corpus callosum
description: The spreading out of the fibers of the corpus callosum in the centrum semiovale of each cerebral hemisphere.

name: central sulcus of insula
synonyms: ["central fissure of insula","central fissure of island","central insula sulcus","central insular sulcus","central sulcus of insula","fissura centralis insulae","sulcus centralis insulae"]

name: anterior segment of paracentral lobule
synonyms: ["anterior part of paracentral lobule","medial segment of precentral gyrus","paracentral lobule, anterior part"]

name: paracentral lobule
description: The junction of the precentral gyrus and postcentral gyrus on the medial surface of the cerebral cortex. It lies across the boundary between the frontal lobe and the parietal lobe.

name: Meyer's loop of optic radiation
description: part of the optic radiation which sweeps back on itself into the temporal lobe, just lateral to the temporal horn of the lateral ventricle.

name: arcuate fasciculus
description: The arcuate fasciculus (Latin, curved bundle) is the neural pathway connecting the posterior part of the temporoparietal junction with the frontal cortex in the brain and is now considered as part of the Superior longitudinal fasciculus.

name: amiculum of inferior olive
synonyms: ["amiculum of olive","amiculum of the olive","amiculum olivae","amiculum olivare","inferior olive amiculum"]

name: amiculum
description: a dense surrounding coat of white fibers, as the sheath of the inferior olive and of the dentate nucleus.

name: central medullary reticular nuclear complex
synonyms: ["central group (medullary reticular formation)","central medullary reticular complex","central medullary reticular group","nuclei centrales myelencephali"]

name: Kimura membrane
description: The thickening of the lower surface of the tectorial membrane into which the hair bundles of the outer hair cells are embedded.

name: space between upper and lower jaws
description: The space between the upper jaw skeleton and lower jaw skeleton (including teeth) that is formed when when biting.

name: life cycle temporal boundary
description: A temporal boundary connecting two life cycle stages that follow in immediate succession. A temporal boundary is an abstract, instantaneous entity.

name: life-death temporal boundary
description: A life cycle temporal boundary that marks the end of the life cycle of the organism.
synonyms: ["end of life cycle","moment of death","time of death"]

name: start of life cycle
description: A life cycle temporal boundary that marks the start of the life cycle of the organism.

name: start of neonate stage
description: A life cycle temporal boundary that marks the start of the neonate stage of the organism.

name: obsolete cerebrum
description: Historically the term cerebrum has been used for several different parts of the CNS including the whole brain, the cerebral hemispheres and the sum of cerebral cortex and adjacent cerebral white matter. A thorough discussion of the definitional history is to be found in Anthoney-1994

name: epididymal lumen
description: The lumen of the epididymis

name: antotic pillar
description: The posteriormost orbital pillar, in front of the otic capsule.

name: preoptic pillar
description: The anteriormost orbital pillar, in front of the otic capsule.

name: orbital pillar
description: A skeletal projection in the chondrocranium that developmentally connects the orbital cartilage and may develop into bone regions.

name: velum feeding organ
description: The locomotory and feeding organ, found in the larval veliger stage of bivalves.

name: obsolete proboscis
description: 1: The trunk of an elephant; also: any long flexible snout. 2: Any of various elongated or extensible tubular processes as the sucking organ of a butterfly of the oral region of an invertebrate.

name: supravaginal part of cervix
description: Supravaginal portion of cervix: the part of the cervix uteri that does not protrude into the vagina.

name: epithelial lining fluid
description: Epithelial lining fluid forms a thin fluid layer that covers the mucosa of the alveoli, the small airways, and the large airways.

name: promontory of tympanic cavity
description: The promontory of the tympanic cavity, better known as the cochlear promontory is a rounded hollow prominence, formed by the projection outward of the first turn of the cochlea. It is placed between the fenestrae, and is furrowed on its surface by small grooves, for the lodgement of branches of the tympanic plexus. A minute spicule of bone frequently connects the promontory to the pyramidal eminence.

name: scleral lamina cribrosa
description: The perforated part of the sclera through which pass the axons of the retinal ganglion cells.

name: alveolar mucosa
description: The mucous membrane apical to the attached gingiva.

name: bulboid corpuscle
description: A receptor in the transitional zone between mucous membrane and skin.

name: encapsulated tactile receptor
description: A tacile mechanoreceptor that lacks a capsule.

name: calcar avis of the lateral ventricle
description: On the medial wall of the posterior cornu of the lateral ventricle is a longitudinal eminence, the calcar avis (hippocampus minor), which is an involution of the ventricular wall produced by the calcarine fissure. It is sometimes visible on ultrasonogram.

name: postsubiculum
description: Division of subicular cortex characterized by projections from the anterodorsal thalamic nucleus and to a lesser extent the anteroventral nucleus, bordered ventrally and laterally by the presubiculum and dorsally and medially by the retrosplenial granular a cortex.. The border is characterized by an abrupt change in the cyto- and chemoarchitecture

name: interanterodorsal nucleus of the thalamus
description: a group of nerve cells that bridges the midline of the thalamus between the anterodorsal nucleus of the thalamus of the left and right sides. According to Crosby (1962), it is more developed and consistently present in rodents than in primates (adapted from Brain Info).

name: nucleus incertus
description: Distinct cell group in caudoventral regions of the pontine periventricular gray, adjacent to the ventromedial border of the caudal dorsal tegmental nucleus.

name: intergeniculate leaflet of the lateral geniculate complex
accessory abducens nucleus
description: A small cluster of neurons in the pontine reticular formation in some mammals, containing the majority of motoneurons innervating thenretractor bulbi muscles of the eye

name: bed nucleus of the accessory olfactory tract
description: a group of cells near the surface of the brain between the supraoptic nucleus and the cortical amygdalar nucleus in the rat ( Swanson-1998 ) and the mouse ( Paxinos-2001 ). It is one of five subdivisions of the medial amygdalar nucleus.

name: dopaminergic cell groups
description: collections of neurons in the central nervous system that have been demonstrated by histochemical fluorescence to contain the neurotransmitter dopamine ( Fuxe-1970 )

name: A13 dopaminergic cell group
description: A group of cells that fluoresce for dopamine and are distributed in clusters that, in the primate, are ventral and medial to the mammillothalamic tract of the hypothalamus; a few extend into the reuniens nucleus of the thalamus (Felten-1983). In the mouse A13 is located ventral to the mammillothalamic tract of the thalamus in the zona incerta (adapted from Brain Info)

name: nucleus of the brachium of the inferior colliculus
intergluteal cleft
description: The line that divided the gluteal regions of the body.
synonyms: ["anal cleft","crena analis","crena ani","crena interglutealis","intergluteal crease","natal cleft"]

name: gluteal sulcus
description: A horizontal crease formed by the inferior aspect of the buttocks and the posterior upper leg.

name: castoreum
description: A yellowish pungent liquid that is a mixture of the castor sacs (an anal gland in the taxon Castoreum) and urine.

name: honey
description: A sweet viscid material elaborated out of the nectar of flowers in the honey sac of various bees.

name: regurgitated substance
description: A bodily fluid consisting of the contents of the digestive tract expulsed through the anterior portion of the digestive tract.

name: regurgitated pellet
description: A mass of undigested parts of a bird's food that some bird species occasionally regurgitate from their proventriculus.

name: castor sac
description: A non-glandular region of the anal wall in which castoreum is produced.

name: cerebellum vermis lobule VIIAf
synonyms: ["lobule VIIAf/crus I (folium and superior semilunar lobule)","VIIAf"]

name: cerebellum vermis lobule VIIAt
synonyms: ["lobule VIIAt/crus II (tuber and inferior semilunar lobule)","VIIAt"]

name: inferior endocardial cushion
description: The endocardial cushion that forms on the ventral surface of the AV canal.

name: superior endocardial cushion
description: The endocardial cushion that forms on the dorsal surface of the AV canal.

name: subglottis
description: The lower portion of the larynx, extending from just beneath the vocal cords down to the top of the trachea.

name: tracheoesophageal fold
description: One of two longitudinal ridges that develop caudal to the pharynx and fuses to give rise to the tracheoesophageal septum.

name: tracheoesophageal septum
description: The tracheoesophageal septum is formed from the tracheoesophageal folds which fuse in the midline to form a structure called tracheoesophageal septum. It divides the esophagus from the trachea. It divides the foregut tube into the laryngotracheal tube ventrally and esophagus dorsally. Developmental abnormalities can lead to a tracheoesophageal fistula.

name: diaphragmaticus muscle
description: A skeletal muscle found in crocodilians that is analogous to the diaphragm of mammals

name: vein of vestibular aqueduct
description: A vein that leaves the vestibule through an individual bone canal running parallel to the vestibular aqueduct up to the dura of the posterior side of the petrosa in the area of the endolymphatic sac. It then opens in the inferior petrosal sinus or the jugular bulb. The vein receives other branches from the bone, dura and sac.

name: meningeal branch of mandibular nerve
description: The meningeal branch of the mandibular nerve (recurrent branch, nervus spinosus) is a branch of the mandibular nerve that supplies the dura mater.
synonyms: ["nervus spinosus","ramus meningeus (Nervus mandibularis)","ramus meningeus nervus mandibularis"]

name: incisive duct
description: an infrequent rudimentary duct, or protrusion of the mucous membrane into the incisive canal, on either side of the anterior extremity of the nasal crest

name: glymphatic system
description: macroscopic waste clearance system that utilizes a unique system of perivascular tunnels, formed by astroglial cells, to promote efficient elimination of soluble proteins and metabolites from the central nervous system.

name: cardiopharyngeal field
description: An region of the mesoderm that includes anterior lateral mesoderm of the first heart field plus contiguous pharyngeal mesoderm that gives rise to second-heart-field-derived regions of the heart and branchiomeric muscles.

name: oral siphon muscle
description: A muscle that is part of an oral siphon

name: suprapubic skin
description: Area of skin in the hypoastric region of the abdomen.

name: skin appendage follicle
description: An organ subunit in the skin that gives rise to cutaneous appendage.

name: diffuse placenta
description: A placenta in which the chorionic sac meets the uterine endometrium over its entire surface. The villi of the chorion are distributed evenly throughout the surface of the chorion, and they extend into processes in the uterine endometrium.

name: cotyledonary placenta
description: A placenta in which the villi clumped together into circular patches called cotyledons. The fetal cotyledon meets with maternal regions called caruncles to form the placentome where maternal-fetal exchanges take place.

name: zonary placenta
description: A placenta in which the chorionic villi have aggregated to form a broad band that circles about the center of the chorion. Such zones may be complete circles (such as those in dogs and cats) or incomplete (such as those in bears and seals). It is thought that zonary placentae form from diffuse placentae in which the villi at the ends regress, leaving only those in the center to function. At the edges of the zonary placenta is the hemophagous organ, which is green. The color is due to the degradation of hemoglobin into bilivirdin. This green organ provides iron for the developing fetus.

name: discoid placenta
description: A placenta in which part of the chorion remains smooth, while the other part interacts with the endometrium to form the placenta. The maternal blood cells are in direct contact with the fetal chorion.

name: epitheliochorial placenta
description: A placenta in which all three maternal layers are retained.

name: endotheliochorial placenta
description: A placenta in which the only maternal layer retained is the uterine endothelium.

name: hemochorial placenta
description: A placenta in which no maternal layers are retained.

name: ambient gyrus
description: a rostral part of the parahippocampal gyrus.

name: Sattler's layer
description: Sattler's layer is layer of medium diameter blood vessels of the choroid.

name: palmaris brevis
description: The Palmaris brevis is a thin, quadrilateral muscle, placed beneath the integument of the ulnar side of the hand. It arises by tendinous fasciculi from the transverse carpal ligament and palmar aponeurosis; the fleshy fibers are inserted into the skin on the ulnar border of the palm of the hand. The muscle is innervated by the superficial branch of the ulnar nerve, containing fibers from the eighth cervical and first thoracic nerves.

name: abductor digiti minimi of hand
description: The Abductor minimi digiti (Abductor digiti quinti) is situated on the ulnar border of the palm of the hand. It arises from the pisiform bone and from the tendon of the Flexor carpi ulnaris, and ends in a flat tendon, which divides into two slips; one is inserted into the ulnar side of the base of the first phalanx of the little finger; the other into the ulnar border of the aponeurosis of the Extensor digiti quinti proprius. In case of polydactyly it may insert to the sixth finger instead, if there is one.
synonyms: ["abductor digiti minimi muscle of hand","musculus abductor digiti minimi"]

name: flexor digiti minimi brevis of hand
description: The flexor digiti minimi brevis is a muscle in the hand that flexes the little finger. It lies in the same plane as the abductor digiti minimi, on its radial side.
synonyms: ["flexor digiti minimi brevis muscle of hand","musculus flexor digiti minimi brevis (manus)"]

name: opponens digiti minimi of hand
description: The opponens minimi digiti (opponens digiti quinti in older texts) is a muscle in the hand. It is of a triangular form, and placed immediately beneath the palmaris brevis, abductor minimi digiti, and flexor brevis minimi digiti. It arises from the convexity of the hamulus of the hamate bone, and contiguous portion of the transverse carpal ligament; it is inserted into the whole length of the metacarpal bone of the little finger, along its ulnar margin.
synonyms: ["musculus opponens digiti minimi (Manus)","opponens digiti minimi muscle of hand"]

name: nucleus recessus
description: The fish catecholamines originate in two large aggregations of neurons: the nucleus recessus lateralis (NRL) and the nucleus recessus posterioris (NRP). The nuclei were found in the hypothalamus of numerous species, e.g., the gold fish, eel, and roach.

name: Sertoli cell barrier
description: The blood-testis barrier (abbreviated as BTB) is a physical barrier between the blood vessels and the seminiferous tubules of the animal testes. The barrier is formed by tight connections between the Sertoli cells, which are sustentacular cells (supporting cells) of the seminiferous tubules, and nourish the spermatogonia. The barrier prevents passage of cytotoxic agents (bodies or substances that are toxic to cells) into the seminiferous tubules.

name: intertragic incisure
description: A surface structure that is the narrowed downward continuation of the conchal space bounded anteriorly by the borders of the tragus, posteriorly by theantitragus, and along its lower lateral margins and inferior boundary by the connection between the first two.

name: rectosigmoid junction
description: An anatomical junction that is between the sigmoid colon and rectum.

name: anatomical surface region
description: Material anatomical entity that forms the outermost boundary of an anatomical structure.

name: tympanic nerve
description: The tympanic nerve (nerve of Jacobson) is a branch of the glossopharyngeal nerve found near the ear.

name: coelomic fluid
description: A bodily fluid that is located in the coelom.

name: secondary prosencephalon
description: The most anterior region of the forebrain including both the telencephalon and the hypothalamus in the prosomeric model

name: ungulate coronary band
description: A region of the pododerm above the hoof where hair growth ends.

name: corticobulbar and corticospinal tracts
description: The corticobulbar and corticospinal tracts combined.

name: respiratory system gland
description: Any gland that is part os the respiratory system.

name: post-embryonic notochord
description: A notochord that has persisted beyond the embryonic stage.

name: vaginal fluid
description: Fluid that lines the vaginal walls that consists of multiple secretions that collect in the vagina from different glands.

name: secretion of serous membrane
description: A transudate found in the serous sac.

name: parenchyma of mammary gland
description: Parenchymal tissue that consists of the alveoli, grape-like clusters where milk is stored, and branching ducts, which are tubular canals carrying gladular secretions.
synonyms: ["lactiferous gland parenchyma","mammary gland parenchyma","parenchyma of lactiferous gland"]

name: incudostapedial joint
description: the small synovial joint connecting the inclus and the stapes, located between the lenticular process on the long crus of the incus and the head of the stapes.

name: incudomallear joint
description: the saddle-shaped synovial joint connecting the incus and the malleus.

name: joint of auditory ossicle
description: Any synovial joint that connects auditory ossicles.
synonyms: ["auditory ossicle joint","auditory ossicles joint","joint of auditory ossicles"]

name: zona pectinata of basilar membrane of cochlea
description: The acellular membrane that forms the outer two thirds of the basilar membrane of the conchlea.
synonyms: ["pectinate zone","pectinate zone of basilar membrane","pectinate zone of organ of corti","zona pectinata"]

name: zone of basilar membrane of cochlea
interdigital space
description: The space between the digits of the hand or foot.

name: piriform aperture
description: A pear-shaped bony inlet comprising the most anterior and narrowest bony portion of the nasal airway.

name: interoceptive system
description: The system that is responsible for sensing the internal state of the body.

name: iliac lymph sac
description: An embryonic lymph sac that forms near the junction of the iliac veins with the posterior cardinal veins.

name: cardial lymph propulsor
description: A lymphatic propulsor that lies tightly against the truncus arteriosus, the major outflow tract of the amphibian heart.

name: embryonic cisterna chyli
description: An embryonic lymph sac that is dorsal to the retroperitoneal lymph sac, at the level of the adrenal glands.

name: accessory lymph sac
description: An extracoelomic lateral abdominal space that accumulates body fluid.

name: uterine ligament
description: Any of the eight ligaments pertaining to the uterus including the anterior, posterior, lateral, sacro-uterine and round ligaments.

name: supraglottic part of larynx
description: The upper part of the larynx, including the epiglottis; the area above the vocal cords.

name: zygomaticotemporal nerve
description: The zygomaticotemporal nerve or zygomaticotemporal branch (temporal branch) is derived from the maxillary branch of the trigeminal nerve (Cranial nerve V). It runs along the lateral wall of the orbit in a groove in the zygomatic bone, receives a branch of communication from the lacrimal, and passes through zygomaticotemporal foramen in the zygomatic bone to enter the temporal fossa. It ascends between the bone, and substance of the Temporalis muscle, pierces the temporal fascia about 2.5 cm. above the zygomatic arch, and is distributed to the skin of the side of the forehead, and communicates with the facial nerve and with the auriculotemporal branch of the mandibular nerve. As it pierces the temporal fascia, it gives off a slender twig, which runs between the two layers of the fascia to the lateral angle of the orbit.
synonyms: ["ramus zygomaticotemporalis (Nervus zygomaticus)","ramus zygomaticotemporalis nervus zygomatici","zygomaticotemporal branch of zygomatic nerve"]

name: pars interarticularis of vertebra
description: The part of vertebra located between the inferior and superior articular processes of the facet joint.

name: epihyoideum
description: an elastic ligament lying between the lateral pharyngeal muscles and the thyroglossus muscle

name: omphalopleure
description: A fetal membrane, part of the yolk sac, that appears during some placentation processes.

name: bilaminar omphalopleure
description: A non-vascular omphalopleure that supports uptake and metabolism of nutrients.

name: trilaminar omphalopleure
description: A vascular omphalopleure that is important for respiration.

name: tonsillar pillar
description: The anterior and posterior borders of the tonsillar fossa. They are composed of muscle tissue.

name: wall of left ventricle
description: Wall of ventricle which is continuous with the wall of aorta.

name: wall of right ventricle
description: Wall of ventricle which is continuous with the wall of pulmonary trunk.

name: anterior wall of right ventricle
description: Region of wall of right ventricle which is continuous with the lateral and septal walls of right ventricle.

name: myocardium of anterior wall of left ventricle
myocardium of anterior wall of right ventricle
adnexa of uterus
description: The fallopian tubes and ovaries.

name: oral frenulum
description: A small fold of mucous membrane in the mouth, connecting either the tongue or the lip to the mouth mucosa.

name: mucosa of lip
description: A mucosa that is part of a lip region.

name: renal pelvis/ureter
description: The upper tract of the renal system. The renal pelvis is the large cavity in the middle of each kidney. Urine drains from each kidney through a long tube called the ureter, into the bladder, where it is stored until it is passed from the body through the urethra.
synonyms: ["renal pelvis and ureter","renal pelvis plus ureter"]

name: vasculature of central nervous system plus retina
anatomical border
description: An anatomical structure that is located along the line dividing two regions of an anatomical structure.

name: wall of uterine tube
synonyms: ["uterine tube wall","wall of fallopian tube","wall of oviduct"]

name: wall of central canal of spinal cord
wall of ventricular system of brain
wall of heart
description: wall of organ which has as its parts the endocardium, myocardium , epicardium, and the cardiac septum, surrounded by the pericardial sac proper and is continuous with the walls of the systemic and pulmonary arterial and venous trees.

name: primary hair
description: very thin, soft, usually unpigmented, downy hair that is sometimes found on the body of a fetal or new-born human.

name: vellus hair
description: short, thin, slight-colored, and barely noticeable hair that develops on most of a person's body during childhood.

name: terminal hair
description: thick and long hair, as compared with vellus hair growing elsewhere.

name: androgenic hair
description: The terminal hair that develops on the human body during and after puberty. It is differentiated from the head hair and less visible vellus hair, which is much finer and lighter in color.

name: waist
description: The part of the human abdomen below the ribs and above the hips, often narrower than the areas above and below.

name: paracardial gastric lymph node
description: Gastric lymph node located around the cardia of stomach.
synonyms: ["aJCC level 16","lymph node ring of cardia of stomach","paracardial gastric node","paracardial lymph node"]

name: subscapular axillary lymph node
description: An axillary lymph node that is placed along the lower margin of the posterior wall of the axilla in the course of the subscapular artery.
synonyms: ["nodus lymphaticus subscapularis axillae","posterior axillary node","subcapsular node"]

name: pectoral axillary lymph node
description: An axiallary lymph node along the lower border of the Pectoralis minor, in relation with the lateral thoracic artery. Their afferents drain the skin and muscles of the anterior and lateral thoracic walls, and the central and lateral parts of the mamma; their efferents pass partly to the central and partly to the subclavicular groups of axillary glands.
synonyms: ["anterior axillary lymph node","nodus lymphaticus pectoralis axillae","pectoral lymph node"]

name: central axillary lymph node
description: An axillary lymph node that is imbedded in the adipose tissue near the base of the axilla.

name: apical axillary lymph node
description: An axillary lymph node that is situated partly posterior to the upper portion of the Pectoralis minor and partly above the upper border of this muscle.

name: intermediate mesenteric lymph node
synonyms: ["central mesenteric lymph node","central superior mesenteric lymph node","intermediate lymph node of small intestine","intermediate mesenteric node"]

name: inferior pancreatic lymph node
description: Pancreaticosplenioc lymph node located along the inferior margin of pancreas.
synonyms: ["inferior pancreatic node","inferior pancreatiosplenic lymph node","jPS 18 node","jPS no. 18 node","no. 18 pancreatic lymph node","no. 18 pancreaticoduodenal lymph node"]

name: left gastric lymph node
description: Gastric lymph node located along the lesser curvature of stomach.

name: lateral axillary lymph node
synonyms: ["brachial axillary node","humeral node","nodus lymphaticus brachialis axillae"]

name: lateral superior deep cervical lymph node
anterior superior deep cervical lymph node
lateral inferior deep cervical lymph node
anterior inferior deep cervical lymph node
retro-aortic lymph node
synonyms: ["post-aortic lymph node","postaortic lymph node","retro-aortic node","retroaortic lymph node"]

name: aortopulmonary lymph node
synonyms: ["5 thoracic lymph node","aortopulmonary window lymph node","mediastinal lymph node station # 5","station 5 lymph node","station 5 N2 lymph node","subaortic lymph node"]

name: para-aortic thoracic lymph node
synonyms: ["6 thoracic lymph node","pre-aortic No. 6 lymph node","station 6 lymph node","station 6 N2 lymph node"]

name: interlobar lymph node
synonyms: ["11 R+L thoracic","11 thoracic lymph node","station 11 lymph node","station 11 N1 lymph node"]

name: lobar lymph node
synonyms: ["12R+L thoracic lymph node","station 12 lymph node","station 12 N1 lymph node"]

name: segmental lymph node
synonyms: ["13R+L thoracic lymph node","station 13 lymph node","station 13 N1 lymph node"]

name: lymph node of inferior pulmonary ligament
synonyms: ["9R+L thoracic lymph node","inferior pulmonary ligament lymph node","node of inferior pulmonary ligament","pulmonary ligament lymph node","station 9 lymph node","station 9 N2 lymph node"]

name: superior left gastric lymph node
description: Left gastric lymph node located along the left gastric artery.
synonyms: ["jPS 7 node","jPS no. 7 node","no. 7 left gastric lymph node","superior left gastric node"]

name: inferior left gastric lymph node
description: Left gastric lymph node located along the cardiac half of the lesser curvature of stomach in the lesser omentum.
synonyms: ["inferior left gastric node","jPS 3 node","jPS No. 3 node"]

name: common hepatic lymph node
description: Hepatic lymph node located along the common hepatic artery.

name: hepatoportal lymph node
description: Hepatic lymph node located along the portal vein.
synonyms: ["jPS 12p node","jPS No. 12p node","no. 12p hepatic lymph node","periportal lymph node","porta hepatis lymph node","portahepatic lymph node","portal lymph node"]

name: proximal superior pancreatic lymph node
description: Superior pancreatic lymph node located along the proximal segment of splenic artery.
synonyms: ["jPS 11p node","jPS no. 11p node","no. 11p superior pancreatic lymph node","proximal superior pancreaticosplenic lymph node"]

name: distal superior pancreatic lymph node
description: Superior pancreatic lymph node located along the distal segment of splenic artery.
synonyms: ["distal superior pancreaticosplenic lymph node","jPS 11d node","jPS no. 11d node","no. 11d superior pancreatic lymph node"]

name: anterior superior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node
description: Superior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node located on the anterior anterior of superior region of head of pancreas.
synonyms: ["anterosuperior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node","jPS 17a node","jPS no. 17a node","no. 17a pancreaticoduodenal lymph node"]

name: posterior superior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node
description: Superior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node located on the posterior aspect of superior portion of head of pancreas.
synonyms: ["jPS 13a node","jPS no. 13a node","no. 13a pancreaticoduodenal lymph node","posterosuperior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node"]

name: anterior inferior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node
description: Inferior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node located on the anterior aspect of inferior region of head of pancreas.
synonyms: ["anteroinferior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node","jPS 17b node","jPS no. 17b node","no. 17b pancreaticoduodenal lymph node"]

name: posterior inferior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node
description: Inferior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node located on the posterior aspect of inferior region of head of pancreas.
synonyms: ["jPS 13b node","jPS no. 13b node","no. 13b pancreaticoduodenal lymph node","posteroinferior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node"]

name: juxta-intestinal mesenteric lymph node
synonyms: ["mural mesenteric lymph node","para-intestinal mesenteric lymph node"]

name: visceral pre-aortic lymph node
description: Intestinal lymph node located anterior to aorta.
synonyms: ["visceral para-aortic lymph node","visceral pre-aortic node","visceral preaortic lymph node"]

name: gastro-epiploic lymph node
description: Gastric lymph node located along the greater curvature of stomach.
synonyms: ["gastro-epiploic node","gastro-omental lymph node","gastro-omental node","jPS 4 node","jPS No. 4 node","lymph node of greater curvature of stomach"]

name: lymph node along bile duct
synonyms: ["biliary lymph node","jPS 12b node","jPS No. 12b node","no. 12b hepatic lymph node"]

name: craniocervical lymph node
description: Lymph node located in either head and neck region.
synonyms: ["head and neck lymph node","lymph node of head and neck"]

name: intermediate deep inguinal lymph node
synonyms: ["cloquet's gland","cloquet's node","intermediate deep inguinal node","intermediate inguinal lymph node","middle inguinal node","nodus inguinales profundi intermedius","nodus lymphoideus inguinales profundi intermedius"]

name: distal deep inguinal lymph node
synonyms: ["distal deep inguinal node","distal inguinal lymph node","nodus inguinales profundi distalis","nodus lymphoideus inguinales profundi distalis"]

name: fibular lymph node
synonyms: ["fibular node","nodus fibularis","nodus lymphoideus fibularis","peroneal lymph node","peroneal node"]

name: paratracheal lymph node
synonyms: ["cervical paratracheal lymph node","nodus paratracheale lymphaticus","paratracheal node","tracheal lymph node"]

name: superior tracheobronchial lymph node
synonyms: ["4 thoracic lymph node","4R+L thoracic lymph node","lower paratracheal lymph node","nodus tracheobronchiale superiore lymphaticus","station 4 lymph node","station 4 N2 lymph node"]

name: buccinator lymph node
synonyms: ["buccinator node","nodus buccinatorius","nodus lymphoideus buccinatorius","noeuds lymphatiques buccinateurs@fr"]

name: nasolabial lymph node
synonyms: ["nasolabial node","nodus lymphoideus nasolabialis","nodus nasolabialis","noeud lymphatique naso-labial@fr"]

name: malar lymph node
synonyms: ["malar node","nodus lymphoideus malaris","nodus malaris","noeud lymphatique malaire@fr"]

name: superior deep lateral cervical lymph node
inferior deep lateral cervical lymph node
jugulodigastric lymph node
synonyms: ["jugulodigastric node","nodus jugulodigastricus","nodus lymphoideus jugulodigastricus","noeud lymphatique jugulodigastrique@fr"]

name: suprapyloric lymph node
description: Pylorioc lymph node located near the bifurcation of gastroduodenal artery and superior to the pylorus.
synonyms: ["jPS 5 node","jPS no.5 node","no. 5 station pyloric lymph node","nodus lymphoideus suprapyloricus","nodus suprapyloricus","noeuds lymphatiques supra-pyloriques@fr","suprapyloric node"]

name: subpyloric lymph node
description: Pylorioc lymph node located in the angle between the superior and descending parts of duodenum.
synonyms: ["infrapyloric lymph node","infrapyloric node","jPS 6 node","jPS no. 6 node","no. 6 station pyloric lymph node","subpyloric node"]

name: bronchopulmonary lymph node
description: A tracheobronchial lymph node situated in the hilum of a lung.
synonyms: ["10 R+L thoracic","bronchopulmonary node","hilar lymph node","station 10 lymph node","station 10 N1 lymph node"]

name: chin ventral margin
description: Subdivision of the head consisting of the area along the lower edge of the chin.

name: collection of hairs on vertex
description: A collection of hairs that grows on the vertex (top of head).

name: cranial midline area
description: The middle part of the head, located approximately equidistant from the left and the right sides of the head.

name: dewlap
description: A longitudinal flap of skin that hangs beneath the lower jaw or neck.

name: collection of hair on external ear
description: A collection of hairs that grows on the external ear.

name: external ear margin
description: Anatomical junction consisting of the area along the edge of the external ear.

name: collection of hair on forehead
description: A collection of hairs that grows on the forehead.

name: forehead protuberance
description: A bulge, knob, or swelling that protrudes from the forehead.

name: left part of face
description: Subdivision of the head consisting of the left half of the face, vertically divided.

name: midline crest
description: A ridge or peak located along the middle part of the head, located approximately equidistant from the left and the right sides of the head.

name: mole
description: A benign tumor on the skin, usually with darker pigment.

name: labial commissure
description: Anatomical structure consisting of either corner of the mouth.

name: nose anterior margin
description: Subdivision of the head consisting of the area along the front edge of the external nose.

name: nose vertex
description: The extreme point of curvature of the external nose.

name: right part of face
description: Subdivision of the head consisting of the right half of the face, vertically divided.

name: skin of snout
description: A zone of skin that is part of the snout.

name: tip of snout
description: Subdivision of the head consisting of the pointed or rounded end or extremity of the snout.

name: tip of external ear
description: Subdivision of the head consisting of the pointed or rounded end or extremity of the external ear.

name: cluster of hairs
description: A small collection or tuft of hairs.

name: top of head
description: The top of the head.

name: collection of hair on snout
description: A collection of hairs that grows on the snout.

name: skin of face
description: A zone of skin that is part of the face.

name: Zymbal's gland
description: A multilobulated modified sebaceous gland that is located at the base of the external ear, lined by stratified squamous epithelium, and secretes into the auditory canal

name: spleen pulp
description: The parenchyma of the spleen, consisting of lymphocytes and macrophages. It lies between the splenic trabecula. Red pulp is the part suffused with blood and white pulp consists of areas of lymphatic tissue where there are sleeves of lymphocytes and macrophages.

name: parenchyma of spleen
description: A parenchyma that is part of a spleen.

name: digestive tract junction
description: An anatomical junction between two parts of the digestive tract.

name: scapular blade
description: Enlarged and broad extension of the scapula distal to the glenoid region that conforms to the contour of the ribs. Origin for the major shoulder muscles including the deltoid group.

name: lateral line canal lumen
description: Anatomical space that contains a portion of the lateral line system.

name: ischial cartilage
description: Paired cartilaginous element forming the posterior portion of the pelvic girdle.

name: paired fin radial bone
description: paired fin radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: mesopterygium cartilage
description: The median, elongated basal cartilage of the pectoral fin.

name: pelvic fin distal radial bone
description: Pelvic fin radial that develops from the pelvic fin endoskeletal disc. Pelvic fin distal radials are paired.

name: pelvic fin basipterygial radial
description: Pelvic fin radial that is an endochondral fused radials or pterygiophores at the base of the pelvic fin.

name: pelvic fin middle radial bone
description: Pelvic fin radial in the middle of the pelvic fin.

name: paired fin radial element
description: Radial element that is part of a paired fin.

name: pelvic fin distal radial element
description: Pelvic fin radial element that develops from the pelvic fin endoskeletal disc. Pelvic fin distal radial elements are paired.

name: obsolete pelvic fin basipterygial radial element
description: Pelvic fin radial element that is an endochondral fused radial elements or pterygiophores at the base of the pelvic fin.

name: pelvic fin middle radial element
description: Pelvic fin radial element in the middle of the pelvic fin.

name: paired fin radial cartilage
description: paired fin radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: Brachet's cleft
description: The visible division between epiblast and hypoblast in the gastrula. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: Kupffer's vesicle
description: Small but distinctive epithelial sac containing fluid, located midventrally posterior to the yolk cell or its extension, and transiently present during most of the segmentation period. Kimmel et al, 1995. Kupffer's vesicle has been compared to the mouse embryonic node. Drummond et al, 2005.

name: ball
description: The anterior round region of the yolk cell present after the yolk extension forms during the segmentation period. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: obsolete forerunner cell group
description: A group of cells that migrate at the leading edge of shield during gastrulation but do not involute. At the end of gastrulation, forerunner cells migrate deep into the embryo and organize to form Kuppfer's vesicle. Cooper and D'Amico, 1996.

name: intermediate cell mass of mesoderm
synonyms: ["ICM","intermediate cell mass of Oellacher","posterior intermediate cell mass"]

name: median fin fold
description: Surface structure that will develop into one of the median fins. Extends from dorsal surface of fish, caudal to the 8th somite, to the ventral surface ending at the caudal side of the vent.

name: myotome somite 14
description: Portion of the somite giving rise to body wall muscle masses. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: dorsal actinotrichium
description: Actinotrichium which is part of the dorsal fin fold.

name: polster
description: The hatching gland rudiment at the time it underlies the forebrain during the early segmentation period. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: somite 1
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: somite 5
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: somite 26
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: ventral actinotrichium
description: Actinotrichium which is part of the ventral fin fold.

name: yolk
description: Nutrient store for embryonic development in the form of semicrystalline phospholipoprotein and contained within yolk granules. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: yolk syncytial layer
