description: Fontanel that is located posterior to the epiphyseal bar, and typically located between the contralateral frontals and parietals (if present) and bordered posteriorly by the supraoccipital.

name: trigeminofacial foramen
description: Foramen through which branches of cranial nerves V (trigeminal) and VII (facial) exit.

name: auditory foramen
description: Foramen through which cranial nerve VIII (auditory) exits.

name: replacement tooth trench
description: Anatomical space within a bone in which teeth develop.

name: premaxilla replacement tooth trench
description: Replacement tooth trench that is located in the premaxilla.

name: dentary replacement tooth trench
description: Replacement tooth trench that is located in the dentary.

name: lateral mesethmoid wing
description: Bony projection located on the anteroventral region of the mesethmoid which articulates with the premaxilla.

name: superficial ophthalmic nerve foramen
description: Foramen through which the superficial ophthalmic nerve passes.

name: dentary-anguloarticular joint
description: Joint that articulates the dentary and anguloarticular. Dentary-anguloarticular joint is paired.

name: rib of vertebra 6
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the sixth centrum.

name: rib of vertebra 5
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the fifth centrum.

name: pre-narial cartilage
description: The pre-narial cartilage is a cartilage that is located anterior to the anterior naris.

name: posttemporal fossa
description: Fossa where the exoccipital forms the medial portion and the epioccipital forms the lateral margin. The posttemporal fossa in most species has two openings separated by the epioccipital bridge.

name: pectoral fin ray 1
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium 1 is the leading or marginal ray of the fin and articulates with the scapula. Lepidotrichium 1 is commonly segmented but unbranched but occasionally may be a massive strong unsegmented element (e.g., spine).

name: pectoral fin ray 2
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the second most anterior pectoral ray that it is usually branched and segmented.

name: pectoral fin ray 3
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the third most anterior pectoral ray that it is usually branched and segmented.

name: pectoral fin ray 4
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the fourth most anterior pectoral ray that it is usually branched and segmented.

name: pectoral fin ray 5
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the fifth most anterior pectoral ray that it is usually branched and segmented.

name: pectoral fin ray 6
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the sixth most anterior pectoral ray that it is usually branched and segmented.

name: pectoral fin ray 7
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the seventh most anterior pectoral ray that it is usually branched and segmented.

name: retractor tentaculi
description: Bilaterally paired dorsal hyoid arch muscle that retracts the maxillary barbel.

name: supraoccipital crest
description: Process that is part of the supraoccipital. It is a posteriorly directed and unpaired median projection off the posterior margin of the supraoccipital bone.

name: autopalatine-vomer joint
description: Joint that articulates autopalatine and vomer bones. Autopalatine-vomer joint is paired.

name: pectoral fin spine
description: Pectoral-fin lepidotrichium 1 with mostly co-ossified and unsegmented hemitrichia that form a stiff and usually thick shaft and enlarged basal processes that moveably articulate with the pectoral girdle. The pectoral fin spine may also result from the fusion of several lepidotrichia that form a stiff shaft.

name: pelvic splint
description: Dermal bone that is located near the lateral margin of the pelvic fin, and lateral to pelvic-fin lepidotrichium 1.

name: dorsal fin spine 1
description: Dorsal-fin lepidotrichium 1 with co-ossified and unsegmented hemitrichia that form a stiff shaft and enlarged base that moveably articulates with first (anteriormost) dorsal-fin pterygiophore.

name: dorsal fin spine 2
description: Dorsal-fin lepidotrichium 2 with co-ossified and unsegmented hemitrichia that form a stiff shaft and enlarged base that moveably articulates with second dorsal-fin pterygiophore.

name: pharyngobranchial 3 bone uncinate process
description: Bony projection that is part of the pharyngobranchial 3.

name: pharyngobranchial 4 bone uncinate process
description: Bony projection that is part of the pharyngobranchial 4.

name: orbitosphenoid-prootic joint
description: Joint that articulates orbitosphenoid and prootic bones. Orbitosphenoid-prootic joint is paired.

name: ceratohyal foramen
description: Foramen in the anterior ceratohyal for passage of the hyoidean artery.

name: epibranchial 2 bone uncinate process
description: Epibranchial uncinate process that is part of epibranchial 2 bone.

name: epibranchial 1 bone uncinate process
description: Epibranchial uncinate process that is part of epibranchial 1 bone.

name: epicentral bone
description: Intermuscular bone that articulates with the vertebral centrum.

name: recessus lateralis
description: Intracranial space formed by confluence of supraorbital, infraorbital, preopercular and temporal sensory canals. See also Di Dario (2004).

name: cephalic rib
description: Modified epicentral intermuscular bone that connects the back of the skull with the pectoral girdle.

name: quadrate-hyomandibula joint
description: Joint that articulates quadrate and hyomandibula bones. Quadrate-hyomandibula joint is paired.

name: quadrate-metapterygoid joint
description: Joint that articulates quadrate and metapterygoid bones. Quadrate-metapterygoid joint is paired.

name: olfactory nerve foramen
description: Foramen for the passage of the olfactory nerve or cranial nerve 1.

name: articular bone
description: Endochondral bone that is located posterior to the dentary, medial to the angular and antero-dorsal to the retroarticular forming the lower jaw. The articular bears a dorso-posterior articular facet for the condyle of the quadrate. The articular is a paired bone.

name: intracranial diverticulum of swimbladder
description: An anterior extension of the swimbladder that passes through a foramen in the exoccipital; part of the otophysic connection between swimbladder and inner ear.

name: preepiotic fossa
description: Fossa that is a concavity on the dorsolateral surface of the skull roof found at least partially on the epiotic (epioccipital).

name: facial foramen
description: Foramen through which cranial nerve VII (facial) exits.

name: trigeminal foramen
description: Foramen through which cranial nerve V (trigeminal) exits.

name: supraorbital sensory canal
description: Sensory canal anterior to and in close proximity to the otic and infraorbital sensory canals. The supraorbital sensory canal is bilaterally paired.

name: infraorbital sensory canal
description: Sensory canal lateral or ventral to and in close proximity to the otic and supraorbital sensory canals at their union. The infraorbital sensory canal is bilaterally paired and associated with the infraorbital bones.

name: preoperculo-mandibular sensory canal
description: Sensory canal lateral or ventral to and in close proximity to the otic and post-otic sensory canals at their union. The preoperculo-mandibular sensory canal is bilaterally paired and associated with the preopercle, angular and dentary bones.

name: preopercular sensory canal
description: Sensory canal lateral or ventral to and in close proximity with the otic and post-otic sensory canals at their union, and anteroventrally with the mandibular sensory canal. The preopercular sensory canal is bilaterally paired and associated with the preopercle bone.

name: mandibular sensory canal
description: Sensory canal anterior and ventral to and in close proximity with the preoperculo-mandibular sensory canal. The mandible sensory canal is bilaterally paired and associated with the angular and dentary bones.

name: nuchal plate
description: Dermal bone that is a bony expansion in the integument anterior to or flanking the dorsal fin that is part of and at the distal end of a supraneural or dorsal fin proximal radial.

name: anterior nuchal plate
description: Nuchal plate that is unpaired and part of the supraneural and in contact, or not, with the supraoccipital crest anteriorly and middle nuchal plate posteriorly.

name: middle nuchal plate
description: Nuchal plate that is unpaired and part of dorsal fin proximal radial 1 and usually in contact with the anterior nuchal plate and paired posterior nuchal plates.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 1
description: dorsal fin proximal radial 1 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 2
description: dorsal fin proximal radial 2 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: posterior nuchal plate
description: Paired nuchal plate that is part of dorsal fin proximal radial 2 and usually in contact with the middle nuchal plate.

name: notochord posterior region
description: Portion of tissue that is part of the caudal fin.

name: epibranchial 3 bone uncinate process
description: Epibranchial uncinate process that is part of epibranchial 3 bone.

name: epibranchial 4 bone uncinate process
description: Epibranchial uncinate process that is part of epibranchial 4 bone.

name: lateral line scale
description: Scale that is associated with the lateral line sensory canal.

name: urohyal lateral process
description: Process that is part of the urohyal; it is the posterolaterally directed process located on the ventrolateral margin of urohyal. Urohyal lateral process is paired.
synonyms: ["branche ventrale de l'urohyal","processus hyo-pelvien","urohyal lateral lamella","urohyal ventral wing"]

name: urohyal median process
description: Process that is part of the urohyal; it is the posterodorsally directed and median process located on the dorsal margin of the urohyal.

name: premaxillary-maxillary ligament
description: Ligament that connects the premaxilla to the maxilla.

name: primordial ligament
description: Ligament that connects the maxilla with the lower jaw.

name: caudal fin dorsal procurrent ray
description: Caudal procurrent ray that forms part of the anterior dorsal series of lepidotrichia of the caudal fin and may be associated with a neural spine or a epural or a uroneural. A pair of hemitrichia forms each ray.
synonyms: ["dorsal caudal procurrent ray","dorsal procurrent caudal-fin ray"]

name: caudal fin ventral procurrent ray
description: Caudal procurrent ray that forms part of the anterior ventral series of lepidotrichia of the caudal fin that may be associated with a neural spine or a epural or an uroneural (dorsal series) and with a hemal spine of a preural vertebra (ventral series). A caudal procurrent ray is an unpaired median bone.
synonyms: ["precurrent ray","ventral caudal procurrent ray","ventral procurrent caudal-fin ray","ventral procurrent ray"]

name: pterosphenoid-orbitosphenoid joint
description: Joint that articulates the pterosphenoid and orbitosphenoid. Pterosphenoid-orbitosphenoid joint is paired.

name: parasphenoid-basioccipital joint
description: Joint that articulates the parasphenoid and basioccipital. Parasphenoid-basioccipital joint is unpaired.

name: premaxillary tooth row
description: Tooth row that is on the premaxilla.

name: tip
description: Anatomical point that is the apex of a projection or anything long and tapered; can be bony or cartilage

name: interhyal-epihyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the interhyal and epihyal bones, or interhyal and ceratohyal cartilages. Interhyal-epihyal joint is paired.

name: epihyal-ceratohyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the epihyal and ceratohyal bones. Epihyal-ceratohyal joint is paired.

name: ceratohyal-dorsal hypohyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the ceratohyal and dorsal hypohyal bones. Ceratohyal-dorsal hypohyal joint is paired.

name: ceratohyal-ventral hypohyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the ceratohyal and ventral hypohyal bones. Ceratohyal-ventral hypohyal joint is paired.

name: dorsal hypohyal-ventral hypohyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the dorsal hypohyal and ventral hypohyal bones. Dorsal hypohyal-ventral hypohyal joint is paired.

name: inter-ventral hypohyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the contralateral ventral hypohyal bones or the contralateral ceratobranchial cartilages. Inter-ventral hypohyal joint is paired.

name: dorsal hypohyal-urohyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the dorsal hypohyal and urohyal bones. Dorsal hypohyal-urohyal joint is paired.

name: ventral hypohyal-urohyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the ventral hypohyal and urohyal bones. Ventral hypohyal-urohyal joint is paired.

name: epihyal-branchiostegal ray joint
description: Joint that articulates the epihyal and branchiostegal ray bones. Epihyal-branchiostegal ray joint is paired.

name: ceratohyal-branchiostegal ray joint
description: Joint that articulates the ceratohyal and branchiostegal ray bones. Ceratohyal-branchiostegal ray joint is paired.

name: postcleithrum 1
description: Postcleithrum that anteriorly articulates with the supracleithrum and/or the cleithrum of the pectoral girdle; most dorsal element in a series of postcleithra.

name: postcleithrum 2
description: Postcleithrum that articulates dorsally with postcleithrum 1, ventrally with postcleithrum 3, and anteriorly with cleithrum.

name: postcleithrum 3
description: Postcleithrum that articulates dorsally with postcleithrum 2 and, sometimes, anteriorly with cleithrum.

name: hyomandibular condyle for the opercle
description: Process on the dorso-posterior margin of the hyomandibula cartilage or bone that articulates with a depression on the antero-dorsal margin of the opercle.

name: gill ray
description: Gill ray is a slender, usually rod-like cartilage within a gill filament and ligamentously tied to its associated pharyngeal arch bone or cartilage.

name: hyoidean artery
description: An artery that passes along the ventral portions of the hyoid arch; supplies oxygenated blood to the pseudobranch.

name: suprapharyngobranchial
description: A pharyngobranchial bone that articulates with the neurocranium dorsally and epibranchial 1 and pharyngobranchial 2 ventrally; lies dorsal to other elements of the dorsal portions of the branchial arches.

name: pharyngobranchial 1 tooth plate
description: Pharyngeal tooth plate that lies ventral to pharyngobranchial 1 bone.

name: epibranchial 4-upper pharyngeal toothplate joint
description: Joint that articulates the epibranchial 4 cartilage or bone and upper pharyngeal toothplate. Epibranchial 4-upper pharyngeal toothplate joint is paired.

name: epibranchial 3-pharyngobranchial 3 joint
description: Joint that articulates the epibranchial 3 cartilage or bone and pharyngobranchial 3 cartilage or bone. Epibranchial 3-pharyngobranchial 3 joint is paired.

name: epibranchial 3-pharyngobranchial 4 joint
description: Joint that articulates the epibranchial 3 cartilage or bone and pharyngobranchial 4 cartilage or bone. Epibranchial 3-pharyngobranchial 4 joint is paired.

name: inter-hypobranchial 3 joint
description: Joint that articulates the left and right hypobranchial 3 cartilages or bones. Inter-hypobranchial 3 joint is unpaired.

name: basibranchial 1 cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is ventral, median, and associated with branchial arch 1 (pharyngeal arch 3).

name: basibranchial 4 cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is ventral, median, and associated with branchial arch 4 (pharyngeal arch 6).

name: basibranchial 5 cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is ventral, median, and associated with branchial arch 5 (pharyngeal arch 7).

name: post-ceratobranchial cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is ventral, median, and at or posterior to the juncture of the bilaterally paired ceratobranchial 5 cartilage or bone.

name: supraneural 2 cartilage
description: Postcranial axial cartilage located dorsal to vertebra 2.

name: supraneural 3 cartilage
description: Postcranial axial cartilage located dorsal to vertebrae 3 and 4.

name: Weberian ossicle set
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of the Weberian ossicles.

name: trunk sensory canal system
description: Lateral line system on trunk.

name: head sensory canal system
description: Lateral line system on head and pectoral girdle.

name: basibranchial 2 cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is ventral, median, and associated with branchial arch 2 (pharyngeal arch 4).

name: basibranchial 3 cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is ventral, median, and associated with branchial arch 3 (pharyngeal arch 5).

name: neural arch 1
description: Neural arch that is the anteriormost neural arch.

name: rib of vertebra 2
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the second centrum.

name: rib of vertebra 1
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the first centrum.

name: rib of vertebra 3
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the third centrum.

name: rib of vertebra 4
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the fourth centrum.

name: parapophysis + rib of vertebra 3 + rib of vertebra 4
accessory neural arch
description: Neural arch that is located posterior to the neurocranium and anterior to neural arch 1. The accessory neural arch is not associated with a vertebral centrum.

name: neural spine 1
description: Neural spine that is associated with the first vertebra.

name: neural spine 2
description: Neural spine that is associated with the second vertebra.

name: neural spine 3
description: Neural spine that is associated with the third vertebra.

name: supraneural 1 bone
description: Supraneural bone located dorsal to vertebra 1.

name: supraneural 1 cartilage
description: Postcranial axial cartilage located dorsal to vertebra 1.

name: interhyal element
description: Skeletal element that is bilaterally paired and articulates dorsally with the hyosymplectic cartilage or the articulation of the hyomandibula and symplectic.

name: hypobranchial element
description: Skeletal element that is bilaterally paired and articulates medially with a median skeletal element and laterally with a ceratobranchial element.

name: hypobranchial 1 element
description: Skeletal element that is ventral, bilaterally paired and articulates with a median skeletal element medially and with a ceratobranchial 1 element laterally.

name: hypobranchial 2 element
description: Skeletal element that is ventral, bilaterally paired and articulates with a median skeletal element medially and with a ceratobranchial 2 element laterally.

name: hypobranchial 3 element
description: Skeletal element that is ventral, bilaterally paired and articulates with a median skeletal element medially and with a ceratobranchial 3 element laterally.

name: hypobranchial 4 element
description: Skeletal element that is ventral, bilaterally paired and articulates with a median skeletal element medially and with a ceratobranchial 4 element laterally.

name: ceratobranchial element
description: Skeletal element that is bilaterally paired and forms part of the ventral branchial arches.

name: epibranchial element
description: Skeletal element that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial element.

name: pharyngobranchial element
description: Skeletal element of the branchial arches located medial to the epibranchials.

name: pharyngobranchial 1 element
description: Most anterior pharyngobranchial element, located medial to the epibranchials.

name: pharyngobranchial 2 element
description: Pharyngobranchial element, located medial to the epibranchials and posteriorly adjacent to pharyngobranchial 1 element.

name: pharyngobranchial 3 element
description: Pharyngobranchial element, located medial to the epibranchials and posteriorly adjacent to pharyngobranchial 2 element.

name: pharyngobranchial 4 element
description: Most posterior pharyngobranchial element, located medial to the epibranchials.

name: obsolete basibranchial element
description: Endochondral element that is ventral, median, and associated with a single pharyngeal arch in the pharyngeal arch 3-7 skeleton.

name: basibranchial 1 element
description: Skeletal element that is median and associated with branchial arch 1.

name: basibranchial 2 element
description: Skeletal element that is median and associated with branchial arch 2.

name: basibranchial 3 element
description: Skeletal element that is median and associated with branchial arch 3.

name: basibranchial 4 element
description: Skeletal element that is median and associated with branchial arch 4.

name: basibranchial 5 element
description: Skeletal element that is median and associated with branchial arch 5.

name: pseudotympanum
description: Anatomical structure that is formed as a hiatus in the muscles covering the anterior chamber of the swim bladder in the area of ribs 5 and 6.

name: adipose eyelid
description: Surface structure that is a fleshy membrane covering part of the eye.

name: inter-frontal joint
description: Joint between the left and right frontal bone.

name: aortic canal
description: Canal that houses the dorsal aorta.

name: occipital artery foramen
description: Foramina that allow passage of occipital arteries.

name: spiracular canal
description: Foramen for passage of nerve supplying otic lateral line.

name: posterior myodome
description: Fossa or chamber on posterior portion of orbital region of neurocranium that serves as attachment site for posterior extrinsic eye muscles.

name: anterior myodome
description: Fossa or chamber on anterior portion of orbital region of neurocranium that serves as attachment site for anterior extrinsic eye musculature.

name: articular fossa of opercle
description: Fossa of opercle that articulates with hyomandibular condyle for opercle.

name: epioccipital posterior process
description: Process of the epioccipital that extends posteriorly, is laminar in form and is usually attached to Weberian apparatus.

name: accessory vomerine tooth plate
description: Dermal bone that is located lateral to vomer off midline of palate. Accessory vomerine tooth plate bears teeth and may be present as one or more pairs.

name: infranuchal scute
description: Scute that is an elongated plate associated with a ligament running between posterior nuchal plate and rib on vertebra 6. Infranuchal scute is paired and develops from its associated ligament and sensory canal tubular ossicle.

name: sensory canal tubular ossicle
description: Dermal bone that is ring-shaped or cylindrical and surrounds a sensory canal.

name: sensory canal tubule
description: Sensory canal that is a side branch between a sensory canal proximally and a pore at its distal end. Sensory canal tubule is bilaterally paired although often imperfectly so.

name: rostral plate
description: Dermal bone that is located on midline of snout in skin above mesethmoid and lateral ethmoid bones. Rostral plate bears type 1 odontodes and is unpaired.

name: oral disk
description: Lip that is expanded to form a broad, rounded cup around the mouth.

name: posterior nasal barbel
description: Barbel that is attached to the anterior rim of the posterior nostril. Posterior nasal barbel is paired.

name: anterior nasal barbel
description: Barbel that is associated with the anterior nostril. Anterior nasal barbel is paired.

name: maxillary barbel
description: Barbel that is attached to the distal end of the maxilla and that originates on the side of the mouth. Maxillary barbel is paired.

name: inter-basipterygium joint
description: Joint that articulates the left and right basipterygium cartilage or bone. Inter-basipterygium joint is unpaired.

name: vertebra 4-vertebra 5 joint
description: Joint between the centra, and sometimes the neural arches or parapophyses of vertebra 4 and vertebra 5.

name: orbitosphenoid-lateral ethmoid joint
description: Joint that articulates the orbitosphenoid cartilage or bone and lateral ethmoid cartilage or bone. Orbitosphenoid-lateral ethmoid joint is paired.

name: autopalatine-maxillary joint
description: Joint that articulates the autopalatine cartilage or bone and maxilla.

name: metapterygoid-autopalatine ligament
description: Ligament that connects the metapterygoid to the autopalatine.

name: lateral ethmoid-autopalatine ligament
description: Lateral ethmoid-autopalatine ligament is a ligament that connects the lateral ethmoid to the autopalatine.

name: mesethmoid-premaxillary ligament
description: Mesethmoid-premaxillary ligament is a ligament that connects the mesethmoid to the premaxilla.

name: mesethmoid-maxillary ligament
description: Mesethmoid-maxillary ligament is a ligament that connects the mesethmoid to the maxilla.

name: hyomandibular-otic region joint
description: Joint that articulates the hyomandibular cartilage or bone and otic region cartilage or sphenotic bone, and often pterotic bone and prootic bone. Hyomandibular-otic region joint is paired.

name: anal fin hook
description: Process that is part of the anal fin lepidotrichium.

name: caudal fin hook
description: Process that is part of the caudal fin lepidotrichium.

name: inter-premaxillary joint
description: Joint that articulates the left and right premaxillary bones. Inter-premaxillary joint is unpaired.

name: skin flap
description: Surface structure that is a portion of skin that projects or hangs from the body.

name: dentary tooth row
description: Tooth row that is on the dentary.

name: epibranchial 1 bone proximal cartilage
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that is part of and at the proximal end of epibranchial 1 bone, and that usually articulates with a pharyngobranchial element. Epibranchial 1 bone proximal cartilage is paired.

name: epibranchial 2 bone proximal cartilage
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that is part of and at the proximal end of epibranchial 2 bone, and that usually articulates with a pharyngobranchial element. Epibranchial 2 bone proximal cartilage is paired.

name: ceratobranchial 3 bone distal cartilage
description: Pharynbeal cartilage that is part of and at the distal end of ceratobranchial 3 bone, and that usually articulates with epibranchial 3 element. Ceratobranchial 3 bone distal cartilage is paired.
synonyms: ["ceratobranchial 3 bone lateral cartilage","ceratobranchial 3 bone posterior cartilage"]

name: ceratobranchial 4 bone proximal cartilage
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that is part of and at the proximal end of ceratobranchial 4 bone, and that usually articulates with basibranchial 4 element. Ceratobranchial 4 proximal cartilage is paired.
synonyms: ["ceratobranchial 4 bone anterior cartilage","ceratobranchial 4 bone mesial cartilage"]

name: ceratobranchial 4 bone distal cartilage
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that is part of and at the distal end of ceratobranchial 4 bone, and that usually articulates with epibranchial 4 element. Ceratobranchial 4 distal cartilage is paired.
synonyms: ["ceratobranchial 4 bone lateral cartilage","ceratobranchial 4 bone posterior cartilage"]

name: ceratobranchial 5 bone distal cartilage
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that is part of and at the distal end of ceratobranchial 5 bone. Ceratobranchial 5 bone distal cartilage is paired.
synonyms: ["ceratobranchial 5 bone lateral cartilage","ceratobranchial 5 bone posterior cartilage"]

name: hypobranchial 1 bone distal cartilage
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that is part of and at the distal end of hypobranchial 1 bone, and that usually articulates with ceratobranchial 1 element. Hypobranchial 1 bone distal cartilage is paired.
synonyms: ["hypobranchial 1 bone lateral cartilage","hypobranchial 1 bone posterior cartilage"]

name: hypobranchial 2 bone distal cartilage
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that is part of and at the distal end of hypobranchial 2 bone, and that usually articulates with ceratobranchial 2 element. Hypobranchial 2 bone distal cartilage is paired.
synonyms: ["hypobranchial 2 bone lateral cartilage","hypobranchial 2 bone posterior cartilage"]

name: epibranchial 3 bone uncinate process cartilage
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that is part of and at the distal end of epibranchial bone 3 uncinate process. epibranchial bone 3 uncinate process cartilage is paired.

name: epibranchial 4 bone uncinate process cartilage
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that is part of and at the distal end of epibranchial bone 4 uncinate process. Epibranchial bone 4 uncinate process cartilage is paired.

name: outer mental barbel
description: Mental barbel that originates on the chin, in a posterolateral position relative to the inner mental barbel.

name: inner mental barbel
description: Mental barbel that originates on the chin, in an anteromedial position relative to the outer mental barbel. The inner mental barbel is nearer to the mandibular symphysis than is the outer mental barbel.

name: parapophysis 4
description: Parapophysis that is the lateral projection from the fourth centrum. Parapophysis 4 is bilaterally paired.

name: intercostal ligament
description: Ligament that connects one rib to another.

name: interorbital septum
description: Anatomical cluster composed of one or more bones and tissue that separates the orbits.

name: pad
description: Surface structure that is a portion of the integument thickened relative to surrounding area.

name: maxillary tooth row
description: Tooth row that is on the maxilla.

name: hyomandibula-metapterygoid joint
description: Joint that articulates the hyomandibula bone and metapterygoid bone.

name: vertebral element 6
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 5.

name: vertebral element 7
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 6.

name: vertebral element 8
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 7.

name: centrum 1
description: Centrum that is part of vertebra 1.

name: centrum 2
description: Centrum that is part of vertebra 2.

name: centrum 3
description: Centrum that is part of vertebra 3.

name: centrum 4
description: Centrum that is part of vertebra 4.

name: centrum 5
description: Centrum that is part of vertebra 5.

name: centrum 6
description: Centrum that is part of vertebra 6.

name: mandibular-hyoid median cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is a spherical mass of cartilage located between the mandibular symphysis and ventral hyoid arch. Mandibular-hyoid median cartilage is unpaired.

name: epibranchial arborescent organ
description: Anatomical cluster that is an outgrowth of the soft tissue around the dorsolateral corner of a branchial arch that is internally supported by a core of rigid cartilage-like tissue. Epibranchial arborescent organ is paired.

name: lateral bone
description: Membrane bone extending between a transverse process of the second proximal dorsal-fin radial and the pleural rib of the sixth vertebra. Lateral bone is paired.

name: branched anal fin ray
description: Anal fin lepidotrichium that is distally branched.

name: branched pectoral fin ray
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that is distally branched and segmented.

name: gill raker row
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of adjacent gill rakers constituting a row and is part of a ceratobranchial or epibranchial element of the branchial arches. Gill raker row is paired.

name: papilla
description: Surface structure that is a small, fleshy protuberance.

name: parietal-supraoccipital
description: Compound dermal and endochondral bone that results from the fusion of the paired dermal parietal bones and the median endochondral supraoccipital. Forms the dorso-posterior element of the dermatocranium.

name: posttemporal-supracleithrum
description: Dermal bone that results from the fusion of the dermal posttemporal and the dermal supracleithrum. Forms the upper skeletal element of the pectoral girdle between the cleithrum and neurocranium. Posttemporal-supracleithrum is paired.

name: posterior cleithral process
description: Process arising from the posterior or postero-dorsal margin of the cleithrum dorsally adjacent to the insertion of the pectoral fin. Posterior cleithral process is paired.

name: posterior dentation of pectoral fin spine
description: Process that is tooth-like or thorn-like and arising from the posteriorly-facing margin of the abducted pectoral spine.
synonyms: ["pectoral fin spine posterior dentation","posterior denticle of pectoral fin spine","posterior serration of pectoral fin spine","posterior thorn of pectoral fin spine","posterior tooth of pectoral fin spine"]

name: anterior dentation of pectoral fin spine
description: Process that is tooth- or thorn-like and arising from the anteriorly-facing margin of the abducted pectoral spine. Anterior dentation of pectoral fin spine is usually present on the proximal and/or middle section of the pectoral fin spine.

name: anterior distal serration of pectoral fin spine
description: Process that is retrorse, thorn-like and arising from the anteriorly-facing margin of the abducted pectoral spine. Anterior distal serration of pectoral fin spine is usually present on the distal section of the pectoral fin spine.

name: posterior dentation of dorsal fin spine 2
description: Process that is tooth or thorn-like and arising from the posteriorly-facing margin of the abducted dorsal-fin spine 2.
synonyms: ["dorsal fin spine 2 posterior dentation","posterior denticle of dorsal fin spine 2","posterior serration of dorsal fin spine 2","posterior thorn of dorsal fin spine 2","posterior tooth of dorsal fin spine 2"]

name: anterior dentation of dorsal fin spine 2
description: Process that is tooth- or thorn-like and arising from the anteriorly-facing margin of the abducted dorsal-fin spine 2.
synonyms: ["anterior denticle of dorsal fin spine 2","anterior serration of dorsal fin spine 2","anterior thorn of dorsal fin spine 2","anterior tooth of dorsal fin spine 2","dorsal fin spine 2 anterior dentation"]

name: canal plate
description: Dermal bone that is ventral to the preopercle and bears a portion of the preopercular sensory canal.

name: axillary pore
description: Pore that is located ventral to the posterior cleithral process and medial to the pectoral fin. Axillary pore is at the end of a duct from an integumentary gland.

name: supraneural 4 bone
description: Supraneural dorsal to neural spine 4.

name: neural lamina
description: Neural lamina is a median, vertical ridge or bony septum between neural spine 3 and neural spine 4 on the dorsal side of the Weberian vertebra. Neural lamina is unpaired.

name: medial cartilage of palatine
description: Pharyngeal cartilage that caps the medial margin of the palatine at the autopalatine-lateral ethmoid joint.

name: hyoideomandibular nerve
description: Nerve that is a branch of cranial nerve VII that passes through or around the suspensorium to innervate muscles and sensory organs on or near pharyngeal arch 2.

name: lateral fontanel of frontal
description: Fontanel within the frontal bone near the frontal-sphenotic joint. Lateral fontanel of frontal is paired.

name: dentary foramen
description: Foramen located on the dentary for passage of the mandibular nerve.

name: ascending limb of ceratobranchial 5 bone
description: Process that is the dorsally directed portion of ceratobranchial 5 bone.

name: ascending limb of ceratobranchial 5 cartilage
description: Process that is the dorsally directed portion of ceratobranchial 5 cartilage.

name: pharyngobranchial tooth plate
description: Dermal bone of upper pharyngeal arches associated with pharyngobranchial bones or cartilages, usually bearing teeth.

name: pharyngobranchial 4 tooth plate
description: Pharyngeal tooth plate that lies ventral to pharyngobranchial 4.

name: anterior limb of ceratobranchial 5 bone
description: Process that is the anterior and medially directed portion of ceratobranchial 5 bone part of ceratobranchial 5 bone.

name: anterior limb of ceratobranchial 5 cartilage
description: Process that is the anterior and medially directed portion of ceratobranchial 5 cartilage.

name: pterotic-posttemporal-supracleithrum
description: Bone that is a fusion of the pterotic, posttemporal, and supracleithrum bones.

name: hypomaxilla
description: Dermal bone bearing teeth located between the distal end of the premaxilla and the middle of the maxilla. The hypomaxilla is a paired bone.

name: ascending process of the parasphenoid
description: Process that is the lateral projection of the parasphenoid arising and articulating with the more dorsal portions of the neurocranium, usually at the level of the prootic.

name: dermethmoid
description: Dermal bone of the dorsal surface of the olfactory region. Dermethmoid can be paired or median.

name: second preethmoid bone
description: Endochondral bone found between the preethmoid and maxilla.

name: mental barbel
description: Barbel that originates on the chin.

name: pectoral fin proximal radial bone 1
description: pectoral fin proximal radial 1 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: pectoral fin proximal radial bone 2
description: pectoral fin proximal radial 2 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: pectoral fin proximal radial bone 3
description: pectoral fin proximal radial 3 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: pectoral fin proximal radial bone 4
description: pectoral fin proximal radial 4 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: ventral keel of coracoid
description: Process on the ventral surface of the horizontal limb of the coracoid, close to and parallel to the coracoid-cleithrum joint. Ventral keel of coracoid is paired.

name: orbital foramen
description: Foramen in the bone or cartilage comprising the anterior wall of the orbit, and through which passes at least the deep ophthalmic branch of cranial nerve V (trigeminal).

name: lateral ethmoid-frontal joint
description: Joint that articulates the lateral ethmoid and frontal. lateral ethmoid-frontal joint is paired.

name: prootic-pterosphenoid joint
description: Joint that articulates the prootic and pterosphenoid. prootic-pterosphenoid joint is paired.

name: prootic-exoccipital joint
description: Joint that articulates the prootic and exoccipital. Prootic-exoccipital joint is paired.

name: basioccipital-exoccipital joint
description: Joint that articulates the basioccipital and exoccipital. Basioccipital-exoccipital joint is paired.

name: dilatator fossa
description: Fossa located on the neurocranium that is formed from portions of the sphenotic, frontal and pterotic bones.

name: inter-coracoid joint
description: Joint between the right and left coracoid bones of the pectoral girdle.

name: parapophysis 6
description: Parapophysis that is the lateral projection from the sixth centrum.

name: parapophysis 5
description: Parapophysis that is the lateral projection from the fifth centrum.

name: posterior limb of parapophysis 4
description: Process that arises and projects posterolaterally from parapophysis 4. Posterior limb of parapophysis 4 is bilaterally paired.
synonyms: ["posterior branch of parapophysis 4","posterior wing of parapophysis 4"]

name: anterior limb of parapophysis 4
description: Process that arises and projects anterolaterally from parapophysis 4. Anterior limb of parapophysis 4 is bilaterally paired.
synonyms: ["anterior branch of parapophysis 4","anterior wing of parapophysis 4","Mullerian ramus","Müllerian ramus"]

name: obsolete alarm substance cell
description: Epithelial cell that produces a chemical that triggers antipredator behavior.

name: obsolete Schreckstoff
description: Chemical substance that functions as an alarm signal.

name: scale circulus
description: Fine ridge on surface of scale, often parallel to the circumference of scale.

name: prootic depression
description: Shallow area that exists on the prootic.

name: bony plate
description: Dermal bone that is located on or subjacent to the surface anywhere on the body and that is not part of the general complement of scales, dermal bone of the dermatocranium, postcranial axial skeleton or paired fin skeleton. Bony plate may exist singly, or as unpaired or paired clusters or series.

name: vertebra 5-vertebra 6 joint
description: Joint between the centra, and sometimes the neural arches or parapophyses.

name: vertebra 6 - vertebra 7 joint
description: Joint between the centra, and sometimes the neural arches or parapophyses of vertebra 6 and vertebra 7.

name: gill opening
description: Anatomical space that is the external opening of a gill slit connecting the pharyngeal cavity to the exterior. Gill opening is usually paired and located on the lateral or ventral surfaces of the head.

name: Weberian complex centrum
description: Centrum that is the fusion of centra 2-4.

name: predorsal vertebra
description: Vertebra that is positioned between the vertebra immediately anterior to the first dorsal-fin pterygiophore to the anteriormost vertebra.

name: branched caudal fin ray
description: Caudal fin lepidotrichium that is distally branched.

name: nuchal plate series
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of more than one type of nuchal plate in an individual.

name: uroneural 1
description: Uroneural that is the anteriormost element of the uroneural series.

name: ural centrum 1
description: A vertebral centrum that is immediately posterior to preural vertebra 1. Ural centrum 1 is an unpaired median bone.

name: auditory fenestra
description: Opening in the neurocranium to allow communication between the swimbladder and the inner ear.

name: upper hypural set
description: Anatomical cluster including hypural 3 and more dorsal hypurals that supports the dorsal series of principal caudal lepidotrichia or rays. The upper hypural set articulates or fuses to ural centra 3, 4 or 5 (polyural terminology) or ural centrum 2 (diural terminology) depending on the teleost subgroup. The upper hypural set is composed of unpaired median bones.

name: lower hypural set
description: Anatomical cluster including hypurals 1 and 2 that supports part of the ventral principal caudal lepidotrichia or rays and that separates from the dorsal hypural set through the hypural diastema. The lower hypural set articulates or fuses to ural centra 1 and 2 (polyural terminology) or ural centrum 1 (diural terminology) depending on the teleost subgroup. The lower hypural set is composed of unpaired median bones.

name: distal cartilage of posterior process of basipterygium
description: Process that is cartilaginous and arises from the distal margin or tip of posterior process of basipterygium and projects posteriorly.

name: internal anterior process of basipterygium
description: Process that is bony and arises from anteromedial corner of basipterygium and projects anteriorly or anteromedially.
synonyms: ["internal anterior arm of basipterygium","internal arm of the basipterygium","mesial anterior arm of basipterygium","mesial anterior process of basipterygium"]

name: distal cartilage of internal anterior process of basipterygium
description: Process that is cartilaginous and arises from the distal tip of internal anterior process of basipterygium.

name: middle anterior process of basipterygium
description: Process that is bony and arises from anterior margin of basipterygium between internal anterior process of basipterygium and external anterior process of basipterygium. Middle anterior process of basipterygium projects anteriorly or anteromedially.

name: distal cartilage of middle anterior process of basipterygium
description: Process that is cartilaginous and arises from the distal tip of middle anterior process of basipterygium.

name: external anterior process of basipterygium
description: Process that is bony and arises from anterolateral corner of basipterygium and projects anteriorly or anteromedially.
synonyms: ["external anterior arm of basipterygium","external arm of basipterygium","lateral anterior process of basipterygium","lateral pelvic process"]

name: distal cartilage of external anterior process of basipterygium
description: Process that is cartilaginous and arises from the distal tip of external anterior process of basipterygium.

name: lateral process of basipterygium
description: Process that is bony and arises from lateral margin of basipterygium lateral to pelvic fin lepidotrichium 1 and projects laterally or anterolaterally.

name: lateropterygium
description: Bone that is attached or adjacent to lateral margin of basipterygium and anterior to pelvic fin lepidotrichium 1. The lateropterygium is a paired bone.

name: hypural plate
description: Perichondrally ossified bone that results from the fusion of two or more hypurals and support a variable number of principal caudal lepidotrichia. The hypural plate is an unpaired median bone.

name: leptocephalous larva
description: Larval stage in some teleosts before metomorphosis.

name: spina occipitalis
description: Process that is a ventral projection from the supraoccipital that extends between the exoccipitals to the dorsal margin of the foramen magnum.

name: basal fulcrum
description: Fulcrum that is large, laterally expanded, paired or unpaired, scale-like, and that precedes the base of a fin. Arratia, G. 2009. Identifying patterns of diversity of the actinopterygian fulcra. Acta Zoologica (Stockholm) 90 (Suppl. 1): 220-235

name: fringing fulcrum
description: Fulcrum that is a small, paired dermal structure associated with the marginal, leading rays of paired and/or unpaired fins. Arratia, G. 2009. Identifying patterns of diversity of the actinopterygian fulcra. Acta Zoologica (Stockholm) 90 (Suppl. 1): 220-235.

name: pleurostyle
description: Postero-dorsal process of preural vertebra 1 or postero-dorsal process of the compound terminal centrum. The pleurostyle is a paired membrane bone.

name: ural centrum
description: A vertebral centrum that is posterior to preural vertebra 1 and consequently the most posterior vertebral centra. Ural centrum is a unpaired median bone.

name: pelvic axillary process
description: Anatomical cluster consisting of only a bony element or a combination of a bony element and one or more scales, or only modified scales, which lies in a fin fold at the base of the uppermost ray.

name: pectoral axillary process
description: Pectoral axillary process is an elongate structure formed by one or more additional postcleithra or modified scales or a combination of both, that is firmly attached to a skin fold above the articular condyle of the uppermost pectoral fin ray or lepidotrichium 1.

name: interhaemal bone
description: A small bone articulating distally with the haemal arch or a short haemal spine.

name: gular plate
description: Dermal bone located on the ventral surface of the skull and positioned between the two rami of the lower jaw. Anteriorly the gular attaches to the symphysis of the lower jaw through fibrous connective tissue. The gular is an unpaired median bone.

name: median caudal cartilage
description: Cartilage associated with hypurals.

name: rostral cartilage
description: Median chondrified cartilage bound to premaxillary ascending process by a rostro-premaxilla ligament.

name: dorsal fin pterygiophore 1
description: Dorsal fin pterygiophore that is the anteriormost pterygiophore of the dorsal fin.

name: ventromedial opening of posttemporal fossa
description: A third opening of the posttemporal fossa posteriorly located relative to the fossa. It is bordered completely by the epiocciptial, or by both the epioccipital and exoccipital.

name: bony plate series
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of more than one bony plate in an individual.

name: sensory canal pore series
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of more than one sensory canal pore.

name: lateral line scale series
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of more than one lateral line scale.

name: branchiostegal ray series
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of the branchiostegal rays within an individual.

name: epibranchial series
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of the epibranchial elements within an individual.

name: ceratobranchial series
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of the ceratobranchial elements within an individual.

name: electrosensory lateral line lobe
description: Anatomical structure located in the hindbrain that receives primary electroreceptor input.

name: eminentia granularis
description: Anatomical structure that is a subdivision of the cerebellum; it is the location of some lateral line nerve synapses.

name: medullary command nucleus
description: Anatomical structure that consists of two neuron types: pacemaker cells and relay cells. The medullary command nucleus commands the timing of the electric organ discharge.

name: buccal papilla
description: Papilla that is part of the mouth.

name: cotylephore
description: Multi-tissue structure that is a transient outgrowth of tissue on skin brooding fish that acts as an attachment site for embryos.

name: ovipositor
description: Organ that functions in egg deposition.

name: scale radius
description: Erosion channel that radiates out from the growth center (focus) of the scale across and through the circuli.

name: pouch scale
description: Scale that forms part of the posterior border of the caudal-fin organ. Pouch scales are usually hypertrophied.

name: nuptial tubercle
description: Surface structure that is a small protuberance on the surface of the body. Nuptial tubercles primarily function to facilitate contact between individuals for breeding.

name: caudal-fin organ
description: Organ that consists of a pouch located on the ventral caudal-fin lobe, opening posteriorly, and composed of glandular tissue. The caudal-fin organ presumably functions to secrete pheromones during courtship.

name: caudal-fin ray pump
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of thickened caudal-fin rays modified into a pumping mechanism associated with the caudal-fin organ.

name: myorhabdoid bone
description: Intermuscular bone that is located in the dorsal and ventral forward flexures of the myoseptum.

name: caudal rod
description: Multi-tissue structure that is a cartilaginous or collagenous bar supporting the caudal appendage.

name: caudal appendage
description: Multi-tissue structure that is region of the body posterior to the last anal-fin ray.

name: obsolete horizontal septum
description: Anatomical structure that consists of a sheet of connective tissue attached to the vertebral column and dividing the epaxial and hypaxial musculature.

name: dorsal organ
description: Surface structure that is a midsaggital strap of flattened ectodermal tissue extending along the posterodorsal midline.

name: annular ligament
description: Ligament that is in the eye and is located at the angle between the cornea and the iris.

name: obsolete anterior catecholaminergic tract
description: CNS white matter, an axonal tract between ventral diencephalon and ventral telencephalon. At 3 d, the anterior catecholaminergic tract includes noradrenergic projections from the hindbrain and dopaminergic projections from ventral dopaminergic neurons. During later development, other catecholaminergic projections may also contribute to the anterior catecholaminergic tract.

name: anterior swim bladder bud
description: Portion of tissue that forms from the swim bladder epithelium at the anterior end of the swim bladder.

name: vertebral element 9
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 8.

name: vertebral element 10
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 9.

name: vertebral element 11
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 10.

name: vertebral element 12
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 11. May have hemal arch and rib.

name: opercular cavity
description: Anatomical space which is located beneath the operculum and external to the gills.

name: obsolete palatine
description: Compound endochdondral and dermal bone that results from the fusion of the dermal dermopalatine and the endochondral autopalatine and forms the antero-lateral region of the palate. Commonly, it articulates with the maxilla antero-laterally and with the ethmoidal region medially. The palatine is paired.

name: caudal basal fulcrum
description: Basal fulcrum that precedes a caudal fin lobe. Arratia, G. 2009. Identifying patterns of diversity of the actinopterygian fulcra. Acta Zoologica (Stockholm) 90 (Suppl. 1): 220-235.

name: ural centrum 3
description: A vertebral centrum that is located immediately posterior to ural centrum 2 (polyural terminology). Ural centrum 3 articulates with hypural 3 ventrally. Ural centrum 3 is an unpaired median bone.

name: ural centrum 4
description: A vertebral centrum that is located immediately posterior to ural centrum 3 (polyural terminology) and may fuse to ural centrum 3 early in ontogeny. Ural centrum 4 articulates with hypural 4 ventrally. Ural centrum 4 is an unpaired median bone.

name: ural vertebra
description: Vertebra that is incomplete or rudimentary and may bear a rudimentary neural arch and sometimes a rudimentary spine or the neural arch and spine are completely absent. Ural vertebrae are one of the last bony elements of the vertebral column, usually smaller than the preural centra. Ural vertebrae are numbered beginning from anterior (1) to posterior (2, 3, 4, etc.). Ural vertebra is an unpaired median bone.

name: ural vertebra 1
description: Ural vertebra that is located directly posterior to preural centrum 1. It may bear a rudimentary neural arch and sometimes a rudimentary spine or the neural arch and spine are completely absent and it may articulate or fuse with hypural 1 (polyural terminology). Ural vertebra 1 is an unpaired median bone.

name: caudal principal ray set
description: Anatomical cluster including all segmented-and-branched rays plus one unbranched but segmented ray located at the leading margin in each lobe of the caudal fin (Hubbs and Lagler, 1947) and that associates with endoskeletal elements such as hypurals and hemal spines of preural centra 1 and 2 (Arratia, 2008). Caudal principal rays are counted from the dorsalmost one ventrally. Caudal principal rays are unpaired median bones.

name: caudal procurrent ray set
description: An anatomical cluster of short rays, shorter than the principal ones, which form the anterior dorsal and ventral series of lepidotrichia of the caudal fin that may be associated with neural spines, epurals and uroneurals (dorsal series) and haemal spines of preural vertebrae (ventral series) (Arratia, 2008). The anteriormost procurrent rays are commonly unsegmented, but the posteriormost ones are usually segmented. The procurrent rays are numbered from caudal to rostral direction. The caudal procurrent ray series is an unpaired median series.

name: pseudourostyle
description: An elongate lateral process ventrally placed to the proximal region of the pleurostyle. The pseudourostyle is paired.

name: stegural
description: Modified neural arch, probably of ural centrum 4, formed by a bony base that may extend along the dorso-lateral surfaces of ural centra and preural centra 1 or 2 and by a well-developed antero-dorsal membranous projection that extends lateral to the base of epural(s) and anterior toward the neural arches and/or spines of preural centra 1 or 2 (Arratia and Schultze, 1992). The stegural is a paired bone.

name: preural centrum 1 + ural centrum 1 + ural centrum 2
description: Urostyle that is the result of fusion of preural centrum 1 with ural centra 1 and 2.

name: octaval nerve motor nucleus
description: Hindbrain nucleus which consists of cell bodies whose axons exit the hindbrain via cranial nerve VIII and innervate hair cells of the lateral line and inner ear. The neurons of these nuclei are unusual in that they extend both contra- and ipsilateral dendrites.

name: obsolete peripheral nucleus of ventral telencephalon
description: Telencephalic nucleus which has migrated away from the ependyma and consists of the central, lateral nuclei and the dorsal and ventral entopeduncular nuclei. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

name: obsolete central nucleus of ventral telencephalon
description: Peripheral nucleus of the ventral telencephalon which is located immediately lateral to the dorsal nucleus of the ventral telencephalon. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

name: climbing fiber
description: Portion of tissue that consists of afferent axons from the inferior olive and synapsing with Purkinje cells within the molecular layer of the valvula cerebelli and corpus cerebelli.

name: dorsolateral motor nucleus of vagal nerve
description: Motor nucleus of vagal nerve that is located within the dorsolateral portion of rhomobomere 8.

name: dorsolateral septum
description: Portion of tissue that grows in from the dorsolateral wall of the otic vesicle, forming a dorsolateral partition between the developing anterior and posterior semicircular canals.

name: epidermal placode
description: Portion of tissue that is a thickening and reshaping of the epidermal basal stratum cells beneath which fibroblasts accumulate to form the scale primordium.

name: obsolete head muscle
description: Muscle which is part of the head.

name: obsolete hindbrain commissure
description: CNS white matter that crosses the midline within the hindbrain.

name: hypobranchial muscle
description: Head muscle that originates on the anterior region of the cleithrum and inserts on the urohyal. The hypobranchial forms initially as left and right parts that later fuse together forming a cone shape.

name: intermediate nucleus
description: Diencephalic nucleus which is located between the dorsal hypothalamus and the caudal tuberal nucleus and does not contain tyrosine hydroxylase immunoreactive cells.

name: obsolete lateral nucleus of ventral telencephalon
description: Peripheral nucleus of the ventral telencephalon that has migrated to the periphery of the brain. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

name: medial motor nucleus of vagal nerve
obsolete mesonephric podocyte
description: Podocyte that is part of the kidney (mesonephros).

name: obsolete optic nerve head
description: Portion of cranial nerve II where large fasicles of axons from the optic fiber layer come together prior to leaving the eye.

name: obsolete periventricular nucleus of ventral telencephalon
preglomerular nucleus
description: Diencephalic nucleus which is located in the caudal tuberculum. The preglomerular nuclei make up most of the migrated nuclei within the caudal tuberculum. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

name: presumptive cardiac ventricle primitive heart tube
obsolete pronephric podocyte
description: Podocyte that is part of the pronephros.

name: supratemporal commissure
description: Lateral line canal that that crosses the supratemporal region posterior to the openings of the endolymphatic ducts and connects the lateral canals of each side.

name: ocular side
description: Organism subdivision that is the side of the body possessing eyes.

name: blind side
description: Organism subdivision that is the side of the body lacking eyes.

name: premaxillary-maxillary joint
description: Joint that articulates the premaxilla and maxilla. Premaxillary-maxillary joint is paired.

name: interarcual cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage located between uncinate process of epibranchial 1 and pharyngobranchial 2.

name: ctenoid scale
description: Scale that possesses cteni (discrete spines).

name: transforming ctenoid scale
description: Ctenoid scale with two or three alternating rows of cteni marginally and truncated cteni submarginally. (Roberts 1993).

name: Jakubowski's organ
description: Neuromast of the supraorbital sensory canal in the nasal bone. It is innervated by the buccal nerve rather than by the supraorbital nerve, which invariably innervates neuromasts of the supraorbital canal. (Johnson and Patterson 1993).

name: obsolete median fin
description: Fin that is an unpaired fin located in the sagittal plane of the organism.

name: pectoral fin distal radial bone 1
description: pectoral fin distal radial 1 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: pectoral fin distal radial bone 2
description: pectoral fin distal radial 2 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: pectoral fin distal radial bone 3
description: pectoral fin distal radial 3 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: preopercle-opercle joint
description: Joint that articulates the preopercle and opercle. Preopercle-opercle joint is paired.

name: body marking
description: Surface structure that is a visible mark on the body resulting from pigmentation.

name: cycloid scale
description: Scale that is smooth-edged, round or oval and composed of acellular dermal bone lacking small spines on the posterior exposed edge. (from http://www.briancoad.com/Dictionary/introduction.htm).

name: obsolete aqueous humor
description: Clear ocular fluid in the anterior segment of the eye. It is produced primarily by dorsal ciliary epithelial cells.

name: obsolete sclera
description: Multi-tissue structure that composes the opaque fibrous outer layer of the eye.

name: obsolete vitreous
description: Portion of organism substance that is a gelatinous extracellular matrix structure that fills the vitreous cavity of the eye.

name: fulcrum
description: Dermal bone that is typically associated with a fin. Arratia, G. 2009. Identifying patterns of diversity of the actinopterygian fulcra. Acta Zoologica (Stockholm) 90 (Suppl. 1): 220-235.

name: epaxial basal fulcrum
description: Basal fulcrum that is positioned at the dorsal or anterodorsal margin of the caudal fin. Arratia, G. 2009. Identifying patterns of diversity of the actinopterygian fulcra. Acta Zoologica (Stockholm) 90 (Suppl. 1): 220-235.

name: hypaxial basal fulcrum
description: Basal fulcrum that is positioned at the anteroventral margin of the caudal fin. Arratia, G. 2009. Identifying patterns of diversity of the actinopterygian fulcra. Acta Zoologica (Stockholm) 90 (Suppl. 1): 220-235.
synonyms: ["hypaxial basal fulcra","ventral basal fulcra","ventral basal fulcrum"]

name: fish scute
description: Dermal bone that is an unpaired, scale-like structure. Arratia, G. 2009. Identifying patterns of diversity of the actinopterygian fulcra. Acta Zoologica (Stockholm) 90 (Suppl. 1): 220-235.

name: mid cerebral vein
description: The mesencephalic veins (MsV) enter the mid cerebral veins (MCeV) at the dorsal midline. THe MCeVs originate at the dorsal midline, proceede lateraly in a ventral direction to drain into the paired primordial midbrain channels (PHBC). ogai et al. 2001., Kimmel et al. 1993

name: pseudobranchial artery
description: A vascular loop attached to the efferent part of the mandibular arch that forms at 3.5 dpf. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: concurrent branch afferent branchial artery
description: The branch of the afferent branchial artery that continues posteriodorsally. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: recurrent branch afferent branchial artery
description: The anterioventral proceeding branch of the afferent branchial artery. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: primordial midbrain channel
description: The vessel between the anterior cerebral vein and the mid cerebral vein. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: central artery
description: Arteries that irrigate the forebrain and midbrain Isogai et al. 2001.

name: cerebellar central artery
description: Extend upward from the PCS, branch to provide an arterial feed to the hindbrain, then drain back down into the PHBC Isogai et al. 2001.

name: opercular artery
description: The opercular artery arises from the hyoid stump on the first aortic arch, then follows the lateral margin of the operculum (gill covering) ventrally to reconnect into the proximal part of the first aortic arch. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: dorsal longitudinal anastomotic vessel
description: Trunk vessel that connects to the primitive hindbrain channel and the basilar artery at the caudal end of the medulla oblongata. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: primary head sinus
description: Main route for venous drainage of the anterior and mid cerebral veins as well as portions of the primordial hindbrain channel. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: posterior cerebral vein
description: Vein that drains the dorsal longitudinal vessel and the caudal portions of the venous capillary network of the medulla oblongata. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: rostral blood island
description: Hematopoietic tissue derived from the cephalic mesoderm. Predominantly produces myeloid cells. de Jong and Zon 2005.

name: dorsal longitudinal vein
description: Vessel that connects to the primitive hindbrain channel and the basilar artery at the caudal end of the medulla oblongata. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: optic vein
description: Vein that connects to the hyaloid vein that drains the eye. External to eye. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: parachordal vessel
description: Vessels run longitudinally along the horizontal myoseptum. These vessels are not functional until after lumenization which occurs near 4 dpf. Isogai et al. 2003.

name: supraintestinal artery
description: A continuation of the anterior mesenteric artery, which branches out from the dorsal aorta just caudal to the pronephric glomus. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: optic artery
description: The artery that carries blood to the eye. It branches from the internal carotid artery and enters the eye ventrally through the optic fissure. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: primitive prosencephalic artery
description: Vessel that branches from cranial division of the internal carotid artery, extending laterally around the rostral end of the head. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: prosencephalic artery
description: After the primitive prosencephalic artery forms it becomes disconnected from the cranial division of the internal carotid artery and instead it connects to the anterior mesencephalic central artery and the communicating vessels of the palatocerebral artery.

name: palatocerebral artery
description: The PLA branches ventrally from the CrDI. It extends rostrally along the base of mid- and forebrain, then loops medially and links to the corresponding vessel from the other side of the embryo. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: communicating vessel palatocerebral artery
description: Connect the palatocerebral artery with the prosencephalic artery. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: anterior mesencephalic central artery
description: Arteries that irrigate rostral regions of the midbrain. They extend between the Basial communicating artery to the anterior cerebral vein. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: median palatocerebral vein
description: Drains the PLA loop proceeds straight caudally along the cranial midline just above the pharynx, just below the diencephalon. Forms a 'T' with the palatocerebral veins. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: palatocerebral vein
description: Vein that drains the median palatocerebral vein into the optic vein. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: bulbus arteriosus outer layer
description: Composed of scattered layers of interrupted elastic lamina. Hu et al. 2001.

name: bulbus arteriosus middle layer
description: Composed of 7-10 layers of helically arranged smooth muscle cells surrounded by a fine network of collagen, reticular, and elastic fibrils. Hu et al. 2001.

name: bulbus arteriosus inner layer
description: Composed of subendothelium with longitudinally oriented collagen, reticular fibrils, elastic fibers, and smooth muscle cells bound by a thin endothelial layer. Hu et al. 2001.

name: central cardiac conduction system
description: Cardiac conduction system, characterized by slow impulse propagation and prolonged refractory periods.

name: peripheral cardiac conduction system
description: Portion of the cardiac conduction system, with rapid impulse propagation.

name: middle mesencephalic central artery
description: Project rostrally and dorsally from the AMCtA to to irrigate the midportion of the midbrain Isogai et al. 2001.

name: posterior mesencephalic central artery
description: Project dorsally from BCA to irrigate the caudal part of midbrain Isogai et al. 2001.

name: anterior mesenteric artery
description: Unpaired artery departing from dorsal aorta, typically supplying the small intestine

name: metencephalic artery
description: These arteies branch dorsally from both sides of the posterior communicating artery looping up to join with the opposite MtA as well as with both middle cerebral veins at the dorsal midline of the head. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: nasal artery
description: The nasal arteries start at the internal carotid artey and travel rostrally, passing along the right and left walls of the nasal sac at the most rostral end of the head. From the nasal sac, the NA flows into the nasal veins. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: posterior mesenteric artery
description: Unpaired artery departing from dorsal aorta that typically supplies the large intestine

name: swim bladder artery
description: An elaborate set of vessels that branche off caudally from the anterior mesenteric artery just after the dorsal aorta. The SBA vascular loops are located on the ventral side of the swim bladder. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: central ray artery
description: Positioned in the intraray mesenchym between the hemirays of the lepidotrichia,. Huang et al. 2003.

name: ray vein
description: Lie flanking and just lateral to the fin ray, in the interray mesenchyme. Huang et al. 2003.

name: intervessel commissure
description: Vessels that travel between artery and veins or vein and vein in a single ray.

name: interray vessel
description: Vessels that travel between veins in adjacent rays.

name: dorsal lateral line neuromast
description: Neuromast that is part of the dorsal lateral line. Kimmel et al, 1995. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.)

name: primary posterior lateral line primordium
description: Primordium that forms the first neuromasts of the posterior lateral line. This primordium travels at 1.5-1.7 somites/hour and deposits neuromast that are polarized along the antero-posterior axis.

name: secondary posterior lateral line primordium
description: Second lateral line primordium. These primordia moves at 0.2 somites/hour and deposite neromasts that are polarized in a dorso-ventral direction.

name: anterior lateral line primordium
description: A migrating group of cells originating from an anterior lateral line placode. The primordium deposits neuromasts and interneuromasts between them during its migration.

name: middle lateral line primordium
description: A migrating group of cells originating from the middle lateral line placode. The primordium deposits neuromasts with interneuromasts between them.

name: barbel primordium
description: A surface structure that will eventually grow to form a barbel. The primordium is rich in taste buds. The final location for taste buds present in the primordium is the distal tip of the mature barbel.

name: intestinal bulb epithelium
description: Intestinal epithelium which lines the lumen of the intestinal bulb.

name: primary dental epithelium
description: Epithelium that surrounds a primary tooth. This epithelium is committed to formation of replacement teeth.

name: obsolete enameloid
description: Skeletal tissue that is hypermineralized and aprismatic and deposited by a combination of ameloblasts and odontoblasts that are excluded from the matrix. Enameloid develops from pre-enameloid tissue.

name: ampullary nerve
description: A branch of the 8th cranial nerve that innervates the cristae ampullaris.

name: distal epidermal cap of regenerating fin/limb
description: Part of regeneration epithelium at the tip of the fin/limb.

name: basal regeneration epithelium of regenerating fin/limb
description: Layer of the wound epidermis that surrounds the blastema in the fin or limb.

name: obsolete gold iridophore
description: Iridescent iridophore containing gold reflecting platelets.

name: obsolete silver iridophore
description: Iridescent iridophore containing silver reflecting platelets.

name: extrahepatic duct
description: Bile duct that collects from the intrahepatic ducts and feeds into the common bile duct.

name: ventral liver lobe
description: Portion of the liver which develops on the fish's ventral side.

name: obsolete CoPA
description: An interneuron in the spinal cord. CoPA are bipolar with 'T' shaped dorsal dendrites, have contralateral longitudinal axons that crosses the cord dorsal to the Mauthner neuron and ascends in the dorsal cord.

name: obsolete CoSA
description: An interneuron of the spinal cord. CoSA, have contralateral longitudinal axons that crosses the cord dorsal to the Mauthner neuron and ascends in the dorsal cord.

name: obsolete CoB
description: A bifurcate interneuron. It is a commissural neuron with both ascending and descending axons in the ventrolateral cord contralateral to its cell body.

name: obsolete midbrain interneuron
description: CNS interneurons located in the midbrain.

name: obsolete CaV
description: Hindbrain interneuron that is part of rhombomere 7, with 2 ventral neurons in each hemi-rhombomere.

name: choroid plexus vascular circuit
description: Cranial vasculature where the posterior cerebral veins and the trans-choroid plexus branch form a circuit around the 4th ventricle choroid plexus.

name: median fin radial bone
description: median fin radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: median fin proximal radial bone
description: median fin proximal radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: obsolete CoBL
description: A bifurcate interneuron where the axon projects ventrally, crossing the spinal cord ventral to the Mauthner axons before bifurcating and extending dorsally.

name: obsolete CiD
description: A interneuron of the spinal cord with an ipsilateral axon that extends ventral to the Mauthner axon then turns dorsally and caudally and sometimes has a minor ascending branch.

name: obsolete CoLA
description: A spinal interneuron with a dorsal dendrite that extends caudally. CoLA also has midlateral process that extend rostrally and caudally, the axon crosses the cord dorsal to the Mauthner cell and ascends, extending dorsally. Axon has minor descending branch.

name: obsolete Kolmer-Agduhr neuron
description: Kolmer-Agduhr neurons are ciliated GABAergic neurons that contact the central canal of the spinal cord and have ipsilateral ascending axons.

name: inter-parietal joint
description: Fibrous joint connecting the parietal bones.

name: obsolete regeneration fibroblast
description: Is a fibroblast that differentiates from the de-differentiated cells of the blastema.

name: obsolete CiA
description: Interneurons of the spinal cord that arise from the V1 proliferation domain. The CiA neurons inhibit motoneurons, other ventral interneurons and also inhibit dorsal sensory neurons involved in sensory gating,. CiA have ipsilateral axonal projections in both motor and sensory regions of spinal cord.

name: intervillus pockets
description: A portion of tissue formed between the base of the intestinal villi that is part of the intestinal epithelium where intestinal stem cells are located. In the intestine no crypts are present, but, the regions between the villi, the intervillus pockets, have a crypt-like function. Cells are produced in the intervillus pockets and shed from the villus tips.

name: continuous capillary
description: Capillary that has endothelial cells that provide an uninterrupted lining, and only allow small molecules, like water and ions to diffuse through tight junctions which leave gaps of unjoined membrane which are called intercellular clefts.
synonyms: ["continuous blood vessel endothelium","continuous blood vessel endothelium","continuous capillary vessel","continuous endothelium"]

name: fenestrated capillary
description: Capillary that has pores in the endothelial cells (60-80 nm in diameter) that are spanned by a diaphragm of radially oriented fibrils and allow small molecules and limited amounts of protein to diffuse

name: hyomandibula-opercle joint
description: Synovial joint that articulates the hyomandibula and the opercle.

name: pterotic fossa
description: Fossa on the pterotic where the hyomandibula articulates.

name: erector muscle
description: Muscle that moves parts of the body in a superior direction to an erect position. Antagonistic to depressor muscle.

name: preopercle horizontal limb-symplectic joint
description: Joint that articulates the posterior edge of the preopercle horizontal limb with the symplectic.

name: hypophyseal fenestra
description: Space enclosed by the trabeculae cranii. The anterior tip of the notochord extends into the posterior region of the hypophyseal fenestra.

name: depressor muscle
description: A muscle that moves body parts into an inferior direction or lowered position. Antagonistic to erector muscle.

name: immature gonad
description: Immature reproductive tissue that has not undergone final maturation into either testis or ovary. During gonadal development, the gonad may be transiently intersexual where there is a parallel presence of both oocytes and spermatocytes.

name: intestinal mucosal muscle
description: A thin layer of smooth muscle immediately beneath the base of the villi which permits the intestinal mucosa to dynamically move and fold.

name: hyomandibular foramen
description: Foramen in the hyomandibula that allows passage of the anterior lateral line nerve and the facial nerve (cranial nerve VII).

name: preopercle vertical limb-hyomandibula joint
description: Joint that articulates the anterior edge of the preopercle vertical limb and the hyomandibula.

name: enteric circular muscle
description: Smooth muscle of the enteric muscle system in which the cells are aligned perpendicular to the lumen of the gut.

name: distal late tubule
description: Portion of the renal tubule which is just posterior to the distal early tubule.

name: pronephric glomerular capsule epithelium
description: Simple squamous epithelium that lines the capsule of the pronephric glomerulus.

name: fin fold pectoral fin bud
description: Fin fold of the pectoral fin bud, resulting from mesenchyme migration into the apical fold.

name: pectoral fin fold
description: The functional webs of the paired fins. They arise as a consequence of apical fold (AER) expansion and of migration of the distal mesenchyme. The fin folds are delimited by a dorsal and a ventral striated epidermis. The cells of the epidermal basal stratum are positioned on a basement membrane. Directly beneath the basement membrane of each side there is an array of actinotrichs, fibers of the extracellular matrix which act as supportive elements of the larval fin folds.

name: obsolete gill ionocyte
description: Ionocyte located in the gills

name: obsolete integument ionocyte
description: Ionocyte located in the integument during embryonic and larval stages.

name: obsolete NaK ionocyte
description: Integument ionocyte rich in Na,K-ATPase.

name: obsolete vH ionocyte
description: Integument ionocyte rich in vacuolar-type H+ ATPase and carbonic anhydrase
