name: posterior recess
description: Posterior protrusion of the third ventricle.

name: endohypothalamic tract
description: CNS white matter, axonal tract interconnecting catecholaminergic cell groups in the posterior tuberculum and hypothalamus.

name: extrapancreatic duct
description: Portion of the pancreatic duct, external to the pancreas body that connects the pancreas with the hepatopancreatic ampulla.

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 1
description: dorsal fin distal radial 1 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 2
description: dorsal fin distal radial 2 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 3
description: dorsal fin distal radial 3 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 4
description: dorsal fin distal radial 4 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 5
description: dorsal fin distal radial 5 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 6
description: dorsal fin distal radial 6 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 7
description: dorsal fin distal radial 7 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 8
description: dorsal fin distal radial 8 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 3
description: dorsal fin proximal radial 3 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 4
description: dorsal fin proximal radial 4 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 5
description: dorsal fin proximal radial 5 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 6
description: dorsal fin proximal radial 6 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 7
description: dorsal fin proximal radial 7 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 8
description: dorsal fin proximal radial 8 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: pars superior ear
description: The dorsal part of the ear. Comprises the three semicircular canals, which connect to the utricle.

name: pars inferior ear
description: The ventral portion of the ear. It contains the saccule and the laguena which are the primary auditory organs.

name: transverse canal
description: Duct that crosses the midline connecting the sacculi.

name: inner ear foramen
description: Foramen in the inner ear.

name: dorso-rostral cluster
description: Early-forming telencephalic neural cluster. Neurons of the dorso-rostral cluster (drc) extend axons to form the supra-optic tract (SOT) and the anterior commissure (AC). Ross et al., 1992.

name: ventro-rostral cluster
description: Early-forming neural cluster located in the rostral diencephalon. At 19 h, axons arising from the vrc grow caudally to pioneer the tract of the postoptic commissure (TPOC). Ross et al., 1992.

name: ventro-caudal cluster
description: Early-forming neural cluster of the ventral midbrain. At 16 h, axons of the vcc grow caudally to pioneer the medial longitudinal fasciculus (MLF), which is part of the larger ventral longitudinal tract (VLT). Later, neurons from this cluster project axons rostrally into the tract of the post-optic commissure (TPOC). Ross et al., 1992.

name: epiphysial cluster
description: Early-developing neuronal cluster of the epiphysis. By 24 hpf the pioneer axon of the dorsoventral diencephalic tract (DVDT) has arisen from the ec and grown ventrally. As this axon encounters axons of the TPOC, it makes a near-90 rostral turn and grows rostrally among axons of the TPOC growing in the opposite direction. Ross et al., 1992.

name: hemal prezygapophysis
description: Hemal prezygapophyses are paired, anteromedially directed processes arising from the bases of hemal arches, ligamentously joined to the hemal postzygapophyses of the preceding vertebra. Posterior caudal vertebrae close to the caudal fin lack hemal prezygopophyses.

name: obsolete eminentia thalami
description: Part of the forebrain that is ventral to the ventral thalamus and dorsal to the preoptic area. See page 44 of the Atlas of Early Zebrafish Brain Development.

name: obsolete vagal root
description: Part of cranial nerve X.

name: preplacodal ectoderm
description: Non neural ectoderm that surrounds the presumptive neural plate and gives rise to neurogenic placodes.

name: hyohyoideus
description: Is a hyoid muscle that inserts at the most anterior basibranchial and also at the posterior ends of the ceratohyals and functions in jaw closure.

name: dorsal adductor hyomandibulae
description: Is a hyoid muscle that attaches to the dorsomedial faces of the hyosymplectics.

name: pillar of the anterior semicircular canal
synonyms: ["anterior hub of the semicircular canal","anterior pillar","anterior pillar of the semicircular canal"]

name: pillar of the lateral semicircular canal
synonyms: ["lateral hub of the semicircular canal","ventral bar","ventral pillar","ventral piller of the semicircular canal"]

name: anal fin proximal radial element
description: Rod-like internal median skeletal support elememts of the anal fin, which articulate with the distal radial elements.

name: radial element
description: Radial elements are the internal skeletal supports of the median and paired fins.

name: pelvic fin radial element
description: Pelvic fin radial elements are internal skeletal supports of the pelvic fin.

name: basipterygium element
description: Endochondral element that is paired and supports the pelvic fin. The basipterygium has a posteromedial process called the ischiac process (Wietzman 1962).

name: anal fin distal radial element
description: Rod-like internal median skeletal support elements of the anal fin, which articulate with the lepidotrichia distally.

name: dorsal fin distal radial element
description: Rod-like internal median skeletal support elements of the dorsal fin, which articulate with the lepidotrichia distally.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial element
description: Rod-like internal median skeletal support elements of the dorsal fin, which articulate with the distal radial elements.

name: pectoral fin radial element
description: Pectoral fin radial elements are the internal skeletal supports of the pectoral fin which develop from the pectoral fin endoskeletal disc, supports the pectoral lepidotrichia or fin rays and connects the lepidotrichia with the primary pectoral girdle.

name: pectoral fin proximal radial element
description: Pectoral fin radial element which develops from the pectoral fin endoskeletal disc, supports a few pectoral lepidotrichia or fin rays and connects the lepidotrichia and distal radial elements with the primary pectoral girdle (scapula and coracoid).

name: pectoral fin distal radial element
description: Pectoral fin radial element that sometimes ossifies, develops from the pectoral fin endoskeletal disc, and is located at the proximal region of a lepidotrichium, between its hemitrichia. Pectoral fin distal radial element is paired.

name: dorsal fin middle radial element
description: Dorsal fin radial element that is the rod-like internal median skeletal support element of the dorsal fin located between the dorsal fin proximal radial element and dorsal fin distal radial element.

name: anal fin middle radial element
description: Anal fin radial element that is the rod-like internal median skeletal support element of the anal fin located between the anal fin proximal radial element and anal fin distal radial element.

name: anal fin radial element
description: Anal fin radial elements are internal skeletal supports of the anal fin.

name: dorsal fin radial element
description: Dorsal fin radial elements are internal skeletal supports of the dorsal fin.

name: pectoral fin proximal radial element 1
description: Pectoral fin proximal radial element that is the most anterior or dorsal pectoral fin radial element.

name: pectoral fin proximal radial element 2
description: Pectoral fin proximal radial element that is the second most anterior or dorsal pectoral fin radial element.

name: pectoral fin proximal radial element 3
description: Pectoral fin proximal radial element that is the third most anterior or dorsal pectoral fin radial element.

name: pectoral fin proximal radial element 4
description: Pectoral fin proximal radial element that is the fourth most anterior or dorsal pectoral fin radial element.

name: median fin radial element
description: Radial element that is part of a median fin.

name: anal fin proximal radial cartilage
description: anal fin proximal radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.
synonyms: ["basal radial of anal fin cartilage","proximal anal-fin radial cartilage"]

name: radial cartilage
description: radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: obsolete pelvic fin radial cartilage
description: pelvic fin radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: obsolete basipterygium cartilage
description: basipterygium element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: anal fin distal radial cartilage
description: anal fin distal radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: dorsal fin distal radial cartilage
description: dorsal fin distal radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

description: dorsal fin proximal radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

description: pelvic fin distal radial 2 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

description: pelvic fin distal radial 3 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: pelvic fin distal radial cartilage 1
description: pelvic fin distal radial 1 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

description: pectoral fin radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: pectoral fin proximal radial cartilage
description: pectoral fin proximal radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: pectoral fin distal radial cartilage
description: pectoral fin distal radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: dorsal fin middle radial cartilage
description: dorsal fin middle radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: anal fin middle radial cartilage
description: anal fin middle radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.
synonyms: ["anal fin medial radial cartilage","medial anal-fin radial cartilage"]

name: anal fin radial cartilage
description: anal fin radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: dorsal fin radial cartilage
description: dorsal fin radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial cartilage 1
description: dorsal fin proximal radial 1 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

description: dorsal fin proximal radial 2 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

description: pectoral fin proximal radial 1 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

description: dorsal fin distal radial 1 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

description: dorsal fin distal radial 2 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

description: dorsal fin distal radial 3 element that is composed of cartilage tissue.

name: alary cartilage
description: Paired, cup-shaped cartilage that are dorsal to the septomaxillae and anterior to the oblique cartilage. The anterior, convex face of each alary cartilage is synchondrotically fused to the superior prenasal cartilage and the ventral edge is fused to the superior margin of the crista intermedia.

name: alary process of premaxilla
description: Dorsal process that extends toward the nasal bone. The posterior (inner) face of each alary process is concave and is invested dorsomedially by the superior prenasal cartilage and ventromedially by the inferior prenasal cartilage.

name: alveolar foramen
description: Foramen for the R. alveolaris of Nerve VII and the alveolar artery.

name: angulosplenial coronoid process
description: Point of insertion of the adductor mandibulae musculature.

name: anterior maxillary process
description: Process that extends anteriorly from the planum triangulare and invests the medial face of the pars facialis of the maxilla.

name: anterior nasal wall
description: Paired, vertical, and relatively straight plates that form the anterior limit of the nasal capsule.

name: anterior process of pars palatina of maxilla
anterior ramus of pterygoid
description: In a triradiate pterygoid, the process that extends anteriorly towards the maxilla.

name: basal process of palatoquadrate
description: Process that extends medially from the ventromedial corner of the palatoquadrate cartilage and articulates or fuses to the anterior wall of the otic capsule via the basitrabecular process.

name: basicranial fenestra
description: Ventral opening of the neurocranium.

name: Bidder's organ
description: Anatomical structure which forms from an enlargement of the anterior portion of each gonad in all male bufonid larvae and consists of ovarian tissues.

name: obsolete blastomere
description: Undifferentiated cell that is produced by early cleavages of the fertilized egg (zygote).

name: braincase and auditory apparatus
description: The part of the skull that encloses the brain and surrounds the inner ear.

name: capsular process
description: Narrow process of the skeletal support that projects forward.

name: obsolete cartilage bridge of nasal skeleton
cartilago ectochoanalis
description: Lateral cartilaginous border of the fenestra endochoanalis.

name: cartilago orbitalis
description: Lateral wall of chondrocranial braincase between lamina orbitonasalis and pila metoptica.

name: cavum inferius
description: Accessory cavity located ventral to the cavum principale and cavum medius.

name: cavum medius
description: Small accessory cavity located between the cavum principale and cavum inferius.

name: cavum principale
description: The largest part of the nasal cavity, containing the olfactory epithelium.

name: hyale
description: Anterior-lateral projections from the corpus of the hyoid apparatus.

name: crista contacta
description: Thin, horizontal ridge that extends medially from the corpus of the septomaxilla; it lays on the lamina inferior.

name: crista intermedia
description: Paired, oblique plates of cartilage located ventral to the alary cartilages. The dorsomedial margin of each crista intermedia is fused to the transitional zone between the septum nasi and the tectum nasi, whereas the ventrolateral margin bears two laminae, the lamina superior and the lamina inferior.

name: crista subnasalis
description: Ventral crest of the paries nasi.

name: crista supraorbitalis
description: Short and blunt process that extends posteriorly from the posteromedial margin of the postnasal wall, on the anterodorsal corner of the orbit above the medial orbitonasal foramen.

name: obsolete dense connective tissue
description: Also known as fibrous connective tissue. Forms ligaments and tendons and is characterized by densely packed collagen fibers that have great tensile strength.

name: dilatatio alaris
description: Flange that extends ventrally from about the middle portion of the margo mandibularis.

name: extremitas anterior
description: Large anterior outgrowth of the septomaxilla that is directed into the space between the alary cartilage and the lamina inferior.

name: fenestra endochoanalis
description: Opening on the ventral aspect of the nasal capsule. It contains the apertura nasalis interna.

name: fenestra endonarina communis
description: Opening on the anterolateral aspect of the nasal capsule. It contains the apertura nasalis externa.

name: fenestra lateralis nasi
description: Opening on the lateral side of the nasal capsule.

name: fenestra nasobasalis
description: Small opening at the anterior tip of the nasal capsule, on the floor of the cavum inferius. It is located medially to the base of the inferior prenasal cartilage and serves for the passage of the ramus medialis narium and arteria orbitonasalis.

name: fenestra nasolateralis
description: Elongated opening located on the lateral side of the nasal capsule.

name: fenestra prechoanalis
description: Large opening of the nasal floor anterior to the fenestra endochoanalis.

name: footplate of pars media plectri
description: Independent, horizontal bar of cartilage located on the anterior part of the fenestra ovalis in front of the pars interna plectri.

name: frontoparietal fontanelle
description: Dorsal opening of the neurocranium.

name: hyolaryngeal complex
description: Complex formed by two units, the hyoid and laryngeal apparatuses, which are both derived from the larval hyobranchial skeleton.

name: inferior prenasal cartilage
description: Elongate cartilage that extends anteroventrally from the solum nasi to abut the ventral portion of the posterior aspect of the alary process of the premaxilla. It was first described by Wiedersheim in 1876.

name: infrarostral cartilage
description: Larval lower jaw lies anterior to Meckels cartilage.

name: lamella alaris
description: Dorsal plate of the squamosal.

name: lamina inferior
description: Lateral expansion of the crista intermedia that serves as the floor of the cavum medium.

name: lamina nariochoanalis
description: Free, dorsal margin of the lamina inferior.

name: lamina precerebralis
description: Posterior face of septum nasi.

name: lamina superior
description: Lateral expansion of the crista intermedia that serves as the roof of the cavum medium.

name: obsolete larval structure
description: Anatomical structure that is part of the larva.

name: margo mandibularis of pterygoid
description: Ventrally directed margin that connects the anterior and posterior rami of the pterygoid.

name: margo orbitalis of maxilla
description: Dorsal margin of the maxilla between the frontal and zygomatico-maxillary processes.

name: margo orbitalis of pterygoid
description: Margin that connects the anterior and medial rami of the pterygoid.

name: margo orbitalis of squamosal
description: Anterior margin of the squamosal that takes part in the formation of the orbit.

name: margo tympanicus of pterygoid
description: Margin that connects the posterior and medial rami of the pterygoid.

name: maxillopalatine
description: A compound bone consisting of maxilla and palatine, can also contain a prefrontal and/or lacrimal; present in adult Gymnophiona.

name: medial orbitonasal foramen
description: Opening on the postnasal wall for the medial branch (= ramus medialis nasi) of the ophthalmicus nerve.

name: medial ramus of pterygoid
description: In a triradiate pterygoid, the process that extends medially towards the otic capsule.

name: median prenasal process
description: Anterior projection of the septum nasi that protrudes through the anterior nasal wall.

name: nasopremaxilla
description: A compound bone consisting of premaxilla, nasal and sometimes septomaxilla in adult members of Caeciliidae and Typhlonectidae.

name: oblique cartilage
description: Semi-circular cartilaginous sheet that lies lateral to the side of the septum nasi.

name: orbitonasal foramen
description: Foramen that forms a passage for one of the branches of the trigeminal nerve into the nasal region.

name: obsolete os articulare
description: Ossified posterior articular portion of Meckel's cartilage.

name: os basale
description: A bone that forms both the floor of the braincase and the posterior part of the skull.

name: otic plate of pterygoid
description: Osseous expansion of the posterior and medial rami of the pterygoid.

name: otic ramus of squamosal
description: Ramus (process) that extends medially toward the otic capsule.

name: otoccipital
description: Fused prootic and exoccipital bones.

name: obsolete palatine
description: Sliver of bone that invest part of or all the posterior aspect of each antorbital plane.

name: obsolete palatine process of pars palatina of premaxilla
palatine process of the pars facialis of the maxilla
paranasal commissure
description: Cartilaginous bridge that extends posteriorly to the anterolateral corner of the posterior nasal wall.

name: cultriform process
description: Process that extends anteriorly from the orbitotemporal region.

name: subotic alae
description: Paired processes extending lateraly from the posterior body of the parasphenoid that, when present, support the otic capsules ventrally.

name: paries nasi
description: Paired, elongate, ventrolaterally-orieted cartilaginous structures that extend to the premaxilla-maxilla articulation.

name: pars articularis of mandibular arch
description: Posterior end of Meckel's cartilage that forms the articular head of the mandibular arch.

name: obsolete pars dentalis of maxilla
description: Tooth-bearing part of the maxilla.

name: obsolete pars dentalis of premaxilla
description: Tooth-bearing part of the premaxilla.

name: pars interna plectri
description: Plate-like structure that lies in the fenestra ovalis. It arises within the membrana opercularis in the posterior part of the fenestra.

name: obsolete pars palatina of maxilla
description: Lingual ledge on the inner surface of the maxilla.

name: obsolete pars palatina of premaxilla
description: Lingual ledge on the inner surface of the premaxilla.

name: perilymphatic system
description: Consists of enlarged cistern against which the operculum and footplate of the columella rest in the oval window. Together with the endolymphatic systems comprises the membranous labryinth of the inner ear. Duellman and Trueb 1994.

name: pila antoptica
description: A strut of cartilage  extending dorsally from the basal plate and with other similar cartilages forming the sides of the brain case. The pila antoptica is posterior to pila metoptica together with which it may enclose the foramen for the ocular motor nerve and opthalmica magna artery.

name: pila metoptica
description: A strut of cartilage  extending dorsally from the basal plate and with other similar cartilages forming the sides of the brain case. The pila metoptica is anterior to pila antoptica together with which it may enclose the foramen for the ocular motor nerve and opthalmica magna artery. Anterior to the pila antoptica is the pila preoptica (another pillar of cartilage) between these two cartilages emerges the optic and trochlear nerves.

name: planum terminale
description: Vertical plate of cartilage that is fused posterodorsally to the oblique cartilage and anteriorly to the lamina inferior.

name: planum triangulare
description: Cartilaginous, distal expansion of the lamina orbitonasalis that invests the pars facialis of the maxilla medially.

name: plectral apparatus
description: Complex sound-conducting anatomical structure.

name: posterior maxillary process
description: Process that extends posteriorly from the planum triangulare and invests the maxilla laterally and the anterior ramus of the pterygoid medially.

name: posterior ramus of pterygoid
description: In a triradiate pterygoid, the process that extends posterolaterally towards the jaw articulation.

name: postnasal wall
description: Paired, anteriorly concave structures that form the posterior limit of nasal capsule. It consists of two parts: a ventral piece, the lamina orbitonasalis, and a dorsal plate that is part of the tectum nasi.

name: prearticular coronoid process
description: Point of insertion of the masticatory musculature.

name: preorbital process of the pars facialis of the maxilla
processus ascendens plectri
description: Cartilaginous or ligamentous connection between the pars externa plectri and the crista parotica.

name: processus infrafenestralis
description: Posterior part of the corpus of the septomaxilla; the posterior surface of the processus infrafenestralis is in contact with the oblique cartilage.

name: processus lingualis of pterygoid
description: Dorsolateral process of the of the medial ramus of the pterygoid.

name: processus posterior of maxilla
description: Posterior, toothless portion of the maxilla by which it usually comes in contact with the quadratojugal.

name: processus pterygoideus of maxilla
description: Posterior end of the pars palatina of the maxilla that is in contact with the anterior ramus of the pterygoid.

name: processus zygomatico-maxillaris
description: Posterodorsal extension of the maxilla by which it establishes contact with the squamosal.

name: pseudodentary
description: Compound bone of adult Gymnophiona, consisting of dentary, coronoid and mentomeckelian.

name: pterygoid
description: Palatal bones of intramembranous origin that lie anterior to the otic capsules, lateral to the orbits, and medial to the maxillae.

name: pterygoid process of palatoquadrate
description: Process that extends anteriorly from the anterolateral margin of the palatoquadrate and articulates or synchondrotically fuses to the posterior end of the posterior maxillary process.

name: recessus marsupiatus of premaxilla
description: Is a recess on the surface of the premaxilla near to the base of the pars facialis.

name: recessus vaginiformis
description: Is a space on the interior surface of the pars facialis of the maxilla

name: retroarticular process
description: Bony process that is part of the articular and is the point of insertion of the m. interhuoideus posterior.

name: rostral process
description: Is a process of the nasal bone directed anteriorly towards the rostrum.

name: septum semicircularium anterior
description: The anterior connective tissue partition between walls of otic capsule around which the membranous semicircular canals pass.

name: septum semicircularium laterale
description: The lateral connective tissue partition between walls of otic capsule around which the membranous semicircular canals pass.

name: septum semircularium posterior
description: The posterior connective tissue partition between walls of otic capsule around which the membranous semicircular canals pass.

name: skeletal support for eminentia olfactoria
description: Elevation of the dorsal surface of the solum nasi medial to the fenestra endochoanalis that provides support for the eminentia olfactoria.

name: solum nasi
description: Unpaired, horizontal plate that forms the floor of the nasal capsule.

name: sphenethmoid
description: Endochondral bone that forms the anterior portion of the braincase and forms from one ossification center on each side of the orbital cartilage.

name: sulcus dentalis of maxilla
description: Groove located between the pars dentalis and the bases of the maxillary teeth.

name: sulcus dentalis of premaxilla
description: Groove located between the pars dentalis and the bases of the premaxillary teeth.

name: sulcus for Meckels cartilage
description: A groove on the palatoquadrate that is occupied by the Meckel's cartilage.

name: superior prenasal cartilage
description: Paired, elongate cartilages that extend anteroventrally to abut the dorsomedial margin of the posterior face of the alary process of the premaxilla. The function of these cartilages is to transmit the movement of the premaxilla to the alary cartilages during the closure of the apertura nasalis externa.

name: obsolete supraangular
description: The suprangular or surangular is a jaw bone found in most land vertebrates, except mammals. It's usually in the back of the jaw, on the upper edge, and is connected to all other jaw bones: dentary, angular, splenial and articular. It is often a muscle attachment site.

name: obsolete supraoccipital
description: Median, unpaired bone that can form the dorsal margin of the foramen magnum.

name: suprasphenoid
description: Endochondral ossification of the dorsomedial portion of the braincase.

name: taenia tecti marginalis
description: Cartilaginous connection between the orbital cartilage and otic capsules.

name: tectum nasi
description: Roof of the nasal capsule, confluent with lamina orbitonasalis posteriorly and united to septum nasi.

name: tympanosquamosal
description: Central, funnel-shaped, ossified portion of the tympanic annulus fused to the squamosal bone.

name: ventral ramus of squamosal
description: Longest of the three squamosal rami; it invests the dorsolateral margin of the palatoquadrate. The distal end of the ventral ramus invests the quadrate and articulates with the quadratojugal.

name: zygomatic ramus of squamosal
description: Ramus (process) that projects anteriorly from the dorsal body of the squamosal and forms part of the posterior margin of the orbit.

name: arcus praeoccipitalis
description: Skeletal structure that separates the inferior and superior perilymphatic foramina.

name: processus lingularis of nasal skeleton
description: Rod-shaped process that extends caudally from the inferior edge of the planum terminale.

name: corpus
description: Basal part of the septomaxilla.

name: margo libera
description: Anterior, rounded portion of the corpus of the septomaxilla.

name: crista interna
description: Sharp ridge that extends medially from the basal part of the processus infrafenestralis; it separates the diverticulum proncipale from the diverticulum medium.

name: crista praeopercularis
description: Synchondrotic or synostotic connection between the footplate of the pars media plectri and the ventral margin of the fenestra ovalis.

name: anterior process of vomer
description: Process that extends anterolaterally toward the maxilla-premaxilla articulation.

name: processus frontalis of maxilla
description: Anterio portion of the maxilla that may contact the nasal and take part in the formation of a groove for the nasolacrimal duct.

name: lamina anterior of maxilla
description: Most anterior part of the maxilla, which is in contact with the premaxilla.

name: fossa maxillaris
description: Depression lacated on the inner surface of the maxilla between the palatine process and the pars palatina.

name: pars glenoidalis of quadratojugal
description: Portion of the quadratojugal that makes contact dorsally with the distal portion of the squamosal.

name: pars jugalis
description: Anterior part of the quadratojugal that is in contact with the processus posterior of the maxilla.

name: processus dorsalis of lamella alaris
description: Dorsal process of the lamella alaris located at the anterior end of the margo orbitalis; a narrow ligament that runs from the frontoparietal is attached to it.

name: processus posterodorsalis of lamella alaris
description: Posterior process of the lamella alaris.

name: dentigerous process
description: Tooth-bearing process of the vomer.

name: prechoanal process
description: Process that extends laterally from the anterior process; its bifurcation from the postchoanal process occurs at the level of the dentigerous process.

name: postchoanal process
description: Process that extends laterally from the anterior process; its bifurcation from the prechoanal process occurs at the level of the dentigerous process.

name: margo choanalis
description: Margin between the prechoanal and postchoanal process. It bounds the fenestra endochoanalis.

name: crista vomeri
description: Ridge on the dorsal surface of the vomer that runs from the anterior to the postchoanal processes of the vomer; it takes part in the fixation of the bone to the lateral margin of the solum nasi.

name: processus posterior of parasphenoid
description: Posterior projection of the median part of the parsphenoid, which may extend over the posterior margins of the subotic alae.

name: hyoid plate
description: Azygous or paired bone that occurs on the ventral surface of the hyoid plate.

name: pars reuniens
description: Area of fusion of the ceratohyals.

name: hyoglossal sinus
description: Is the space along the anterior edge of the hyoid plate between the hyale and through which passes the hyoglossus muscle as it passes dorsally into the tongue.

name: anterolateral process of hyoid plate
description: Processes that flank the hyales laterally and extend anterolaterally from the anterolateral margin of the hyoid plate. They are formed as a result of new cartilaginous growth lateral to the basibranchial.

name: posterolateral process
description: Paired processes that extend posterolaterally from the posterolateral margin of the hyoid plate. These processes are formed as a result of new cartilaginous growth lateral to the basibranchial and hypobranchial plate.

name: posteromedial process
description: Cartilaginous, paired processes that extend posterolaterally from the posterior margin of the hyoid plate. These processes invest the laryngeal apparatus and are ossified in the adult.

name: bronchial process
description: Paired processes that extend posteroventrally from the anterolateral margins of the cricoid ring.

name: esophageal process
description: Median process located on the posterior end of the cricoid cartilage.

name: manubrium of hyale
description: Proximal section of the hyale.

name: sinus nervi hypoglossi
description: Depression that houses the hypoglossus nerve and is located between the anterolateral process and the proximal part of the hyale.

name: foramen nervi hypoglossi
description: Foramen that houses the hypoglossus nerve and is located between the anterolateral process and the proximal part of the hyale.

name: processus confluens
description: Strip of cartilage that forms the lateral margin of the foramen nervi hypoglossi.

name: prominentia apicalis dorsalis
description: Anterior end of the arytenoid cartilage.

name: prominentia apicalis ventralis
description: Posterior (cardiac) end of the arytenoid cartilage.

name: pedicel
description: Paired stalks located dorsolateral to the vertebral centrum that provide support to the lateral margins of the neural arch laminae.

name: atlantal cotyle
description: Anterior, single or paired concave facets for articulation with the condyle(s) of the urostyle.

name: posterior intervertebral notch
description: Indentation on the anterior margin of the pedicel. When two vertebrae articulate, the anterior notch of one vertebra and the posterior notch of the other create a bilateral intervertebral space.

name: intervertebral space
description: Space formed by the anterior and posterior intervertebral notches. The intervertebral spaces accommodate the spinal nerves as they emerge from the spinal canal.

name: anterior intervertebral notch
description: Indentation on the posterior margin of the pedicel. When two vertebrae articulate, the anterior notch of one vertebra and the posterior notch of the other create a bilateral intervertebral space.

name: pleurapophysis
description: Paired processes that represent the rib attachments to the vertebra plus the ribs.

name: procoelous
description: Holochordal vertebral centra that are concave anteriorly and convex posteriorly; they bear a condyle on the posterior end for the articulation with the posterior adjacent vertebral centrum, forming a ball-and-socket joint that allows extensive motion in most directions.

name: opisthocoelous
description: Ectochordal or stegochordal vertebral centra that are convex anteriorly and concave posteriorly; they bear a condyle on the anterior end for the articulation with the posterior adjacent vertebral centrum, forming a ball-and-socket joint that allows extensive motion in most directions.

name: epichordal
description: Vertebral centrum that originates from ossification of the dorsal portion of the perichordal tube; the resulting element tends to be depressed in cross section.

name: perichordal
description: Vertebral centrum that originates from ossification of the entire perichordal tube; the resulting element is cylindrical in cross section and may have an open (notochord retained) or solid center.

name: heterocoelous
description: Vertebral centrum that bears saddle-shaped articular surfaces at both ends, having a convexity in the right-left axis and a concavity in the dorsoventral axis. This morphology allows great lateral and vertical flexion.

name: acoelous
description: Vertebral centrum with flat ends. Between successive vertebrae there is a fibrocartilaginous intervertebral body with a gel-like core, the nucleus pulposus, which is derived from the embryonic notochord. Acoelous vertebrae seem especially suited to receive and distribute compressive forces within the vertebral column.

name: amphicoelous
description: Ectochordal, biconcave or terminally flat vertebral centrum. This design seems to allow limited motion in most directions. An intervertebral body (which may or may not be independent from the adjacent centra) fills the cavity between successive centra. The intervertebral body usually is formed by soft material that may be derived, at least in part, from the embryonic notochord.

name: ectochordal
description: Spool-shaped vertebral centrum with an open center in which the notochord lies.

name: holochordal
description: Spool-shaped vertebral centrum with a solid center. All traces of the notochord dissapear.

name: stegochordal
description: Vertebral centrum that is depressed dorsoventrally and solid. All traces of the notochord dissapear.

name: haemal arch lamina
description: Paired plates that form the haemal arch. The lateral margin of each lamina is firmly attached to the ventral surface of the caudal vertebral centrum and the medial end fuses to the medial end of the opposite lamina.

name: nucal keel
description: Longitudinal process found in all cervical vertebrae, except the atlas, for the attachment of dorsal head musculature.

name: foramen nutritium
description: Opening on the lateral side of the vertebra for the passage of blood vessels.

name: mid-dorsal keel
description: Ridge-shaped structure present on the dorsomedial surface of the neural arch lamina; this structure is produced at the point of junction of the contralateral sides of each neural arch.

name: obsolete deltopectoral crest
description: Ridge on the ventral aspect of the humeral shaft. It serves for the attachment of the mm pectoralis and shoulder musculature used primarily for limb adduction.

name: sacral condyle
description: Anterior, paired convex facets for articulation with the cotyle(s) of the urostyle.

name: urostyle cotyle
description: Anterior, single or paired concave facets for articulation with the sacral condyle(s).

name: webbing of bone in vertebral column
description: In anurans, pair of bony plates that connect the posteromedial margins of the sacral diapophyses with the lateral margins of the anterior portion of the urostyle.

name: urostyle ridge
description: Longitudinal crest on the dorsal side of the urostyle formed by the caudal neural arches.

name: suprascapula
description: Paired, cartilaginous elements located in the dorsolateral shoulder region. Each suprascapula is a flat broad blade that extends medially.

name: pars acromialis
description: Prominent structure (anteromedial head) that forms the anterior section of the ventral margin of the scapula.

name: pars glenoidalis of scapula
description: Concave structure (posteromedial head) that forms the posterior head of the ventral margin of the scapula. The pars glenoidalis articulates with the humerus, and comprises the dorsal portion of the glenoid fossa.

name: crista dorsalis humeri
description: Small hooked process on the dorsal aspect of the humeral shaft; it does not extend on to the glenoid head. The m subscapularis is inserted on it.

name: zonal area
description: All those parts of the pectoral girdle ventral and medial to the glenoid fossa.

name: omosternum
description: Proximal portion of the prezonal element of the pectoral girdle. It may be a flat, midventral cartilaginous structure or a calcified or bony element elaborated into a stylum.

name: epicoracoid
description: Paired, flat cartilaginous arches that compose the central portion of the zonal area, unites the clavicle and coracoid of each half of the pectoral girdle, and form the medial margins of the pectoral fenestrae.

name: epicoracoid bridge
description: A pair of cartilaginous expansions (one from each epicoracoid cartilage) that project anteriorly. They articulate anteriorly with the omosternum.

name: acetabular depression
description: The central, most concave portion of the acetabulum, which remains open.

name: ilial ridge
description: Longitudinal crest on the dorsal side of the shaft of the ilium.

name: ilial shaft
description: Anterior rod that articulates with the sacrum.

name: obsolete ilial corpus
description: Posterior body of the ilium that forms the anterior half of the acetabulum.

name: glenoid foramen
description: Opening on the glenoid fossa.

name: epicoracoid horn
description: A pair of cartilaginous expansions (one from each epicoracoid cartilage) that project posteriorly. They articulate with the sternum by means of grooves, pouches or fossae in the dorsal surface of the sternum and provide a site for the insertion of a pair of muscles derived from the m. rectus abdominis.

name: supracoracoid foramen
description: Opening on the scapulocoracoid bone through which passes the n. supracoracoideus and the corresponding artery and vein.

name: pectoral fenestra
description: Ovoid space on the pectoral girdle limited anteriorly by the procoracoid, medially by the epicoracoid, and posteriorly by the coracoid.

name: incisura coracoidea
description: Notch that separates the cartilaginous regions of the procoracoid and coracoid.

name: fovea capitis of humerus
description: Ovoid roughened pit, which is situated a little below and behind the center of the head, and serves as a site of attachment for ligaments.

name: ulnar condyle
description: Semi-elliptical ball located at the lower end of the humerus, adjacent to the humeral ball.

name: trochlear groove of humerus
description: Furrow between the humeral head and the ulnar condyle.

name: fossa cubitalis ventralis
description: Depresion on the distal end of the humerus, just anterior to the humeral head, in which the end of the radius fits when the forelimb is flexed.

name: collum antibrachii
description: In a fused radio-ulna, the proximal portion of the compound bone (where the sulcus longitudinalis is barely evident or absent) is a cylindrical pillar.

name: anterior ramus of cleithrum
description: Subdivision of the cleithrum that extends along the anterior edge of the suprascapula.

name: anomocoelous
description: Stegochordal slightly biconcave or flat terminally vertebral centrum. Each intervertebral cartilage is subdivided anteriorly and posteriorly, producing a free intervertebral element between adjacent vertebrae. This element subsequently ossifies and remains free.

name: displasiocoelous
description: Vertebral column in which the first seven vertebrae have holochordal centra and the intervertebral cartilages are posteriorly subdivided in the procoelous manner. The eighth presacral vertebra has a holochordal centrum and the intervertebral cartilage is subdivided in the opisthocoelous manner. Thus, the first seven presacral vertebrae are concave anteriorly and convex posteriorly, whereas the eighth is biconcave.

name: imbricate neural arch
description: Overlapping neural arches that obscure the spinal cord dorsally.

name: non-imbricate neural arch
description: Neural arches that do not overlap, thus exposing the spinal cord dorsally.

name: presacral shield
description: Dorsal, dermal plate of bone that overlies the presacral vertebrae. Such shield usually has irregular, sculptured surfaces, frequently is broadly expanded, and may be composed of several separate plates.

name: cartilago paraglenoidalis
description: Strip of cartilage that separates the coracoid from the scapula.

name: intercotylar space
description: Space between the atlantal cotyles.

name: caput glenoidale
description: Convex articular facet of the vertebral centrum for the articulation with the adjacent centrum.

name: fossa glenoidalis
description: Concave articular facet of the vertebral centrum for the articulation with the adjacent centrum.

name: sulcus articularis lateralis
description: In a zygapophysis that has ridges and sulci, the lateral canal between the carina distalis and the carina medialis.

name: sulcus articularis medialis
description: In a zygapophysis that has ridges and sulci, the medial canal between the carina medialis and the carina proximalis.

name: carina proximalis
description: In a zygapophysis that has ridges and sulci, the proximal ridge.

name: carina medialis
description: In a zygapophysis that has ridges and sulci, the medial ridge.

name: carina distalis
description: In a zygapophysis that has ridges and sulci, the distal ridge.

name: parasagittal processes
description: Paired, posteriorly directed process at the posterior margin of each neural arch lamina.

name: accessory articulation
description: Paired, additional vertebral articulations located medial to the intervertebral space, adjacent to the vertebral centrum.

name: fissura sagittalis
description: Medial groove in the longitudinal ridge of the urostyle formed by the incomplete dorsal fusion of the caudal neural arches.

name: glenoid end of clavicle
description: Lateral end of the clavicle, which usually lies in close proximity to the pars acromialis of the scapula, and occassionally may fuse to it.

name: sulcus pro cartilagine praecoracoidealis
description: Canal on the posterior aspect of the clavicle that accomodates the anterior margin of the procoracoid cartilage.

name: glenoid head of coracoid
description: Lateral end of the coracoid, which forms the medial portion of the glenoid fossa.

name: sternal head of coracoid
description: Medial end of the coracoid, which is synchondrotically fused to the epicoracoid cartilage.

name: margo fenestralis
description: Anterior margin of the coracoid, which forms the posterior edge of the pectoral fenestra.

name: margo posterior
description: Posterior margin of the coracoid.

name: margo anterior of scapula
description: Anterior margin of the scapula.

name: margo clavicularis
description: Inferior margin of the pars acromialis of the scapula, which articulates with the clavicule.

name: margo posterior of scapula
description: Posterior margin of the scapula.

name: margo suprascapularis
description: Superior margin of the scapula, which articulates with the suprascapula.

name: pars suprascapularis
description: Superior portion of the scapula, which is thinner than the rest of the shaft.

name: sinus interglenoidalis
description: Notch or indentation between the pars glenoidalis and pars acromialis of the scapula.

name: tenuitas cristaeformis
description: Leading (anterior) portion of the scapula, which is thinner than the rest of the shaft.

name: crista longitudinalis scapula
description: Longitudinal ridge on the medial (inner) face of the scapula.

name: margo anterior of cleithrum
description: Anterior margin of the anterior ramus of the cleithrum.

name: margo posterior of cleithrum
description: Posterior margin of the posterior ramus of the cleithrum.

name: margo scapularis
description: Lateral margin of the suprascapula, which articulates with the scapula.

name: margo vertebralis
description: Medial margin of the suprascapula, which lies dorsal to the vertebral column.

name: spina acromioidea
description: Small process of the lamina recurvata that extends laterally toward the scapular-suprascapular articulation.

name: anterior lamina recurvata
description: Portion of the anterior ramus of the cleithrum that invest the anterior margin of the suprascapula, extending onto its dorsal surface.

name: sinus dorsalis
description: Notch or indentation between the anterior and posterior rami of the cleithrum.

name: posterior lamina recurvata
description: Portion of the posterior ramus of the cleithrum that invests the posterior margin of the suprascapula, extending onto its dorsal surface.

name: crista lateralis humeri
description: Ridge on the lateral aspect of the humeral shaft located just anterior to the radial (lateral) epicondyle.

name: crista medialis humeri
description: Ridge on the medial aspect of the humeral shaft that extends from the level of the middle portion of the shaft to ulnar (medial) epicondyle.

name: crista radii
description: Small ridge on the lateral aspect of the radial shaft, located at the level of the collum antibrachii.

name: capitulum of radius
description: Lateral portion of the proximal (upper) articular surface of the radius that consists of an eminence with a rounded apex.

name: obsolete capitulum radii
description: Small eminence on the distal articular head of the radius.

name: capitulum ulnae
description: Small eminence on the distal articular head of the ulna.

name: sulcus longitudinalis
description: In a fused radio-ulna, longitudinal furrow that demarcates the area of fusion of both elements. This sulcus is deep in the distal portion of the compound bone, but barely evident or absent at the proximal end.

name: element Y of fore mesopodium
description: Oval carpal element that is located on the anteromedial side of the radiale and the anterolateral side of the ulnare. Anteriorly, it articulates with carpals 1 through 4 (or 2 through 5 according to some authors). It is also recognized as centrale by some authors. This element originates from one, two, or three condensation centers. Occasionally it may fuse to carpal 2(1), carpal 3(2), the ulnare, or other elements.

name: intercalary element of fore digit
description: Small elements present in all digits of the manus, when present in a taxon. Each intercalary element articulates with the anteroventral end of the penultimate phalanx proximally and the distal phalanx distally.

name: foramen perforans carpi
description: Opening for the passage of the perforans carpi artery from the ventral to the dorsal side. It perforates the compound ulnare + intermedium.

name: pubo-ischium
description: Composite element formed by the fusion of the ischium and pubis.

name: epileon
description: Dorsal extremity of the ilial shaft, which remains cartilaginous.

name: agger limitans anterior of ilium
description: Shelf-like expansion of the ilial corpus that forms the anterior border of the acetabulum.

name: agger limitans anterior of ischium
description: Shelf-like expansion of the ischium that forms the posterior border of the acetabulum.

name: obsolete supra-acetabular expansion
description: Dorsal portion of the ilial corpus, located above the acetabulum.

name: ilial protuberance
description: Small, dorsolaterally projecting knob located just anterior to the supra-acetabular expansion and about the level of the anterior border of the acetabulum.

name: preacetabular expansion
description: Ventral portion of the ilial corpus, located anteroventral to the acetabulum.

name: fossula tuberis superioris
description: Small depression dorsal to the proximal portion of the collum ilei and ventral to the ilial protuberance.

name: collum ilei
description: Cyllindrical pillar that originates anterior to the acetabulum and extends to the ilial shaft.

name: pars cylindriformis ilei
description: Elongate, cylindrical structure on the ventral side of the shaft of the ilium that extends through its entire length.

name: crista ischii
description: Crest on the posterior side of the ischium, which may also extend to the posteroventral aspect of pubis.

name: spina pelvis posterior
description: Small, rounded process on the anterodorsal margin of the ischium, just posterior to the area of articulation with the ilium.

name: spina pelvis anterior
description: Small, rounded process on the anteroventral margin of the preacetabular expansion of the ilial corpus.

name: intumescentia bilateralis inferior
description: Small protuberance on the ischium, located close to its posteroventral margin.

name: intumescentia bilateralis superior
description: Small protuberance on the ischium, located at the level of the superior margin of the acetabulum and close to its posterior margin.

name: incisura terminalis
description: Small indentation on the posterior margin of the ischium, ventral to the intumescentia bilateralis superior.

name: crista hypertrophica ischium
description: Large protuberance on the dorsal aspect of the ischium that extends from the ischio-ilium articulation to the spina pelvis posterior.

name: interilial region
description: Area of convergence of the ilial shafts. When the preacetabular ilium is narrow, the interilial configuration is V-shaped or narrowly rounded, whereas when the interilial region is broadly expanded the interilial configuration is U-shaped.

name: recessus coccygealis
description: Area dorsal to the pelvic girdle symphysis, between the dorsal portions of the ilial corpora, where lies the posterior terminus of the urostyle.

name: epipubis
description: Small prepubic element formed by a plate of cartilage (which may calcify in the adult) that is synchondrotically united with the pubis.

name: obsolete Nobelian bone
description: Paired cartilaginous rods that lie within the copulatory organ (or so-called tail) and are attached to the posteroventral part of the pelvic girdle.

name: ypsiloid cartilage
description: Y-shaped cartilage lying in the middle line, anterior to the pubo-ischium with which it articulates. It lies dorsal to the rectus abdominis muscle with which it articulates.

name: femoral ridge
description: Low crest that arises just behind the acetabular head and extends distally for about one-third the length of the femoral shaft.

name: obsolete trochlear groove of femur
description: Canal on the posteroventral surface of the femoral head, which articulates with the ischial process on the rim of the acetabulum.

name: foveal depression
description: Ovoid roughened pit situated on the dorsal and anteroventral surface of the acetabular head wherein the ligaments attaching the bone to the acetabulum are inserted.

name: trochanteric crest
description: Paired ridges on the ventral surface of the femoral shaft that run toward the femoral trochanter; the posterior crest is less developed.

name: tibial crest
description: Ridge that arises from the dorso-masial side of the extensor surface of the tibia. It receives the insertion of the tendon of the extensor ilio-tibialis muscle.

name: apophysis distalis of tibiofibula
description: Swelling on the extensor surface of the distal head of the tibiofibula.

name: caput ossis cruris
description: Proximal head of the tibiofibula that articulates with the distal head of the femur.

name: sulcus pro musculo extensori cruris brevis
description: Small canal on the proximal head of to the tibiofibula, lateral to the apophysis distalis, for the insertion of the cruris brevis muscle.

name: eminentia arcuata
description: Small crest on the extensor surface of the proximal head of the tibiofibula (tibial side).

name: sulcus distalis ossis cruris
description: In a fused tibiofibula, longitudinal furrow in the distal portion of the compound bone that demarcates the area of fusion of both elements.

name: sulcus proximalis ossis cruris
description: In a fused tibiofibula, longitudinal furrow in the proximal portion of the compound bone that demarcates the area of fusion of both elements.

name: foramen nutritium exterius
description: Foramen for the tibial artery and vein and the deep peroneal nerve; it pierces through the midpoint of the shaft of the tibiofibula.

name: spatium intertarsale
description: Separation of the tibiale and fibulare along their longitudinal axia.

name: apophysis proximalis
description: Swelling on the extensor surface of the proximal compound head of the tibiale and fibulare.

name: apophysis distalis of tibiale fibulare
description: Swelling on the extensor surface of the distal compound head of the tibiale and fibulare.

name: element Y of hind mesopodium
description: Oval tarsal element that is located on the anteromedial side of the tibiale. Anteriorly, it articulates with the proximal prehallux, tarsals 1, 2, and 3.

name: prehallux skeleton
description: One to three or four elements located ventral and medial to the metatarsal of digit I. When more than one elements are present, they are smaller than the proximal prehallux.

name: intercalary element of hind digit
description: Small elements present in all digits of the pes, when present in a taxon. Each intercalary element articulates with the anteroventral end of the penultimate phalanx proximally and the distal phalanx distally.

name: foramen perforans tarsi
description: Small opening between the centrale and fibulare that allows the perforans tarsi artery to pass from the ventral to the dorsal side of the ankle.

name: obsolete scapular area
description: Dorso-lateral portion of the pectoral girdle.

name: zonal element
description: All those parts of the pectoral girdle in the central region of the zonal area.

name: prezonal element
description: All those parts of the pectoral girdle that lie anterior to the zonal area.

name: postzonal element
description: All those parts of the pectoral girdle that lies posterior to the zonal area.

name: arciferal girdle
description: Pectoral girdle in which the epicoracoid cartilages are elaborated into posteriorly directed epicoracoid horns. Most arciferal pectoral girdles are characterized by fusion of the epicoracoid cartilages in the interclavicle region. Posterior to the clavicles, the epicoracoids usually are free and overlapping.

name: firmisternal girdle
description: Pectoral girdle that lacks epicoracoid horns. The sternum is fused to the pectoral arch, and the epicoracoid cartilages of each half of the girdle are fused to one another. The midzonal length of the girdle is shorter than that of an arciferal girdle, but pre- and postzonal elements tend to be longer.

name: pseudofirmisternal girdle
description: Modified arciferal pectoral girdle in which the fusion of the epicoracoid cartilages in the interclavicle region is extended posteriorly. Thus, the cartilages no longer overlap freely, and functionally a partially firmisternal condition is created.

name: pseudoarciferal girdle
description: Modified firmisternal pectoral girdle in which the epicoracoid cartilages are partly free and overlapping; however, the epicoracoids are fused to one another and the sternum postermodially.

name: inscriptional rib
description: Three pairs of cartilaginous elements posterior to the sternum that lie in the myosepta of the ventral trunk musculature.

name: articular process
description: Paired processes located on the anterior end of the cricoid cartilage.

name: posterior ramus of cleithrum
description: Laminar subdivision of the cleithrum that extends along the ventral (lateral) midbody of the suprascapula.

name: os triangulare
description: Small, broadly triangular bar of bone lying across the ventral side of the pharynx at the junction of the M. genio-hyoideus and the M. rectus cervicis superficialis.

name: anterior radial
description: Paired, horn-like processes of basibranchial I that protrude in an antero-dorso-lateral direction, being more or less embedded in the tongue musculature. These elements contitute the hypohyals.

name: posterior radial
description: Paired, horn-like processes of basibranchial I that protrude in an antero-dorso-lateral direction, being more or less embedded in the tongue musculature. They arise secondarily during metamorphosis, and are therefore not strictly part of the visceral skeleton.

name: ceratobranchials II--IV
description: Paired bars that articulate with hypobranchial II. Reduction of loss of these elements is common in salamanders.

name: hypobranchial I
description: Paired bar that articulates with basibranchial I. It forms the anterior portion of the posterior cornu of the hyoid.

name: ceratobranchial I
description: Paired bar that articulates with, or is fused to, hypobranchial I. It forms the posterior portion of the posterior cornu of the hyoid.

name: hypobranchial II
description: Paired bar that articulates anteriorly with basibranchial I and posteriorly with ceratobranchials II--IV.

name: obsolete basihyal
description: Paired, anterior element that articulates medially with basibranchial I and posterolaterally with the paired hypohyals.

name: external integument structure
description: Structures of the dermis, epidermis, glands and pigment cells recognizable on the external surfaces of the integument.

name: basale commune (carpal)
description: Amalgamation of distal carpals 1 and 2.

name: angulosplenial
description: Dermal bone of anuran lower jaw investing lingual and ventral surfaces of Meckel's cartilage; forming coronoid process and articulating with palatoquadrate posteriorly.

name: head external integument structure
description: Dermal, epidermal, glandular and pigment structures of the external head integument.

name: body external integument structure
description: Dermal, epidermal, glandular and pigment structures of the body integument.

name: limb external integument structure
description: Dermal, epidermal, glandular and pigment structures of the limb integument.

name: tail external integument structure
description: Dermal, epidermal, glandular and pigment structures of the tail integument.

name: obsolete principal cavity
description: The largest part of the nasal cavity, containing the olfactory epithelium.

name: suprarostral cartilage
description: Larval upper jaws articulate with trabecular horns.

name: basale commune (tarsal)
description: Amalgamation of distal tarsals 1 and 2.

name: pit organ
description: Mechanoreceptive organ of the lateral line, smaller than neuromasts, they are located on the surface of the epidermis. These receptors receive afferent and efferent innervation.

name: larval chondrocranium
description: Cartilaginous larval skull.

name: M. glutaeus magnus
description: Originates from the superior process of the ilium and inserts on the aponeuronis of the M. cruralis.

name: M. tensor fasciae latae
description: Originates on the ventro-lateral aspect of the ala ossis ilei and the ventral surface of the iliacus externus. Inserts on the lateral surface of the cruralis, the dorso-lateral surface of the gluteus magnus, and on the aponeurosis of the cruralis.

name: M. sartorius
description: Originates on the ventral pelvic rim, the pubic region, and the ventral surface of the adductor longus. The insertion bifurcates distally; the ventral portion attaches to the aponeurosis of the cruralis and the dorsal part attaches to the distal attachment of the gracilis major, the semitendinosus, and to the aponeurosis of the cruralis.

name: obsolete gonochoristic organism
description: Multi-cellular organism that has male and female sexes.

name: M. semitendinosus
description: Originates by two tendons: one on the postero-ventral aspect of the pelvic rim, the other, a dorsal tendon from the postero-dorsal pelvic rim under the ventral edge of M. semimembranosus. Inserts on the ventral surface of the tibiofibula.

name: protandrous hermaphroditic organism
description: Sequential hermaphroditic organism that produces gametes first of the male sex, and then later of the female sex.

name: protogynous hermaphroditic organism
description: Sequential hermaphroditic organism that produces gametes first of the female sex, and then later of the male sex.

name: centrale 1
description: Distal-most centrale when two are present.

name: M. quadratus femoris
description: Originates on the ventro-lateral border of the ischium and inserts on the ventro-medial surface of the femur at the base of caput femoris.

name: M. gemellus
description: Originates from the dorso-lateral margin of the ischium and inserts on the medial surface of the femur.

name: dermal annular fold
description: A dermal fold surrounding the body reflecting body segmentation. Found in Caecilians.

name: centrale (fore)
description: Rectangular cartilage or bone between the distal basal commune and the proximal intermedium.

name: anterior quadratocranial commissure
description: Cartilage that bridges palatoquadrate to ethmoid region.

name: M. gracilis major
description: Originates by a broad tendon from the postero-ventral surface of the pelvic rim and inserts by two tendons. One broad tendon inserts on the knee aponeurosis, and in part on the ventro-medial surface of the tibiofibula. The other long tendon inserts on the posterior surface of the tibiofibula just below the proximal head.

name: M. gracilis minor
description: Originates from the pelvic rim just ventral to the anus and merges with M. gracilis major. M. gracilis minor also attaches to the skin.

name: M. semimembranosus
description: Originates on the ventro-lateral surface of the ischium below the anus and inserts on the ventro-medial aspect of the femur and the head of the tibiofibula by a stout tendon, which is formed by the ventral origin of the plantaris longus.

name: intermedium (fore)
description: Quadrangular cartilage or bone lying between the preaxial radiale and the postaxial ulnare in the proximal level of the mesopodium.

name: M. ileo-fibularis
description: Originates from the ventral border of the ala ossis ilei just posterior to the origin of M. glutaeus maximus. Insterts in the aponeurosis covering the knee joint.

name: M. pyriformis
description: Originates on the dorso-lateral border of the distal urostyle and inserts on the dorsal surface of the crista femoris. This muscle inserts between the M. ilio-fibularis/M. glutaeus magnus and M. semimembranosus.

name: centrale 2
description: The proximal-most rectangular cartilage or bone when two centralelia are present.

name: M. ileo-femoralis
description: Originates from the postero-ventral surface of the ala ossis ilei and from the insertion tendon of M. ileo-fibularis. Inserts along the dorso-medial border of the femur.

name: M. iliacus internus
description: Muscle originates on the ventral border of the ala ossis ilei to insert on the dorso-medial surface of the femur.

name: M. iliacus externus
description: Originates on the ventral and lateral surfaces of the ala ossis ilei and inserts on the postero-dorsal face of the caput femoris.

name: M. pulmonum proprius
description: Originates along the connective tissue covering the dorsal surface of the lung and inserts on the dorsal surface of the femur. Muscle found only in Pipa.

name: M. tibialis posticus
description: Originates on the entire medial surface of the shaft of the tibiofibula. Inserts on the tibiale by a long tendon proximo-lateral to the insertion of the medial belly of M. tibialis anticus longus.

name: M. tibialis anticus longus
description: Originates on the ventro-lateral surface of the medial condyle of the femur. Its tendon extends in a groove over the knee in the lateral surface of the tibiofibular head, and penetrates the M. peroneus tendon. Insertion is by a lateral and medial head on the dorso-lateral surface of the fibulare and the medial border of the proximal end of the tibiale respectively.

name: M. extensor cruris brevis
description: Originates by a slender tendon from the ventral surface of the medial condyle of the femur and passes over the knee to insert as a fleshy belly on the ventro-lateral surface of the tibiofibula.

name: M. tibialis anticus brevis
description: Originates from the dorso-lateral surface of the tibiofibula and inserts on the proximo-medial surface of the tibiale dorsal to the medial head of M. tibialis anticus longus.

name: basitrabecular process
description: A process of the otic capsule that will bridge to the palatoquadrate basal process.

name: villosities
description: Small hair or nipple like projection on the integument.

name: quadratoethmoid process
description: Process that projects from anterior margin of commissure as site of attachment for quadratoethmoid ligament.

name: M. tarsalis posticus
description: Originates on the medial border of the ligamentum calcanei and inserts along the ventral surface of the tibiale.

name: M. plantaris profundus
description: Originates on the medial half of the ligamentum calcanei and inserts along the dorsal surface of the aponeurosis plantaris and extends to the level of the base of the prehallux.

name: obsolete musculus rectus superior
description: Cranial nerve III innervated; dorsal in the rectus group.

name: obsolete musculus rectus inferior
description: Cranial nerve III innervated; ventral in the rectus group.

name: anterodorsal lateral line nerve (ADLLN)
description: Sensory nerve of the anterior lateral line component. It develops from the preotic anterodorsal placode. ADLLN branches into two rami innervating orbital lines of neuromasts.

name: anteroventral lateral line nerve (AVLLN)
description: Sensory nerve of the anterior lateral line component. It develops from preotic anteroventral placode. AVLLN innervates lower jaw lines of neuromasts.

name: obsolete musculus rectus medialis
description: Cranial nerve III innervated; medial in the rectus group.

name: posterior lateral line nerve (PLLN)
description: Sensory nerve of the posterior lateral line component. It develops from de postotic posterior placode. PLLN innervates the trunk lines of neuromasts.

name: obsolete musculus obliquus inferior
description: Cranial nerve III innverated; ventral in the obliquus group.

name: quadrato-orbital commissure
description: Cartilage that bridges palatoquadrate muscular process to dorsal orbitonasal plate.

name: musculus levator bulbi
description: Cranial nerve V innervated; ventral to the eye.

name: middle lateral line nerve (MLLN)
description: Sensory nerve of the posterior lateral line component. It develops from the postotic middle placode. MLLN innervates neuromasts located over the otic capsule and the suprabranchial line of neuromasts.

name: fringe on postaxial edge of finger IV
taeniae tecti marginalis
description: Compose lateral rim of frontoparietal fenestra, ventrally confluent with orbital cartilages, posteriorly confluent with tectum synoticum.

name: taenia tecti transversalis
description: Cartilaginous connection that partitions frontoparietal fenestra into anterior and posterior regions. Often persists form larva into adults.

name: orbital cartilages
description: Forms lateral walls of braincase, confluent posteriorly with otic capsules via taenia tecti marginalis and anteriorly with lamina orbitonasalis via sphenethmoid commissure.

name: taenia tecti medialis
description: Cartilaginous connection between the taenia tecti transversalis to the tectum synoticum, and subdividing the parietal fenestra into left and right fenestrae. Often persist from larva to adult.

name: M. cruralis
description: Originates from the anterior surface of the hip joint capsule between the iliacus internus and the pectineus. Inserts by an aponeurosis attaching to the condyles of the femur and on the head of the cruris. This continues over the cruris to cover the tibialis anticus longus and peroneus to insert on the dorsal surface of those muscles.

name: obsolete trabecular plate
description: Ventral plate anterior to and confluent with ethmoid plate.

name: trabecular horn
description: Anterior extensions.

name: occipital arch
description: Posterior chondrocranium forming ventral and lateral margins of foramen magnum, medial to otic capsules.

name: odontoids
description: Toothlike processes found on the mandible of some anurans; can be formed by dentary or dentary + mentomeckelian bones; odontoids lack enamel and dentine present in true teeth.

name: otic operculum
description: Plate of cartilage occluding fenestra ovalis.

name: lacrimal
description: Investing bone in non-teleosts associated with nasolacrimal duct and lying between pars facialis of maxilla and prefrontal and sometimes nasal.

name: fringe on postaxial edge of toe V
subarticular tubercles
description: Is a integumentary structure located on the ventral surface of the hand and/or foot. Found at the junction between, in the hand, the metacarpal and most proximal phalanx of the digit and between phalanges, and in the foot between the metatarsal and most proximal phalanx of the digit and between phalanges.

name: mediale
description: A recurrent variant of salamanders; a rhomboidal cartilage lying immediately postaxial from the centrale or centrale 1.

name: lateral appendix
description: A small lateral diverticulum of the nasal cavity found in anuran larvae.

name: lateral recess
description: A part of the inferior cavity of the olfactory organ, found in anurans.

name: vasculature of respiratory integument
description: Blood vessels in respiratory skin.

name: postminimus
description: A rounded  cartilage lying in the postaxial margin of the mesopodium, adjacent to the distal end of the fibulare.

name: obsolete carotid
description: Either of two arteries which carry blood to the head.

name: obsolete external carotid
description: An artery which supplies blood to the muscles of the tongue and floor of the mouth via four major branches.

name: obsolete internal carotid
description: An artery which supplies the upper jaw and cranium.

name: obsolete orbital region
description: An anatomical cluster that is part of the cranium and structurally supports the eye.

name: Nobelian rod
description: Either of a pair of cartilaginous rods that support the intromittent organ of male Ascaphus, and are attached to the posteroventral part of the pelvic girdle.

name: phallodeum
description: Eversible phalloid portion of the cloaca that is inserted in the female's vent during copulation. Found in male Caecillians.

name: intromittent organ (Ascaphus type)
description: A tail like posterior extension of the cloaca supported by a pair of Nobelian rods

name: obsolete asexual organism
description: Multi-cellular organism that does not produce gametes.

name: obsolete cell space
description: Anatomical space that is part of a cell.

name: obsolete epithelial cell
description: Cell which has as its part a cytoskeleton that allows for tight cell to cell contact and which has apical-basal cell polarity.

name: obsolete obsolete single cell organism
description: Cell that is an individual member of a species.

name: obsolete tip
description: Anatomical point that is the apex of a projection or anything long and tapered; can be bony or cartilage.

name: obsolete animal blastomere
description: Pigmented, smaller blastomere of the animal (upper) hemisphere of the cleaving embryo.

name: obsolete vegetal blastomere
description: Unpigmented, larger blastomere of the vegetal (lower) hemisphere of the cleaving embryo.

name: obsolete bottle cell
description: Cell type that is first to migrate inwards at the blastopore during gastrulation.

name: obsolete chondrocyte
description: Polymorphic cell type that forms cartilage.

name: obsolete fibroblast
description: A connective tissue cell that secretes an extracellular matrix rich in collagen and other macromolecules.

name: obsolete primordial germ cell
description: Primitive cell type that is involved in the reproduction of the organism beginning with the sexual differentiation of the gonads at NF stage 52. In males specifically, it migrates from the genital ridge cortical region into the medullary tissue, where it forms spermatogonia. In females it is embedded in the cortical region and multiplies as oogonia.

name: obsolete spermatozoon
description: A mature male germ cell that develops from a spermatid.

name: obsolete primary oogonium
description: A germ cell that is a primordial oocyte in a female and that develops into secondary oogonia by mitotic division.

name: obsolete primary spermatogonium
description: A germ cell that is a primordial spermatocyte in a male and that develops into secondary spermatogonia by mitotic division.

name: obsolete secondary oogonium
description: A type of germ cell that results from the mitotic division of a primary oogonium.

name: obsolete secondary spermatogonium
description: A type of germ cell that results from the mitotic division of a primary spermatogonium.

name: obsolete mitochondrial aggregate
description: A large distinctive organelle aggregate comprised of mitochondria found in developing oocytes of many species. From Pepling et al. 2007.

name: obsolete lymphocyte
description: A cell of the B cell, T cell, or natural killer cell lineage.

name: obsolete B cell
description: A lymphocyte of B lineage with the phenotype CD19-positive and surface immunoglobulin-positive.

name: obsolete natural killer cell
description: A lymphocyte that can spontaneously kill a variety of target cells without prior antigenic activation via germline encoded activation receptors and also regulate immune responses via cytokine release and direct contact with other cells.

name: obsolete T cell
description: A type of lymphocyte whose defining characteristic is the expression of a T cell receptor complex.

name: obsolete thymocyte
description: An immature T cell located in the thymus.

name: obsolete myoblast
description: Embryonic (precursor) cell of the myogenic lineage that develops from the mesoderm.

name: obsolete abdominal myoblast
description: The myoblast that forms the muscles of the anterior abdominal walls.

name: obsolete neuron
description: Cell that is the basic unit of nervous tissue, each consisting of a body, an axon, and dendrites, and the purpose of which is to receive, conduct, and transmit impulses in the nervous system.

name: obsolete pigment cell
description: Cell type that contains a deposition of coloring matter.

name: obsolete iridophore
description: A pigment cell derived from the neural crest. The cell contains flat light-reflecting platelets, probably of guanine, in stacks called reflecting platets or iridisomes. The color-generating components produce a silver, gold, or iridescent color.

name: obsolete melanocyte
description: A pigment cell derived from the neural crest. Contains melanin-filled pigment granules, which gives a brown to black appearance.

name: obsolete xanthophore
description: A pigment cell derived from the neural crest. Contains cartenoid pigments in structures called pterinosomes or xanthosomes. This gives an appearance ranging from a golden yellow to orange and red.

name: obsolete podocyte
description: Cell type that is a component of the glomus.

name: obsolete stem cell
description: A relatively undifferentiated cell that retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life to provide progenitor cells that can differentiate into specialized cells.

name: obsolete hematopoietic stem cell
description: A stem cell from which all cells of the lymphoid and myeloid lineages develop, including blood cells and cells of the immune system.

name: obsolete zygote
description: Diploid cell produced by the fusion of sperm cell nucleus and egg cell.

name: obsolete blastocoel anlage
description: The first appearance of the antomical space that will become the blastocoel.

name: obsolete branchial arch skeleton
description: Skeletal and cartilaginous elements of the branchial arches; the last five of the set of seven pharyngeal arches; the numbering system can be confusing; generally branchial arch #1 is the first branchial arch, or the third pharyngeal arch, but some authors do not follow this convention.

name: inner fin tissue
description: Part of the fin consisting of a supporting core of mesenchyme and extracellular matrix.

name: outer fin tissue
description: Part of the fin consisting of flattened epidermal cells elevated into a keel-like structure.

name: mesonephric late distal segment
description: The site of bicarbonate resorption in the adult kidney. It is equivalent to the convoluted distal segment of metanephric nephrons.
