name: capillary system of liver
description: The smallest of the blood vessels, parts of the microcirculation, of the liver.

name: M. extensor digitorum communis longus
description: It arises on the lateral epicondyle of the humerus by two heads: the lateral one arises by a thin tendon in common with the m.extensor carpi ulnaris with fibers proximally fused. The internal one arises by a short tendon in common with proximally fused fibers of the m. extensor carpi radialis. It divides distally in two heads: the external head inserts with a long and thin tendon on the metacarpal V, at the same point of insertion of the m. abductor brevis dorsalis digiti V; the internal one inserts by a thin tendon on the proximal region of the metacarpal IV, between the m. extensor brevis superficialis digiti IV and the m. extensor brevis medius digiti IV (Pristimantis bogotensis).

name: dorsal marginal zone
description: Marginal zone that is a key embryonic tissue region of the early gastrula stage embryo and that houses the Spemann-Mangold organizer.

name: muscular artery
description: Part of the external carotid which delivers blood to the mm rectus cervicis and interhyoideus posterior.

name: lateral pretrosal artery
description: Part of the internal carotid which supplies blood to the ear and branches to two additional arteries.

name: mandibular artery
description: Part of lateral pretrosal artery which supplies blood to the roof of the mouth.

name: cutaneus artery
description: Artery which supplies blood to the thymus and parotoid region.

name: coeliaco-mesenteric artery
description: This artery has many branches which supply blood to various organs in the viscus.

name: gastrico-linealis
description: Major branch which supplies blood to the spleen and dorsal wall of the stomach.

name: duodeno-pancreatic artery
description: Major branch which supplies blood to pancreas and duodenum.

name: duodeno-hepatic artery
description: Major branch supplying blood via many smaller branches to the liver, duodenum, ventral wall of the stomach, and gall bladder.

name: oviduct artery
description: One of three arteries which are part of the renal artery supplying blood to the anterior, middle, and posterior parts of the oviduct.

name: postcaval vein
description: One of three major veins which enter the sinus venosus.

name: precaval vein
description: Either of a pair of veins which enter on either side of the sinus venosus.

name: lateral vein
description: Either of the veins which collect blood from the trunk and skin and drain into the subclavian vein.

name: cutaneus magnus
description: Anterior part of the lateral vein.

name: ventral abdominal vein
description: A vein formed by the combination of veins in the pelvic region which collects blood from the liver, stomach, intestines, and gall bladder.

name: Jacobson's vein
description: Either of a pair of veins which receives many small vesicles from the kidney and collects blood from the oviducal vein.

name: oviducal vein
description: Vein which collects blood from the oviduct.

name: M. plantaris longus
description: Originates by two heads, one from the dorso-distal border of the aponeurosis covering the knee and the other from two tendinous branches along the medial border of the knee joint. Inserts by a thick, broad tendon to form the aponeurosis plantaris.

name: bronchial tube
description: Either of the short tubes which bifurcate posteriorly from the trachea and lead into the lungs.

name: ovisac
description: Part of the ovary consisting of a thin sheath of connective tissue enclosing the ovarian follicles.

name: obsolete mesorchium
description: A thin membrane which attaches the testes to the kidneys and supports the efferent ductules from the testes to the kidneys.

name: obsolete pars nervosa
description: Region of the neurohypophysis which secretes neurohypophyseal hormones, regulating water loss and salt balance.

name: median pars intermedia
description: Region of the adenohypophysis which secretes melanophore-stimulating hormone, affecting the integumentary chromatophores.

name: obsolete gastrula cell
description: A cell of the embryo in the early stage following the blastula, characterized by morphogenetic cell movements, cell differentiation, and the formation of the three germ layers.

name: obsolete blastoderm cell
description: An undifferentiated cell produced by early cleavages of the fertilized egg (zygote).

name: obsolete ectodermal cell
description: A cell of the outer of the three germ layers of the embryo.

name: obsolete endodermal cell
description: A cell of the inner of the three germ layers of the embryo.

name: obsolete mesodermal cell
description: A cell of the middle germ layer of the embryo.

name: pila preoptica
description: A strut of cartilage  extending dorsally from the basal plate and with other similar cartilages forming the sides of the brain case. Posterior to the pila preoptica is the pila antoptica between these two cartilages emerges the optic and trochlear nerves.

name: prenasal (amphibians)
description: A dermal bone that forms anterior to the premaxillae between the maxillae and articulates with the nasals posteriorly.

name: basibranchial I
description: Bilaterally unpaired ventral element with which articulates with lateral paired elements.

name: mandibular arch neural crest
description: Anterior most migratory stream of cranial neural crest.

name: basibranchial II
description: Unpaired medial element that articulates with the anterior basibrachial I (if present).

name: vasa efferentia
description: Sperm travel through these 4 or 5 fine ducts which pass through the mesorchium from the testis to the sexual kidney.

name: hyoid arch neural crest
description: Population of cranial neural crest that give rise to hyoid arch elements.

name: cloacal papilla
description: A small, ridge-like projection from the antero-ventral wall of the cloacal chamber.

name: amphibian cloacal gland
description: A structure that surrounds the cloacal opening, consisting of a mass of coarse tubules.

name: granular gland
description: A gland that contains toxic secretions within the lumen. In frogs and salamanders, this is the larger of the two types of gland, the other being the mucuous gland

name: laryngo-tracheal chamber
description: Muscular vestibule between the pharynx and lungs, lying between the posterior cornua of the hyoid.

name: cartilago lateralis of aryngo-tracheal chamber
description: A series of semicircular cartilages on the side of the laryngo-tracheal chamber.

name: constrictor laryngis externus
description: Involved in the movement of the arytenoid cartilages.

name: dilatator laryngis
description: Involved in the movement of the arytenoid cartilages.

name: constrictor laryngis anterior
description: Involved in the movement of the arytenoid cartilages.

name: subarticular sesamoid
description: Is an endochondral structure located on the ventral to the junction between, in the hand, the metacarpal and most proximal phalanx of the digit and between phalanges, and in the foot between the metatarsal and most proximal phalanx of the digit and between phalanges. Typically subarticular sesamoids are found with the subarticular tubercles.

name: obsolete embryonic hypochord
description: A transient rod-like structure ventral to the notochord in salamander embryos. Derived from endoderm.

name: obsolete leydig cells
description: A type of mucus and/or fluid secreting cell in larvae.

name: obsolete dorsal ramus of occulomotor nerve
description: Innervates m. rectus superior (m. dorsal rectus).

name: obsolete Stiftchenzellen
description: Possibly chemoreceptor cells in anuran larvae.

name: obsolete ventral ramus of occulomotor nerve
description: Innervates m. rectus medialis, m. rectus inferior, m. obliquus inferior.

name: obsolete flask cell
description: Type of cell that appears in epidermis during metamorphosis and is rich in mitochondria.

name: obsolete goblet cell
description: A mucous surface cell type known in tadpoles of Xenopus.

name: egg capsule
description: Protective membranes that surround amphibian embryos.

name: obsolete mucous surface cell
description: Type of mucous-producing cell that appears in early larval stages and persists after metamorphosis.

name: obsolete ciliary cell
description: A type of cell that develops in embryos and functions in embryonic movements.

name: cephalodorsosubpharyngeus
description: One of the principal muscles used in swallowing.

name: levator bulbi
description: One of the principal muscles used in swallowing.

name: ramules nasalis lateralis
description: First branch gives rise to two ramules that border the naris and innervate the surrounding tissue.

name: ramus nasalis medialis
description: First branch gives rise to two ramules that border the naris and innervate the surrounding tissue.

name: rectus cervicis
description: Retracts the hyoid and, therefore, the tongue.

name: subhyoideus
description: Deep, visceral muscle associated with tongue movement.

name: subarcualis rectus I
description: Deep, visceral muscle associated with tongue movement.

name: ramus nasalis internus
description: Distal part of the opthalmicus profundus gives rise to 2 ramules: palatinus and cutaneous.

name: m. intertransversarius capitus superior
description: Involved in the movement of the head.

name: ramule palatinus
description: Ramules that descends towards the buccal roof and give rise to several short branches that anastomose with palatine ramus of the facial nerve.

name: m. intertransversarius capitis inferior
description: Involved in the movement of the head.

name: ramules cutaneous
description: Many branches of the maxillary ramus that terminate in the integument of the maxillary region.

name: trunk maxillary-mandibularis
description: Portion of the trigeminal nerve where the maxillary and mandibular rami run together prior to bifurcating.

name: ramule palatonasalis
description: Descends and branches to the buccal roof where it anastomoses with the palatine ramus of the facial nerve.

name: m. rhomboideus anterior
description: Muscle which originates on the posterior surface of the frontoparietal and the anterior part of the dorsal fascia. Inserts on the ventral surface of the anteromedial corner of the suprascapula.

name: bony nodule of terminal phalanx of hind digit
description: Endochondral element distal to terminal phalanx of hind digit.

name: proximal-most prepollical element
description: Is the proximal-most prepollical element.

name: distal-most prepollical element
description: Is the distal-most prepollical element.

name: fetal tooth
description: Type of deciduous dentition found in foetuses and altricial juveniles of some caecilians.

name: m. opercularis
description: Muscle which arises from the dorsal m. levator scapulae and extends between the operculum and suprascapula.

name: m. cucullaris
description: Muscle which originates on the prootic and the otic ramus of the squamosal and inserts on the anterior border of the suprascapula.

name: ramus posterior profundus of V3
description: In the adult anuran, this innervates the muscles levator mandibulare internus and longus.

name: m. rhomboideus posterior
description: Muscle which originates from the transverse process of presacral vertebrae IV and insert on the dorso-medial surface of the suprascapula.

name: m. serratus superior
description: Muscle which originates from the transverse process of presacral vertebrae IV and inserts on the dorso-medial surface of the suprascapula beneath the insertion M. rhomboideus posterior.

name: m. serratus medius
description: Muscle which originates from the transverse process of presacral vertebrae III and inserts on the central and medial surface of the suprascapula.

name: m. serratus inferior
description: Muscle which originates as a posterior and anterior head. The posterior head originates from the transverse process and cartilaginous epiphysis of presacral vertebra IV. The anterior head originates on the same parts of presacral vertebrae III. Both insert on the medial surface of the suprascapula near its postero-ventral edge.

name: levator mandibulae externus
description: Responsible for the closing of the jaw.

name: m. latissimus dorsi
description: Muscle which originates from the ventral surface of the dorsal fascia and inserts on the deltoid crest of the humerus.

name: levator mandibulae longus
description: Responsible for the closing of the jaw.

name: m. dorsalis scapulae
description: Muscle which originates on the lateral surface of the suprascapulae and inserts on the deltoid crest of the humerus.

name: levator mandibulae articularis
description: Muscle which is responsible for the closing of the jaw.

name: levator mandibulae lateralis
description: Responsible for the closing of the jaw.

name: m. interscapularis
description: Muscle which originates from the ventro-medial surface of the suprascapula and inserts on the ventral surface of the scapula.

name: levator mandibulae externus superficialis
description: Responsible for the closing of the jaw.

name: levator mandibulae externus profundus
description: Muscle which is responsible for the closing of the jaw.

name: m. sternoepicoracoideus
description: Muscle which originates on the anterior border of the distal part of the sternal horn and inserts antero-medially on the postero-dorsal surface of the epicoracoid cartilage.

name: dilated medial process of metacarpal IV
ramus hyomandibularis
description: The posttrematic branch of the facial nerve, both motor and sensory in function.

name: ramus palatinus
description: Sensory branch of facial nerve from palatal region.

name: levator quadrati
description: Responsible for the closing of the jaw.

name: M. coracoradialis
description: Muscle which originates from the omosternum and epicoracoid cartilage and inserts on the proximal radioulna.

name: ramus muscularis of glossopharyngeus nerve
description: Branchiomotor branch of the glossopharyngeus nerve innervating the m. subarcuales rectus I.

name: otic opercular element
description: Round, flat bone or cartilage that lies in the fenestra ovalis and articulates with the columella.

name: M. coracobrachialis longus
description: Muscle which originates as a long belly from the dorsal coracoid near the sternum and inserts on the shaft of the humerus.

name: M. coracobrachialis brevis
description: Muscle which originates on the dorsal surface of the coracoid and scapula and inserts on the deltoid crest of the humerus.

name: M. flexor carpi ulnaris
description: Muscle which originates from the medial condyle of the humerus and inserts on the carpus.

name: ramus anterior of CN VIII
description: Formed by fibers from the anterior semicircular canal and sacculus.

name: ramus posterior of CN VIII
description: Composed of two rami: a short ventral ramus innervating the cochlea (lagena and papille basilar), and a long dorsal ramus innervating the posterior semicircular canal.

name: M. palmaris longus
description: Originates from the medial epicondyle of the humerus and inserts on the palmar aponeurosis.

name: M. palmaris profundis
description: Originates on the ulnar aspect of the radioulna and inserts on the palmar aponeurosis.

name: M. flexor antibrachii medialis
description: Originates on the medial epicondyle of the humerus and inserts on the radial aspect of the radioulna.

name: ramus auricularis of the vagus nerve
description: An afferent branch of the vagus nerve.

name: M. ulnocarpalis
description: Originates along distal third of the ulna and inserts on the ulnare.

name: M. flexor antibrachii lateralis superficialis
description: Originates as a superior and inferior head. The superior head originates on the outer edge of the humerus and the inferior head originates on the lateral epicondyle of the humerus. Both bellies converge to form a tendon, which inserts on the carpus and the extensor tendon of digit I.

name: M. flexor antibrachii lateralis profundus
description: Originates on the lateral epicondyle of the humerus and inserts on the lower ridge of the radioulna.

name: M. coccygeosacralis
description: Originates on the lateral surface of the urostyle and inserts on the neural arch of the sacrum or on the sacral diapophysis.

name: M. coccygeoiliacus
description: Originates on the lateral surface of the urostyle and passes ventral to the sacral diapophysis to insert on the anterior and medial surfaces of the ilial shaft.

name: M. iliolumbaris
description: Originates on the anterior and lateral aspect of the ilial shaft and inserts on the transverse processes of presacral vertebrae IV-VII.

name: descending branch of the vagus nerve
description: Major branch of the vagus supplying parasympathetic innervation to viscera.

name: ramus muscularis of vagus nerve
description: Motor nervous branch of the vagus innervating m. subarcualis rectus I.

name: ramus recurrens
description: Branch of the vagus nerve that separates from the vagus well postcranially, then continues anteriorly to innervate the larynx.

name: ramus superficial ophthalmic
description: Dorsal branch of ADLLN that innervates supraorbital line of neuromasts.

name: M. coccygeocutaneus
description: Originates from the posterior tip of the urostyle and inserts on the cloacal musculature and the overlying skin.

name: ramus buccal
description: Ventral ramus of the ADLLN that innervates the infraorbital line of neuromasts.

name: laryngeus ventralis
description: A branch of the vagus nerve innervating heart, stomach, and lung muscle.

name: ramus mandibularis externus
description: Runs together with motor fibers of the hyomandibular trunk of VII. The mandibularis externus of AVLLN branches into three ramules .

name: M. dorsalis trunci
description: Originates on the postero-dorsal edge of the postzygopophyses and insert on the dorsal surface of the neural arch of the posterior, adjacent vertebra.

name: jugal ramule
description: This ramule innervates the jugal line of neuromasts and is the dorsal branch of the ramus mandibularis externus.

name: m. oblique externus
description: Originates on the posterior margin of the suprascapula and the epaxial fascia and inserts ventrally on the lateral fascia of the M. rectus abdominus and the ilial shaft.

name: m. oblique internus
description: A muscular sheet in which the fibers run in right angles to those of the m. oblique externus, slanting downward anteriorly. This is one of three sheets composing the flank musculature.

name: muscle rectus abdominis superficialis
description: A component of the rectus abdominal muscle that is some taxa.

name: musculus rectus abdominis profundus
description: A component of the rectus abdominal muscle that is some taxa (see comment) forms a disctinct and separate muscle.

name: m. ypsiloideus anterior
description: Hypaxial muscle in which contraction elevates the ypsiloid cartilage; originates from the anterior edge of the lateral process of the ypsiloid cartilage and insert on the anteriorly adjacent inscription.

name: oral ramule
description: Medial branch of the ramus mandibularis externus. This ramule innervates the oral and angular lines of neuromasts.

name: preopercular ramule
description: Ventral branch of the ramus mandibularis externus. This ramule have a superior and an inferior division, both innervating the preopercular line of neuromasts.

name: ramus supraotic
description: Small ramus of the MLLN that innervates neuromasts located at the posterior margin of the otic capsule.

name: m. ypsiloideus posterior
description: Contraction depresses the ypsiloid cartilage; arises from the anterodorsal edge of the pubis deep to the m. rectus abdominis profundus and spreads anteriorly in a fan shape to insert on the lateral edges of the shaft and the posterior edges of the lateral processes of the ypsiloid cartilage .

name: ramulus suprabranchialis anterior
description: Ramulus that innervates the suprabranchial line of neuromasts.

name: ramulus suprabranchialis posterior
description: Ramulus innervating the suprabranchial line of neuromasts.

name: ramus lateral
description: Ventral division of the trunk of the PLLN, this prominent ramus extends over the lateral trunk and caudal musculature innervating the lateral line of neuromasts.

name: ramus ventral
description: This ramus leaves the postotic ganglionic complex together with the third branchial ramus of X. This ramule innervates the ventral line of neuromasts.

name: m. flexor indicis superficialis proprius
description: Originates on the internal border of the distal carpal 5-4-3 and inserts on the distal end of phalynx I.

name: hepatic peritoneum
description: Peritoneum that surrounds the liver.

name: gastrointestinal peritoneum
description: Peritoneum that surrounds the stomach and intestines.

name: hyoquadrate process
description: A projection on the suboccular arch, ventral to the muscular process, that serves as the articulation point for the lateral process of the ceratohyal of the hyobranchial skeleton.

name: occipito-petrosal
description: Fusion of the occipital segment or occipital ring and otic capsule (Francis, 1934).

name: occipital segment
description: Metameric segment forming the back of the skull.

name: posterolateral supplementary element
description: A muscle slip arising from the ventral surface of the mandible by means of the ligament near the site of mandibular articulation. The fibers pass anteromedially and attach upon the ventral surfaces of the principal element of the m. intermandibularis (Tyler, 1971).

name: apical supplementary element
description: A muscle slip arising from the lingual surface of the mandible on each side of the m. submentalis. The fibers pass posteromedially and attach upon the median raphe of the principal element (Tyler, 1971).

name: anterolateral supplementary element
description: A muscle slip arising from the lingual surface of the mandible on the anterior portion of the bone. The fibers pass anteriorly, parallel to the mandible, and attach upon the ventral surface of the m. submentalis (Tyler, 1971).

name: obsolete portion of cell substance
description: Portion of organism substance located within a cell.

name: obsolete mode of ossification
description: The formation of bone or of a bony substanc, or the conversion of fibrous tissue or of cartilage into bone or a bony substance.

name: permanent cartilage
description: Chondrogenic element that is composed of cartilage that is not replaced.

name: obsolete opercle bone
description: Dermal bone that forms the postero-dorsal part of the opercular series. The opercle articulates with the hyomandibula antero-dorsally and with the subopercle ventrally. The opercle is a paired bone.

name: obsolete basihyal bone
description: Endochondral bone that is median and is the anterior-most bone of the ventral hyoid arch.

name: obsolete notochordal cell
description: Cell of the notochord, often vacuolated or resembles a chondrocyte.

name: obsolete skeletogenic cell
description: Cell that has the potential to form a skeletal cell type (e.g., cells in periosteum, cells in marrow) and produce extracellular matrix (often mineralized) and skeletal tissue (often mineralized).

name: mineralized skeletal tissue
description: Skeletal tissue that is mineralized.

name: obsolete basihyal cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is median and is the anterior-most cartilage of the ventral hyoid arch.

name: obsolete chordablast
description: Epithelial cell that is large, vacuolated, and part of the notochord.

name: mineralized extracellular matrix
description: Extracellular matrix that is mineralized.

name: obsolete proteinaceous extracellular matrix
description: A layer consisting mainly of proteins (especially collagen) and glycosaminoglycans (mostly as proteoglycans) that forms a sheet underlying or overlying cells such as endothelial and epithelial cells. The proteins are secreted by cells in the vicinity. An example of this component is found in Mus musculus..

name: obsolete extracellular matrix
description: Combination of protein fibers, ground substance and tissue fluid; typically has embedded cells.

name: obsolete intercalar
description: Small membrane bone homologous with a cartilage bone in more basal fishes (Patterson, 1977). Situated between the exoccipital and the pterotic at point of attachment of short ligament that originates on the ventral arm of the posttemporal.

name: integumentary papilla
description: Odontogenic papilla that is located in the integument.

name: oropharyngeal papilla
description: Odontogenic papilla located along the jaws or pharyngeal skeleton.

name: obsolete preameloblast
description: Skeletogenic cell that has the potential to develop into an ameloblast.

name: obsolete chordoblast
description: Skeletogenic cell that is derived from the notochordal mesoderm and produces notochordal tissue (and cartilage tissue in some taxa).

name: obsolete preodontoblast
description: Skeletogenic cell that has the potential to form an odontoblast, deposits predentine, and arises from a neural crest cell.

name: obsolete precementoblast
description: Skeletogenic cell that has the potential to develop into a cementoblast.

name: obsolete prechondroblast
description: Skeletogenic cell that has the potential to develop into a chondroblast; and arises from neural crest, meseosdermal and notochordal and connective tissue cells.

name: obsolete preosteoblast
description: Skeletogenic cell that has the potential to transform into an osteoblast, and develops from neural crest or mesodermal cells.

name: lepidosteoid scale
description: Multi-layer ganoid scale composed of ganoine and cellular bone.

name: ganoid scale
description: Thick, rhomboid-shaped integumentary skeletal element composed of multiple tissues including ganoine and bone.

name: vacuolated notochordal tissue
description: Connective tissue that is matrix-poor with large number of vacuolated cells.

name: polypteroid scale
description: Multi-tissue structure composed of ganoine, dentine, elasmodine and cellular bone.

name: avascular GAG-rich matrix
description: Proteinaceous extracellular matrix that is avascular and consists primarily of glycosaminoglycans.

name: elasmoid scale
description: Multi-tissue integumentary element composed dentine, elasmodine, and hypermineralized tissue.

name: palaeoniscoid scale
description: Multi-tissue structure composed of ganoine, dentine and bone; not known in extant taxa.

name: chondroid tissue
description: Skeletal tissue that is mineralized, has large chondrocyte-like cells, sparse extracellular matrix, and minimal perichondrium; develops from non-mineralized chondroid tissue.

name: keratin-based scale
description: Fold or elevation of the epidermis rich in keratin proteins; possibly calcified but does not contain skeletal elements.

name: cosmoid scale
description: Multi-tissue integumentary element composed of enamel or enameloid, dentine and lamellar bone, and characterized by pore-canal system.

name: secondary cartilage tissue
description: Cartilage tissue that is part of the exoskeleton, deposited adjacent to bone after bone formation.

name: mineralized cartilage tissue
description: Cartilage tissue that is mineralized.

name: integumentary skeleton
description: Skeletal subdivision that is part of the extra-oral dermal skeletal system that develops and remains invested within the integument, primarily the dermis.

name: obsolete non-terminally differentiated odontoblast
description: Odontoblast that non-terminally differentiated, located in the odontogenic papilla and dentine tissue, and transforms from a odontoblast cell.

name: obsolete terminally differentiated odontoblast
description: Odontoblast that is terminally differentiated and derived from an odontogenic papilla and associated with dentine.

name: orthodentine
description: Odontoid tissue that typically contains tubules and is acellular.

name: ganoine
description: Odontogenic tissue that is hypermineralized acellular, noncollagenous, covered by an epidermis and often deposited in multiple layers.

name: limiting layer of elasmoid scale
description: Hypermineralized tissue lacking collagen (except Sharpey's fibres), developing in close proximity to the basal cells of the overlying epithelium.

name: vasodentine
description: Dentine tissue that lacks dentine tubules and that is penetrated by blood capillaries.

name: elasmodine
description: Odontogenic tissue that consists of multiple layers of collagen fibers organized in orthogonal or twisted arrangements.

name: non-mineralized hyaline cartilage tissue
description: Hyaline cartilage tissue that is not mineralized.

name: mineralized hyaline cartilage tissue
description: Hyaline cartilage tissue that is mineralized.

name: mineralized bone tissue
description: Bone tissue mineralized with hydroxyapatite.

name: obsolete terminally differentiated osteoblast
description: Osteoblast that is terminally differentiated, located adjacent to acellular or cellular bone tissue within periosteum, and is capable of mineralizing the matrix.

name: obsolete non-terminally differentiated osteoblast
description: Osteoblast that is non-terminally differentiated and located in cellular bone tissue or under the periosteum in acellular bone.

name: cellular bone tissue
description: Mineralized bone tissue that always includes non-terminally differentiated osteoblasts and osteocytes.

name: non-mineralized avascular GAG-rich matrix
description: Avascular GAG-rich matrix that is not mineralized.

name: mineralized avascular GAG-rich matrix
description: Avascular GAG-rich matrix that is mineralized.

name: acellular bone tissue
description: Mineralized bone tissue that has terminally differentiated osteoblasts but lacks osteocytes.

name: odontode tissue
description: Skeletal tissue that is avascular tubular mineralized matrix, primarily made of dentine that is deposited by odontoblasts that are excluded from the matrix; develops from pre-dentine tissue.

name: ossified tendon
description: Sesamoid that develops within a tendon, distal to an articulation or joint.

name: obsolete direct ossification
description: Ossification that does not require the replacement of pre-existing tissues, most often a cartilaginous model.

name: ligamentous replacement element
description: Replacement element that forms as a replacement of a ligament.

name: obsolete replacement ossification
description: Ossification that requires the replacement of a pre-existing tissue prior to bone tissue formation.

name: obsolete intramembranous ossification
description: Direct ossification that occurs within mesenchyme with the formation of an osteogenic condensation not associated with a perichondrium.

name: obsolete metaplastic ossification
description: Direct ossification in which transformation of the pre-existing tissue occurs without dedifferentiation of cells or reinitiation of cell division; direct transformation of a non-bone tissue into a bone tissue.

name: obsolete endochondral ossification
description: Replacement ossification wherein bone tissue replaces cartilage.

name: obsolete perichondral ossification
description: Intramembranous ossification on the surface of a cartilage element as the perichondrium becomes a periosteum, without replacement of cartilage.

name: transient cartilaginous element
description: Chondrogenic element that is composed of cartilage during development and has the potential to become replaced by another tissue.

name: ossified ligament
description: Sesamoid that develops within a ligament, distal to an articulation or joint.

name: anocleithrum
description: Dermal bone of pectoral girdle that is dorsal to and articulates with the cleithrum.

name: median fin
description: Fin that is an unpaired fin located in the sagittal plane of the organism.

name: anal fin
description: Median fin that is located posterior to the anus.

name: caudal fin
description: The caudal fin is the most posterior median fin. It is composed of a complex of modified centra and modified neural and hemal arches and spines.

name: anal fin skeleton
description: Median fin skeleton that is located posterior to the anus.

name: caudal fin skeleton
description: Median fin skeleton supporting the caudal fin.

name: dorsal fin skeleton
description: Median fin skeleton located on the dorsal surface of the organism.

name: median fin skeleton
description: Postcranial axial skeleton that is unpaired and located on the sagittal plane of the organism.

name: scapular complex
description: Skeletal subdivision of dermal bones that may include the anterolateral plate (AL), the spinal process (Sp), and anteroventral plate (AV) and other dermal bones that are part of the pectoral girdle.

name: lepidotrichium
description: Dermal bone that is rod-like, formed and usually contained in a fin membrane, and jointed to or adjacent to distal radials. Lepidotrichia are formed from paired hemitrichia surrounding actinotrichia. There are usually two more lepidotrichia than distal radials.

name: pelvic fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium that is part of the pelvic fin skeleton.

name: caudal fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium that is part of the caudal fin skeleton.

name: pectoral fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium that is part of the pectoral fin skeleton.

name: anal fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium that is part of the anal fin skeleton.

name: dorsal fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium that is part of the dorsal fin skeleton.

name: suprabranchial fin
description: Paired fin that is a bilaterally paired anterior outgrowth located high on the side of the animal, not far behind the orbit, with the posterior extremity corresponding with the expected posterior end of the branchial region.

name: skeletal element projection
description: Anatomical projection that is composed of bone or cartilage tissue.

name: obsolete astragalus-calcaneum unit
description: Anatomical cluster that is an osteological unit consisting of the astragalus and calcaneum.

name: obsolete ectepicondylar flange
description: Flange on the dorsal part of the humerus, associated with extensor musculature of the forelimb (manus. carpus).

name: articular surface
description: Anatomical surface that is part of a skeletal element and articulates with another skeletal element.

name: ischial peduncle
description: Bony projection (peduncle) that is located on the posterior portion of the ilium, posterior to the acetabulum.

name: second phalanx
description: Second most proximal phalanx in manual or pedal digits.

name: parasternal process
description: Posterior projection of the interclavicle that extends betwen and sometimes beyond the clavicles.
synonyms: ["posterior stalk of intercalvicle","posterior stem of interclavicle"]

name: pectoral articular facet
description: Facet of scapulocoracoid with which the pectoral fin radial(s) articulates. Facet of scapulocoracoid with which the pectoral fin radial(s) articulates. Based on Goujet and Young (1995).

name: pedal claws
description: Claws on the pes.

name: pedal digit 7 phalanx
description: Phalanx of the 7th pedal digit.

name: post-glenoid process
description: Distinct notch ventral to the glenoid.

name: postacetabular buttress
description: A bony process at the distal margin of the acetabulum formed by the ischium and/or the ischial peduncle of the ilium.

name: postacetabular zone
description: Region of the ilium posterior and dorsal to the acetabulum.

name: postcoracoid
description: The posterior of the two coracoid elements found in basal tetrapods. Corresponds directly to the 'coracoid' of synapsids.

name: posterior dorsal fin
description: Dorsal fin located posterior to the anterior dorsal fin.

name: obsolete posterior iliac process
description: Posterior most of the two 'double heads' of the blade of the ilium in some take. Distinct and separate for the dorsal iliac process.

name: posterior process of ilium
description: A posteriorly directed bony projection from the ilium that is the attachment site of the iliofibularis muscle (see Sumida, 1997).

name: parasphenoid flange
description: Lateral expansion of the parasphenoid.

name: hemipenal sheath
description: Soft tissue sheath covering the hemipenis.

name: radial facet
description: Facet to accommodate the radius on the distal end of the humerus.

name: dermal intracranial joint
description: Hinge in the skull skeleton to allow for kinetic movement of different parts.

name: anterior distal condyle of femur
description: Anatomical projection in the distal region of the femur.

name: spiracular notch
description: Soft tissue notch/opening lying on a spiracle.

name: posterior distal condyle of femur
description: Anatomical projection in the posterior/distal region of the femur.

name: presacral rib
description: Rib located anterior to the sacral region.

name: trunk rib
description: Rib located in the trunk (ribcage) area (i.e. excluding cervical and caudal axial series.

name: extratemporal bone
description: Extratemporal bone: Skull bone in the posterior half of the cranium, bordering the squamosal and opercular.

name: obsolete prezygapophyses
description: Anteriorly projecting processes allowing de facto contact between consecutive vertebrae (some soft tissues are also present) via articular facets.

name: thagomizer
description: The distinctive arrangement of four to ten spikes on the tails of stegosaurid dinosaurs. These spikes are believed to have been a defensive measure against predators.

name: medial blade of ilium
description: The medial surface of the iliac blade. Origin site of the iliofemoralis internus muscle and its homologues.

name: postpubis
description: The region of the pubis posterior to the acetabulum.

name: coracoid plate
description: Broad, convex expansion of the coracoid bone below the level of the glenoid. Based on Romer 1956

name: archipterygial fin
description: A type of pectoral fin in which the endoskeletal elements have a main axis that runs through the center of the fin. This creates a bilaterally symmetrical fin. (Modified from Kardong 2012).

name: intertrochanteric fossa
description: Depression on the ventreal side of the femoral head. Associated with the pubioischiofemoralis externus muscle.

name: obsolete postbranchial lamina
description: Medial facing projection or surface on the anterior ( cranial) region of the cleithrum that is often textured or denticled. This process has two primary functions: 1) its shape enhances the vertical strength of the cleithrum and 2) it forms the edge of the gill chamber and helps to direct water after it has passed over the gills (modified from Clack 2012).

name: infraglenoid buttress
description: An anatomical projection ventral to the glenoid fossa on the scapulocoracoid that abuts on the cliethrum (if present).

name: transverse pelvic ridge
description: The transverse pelvic ridge is a short crest directly anterior to, and not extending posterior to, the prominent supra-acetabular buttress  from Pawley and Warren 2006.

name: inter-clavicle joint
description: Joint that articulates left and right clavicles.

name: hypochordal lepidotrichium
description: Caudal fin lepidotrichium located ventral to the notochord.

name: ventral humeral ridge
description: A distinct bony ridge on ventralsurface of the humeral shaft that corresponds to the attachment site of the pectoralis muscle.

name: pedal centrale
description: A centrale found in the pes.

name: ectepicondylar flange
description: Flange present of the distal region of the humerus, associated with extensor musculature of forelimb.

name: flexor surface
description: Surface of a long bone that possess the flexor muscle attachment sites.

name: lateral tuber of ulna
description: Projection on the lateral side of proximal part of the ulna.

name: inner digits of foot
description: The medial most digits of the pes.

name: postbranchial lamina
description: Medial facing projection or surface on the anterior ( cranial) region of the cleithrum that is often textured or denticled. This process has two primary functions: 1) its shape enhances the vertical strength of the cleithrum and 2) it forms the edge of the gill chamber and helps to direct water after it has passed over the gills (modified from Clack 2012)

name: obsolete infraglenoid buttress
description: An anatomical projection venteral to the glenoid fossa on the scapulocoracoid that abuts on the cliethrum.

name: calcaneal tuber
description: An enlargement of the distal region of the calcaneum that corresponds to the attachment site for the foot extensor muscles.

name: preacetabular process
description: Process on ilium located anteriorly to acetabulum.

name: suprascapular fossa
description: Fossa on the medial surface on the scapula above the glenoid.

name: astragalus-calcaneum unit
description: Osteological unit consisting of the astragalus and calcaneum.

name: extracleithrum
description: Narrow bone that lies ventral to the level of insertion of the pectoral fin and is sutured to the posterior edges of both the clavicle and cleithrum. Based on Forey 1998.

name: anterior dorsal fin
description: A dorsal fin located anterior to posterior dorsal fin.

name: obsolete suprascapular fossa
description: Fossa located on the medial surface of the scapula above the glenoid

name: ascending process of the astragalus
description: Flattened process of the dorsl surface of the astragalus which contacts the tibia anteriorly.

name: supraglenoid foramen
description: Foramen that perforates supraglenoid buttress.

name: supraglenoid buttress
description: A bony projection dorsal to the glenoid articulation on the scapulocoracoid.

name: adductor blade
description: A prominent ridge in basal tetrapods on the ventral side of the femur that includes the fourth trochater, internal trochanter and the adductor crest (based on Coates, 1996).

name: adductor crest
description: A bony crest on venteral side of femur that is the attachment site for the adductor muscles.

name: antitrochanter
description: Raised surface at the posterior portion of the acetabulum (see Nesbitt, 2011).

name: caudalipuboischiotibialis
description: Muscle that is associated with tail flexion. Orginates on one of the first post sacral vertebrae posteriorly and inserts on the posterior edge of the m.puboischiotibialis. (modified from Duellman and Trueb 1994)

name: clavicle blade
description: Expanded and flattened ventral region of clavicle bone.

name: cleithrum head
description: Expanded dorsal region of the cleithrum.

name: cnemial crest
description: Longitudnal bony ridge on tibia, attachment site of the major extensor muscle of the hind limb.

name: internal trochanter
description: A boney projection on the internal diaphysis of the femur anterior or medial to the intertrochanteric fossa, below the femoral head. Muscle attachment site for ventral muscle mass notably the puboischiofemoralis externus. Modified from Romer 1956

name: supinator process
description: A bony process that corresponds to the attachment site for the forelimb supinator muscles in tetrapods, distal to the deltopectoral crest and anterior to the radial condyle.

name: subscapular fossa
description: A marked depression on the medial side of the scapula blade, often opposite the glenoid region.

name: supraacetabular buttress
description: A bony protuberance dorsal to the acetabulum on the ilium, confluent with the supraacetabular crest (when present). Acts as a bone brace to prevent excessive femoral abduction and the origin site for part of the M. iliofemoralis.

name: acrocoracoid process
description: Anatomical process located in the proximal region of the coracoid in avian theropods, that is hook-shaped.

name: aponeurosis palmaris
description: The palmar aponeurosis is a fibrotendinous complex that functions as the tendinous extension of the palmaris longus, when present, and as a strong stabilizing structure for the palmar skin of the hand. It has five longitudinal slips that project into the base of each digit and a deeper transverse portion that crosses the palm at the proximal end of the metacarpals bones (from Wikipedia).

name: brevis shelf
description: Anatomical projection on the ilium, anchoring caudal muscles.

name: brevis fossa
description: Fossa located on the brevis shelf.

name: articular surface for the calcaneum on the astragalus
description: Contact surface between the calcaneum and the astragalus located on the astragalus.

name: articular surface for the astragalus on the calcaneum
description: Contact surface between the calcaneum and the astragalus located on the calcaneum.

name: astragalo-calcaneal canal
description: The astragalo-calcaneal canal forms a foramen between the articulated astragalus and calcaneum when the canal is ossified (Nesbitt, 2011).

name: attachment site
description: Morphological struture denoting the exent of an attachment site for a soft tissue on a skeletal element.

name: bicipital crest
description: Anatomical projection that is an expansion on the proximal region of the humerus.

name: cartilago sesamoides
description: A sesamoid found in the found in the ligamentum calcanei of a wide variety of frogs. (based on Nussbaum, R. A. 1982

name: cotyla
description: A cup shaped articular surface on a bone.

name: cotyloid notch
description: A notch or opening in the ventral part of the acetabular rim.

name: crista tibiofibularis
description: Tuberosity on the posterior surface of the lateral femoral condyle

name: diphycercal tail
description: An internally and externally symmetrical tail (caudal) fin

name: heterocercal tail
description: Type of tail (caudal) fin in which the vertebral column turns upwards into the upper lobe which is longer than the lower. Asymmetrical externally as well as internally.

name: homocercal tail
description: Type of tail fin in which the vertebrae generally turn upward at the hind end of the column, but which is externally symmetrical. The fin rays of the caudal are supported by hypaxial elements

name: hypocercal tail
description: Type of tail fin where the lower lobe is the longer and is supported by the vertebral column. Asymmetrical externally as well as internally

name: ectepicondylar foramen
description: Formen present on the ectepicondyle of the humerus.

name: epicercal tail
description: Tail fin in which the the caudal part of the notochord tapers posterodorsally. Based on Pradel et al. 2007

name: epichordal lepidotrichium
description: Caudal fin lepidotrichium located upon or above the notochord.

name: ectocondylar tubercle
description: Posteriorly projecting bony tubercle that is located proximal to the lateral condyle of the femur.

name: prepubic element
description: A small plate of cartilage synchondrotically united with the pubis. Modified from Baez and Harrison 2005.

name: sternal keel
description: The vertical plate of bone or cartilage attached to the median line of the sternum. Modified from Baumel et al. 1993

name: median fin spine
description: Fin spine that is part of a median fin.

name: fin spine
description: A spine that is part of some fin.

name: trunk armor pectoral fenestra
description: An opening in the dermal armour of basal gnathostomes that encloses the pectoral fins. (modified from Young 2010).

name: obsolete posterior iliac process
description: Distinct posterior most of the two 'double heads' of the blade of the ilium.

name: clavicular facet
description: A notch for the articulation of the clavicle on other girdle elements.

name: dorsal iliac process
description: Posteriordorsal process of the ilium.

name: fibular crest
description: A bony projection on the lateral side of the tibia, allowing contact between the later and the fibula.

name: hypocleideum
description: Zone of bone organ located on the flat ventral side of the distal region of the furcula, serving as attachment region for pectoral muscles.

name: postaxial centrale
description: Centrale in the postaxial region of the mesopodium.

name: preaxial centrale
description: Centrale in the preaxial side of the mesopodium.

name: obsolete glenoid head of scapula
description: The scapula's contribution to the glenoid fossa.

name: iliac neck
description: A constricted region of the ilium which is dorsal to the acetabulular region. Prior to the expansion of the iliac blade.

name: iliac peduncle
description: Bony projection that is part of the dorsal surface of the ischim, where it articulates with the ilium.

name: iliac peduncle of the pubis
description: Bony projection that is part of the dorsal surface of the pubis where it meets the ilium.

name: fibular facet of the calcaneum
description: Articular surface on calcaneum for the fibula.

name: fibular facet of the astragalus
description: Articular surface on the astragalus for the fibula.

name: ethomosphenoid region
description: Region consisitng of the ethmoid and sphenoid bones.

name: flexor tubercle of ungual
description: Eminence on the proximo-dorsal surface of the ungual, for attachment of flexor muscles.

name: inner digits of hand
description: The medial most digit of the manus skeleton.

name: infraspinous process
description: Process on infraspinous (region below the spine) of scapula.

name: intercondylar fossa
description: The deep fossa between the femoral condyles in which the cruciate ligaments are attached. From Medilexicon.com

name: intermediate spine
description: Spine ventrally located on the body and not part of the pectoral, pelvic or anal fins.

name: ischial foot
description: Expansion of the distal region of the ischium.

name: lateral extrascapular
description: The most lateral of the paired series of extrascapular bones and is the bone where the intersection of the otic, postotic and extrascapular or supratemporal canals occur.

name: latissimus dorsi process
description: A bony process on the dorsal side of the proximal region of the humerus which corresponds to the insertion site of the Latissimus dorsi muscle.

name: m.scapulotriceps
description: Muscle that represents one branch of the larger triceps brachii, origination site near the glenoid fossa on the scapula.

name: median dorsal plate
description: Dermal armour plate that is situated behind the head and constitute the dorsal most portion of the dermal shoulder girdle. Modified from Brazeau 2009, Young 2010

name: median extrascapular
description: The medial of the the paired series of extrascapular bones which carries the extrascapular or supratemporal canal.

name: metacarpal extensor pit
description: Pits located on the proximodorsal part of metacarpals denoting the attachemnt sites for ligaments.

name: nerve foramen
description: Opening and/or passageway for nerve(s) in bone.

name: muscle scar
description: A distinct region on a skeletal element that demarcates the attachment area of a muscle or tendon. Often associated with rugosity or tubercles.

name: obturator process of ischium
description: Process located on the ventral shaft of the ischium that denotes the attachment site of the pubio-ischio-femoralis externus.

name: outer digit of hand
description: The flanking digit of the manus.

name: outer digits of pes
description: The flanking digit of the pes.

name: prepectoral spine
description: Spine located anterior to the pectoral fin

name: prepelvic fin spine
description: Spine located anterior to the pelvic fin and posterior to the pectoral fin.

name: prepectoral space
description: A triangular, anteroventrally facing area developed between the preaxial margin of the humerus and the proximal limb of the ventral humeral ridge. Based on Callier et al. 2009

name: prepubic process
description: Elongate process forming the anteriormost part of the pubis.

name: presupracleithrum
description: An skeletal element of the upper pectoral girdle overlapped by the opercular and posttemporal bones.

name: pteroid
description: Slender bone connected to the carpus in pterosaurs. The bone, which may have pointed forward, supports the propatagium, a membrane located between the carpus and pectoral region.

name: pubic boot
description: Anteroposterior expansion of the distal region of the pubis.

name: pubic peduncle
description: Bony projection on the anterior portion of the ilium, anterior to the acetabulum that articulates with the pubis.

name: pubis-ischium contact
description: Contact zone between the pubis and the ischium.

name: puboischiadic plate
description: A broad expnase of bone incorperating both the pubis and the ischium. Origin site for ventral limb muscle including the pubioishciofemoralis externus. Modified from Romer 1956

name: puboischiotibialis muscle
description: A muscle that originates from the puboischaidic plate and inserts on the tibia. Acts to adduct the hindlimb. Is anterior to cloacal gland in males. Modified from De luliis and Pulera.

name: pubotibialis
description: Originates in on the pubic cartillage and inserts on the tibia, acts to adduct the hindlimb. Modified from De luliis and Pulera.

name: scapular process
description: The dorsal extension of the scapulocoracoid above the level of the glenoid region in basal gnathostomes. Modified from Brazeau 2009.

name: sternal trabecula
description: Anatomical projections that are  elongate processes in the mid and posterior regions of the sternum.

name: supraacetabular crest
description: Anatomical projection (crest) located dorsaly to the acetabulum.

name: supraacetabular rim
description: Bony rim that is part of the supraacetabular region.

name: suprascapula foramen
description: The route through which structures pass between the base of the neck and the posterior scapular region. It is formed by the suprascapular notch of the scapula and the superior transverse scapular ligament. From http://medical-dictionary.thefreedictionary.com/suprascapular+foramen

name: synarcual region of vertebral column
description: Series of fused cervical vertebrae or vertebral elements. Based on Jeffrey C. Carrier. Biology of Sharks and Their Relatives, 2012. CRC Press.

name: synarcual region
description: Axial subdivision that includes a series of fused cervical vertebrae or vertebral elements. Based on Jeffrey C. Carrier. Biology of Sharks and Their Relatives, 2012. CRC Press.

name: tibial facet of astragalus
description: Facet for the articulation of the tibia on the astragalus (talus).

name: trochanteric shelf
description: Anatomical projection on the anterolateral region of the proximal end of the femur.

name: tuber
description: Eminence or swelling on anatomical surface.

name: crest
description: A ridge or similar projection rising above the surface of an anatomical structure.

name: antimere
description: A part in the body of an organism that corresponds to an opposite symmetrical part.

name: puboischiadic bar
description: A transverse flattened or cylindrical plate in the posterior body wall opposite the anterior ends of the pelvic fins, in front of the vent and at the posterior end of the body cavity, that supports a few anterior pelvic radials and a basal cartilage, the basipterygium.  from  Leonard J. V. Compagno. 2001. Sharks of the World: An Annotated and Illustrated Catalogue of Shark Species Known to Date. Volume 2.

name: triphycercal tail
description: A caudal fin with three lobes.

name: palatoquadrate element
description: Endochondral element that is part of the suspensorium sometimes ossifying distally as the quadrate bone and linking the basal section of the braincase to the lower jaw.

name: prepollical element
description: Is a endochondral element that is part of the mesopodial skeleton and is contained within the prepollex which in some taxa appears as a pre-axial digit-like projection anterior to the first digit of the hand.

name: prehallical element
description: Is a endochondral element that is part of the mesopodial skeleton and is contained within the prehallux which in some taxa appears as a pre-axial digit-like projection anterior to the first digit of the foot.

name: accessory foramen
description: Foramen found on the humerus of tetrapodomorphs beyond the entepicondyle and ectepicondyle foramen. Often denoted as foramen 'c' and 'd' after Jarvik 1996

name: intertarsale sesamoid
description: Sesamoid bone in the tarsal region.

name: ventral ridge system
description: A collection of attached ridges on the ventrl surface of the femur consisting of the internal and fourth trochanters plus the adductor blade and crest. Most notible in early amniotes (based on Romer 1956)

name: mesomere (fin)
description: The median series of bones supporting the pectoral fin of sarcopterygian fish. See Dipnomorpha. In the pectoral fin, the first mesomere is the humerus, the second the ulna, and the third probably the intermedium. The radius is the first preaxial radial. All other homologies are suspect. from http://palaeos.com/vertebrates/glossary

name: basal scute
description: A scute parte of the basal surface of the fin in Sarcopterygian fish

name: hindlimb interepipodial space
description: The space between the bones of the tibia and the fibula.

name: process 2
description: Process on the humerus of basal tetrapods, anterior to the entepicondyle and associated with subscapularis muscle (based on Coates 1996)

name: process 3
description: Process on the humerus of basal tetrapods, anterior to the entepicondyle (see Coates 1996)

name: process 4
description: Process on the humerus of basal tetrapods, anterior to the entepicondyle (see Coates 1996)

name: distal condyle of humerus
description: The area encompassing the radial and ulnar condyles of the humerus.

name: ascending process of clavicle
description: A bony dorsal extension of the clavicle.

name: semilunate carpal
description: The moon shaped fusion of distal carpals 1 and 2 found in some theropod dinosaurs, permitting greater wrist mobility.

name: astragalus head
description: The region of the astragalus/ talus that carries the articular surface for the navicular.

name: bicipital tuberosity
description: The rough eminence which is on the anterior inner aspect of the neck of the radius and into which the tendon of the biceps is inserted. From http://www.merriam-webster.com/medical

name: ulnar tuberosity
description: his roughened area of bone sits distomedially at the base of the coronoid process. It is the attachment site for the brachialis muscle. From http://www.anatomyexpert.com/

name: entepicondyle fossa
description: A fossa on the distal humerus proximal to the entepicondyle.

name: obsolete hyperphalangy of manus
description: Increase the number of phalanges per digit beyond their ancestral digital formulas. Modified from Cooper and Dawson 2009

name: zygosphene
description: An articular process on anterior surface of neural arch of vertebrae which fits into zygantrum. Modified from Henderson's dictionary of Biological terms 12th Edition.

name: obsolete humeral facet of the ulna
posterodorsal process of ilium
description: Anatomical project part of the blade of the ilium that projects posteriorly.

name: intercentrum
description: The anteriormost of the two possible elements found in the tetrapod centrum (when the centrum is not a single element).

name: pleurocentrum
description: The posteriormost of the two possible elements found in the tetrapod centrum (when the centrum is not a single element).

name: atlas intercentrum
description: The intercentrum unit of the atlas vertebra.

name: anterior humeral ridge
description: Ridge or keel at the proximal end of the humerus. (see Laurin 1998)

name: incisor process
description: Process that is part of the mandible that is in close proximity to the incisor teeth.

name: sallet sensory system
description: Ciliary restraint system in the inner ear that uses sallets instead of the tectorial membrane.

name: humeral facet on the ulna
description: Facet on the ulna for articulation with the ulnar condyle of the humerus.

name: humeral facet on radius
description: Facet on the radius for articulation with the radial condyle of the humerus.

name: internal rim of coracoid foramen
description: The internal part of the rim denoting the coracoid foramen.

name: external rim of the coracoid foramen
synonyms: ["the external wall of the rim denoting the coracoid foramen."]

name: pectoral fin intermediate radial bone
description: Radial bone found in between the proximal and distal radial bones.

name: postaxial process of the ulnare
description: A projection on the postaxial region of the ulnare.

name: postaxial process of the femur
description: A projection on the postaxial region of the femur.

name: postaxial process of the fibula
description: A projection on the postaxial region of the fibula.

name: epipodial facet
description: Facets for the articulation of the epipodial (zeugopodial) elements.

name: suture
description: Line of junction between two parts immovably connected. Modified from Henderson's Dictionary of Biological Terms.

name: fibula facet of femur
description: Facet on the femur for the fibula.

name: tibial facet of femur
description: Facet on the femur for the tibia.

name: musculotendinous bundle
description: A collection of muscle and tendinous tissue.

name: growth line
description: Distinct layer that indicate the growth of an organism.

name: distal groove of humerus
description: Groove along the distal margin of the humerus, ventral to the radial and ulnar condyle.

name: foramen C
description: Foramen located on the scapulocoracoid, located just behind the cleithral anteroventral process(the articulation with the cleithrum). Modified from Coates 1996

name: columnar area
description: Modified from Garvey et al. 2005. \" Between the dorsal ridge and the caput humeri is a futher recessed area......that clearly separates the two structures and is slightly separted from the dorsal surface of the entepicondyle, and more specifically from the unfinished bone of the entepicondyle, by a narrow ridge.\"

name: scapulohumeralis muscle
description: Muscle found primarily in basal sarcopterygians that runs between teh scapulocoracoid and the humerus. Its exact homologies with more derived shoulder muscles in Tetrapoda is unclear.

name: anteroventral process of cleithrum
description: A ramus of the celithrum that descend along the girdle. Its rounded outer surface forms the articulation surface for the clavicle while its anterior surface overlaps with the anterior process of the scapulocoracoid.

name: surface of bone
description: An anatomical surface that is part of a bone

name: unfinished bone surface
description: A bone surface that is not smooth and periosteal.  The usual implication is that the bone was still growing, was covered in cartilage, or both. From Paleos.com

name: finished bone surface
description: A smooth periosteal bone surface.

name: dorsal clavicular process
description: A process, extending dorsally from the clavicular plate, that attaches to the cleithrum. Modified from Clack 2012 and Coates 1996.

name: surangular pit line
description: ...a v-shaped pair of ridges, each carrying three or four smallpores Modified from Ahlberg et al. 2005

name: parasymphysial plate
description: Bone, often with tooth attachments, on the lingual side of the anterior of the lower jaw.

name: meckelian bone
description: The ossification of the Meckel's cartilage.

name: obsolete maxillary saddle
description: A fossa that is a depression in the proximal end of the maxilla involved in articulation with the palatine.

name: palatine prong
description: A process on the palatine that projects outward and upward and articulates with a depression (maxillary saddle) in the proximal end of the maxilla.

name: urodermal bone
description: Paired, thin dermal bones at the rear of the caudal fin skeleton, derived from scales.

name: scale pocket
description: A continuous flap of skin with scales implanted in pockets or invaginations.

name: aphakic space
description: The space in the pupil, which is not occupied by the lens. A rostral aphakic space may enhance the forward binocular field of vision.

name: scale row
description: A series of scales in alignment with each other along some axis of the body..

name: medial pelvic process
description: Process that is posteriorly oriented and medially located on the basipterygium. It is a paired projection.

name: epipleural series
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of the epipleurals.

name: clavus
description: A rudder-like lobe formed from extensions of dorsal and anal fin rays.

name: pelvic cartilage
description: Cartilage element associated with the pelvic fin in aulopiform fishes.

name: rostrodermethmoid
description: Dermal bone formed by the fusion of dermethmoids and rostral bones.

name: ventral marginal cartilage
description: In the clasper skeleton, a flat semicylindrical cartilage that is partially fused to the lateral edge of the axial cartilage, and forms the lateral wall of the clasper groove.

name: dorsal fin basal cartilage (elasmobranchs)
description: The large cartilage of the dorsal fin, on which the radials articulate distally.

name: anal fin basal cartilage
description: The large cartilage of the anal fin, on which the radials articulate distally.
synonyms: ["anal fin basal plate","anal fin base plate","basal plate"]

name: anterolateral plate
description: Dermal bone that is part of the scapular complex in placoderm fishes.

name: anteroventral plate
description: Dermal bone that is part of the scapular complex in placoderms.

name: interolateral plate
description: Dermal bone that is part of the scapular complex in placoderms.

name: spinal plate
description: Dermal bone that is part of the scapular complex in placoderms.

name: posterior dorsolateral plate
description: Dermal bone that is part of the scapular complex in placoderms.

name: anterior ventrolateral plate
description: Dermal bone that is part of the scapular complex in placoderms.

name: posterior ventrolateral plate
description: Dermal bone that is part of the scapular complex in placoderms.

name: dermal neck joint
description: Dermal articulation between skull and shoulder girdle localized to paired dermal neck-joint between anterior dorsolateral plate (ADL) and paranuchal (PNu) plates in placoderms.

name: fin web
description: Membrane that connects the lepidotrichia or ceratotrichia of a fin.

name: posterior dorsal fin basal cartilage (elasmobranchs)
description: The large cartilage of the posterior dorsal fin, on which the radials articulate distally.

name: anterior dorsal fin basal cartilage (elasmobranchs)
description: The large cartilage of the anterior dorsal fin, on which the radials articulate distally.

name: antorbital cartilage
description: Cartilage element on the neurocranium of sawsharks and batoids, separate cartilages attached to the sides of the nasal capsules that support the sides or front of the head.

name: supraneural element
description: Endochondral element that is median and located in the dorsal skeletogenous septum between the cranium and the dorsal fin.

name: bony fin ray
description: Fin ray that is composed of bone tissue.

name: facet
description: A small smooth area on a bone or other firm structure.  A worn spot on a tooth, produced by chewing or grinding.

name: X bone
description: The x bone is a detached neural spine anterior to the neural spine of preural centrum 2.

name: Y bone
description: The y bone is a detached neural spine anterior to the haemal spines of preural centrum 2.

name: anal fin pterygiophore 1
description: Anal fin pterygiophore that is the anteriormost of the series.

name: anal fin spine 1
description: Anal fin spine that is the anteriormost element of the series.

name: anal fin spine 2
description: Anal fin spine that is located posteriorly adjacent to the first anal fin spine.

name: dorsal fin ceratotrichial spine (elasmobranchs)
description: A small to large enameloid-covered, dentine-cored spine located on the anterior margins of one or both of the dorsal fins, found on bullhead sharks (Heterodontiformes), many dogfish sharks, fossil (but not living) batoids, chimaeroids, but lost entirely or buried in the fin bases of other shark-like fishes.

name: postcleithral scale
description: Scale that is posteriorly adjacent to the pectoral girdle.

name: rudimentary pectoral fin ray
description: Pectoral fin lepidtrichium that is small, unbranched and unsegmented.

name: ectocoracoid bone
description: A paired dermal bone in Gasterosteiformes connected with the coracoid and extending posteriorly. Has also been applied to the element below the scapula and applied to the coracoid in Dipnoi. Dictionary of Ichthyology.

name: caudal vertebra 1
description: Caudal vertebra that is the anteriormost element of the series.

name: ventral limb of posttemporal
description: Zone of bone organ that is the ventral extension of the posttemporal.

name: lepidotrichial segment
description: Zone of bone organ that is part of a lepidotrich and connected to other segments by collagen fibers. These segments lend flexibility to the lepidtrich.

name: proximal segment of caudal ray
description: Lepidotrichial segment that is part of the proximal region of a caudal fin ray.

name: lateral ethmoid element
description: Endochondral element that separates the olfactory region from the orbit, extends medially to meet its fellow medially below the frontal bones and is bordered by the mesethmoid anteriorly. It may articulate with the autopalatine and infraorbital 1 laterally. The lateral ethmoid is paired.

name: distal segment of caudal ray
description: Lepidotrichial segment that is part of the distal region of a caudal fin ray.

name: pelvic sucking disc
description: An adhesive disk modified from the pelvic fins in, for example, clingfishes (Gobiesocidae), gobies (Gobiidae) and snailfishes (Liparidae).
synonyms: ["adhesive disc","pelvic fin sucking disc","sucking disc","ventral sucking disc"]

name: sucking disc
description: Distinctive first dorsal fin taking the form of a modified oval sucker-like organ with slat-like structures that open and close to create suction and take a firm hold against the skin of larger marine animals.

name: dorsal fin ray
description: Soft ray that is part of the dorsal fin.

name: pelvic fin ray
description: Soft ray that is part of the pelvic fin.

name: glenoid region
description: Region surrounding the glenoid fossa on the scapulocoracoid.

name: spinous region of dorsal fin
description: Region of dorsal fin that is composed of spinous rays (vs soft rays).

name: zygantrum
description: A fossa on the posterior median part of the neural arch of a vertebra (as of a snake) that accommodates the zygosphene of the next vertebra.

name: pre-axial region
description: Anatomical region lying to the anterior or dorsal side of the metapterygial axis.

name: axis intercentrum
description: The intercentrum unit of the axis vertebra.

name: dorsal iliac ridge
description: Ridge that is part of the ilium.

name: tectorial restraint system
description: Tectorial restraint system is a type of ciliary restraint system for hair cells in the inner ear.  In tectorial restraint systems, the tectorial membrane restrains the cilia of the hair cells by attaching either directly to ciliary tufts or indirectly through various kinds of fibrous structure (simple fibers, fibrous strands, finger-like processes, tectorial plates).

name: nuchal crest
description: Bony protuberance on the external surface of the occipital bone.

name: sacral rib
description: Elements of the sacrum joining true sacral vertebrae to pelvis.

name: dorsal pelvic gland
description: Cloacal glands that secrete into the dorsal roof of the cloacal tube and or the anterior cloacal chamber. Found in male salamanders.

name: glossopharyngeal nerve foramen
description: Foramen for the passage of the glossopharyngeal nerve IX.

name: upper jaw symphyseal region
description: The region of the upper jaw on or near the midline.

name: lateral commissure
description: Region of the braincase which bears the facets for the hyomandibula in fishes. This region disappears in the origin of tetrapods and the space it occipied comes to contribute to the fenestra vestibulii. Clack, JA, 2001. Ch. 23, The otoccipital region. In Major Events in Early Vertebrate Evolution. Per Ahlberg editor.

name: upper jaw symphyseal tooth
description: Tooth of the upper jaw that is adjacent to the upper jaw symphysis.

name: lingual region
description: The region of an anatomical structure (such as a tooth or jaw bone) facing the tongue.

name: labial region
description: The region of an anatomical structure, such as a tooth or jaw bone, facing the lips.

name: posterolingual region
description: The region of an anatomical structure, such as a tooth or jaw bone, oriented posteriorly and facing the lips.

name: mesial region
description: The region of an anatomical structure, such as a tooth or jaw bone, facing the midline of the jaw.

name: internal carotid foramen
description: Foramen for the passage of the internal carotid artery.

name: profundus foramen
description: Foramen for the profundus or ophthalmic nerve

name: pectoral fin base
description: Subdivision of organism that is the basal region of the pectoral fin..

name: gill membrane
description: Membrane organ that is usually supported by branchiostegal rays and forms the ventral and posterior wall of the gill cavity.

name: pelvic intercleithral cartilage
description: Cartilage element that lies between processes of the cleithrum and pelvic girdle in gobioid fishes. Posterodorsal to the ventral end of each cleithrum is a posteriorly projecting process. The pelvic intercleithral cartilage (an unpaired, median structure) forms a bridge between the processes (From Springer, 1983).

name: accessory nasal sac
description: Accessory nasal sacs are found in a variety of teleosts (Webb, 1993) and likely assist in ventilating the olfactory epithelium by transmitting pressure ﬂuctuations associated with gill irrigation from theoral cavity to the nasal (or sensory) sac (Jakubowski,1975; Webb, 1993; Belanger et al., 2003).

name: Sharpey's fiber
description: Sharpey's fibres (bone fibres, or perforating fibres) are a matrix of connective tissue consisting of bundles of strong collagenous fibres connecting periosteum to bone. They are part of the outer fibrous layer of periosteum, entering into the outer circumferential and interstitial lamellae of bone tissue.

name: procurrent spur
description: A ventrally projecting spur on the posteriormost ventral procurrent caudal ray overlapping ventrally the preceding ray in various percomorphs (Johnson, 1975).

name: pectoral splint
description: Unpaired bone that covers the base of the first pectoral ray.

name: midshaft
description: Region in the middle of the shaft of a long bone (e.g. humerus, femur etc).

name: pectoral fin bud
description: A paired fin bud that develops into a pectoral fin.

name: pelvic fin bud
description: A paired fin bud that develops into a pelvic fin.

name: actinopterygian pyloric caecum
description: A finger-like out-pocketing of the intestine where it meets the end of the stomach (pylorus). Also spelled cecum (ceca). Serves to aid digestion.

name: procumbent dorsal fin spine
description: Fin spine that precedes the dorsal fin, oriented anteriorly towards the head of the fish.

name: parietal branch of the supraorbital canal
description: Branch of supraorbital sensory canal that extends to the parietal.

name: replacement tooth row
description: Tooth row consisting of replacement teeth.

name: inner tooth row of dentary
description: Dentary tooth row that is lingual in position relative to other tooth rows.

name: inner tooth row of premaxilla
description: Tooth row on the premaxilla that is lingually located relative to other tooth rows.

name: isthmus
description: The fleshy throat region of a fish which extends forward from the ventral part of the chest and narrows anteriorly, and externally separating the two gill chambers; that narrowed portion of the breast which lies between the gill chambers and separates them.

name: posterior sclerotic cartilage
description: Sclerotic cartilage that is located posterior to the eye.

name: anterior sclerotic cartilage
description: Sclerotic cartilage that is located anterior to the eye.

name: neural spine 5
description: Neural spine that is associated with the fifth vertebra.

name: neural spine 6
description: Neural spine that is associated with the sixth vertebra.

name: neural spine 7
description: Neural spine that is associated with the seventh vertebra.

name: terminal scale
description: The posteriormost scale in a scale series.

name: parapophysis 3
description: Parapophysis that is the lateral projection from the third centrum. Parapophysis 3 is bilaterally paired.

name: claustrum element
description: Postcranial axial skeletal element and Weberian ossicle that is located dorsal to the scaphium. The claustrum skeletal element is bilaterally paired.

name: branched pelvic fin ray
description: Pelvic fin lepidotrichium that is distally branched and segmented.

name: unbranched anal fin ray
description: Anal fin lepidotrichium that is not distally branched.

name: photophore
description: A light-emitting organ which appears as luminous spots on various marine animals, including fish and cephalopods.

name: rostral tubule
description: Consists of a set of tubuli occupying the space between the external dermal bones above the dorsal and anterior wal of the nasal capsule below. Thomson and Campbell (1971)..

name: Westoll line
description: More or less concentric lines of discontinuity in the cosmine of Dipnoi, probably due to cyclic resorption and redeposition during growth occurring on the bases of individual scales and also as large structures between headshield plates.

name: epichordal radial
description: Radial found above the vertebral column.

name: postsplenial
description: Dermal bone of the lower jaw.

name: postparietal shield
description: Dermal bones (postparietals, supratemporals, intertemporals, extrascapulars) posterior to the intracranial joint. Forey 1997.

name: subepiotic fossa
description: Fossa for epaxial musculature inserting on the braincase. Forey et al. 1996.

name: endoskeletal cranial joint
description: The braincase of most plesiomorphic sarcopterygians is divided by the intracranial point into ethmosphenoid and otic-occipital portions each covered by dermal bones. The function of the joint is presumably to increase the gape of the mouth rapidly during opening phases. (Forey 1997)

name: tectum orbitale
description: The dorsal portion of the endocranium that covers the orbital region. Hanken and Hall (1993)

name: obsolete accessory nasal sac
description: Structures that communicate with the main olfactory chamber and may be located posterior, ventral, or dorsal to it.

name: palato-maxillary ligament
description: Ligament between the palatine and maxilla.

name: mandibulo-lacrimal ligament
description: Ligament that connects the ventromedial end of the lacrimal to the anguloarticular (or ‘mandible’). Parenti (2008)

name: submandibular series
description: A series of plate like bones found ventrally to the jaw.

name: transversus epibranchialis 2
description: Dorsal gill-arch muscle connecting right and left epibranchial 2s. Springer and Johnson (2015)

name: lateral plate
description: Body plates on the lateral sides of the body that occur as single bilateral rows and their number is highly heritable. Bell and Richkind (1981)
