name: acrodin
description: Odontoid tissue forming a cap on teeth found in teeth of actinopterygian fishes.

name: supraneural 1 element
description: Postcranial axial skeletal element located dorsal to vertebra 1.

name: supraneural 2 element
description: Postcranial axial skeletal element located dorsal to vertebra 2.

name: supraneural 3 element
description: Postcranial axial skeletal element located dorsal to vertebrae 3 and 4.

name: supraneural 4 element
description: Supraneural element dorsal to neural spine 4.

name: supraneural 5 element
description: Supraneural element dorsal to neural spine 5.

name: supraneural 6 element
description: Supraneural element dorsal to neural spine 6.

name: supraneural 7 element
description: Supraneural element dorsal to neural spine 7.

name: supraneural 8 element
description: Supraneural element dorsal to neural spine 8.

name: supraneural 9 element
description: Supraneural element dorsal to neural spine 9.

name: axilar scale
description: Scale that is adjacent to the pelvic fin and aligned with the origin of the pelvic fin. It is typically an elongate scale.

name: precaudal vertebra
description: Vertebral bone lacking hemal spines (Weitzman, 1962), refers generally to the anterior vertebral region bounding the abdominal cavity. Alternate but not quite synonymous terms are abdominal or trunk vertebrae, which bear parapophyses and ribs. In many actinopterygians dorsal to the posterior abdominal cavity there are transitional vertebrae lacking ribs but also without hemal spines or sometimes even enclosed hemal arches. The primary definition would identify these vertebrae as precaudal. Bird and Mabee, 2003.

name: precaudal vertebra endochondral element
description: Vertebral elements lacking hemal spines (Weitzman, 1962), refers generally to the anterior vertebral region bounding the abdominal cavity. Alternate but not quite synonymous terms are abdominal or trunk vertebrae, which bear parapophyses and ribs. In many actinopterygians dorsal to the posterior abdominal cavity there are transitional vertebrae lacking ribs but also without hemal spines or sometimes even enclosed hemal arches. The primary definition would identify these vertebrae as precaudal.(Bird and Mabee, 2003)

name: precaudal vertebra cartilage element
description: Vertebral cartilage elements lacking hemal spines (Weitzman, 1962), refers generally to the anterior vertebral region bounding the abdominal cavity. Alternate but not quite synonymous terms are abdominal or trunk vertebrae, which bear parapophyses and ribs. In many actinopterygians dorsal to the posterior abdominal cavity there are transitional vertebrae lacking ribs but also without hemal spines or sometimes even enclosed hemal arches. The primary definition would identify these vertebrae as precaudal.(Bird and Mabee, 2003)

name: forelimb bud mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a forelimb bud.

name: hindlimb bud mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a hindlimb bud.

name: pectoral fin bud mesenchyme
description: Mesechyme that is part of a pectoral fin bud.

name: pelvic fin bud mesenchyme
description: Mesechyme that is part of a pelvic fin bud.

name: forelimb wing bud
description: A wing bud that develops into a wing

name: forelimb wing bud mesenchyme
description: Mesenchyme that is part of a forelimb wing bud.

name: mammiliform tooth
description: Calcareous tooth with a hyptertrophied base.

name: scale sheath
description: Series of scales in which each scale envelopes or overlaps an adjacent scale.

name: spinoid scale
description: A cycloid scale bearing a serrated margin; superficially similar to ctenoid scales but having spines as outgrowths of the scale as oppose to true ctenii.

name: rib of vertebra 7
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the seventh centrum.

name: rib of vertebra 8
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the eighth centrum.

name: hind flipper
description: Hindlimb that is used to propel an animal through water.

name: rostral ossicle
description: Ossicle that surrounds the sensory canals of the snout when passing from the ethmoidal commissure to the infraorbital series and have first been noticed by Nybelin in Elops. From: Filleul and Lavoué. (2001). Basal teleosts and the question of elopomorph monophyly. Morphological and molecular approaches. Comptes rendus de l'Académie des sciences. Série III, Sciences de la vie. 324. 393-9. 10.1016/S0764-4469(00)01302-0.

name: ethmoid commissure
description: Sensory canal that traverses the rostral bone.

name: lateral line scale 6
description: The sixth scale in the lateral line series.

name: premaxillary tooth 2
description: Premaxillary tooth that is the second tooth in a premaxillary tooth series, and positioned adjacent to the symphyseal tooth.

name: premaxillary tooth 3
description: Premaxillary tooth that is the third tooth in a premaxillary tooth series, and positioned adjacent to the second tooth.

name: dentary tooth 2
description: Dentary tooth that is the second tooth in a dentary tooth series, and positioned adjacent to the symphyseal tooth.

name: dentary tooth 3
description: Dentary tooth that is the third tooth in a dentary tooth series, and positioned adjacent to the symphyseal tooth.

name: fused hypural 1 and 2
description: Single hypural element formed from the fusion of hypural 1 and 2.

name: lateral occipital foramen
description: Foramen that has the exoccipital as the anterior and dorsal rim. The occipital forms the anterior rim during early development.

name: ethmo-palatine cartilage
description: The ethmo-palatine cartilage (EPC) is a distinct body situated between the posterior surface of the upper arm of the premaxilla and the anterior margin of the palatine. There is usually only a single cartilage mass lying between these bones, although that cartilage is apparently subdivided into two units in some taxa (e.g., the Old World characiform family Citharinidae, Vari, 1979:294). Vari 1989a.

name: pectoral fin hook
description: Process that is part of the pectoral fin lepidotrichium.

name: pelvic fin hook
description: Process that is part of the pelvic fin lepidotrichium.

name: epioccipital bridge
description: Extension of the exoccipital that extends over the posttemporal fossa.

name: outer tooth row of premaxilla
description: Tooth row on the premaxilla that is labially located relative to other tooth rows.

name: interneural spine cartilage
description: Cartilage element adjacent to neural spine of preural centrum.

name: interhaemal spine cartilage
description: Cartilage element adjacent to haemal spine of preural centrum.

name: adipose fin ray
description: Soft ray that is part of the adipose fin.

name: suborbital stay
description: A backwards extension of the third circumorbital bone (part of the lateral head/cheek skeleton, below the eye socket) across the cheek to the preoperculum, to which it is connected in most species

name: outer tooth row of dentary
description: Dentary tooth row that is labial in position relative to other tooth rows.

name: metapterygoid tooth
description: Tooth that is attached to the metapterygoid.

name: dorsal fin hook
description: Anatomical projection that is part of the anal fin lepidotrichium.

name: dorsal myorhabdoid bone
description: Myorhabdoid bones located dorsal to the epineurals.

name: ventral myorhabdoid bone
description: Myorhabdoid bones located ventral to the epipleurals.

name: fin hook
description: Anatomical projection that is part of a fin.

name: second preethmoid cartilage
description: Cartilage element found between the preethmoid and maxilla.

name: second preethmoid element
description: Endochondral skeletal element found between the preethmoid and maxilla.

name: nasal barbel
description: Barbel that is associated with a nostril. Nasal barbels are paired.

name: rictal barbel
description: Barbel located from the fleshy corner of the mouth.

name: metapterygium cartilage
description: The posterior and innermost of the three principal basal cartilages in the fins of fishes.

name: ceratotrichium
description: Elastoidin fin ray that is thickened, generally unbranched and found in the fins of Chondrichthyes.

name: fin ray
description: A rod-like entity that functions in support of fin folds and fins

name: elastoidin fin ray
description: Fin ray that is composed of elastoidin, unmineralized, and unsegmented.

name: camptotrichium
description: Fin ray found in dipnoans that are composed of a superficial region of acellular fibrous bone, and a deep, mostly unmineralized, zone (Géraudie and Meunier 1982)

name: paired fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium that is part of a paired fin.

name: upper uroneural
description: Uroneurals that form the uppermost three uroneural series that overlap, and lie at an angle to, longer anterior ones.

name: predorsal scale
description: Scale that is part of row along the midline between the dorsal fin and the back of the skull. In counting, all scales crossing the midline are included. (Fishbase)

name: adipose fin skeleton
description: Median fin skeleton supporting the adipose fin.

name: prenasal ossicle
description: Tubular ossifications around extension of nasal lateral line canal in fishes; typically one or two.

name: anal fin ray
description: Soft ray that is part of the anal fin.

name: pectoral fin ray
description: Soft ray that is part of the pectoral fin.

name: median fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium that is part of a median fin.

name: paired fin spine
description: Fin spine that is part of a paired fin.

name: unbranched pectoral fin ray
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that is not distally branched.

name: unbranched pelvic fin ray
description: Pelvic fin lepidotrichium that is not distally branched.

name: hypobranchial series
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of the hypobranchial elements within an individual.

name: pharyngobranchial series
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of the pharyngobranchial elements within an individual.

name: basibranchial series
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of the basibranchial elements within an individual.

name: premaxilla articular process
description: Pharyngeal arch bone immediately posterior to the ascending process, the medial surface of which articulates with the anterior end of the maxillary.

name: interarcual bone
description: Pharyngeal arch bone located between uncinate process of epibranchial 1 and pharyngobranchial 2.

name: premaxilla maxillary process
description: Process of the premaxilla that extends upward, and often lies against the medial surface of the maxillary.

name: pelvic fin distal radial cartilage
description: Pelvic fin distal radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue

name: panarthropod tagma
description: The three main divisions of the whole organism formed from groups of segments.

name: insect ocular segment
description: Head segment derived from the second embryonic segment (between the labral and antennal segments). In the larva, this segment includes Bolwig's organ.

name: head segment
description: Any segment that is part of some head.

name: procephalic segment
description: A segment that is anterior to the gnathal segments.

name: labral segment
description: Procephalic segment anterior to the antennal segment. In the adult it bears the clypeo-labrum.

name: antennal segment
description: Segment anterior to the intercalary segment. In the adult it bears the antennae.

name: insect gnathal segment
description: The head segments that develop posterior to the embryonic/larval mouth.

name: insect labial segment
description: Most posterior of the gnathal segments. In the adult it bears a pair of fused appendages, the labia, and its ectodermal invaginations give rise to the salivary glands.

name: insect thorax
description: The main middle section of the insect body comprising three thoracic rings: the pro-, the meso- and the metathoraces which are more or less well fused and cask-like sometimes having on the upper lateral part one of two pairs of wings, while on the ventrolateral part each thoracic ring bears a pair of legs.

name: insect thoracic segment
description: Any segment (UBERON:6000003) that is part of some thorax (UBERON:6000015).

name: insect prothoracic segment
description: The first (most anterior) segment of the thorax.

name: insect mesothoracic segment
description: The second (middle) segment of the thorax.

name: insect metathoracic segment
description: The third (most posterior) segment of the thorax.

name: insect abdomen
description: The most posterior of the three tagma (UBERON:6000002).

name: insect abdominal segment
description: Metameric subdivision of the abdomen.

name: insect dorsal appendage
description: Paired appendage of the eggshell, located on the anterior-dorsal side of the egg, just posterior to the operculum. Functions as a respiratory structures.

name: insect anterior ectoderm
description: The region of the ectoderm anterior to the cephalic furrow.

name: insect trunk mesoderm
description: The mesoderm of segments T1-A9. It first becomes morphologically distinct during ventral furrow formation. Following invagination during stages 6 and 7, it remains a coherent structure with no morphologically apparent subdivisions, apart from transient metamery during stage 9, until stage 11. It undergoes a number of morphological changes during this period: as its cells divide following invagination, it loses its epithelial integrity and by stage 9 has rearranged into a monolayer of cuboidal cells. A further division happens during stage 10 leading to two distinct layers by stage 11.

name: insect mesodermal crest of segment T3
embryonic tagma
description: Any tagma (UBERON:6000002) that is part of some embryo (UBERON:6000052).

name: embryonic segment
description: Any segment that is part of some embryo.

name: embryonic head segment
description: Any segment that is part of some embryonic head.

name: insect embryonic procephalic segment
description: Any procephalic segment (UBERON:6000007) that is part of some embryonic head (UBERON:6000155).

name: insect embryonic thorax
description: Any thorax (UBERON:6000015) that is part of some embryo (UBERON:6000052).

name: insect embryonic thoracic segment
description: Any segment (UBERON:6000003) that is part of some embryonic thorax (UBERON:6000166).

name: insect embryonic prothoracic segment
description: Prothoracic segment of the embryo.

name: insect embryonic mesothoracic segment
description: Mesothoracic segment of the embryo.

name: insect embryonic abdomen
description: Abdomen of the embryo.

name: insect embryonic abdominal segment
description: Metameric subdivision of the embryonic abdomen.

name: insect embryonic abdominal segment 8
description: Any abdominal segment 8 (UBERON:6000029) that is part of some embryonic abdomen (UBERON:6000171).

name: insect embryonic abdominal segment 9
description: Any abdominal segment 9 (UBERON:6000030) that is part of some embryonic abdomen (UBERON:6000171).

name: insect presumptive embryonic/larval nervous system
description: The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the embryonic/larval nervous system.

name: insect presumptive embryonic/larval central nervous system
description: The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the embryonic/larval central nervous system.

name: insect embryonic brain
description: Brain of the embryo.

name: insect proneural cluster
description: An equivalence group of the neurectoderm where all cells can, although only one will, become a neural progenitor cell.

name: insect embryonic imaginal precursor
description: Embryonic structure that will proliferate during larval development into a larval imaginal disc. During early embryogenesis the precursor is part of the epithelial sheet before segregating from the epithelial sheet by late embryogenesis (Bate and Martinez Arias, 1991).

name: insect imaginal disc primordium
description: Population of contiguous, morphologically distinct cells that will form an imaginal disc.

name: insect labial disc primordium
description: Primordium that will form the labial disc.

name: insect eye-antennal disc primordium
description: Primordium from which the eye-antennal disc develops.

name: insect genital disc primordium
description: Primordium from which the genital disc develops.

name: insect male genital disc primordium
description: Primordium from which the male genital disc derives.

name: insect female genital disc primordium
description: Primordium from which the female genital disc derives.

name: insect embryonic/larval circulatory system
description: Tubular system of the embryo/larva through which hemolymph flows.

name: insect embryonic/larval lymph gland
description: Hematopoietic organ of the larva, located along the dorsal vessel, behind the brain. It produces the plasmatocytes, crystal cells and lamellocytes which are released at the end of the larval instar and onset of metamorphosis. It is composed of 3 pairs of bilateral lobes: an anterior primary lobe, a posterior secondary lobe and the most posterior lobe (or multiple lobes), the tertiary lobe. Each lobe is separated by pericardial cells. In the late embryo, the lymph gland consists of a single pair of lobes (primary lobes) containing around 20 cells each that flank the dorsal vessel. By the second larval instar, the lymph gland is composed of two or three new pairs of posterior lobes, and the primary lobes have increased in size to contain around 200 cells. During the first and early second larval instars, the lymph gland comprises only the hematopoietic progenitor population. The lymph gland increases in size ten-fold by the late third instar, and at this stage the progenitor cells (prohemocytes) become restricted to the medial region (medullary zone) of the primary lobe and become quiescent. The differentiated hemocytes are found in the periphery (cortical zone) of the primary lobe and these cells proliferate extensively. The posterior signalling center is a group of about 30 cells at the posterior tip of the primary lobe that secretes several signalling molecules and functions as a stem-cell niche. The secondary and tertiary lobes contain prohemocytes, and rarely a differentiated cell. Lymph glands are eliminated at metamorphosis.

name: insect ring gland
description: A closely associated cluster of three neuroendocrine glands located anterior to the aorta and dorsal to the esophagus. At embryonic stage 17 and in larva it is found anterior to the brain and is formed by the corpus cardiacum ventrally, the prothoracic gland laterally and the corpus allatum dorsally. The adult ring gland is located anterior to the proventriculus and is formed by the corpus cardiacum ventrally, the corpus allatum dorsally and the hypocerebral ganglion posterior to the corpus cardiacum. It is innervated by neurons of the nervus corporis cardiaci (NccI-III).

name: insect larval tagma
description: Any tagma (UBERON:6000002) that is part of some larva (UBERON:6001727).

name: insect larval segment
description: Any segment that is part of some larva.

description: Any ocular segment (UBERON:6000005) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

description: Any procephalic segment (UBERON:6000007) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

name: insect larval gnathal segment
description: Any gnathal segment (UBERON:6000011) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

description: Any mesothoracic segment (UBERON:6000018) that is part of some larval thorax (UBERON:6001741).

name: insect larval metathoracic segment
description: Any metathoracic segment (UBERON:6000019) that is part of some larval thorax (UBERON:6001741).

name: insect larval abdomen
description: Any abdomen (UBERON:6000020) that is part of some larva (UBERON:6001727).

name: insect larval abdominal segment
description: Any segment (UBERON:6000003) that is part of some larval abdomen (UBERON:6001746).

name: insect larval abdominal segment 8
description: Any abdominal segment 8 (UBERON:6000029) that is part of some larval abdomen (UBERON:6001746).

name: insect larval abdominal segment 9
description: Any abdominal segment 9 (UBERON:6000030) that is part of some larval abdomen (UBERON:6001746).

name: insect embryonic/larval imaginal precursor
description: Imaginal precursor that is part of the embryo/larva.

name: insect labial disc
description: Imaginal disc that, in the adult, gives rise to the proboscis, including the prementum, prestomal cavity, labellum, labellar cap and pseudotrachea (Cohen, 1993).

name: insect clypeo-labral disc
description: Imaginal disc that in the adults gives rise to the labrum, anterior and posterior cibarial plates, fish trap bristles, epipharyngeal sclerite and clypeus (Cohen, 1993).

name: insect eye-antennal disc
description: Imaginal disc that, in the adults, gives rise to the eye, antenna, head capsule (including all bristles and external membranes) and the maxillary palps (Cohen, 1993).

name: insect antennal disc
description: Posterior portion of the eye-antennal disc. It gives rise to the adult antennal segments and the maxillary palp, as well as contributing to the head capsule.

name: insect dorsal thoracic disc
description: Imaginal disc that is a precursor of dorsal thoracic structures of the adult.

name: insect wing disc
description: Dorsal imaginal disc of the mesothorax. Precursor of dorsal mesothoracic structures of the adult including the postnotum, scutum, scutellum, wing, wing hinge and part of the notal pleura.

name: insect haltere disc
description: Dorsal imaginal disc of the metathorax. Precursor of structure of the adult dorsal metathorax including the haltere.

name: insect ventral thoracic disc
description: Imaginal disc that is a precursor of ventral thoracic structures of the adult.

name: insect prothoracic leg disc
description: Imaginal disc of the ventral prothoracic segment. Precursor of structures of the adult ventral prothorax including the prothoracic (1st) leg.
synonyms: ["1st leg disc","T1 leg disc","ventral prothoracic disc"]

name: insect genital disc
description: Imaginal disc that gives rise to the internal and external genitalia, analia and adult hind gut (Cohen, 1993).

name: insect male genital disc
description: Genital disc that gives rise to the penis and external genitalia, sperm pump, ejaculatory duct, paragonia and vas deferens, anal plates and adult hindgut (Cohen, 1993).

name: insect female genital disc
description: Genital disc that gives rise to the vagina and vaginal plates, uterus, parovaria, spermatheca, seminal recepticle, oviducts, female analia and hindgut. (Cohen, 1993).

name: insect histoblast
description: A progenitor of the adult external abdomen.

name: insect histoblast nest
description: One of several groups of cells in the larval abdomen that gives rise to the adult external abdomen.

name: insect anterior dorsal histoblast nest abdominal
insect posterior dorsal histoblast nest abdominal
insect cephalopharyngeal skeleton
description: A group of connected sclerites of the anterior embryonic/larval digestive system (atrium, pharynx and dorsal pouch). The cibarial dilator muscles connect to the cephalopharyngeal skeleton to lift the roof of the pharynx and thereby widen its lumen (Jurgens, 1986).

name: insect epipharyngeal sclerite
description: Unpaired sclerite to which the median tooth (labrum) posteriorly merges, and bears the cuticular pores of the labral sense organ.

name: insect embryonic/larval nervous system
description: Nervous system of the embryo/larva.

name: insect embryonic/larval central nervous system
description: Central nervous system of the embryo/larva.

name: insect embryonic/larval brain
description: Brain of the embryo/larva.

name: insect embryonic/larval protocerebrum
description: Protocerebrum of the embryo/larva.

name: insect larval sense organ
description: Any sense organ that is part of some larva.

name: insect embryonic/larval ocular segment sensillum
description: Any embryonic/larval sense organ (UBERON:6002639) that is part of some larval ocular segment (UBERON:6001731).

name: insect adult tagma
description: Any tagma (UBERON:6000002) that is part of some adult (UBERON:6003004).

name: adult segment
description: Segment of the adult.

name: insect adult head
description: Head of the adult organism.

description: Segment of the adult head.

name: insect adult labral segment
description: Any labral segment (UBERON:6000008) that is part of some adult head (UBERON:6003007).

name: insect adult antennal segment
description: Any antennal segment (UBERON:6000009) that is part of some adult head (UBERON:6003007).

name: insect adult thorax
description: Thorax of the adult.

name: insect adult thoracic segment
description: Any segment (UBERON:6000003) that is part of some adult thorax (UBERON:6003018).

name: insect adult prothoracic segment
description: Any prothoracic segment (UBERON:6000017) that is part of some adult thorax (UBERON:6003018).

name: insect adult mesothoracic segment
description: Any mesothoracic segment (UBERON:6000018) that is part of some adult thorax (UBERON:6003018).

name: insect adult abdomen
description: Abdomen of the adult.

name: insect adult abdominal segment
description: Any abdominal segment (UBERON:6000021) that is part of some adult abdomen (UBERON:6003023).

name: insect adult muscle system
description: Muscle system of the adult.

name: insect adult somatic muscle
description: Muscle attached to the inner surface of the adult body wall, extending between articulated or flexibly joined areas, that serves to move the parts of the exoskeleton.

name: insect adult central nervous system
description: Central nervous system of the adult.

name: insect adult brain
description: Brain of the adult.

name: insect supraesophageal ganglion
description: The pre-oral neuropils of the brain located above and some of it below the esophagus, comprising three fused ganglia (protocerebrum, deutocerebrum, and tritocerebrum) in the head.

name: insect protocerebrum
description: The most anterior of the segmental subdivisions of the insect CNS; thought to represent the first pre-oral segment of the brain. The protocerebrum comprises many discrete neuropil regions including the central body complex and mushroom bodies.

name: insect adult central complex
description: A midline crossing complex of 4 synaptic neuropil domains of the adult brain: the ellipsoid body, the fan-shaped body, the paired noduli, and the protocerebral bridge. It is closely associated with another paired synaptic neuropil domain, the lateral complex. It lies in the middle of the brain between the pedunculi of the mushroom bodies and is bounded ventrally by the esophagus, dorsally by the pars intercerebralis and laterally by the antenno-glomerular tracts.

name: insect sex comb
description: A row of darkly pigmented, male specific chaetae located on the prothoracic metatarsal segment of the prothoracic leg. The number of chaetae (teeth) per sex comb varies between individuals, e.g.- Hannah-Alava and Stern report 10-13.

name: insect wing hair
description: The posteriorly oriented trichome of a cell of the wing blade. Each cell makes one of these trichomes at its posterior vertex.

name: insect sclerite
description: A region of integument whose external cuticular part is a hard, sclerotized plate.

name: insect tergite
description: The dorsal plate (sclerite) of an adult abdominal segment.

name: insect sternite
description: An adult ventral sclerite.

name: insect arista
description: Highly specialised, slender sixth segment of the antenna covered in bristle-like outgrowths known as laterals. It extends laterally from the dorsal region of the third segment of the antenna.

name: insect clypeus
description: The anterior part of the head between the frons and the labrum, which occasionally may fuse with either one to form the frontoclypeus and the clypeolabrum. In the context of Drosophila refers to a round structure on the center of the frontal adult external head.

name: insect proboscis
description: The trunk-like extension of adult head, forming a protrusible sucking proboscis for the ingestion of liquid food (pg 425 Miller et al., 1950; pg 383, Ferris et al., 1950).

name: insect tergum
description: The upper, originally unpaired plate of the segmented insect body, which either independently or fused with a ventral plate covers the body dorsally, specifically that of the thorax.

name: insect mesothoracic tergum
description: The dorsal sclerites (tergites) of the mesothorax.

name: insect tarsal segment
description: A segment of the tarsus of the adult leg. The first tarsal segment, the metatarsus, is proximally connected to the tibia. Tarsal segments are covered in 8 longitudinal rows of bristles, with row 1 being the most ventral.

name: insect metatarsus
description: The first of the tarsal segments of the adult leg. It is located between the tibia and the second tarsal segment and is longer than the other tarsal segments. It has 8 longitudinal rows of bristles around the circumference.
synonyms: ["1st tarsal segment","basitarsus","first segment of the tarsus","first tarsal segment","tarsal segment 1"]

name: insect prothoracic leg
description: Leg of the prothoracic segment.

name: insect prothoracic tarsal segment
description: Tarsal segment of the adult prothoracic leg.

name: insect prothoracic metatarsus
description: First tarsal segment of the prothoracic leg. Proximally, it articulates with the tibia and distally with the second tarsal segment. Its surface is covered with eight longitudinal rows of bristles and with transverse rows of bristles (TR) in the anterior compartment, between proximo-distal rows 7 and 8. There is sexual dimorphism in the number of TRs (transverse row bristles, TR). In males, 2 TRs are replaced by the sex comb and one central bristle.
synonyms: ["prothoracic basitarsus","prothoracic tarsal segment 1","T1 tarsal segment 1","T1 Ts1"]

name: insect trichome
description: Non-innervated projection of the cuticle around an actin-rich cellular process of an underlying epidermal cell.

name: insect imaginal precursor
description: Structure that proliferates to produce a larval imaginal disc and which gives rise to adult tissues (Bate and Martinez Arias, 1991).

name: insect tracheal pit
description: Deep and narrow pit formed by the invagination of a tracheal placode in a late extended germ band embryo. Invagination of the placode begins during stage 11. Branches begin to bud from the pit during stage 11, with a dorsal and ventral stem being apparent by mid-stage 12. The pit closes over during stage 13. There are 10 pairs of tracheal pits - one pair in each tracheal metamere (each segment from T2 to A8). Pits are located in the central one third of each parasegment, with the most anterior in parasegment 4 and the most posterior in parasegment 14.

name: insect tracheal primordium
description: Primordium of a single tracheal metamere of the embryonic/larval tracheal system from its appearance as a placode during stage 11 to the completion of fusion with adjacent tracheal metameres in stage 15/16. There are 10 pairs of tracheal primordia - one pair in each segment from T2 to A8. Each tracheal primordium originates as a slight depression in the lateral ectoderm during stage 10 known as a tracheal placode. During stage 11, these placodes invaginate to form tracheal pits that elongate and branch. These pits close over during stage 13. Fusion of tracheal primordia begins at stage 14 with fusion of the dorsal trunk primordia and is complete by early stage 16.

name: insect spiracle
description: Opening of the tracheal system on the surface of the body.

name: obsolete visceral muscle
description: The visceral musculature comprises circular and longitudinal fibers which surround the entire intestinal tract, with the exception of the recurrent layer of the proventriculus. The circular fibers derive from a bilaterally symmetrical band of mesodermal cells extending continuously throughout most of the germ band. The longitudinal fibers derive from clusters of mesodermal cells which appear during stage 12 at the posterior end of the embryo and migrate anteriorly.

name: insect stomatogastric nervous system
description: A group of small, interconnected ganglia situated posterior to and between the two brain hemispheres and associated with the pharynx, esophagus and aorta.

name: insect chaeta
description: A sensillum with a long, unicellular, setiform outgrowth that is strongly chitinized.

name: insect wing margin
description: The border or edge of the wing. It separates the dorsal and ventral compartments.

name: insect anlage in statu nascendi
description: \"anlagen in statu nascendi\" are domains that do not yet coincide 1:1 with a later organ. Anlagen in statu nascendi are typically defined for the early blastoderm by the expression domains of genes which, in the late blastoderm or later, are expressed in specific anlagen, but initially come on in larger domains.

name: insect visual anlage in statu nascendi
insect presumptive embryonic/larval tracheal system
description: The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the embryonic/larval tracheal system. This corresponds to the tracheal primordia and their component tracheal branch primordia along with primordia of the spiracles.

name: insect Bolwig organ
description: Visual organ of the larva. It consists of a dense cluster of 12 ciliated photoreceptor neurons.
synonyms: ["Bolwig's organ","embryonic Bolwig's organ","embryonic visual system","larval Bolwig's organ"]

name: insect arista lateral
description: A bristle-like, non-innervated outgrowth of the arista. Each lateral is formed from the outgrowth of a single polyploid central core cell.

name: insect pharate adult
description: The developing adult after pupal-adult apolysis, i.e. from stage P8 (when yellow eye color first becomes visible through the pupal case), to eclosion.

name: insect mesothoracic tergum primordium
description: Region of the dorsal mesothoracic disc that will develop into the mesothoracic tergum.

name: insect metatarsus of male prothoracic leg
description: First tarsal segment of the male prothoracic leg. In contrast to females, it has a sex comb, central bristle and 5 to 6 transverse rows of bristles (TR).

name: insect trunk ectoderm
description: The region of the ectoderm posterior to the cephalic furrow.

name: insect centro-posterior medial synaptic neuropil domain
description: A synaptic neuropil domain of the larval brain located posterior to the medial lobe of the mushroom body. It is separated from the centro-lateral compartment by the peduncle, and from the centro-posterior intermediate compartment by the antenno-cerebral tract to which it is connected via a branch.
synonyms: ["centro-posterior medial neuropil","centro-posterior medial synaptic neuropil domain","larval central complex"]

name: insect presumptive embryonic/larval system
description: The sum of all the developing presumptive components of a specific embryonic/larval system in an embryo.

name: insect adult protocerebrum
description: Protocerebrum of the adult brain.

name: insect segment of antenna
description: Any appendage segment that is part of some antenna.

name: insect segment of leg
description: Any appendage segment (UBERON:6007018) that is part of some leg (UBERON:6004640).

name: insect external sensillum
description: Sensillum which is embedded in the body wall and has a specific cuticular structure involved in the transduction of some sensory signal as a part.

name: insect eo-type sensillum
description: Sensillum with innervated external cuticular sensory structure consisting of one or more bipolar sensory neurons, and 3 support cells: a trichogen cell which makes the external cuticular sensory structure, a thecogen cell which makes the socket that holds the base of the external sensory structure and a tormogen cell which makes the cuticular matrix (cap) at the tip of the innervating dendrite(s).

name: insect internal sensillum
description: Sensillum that is internal to the animal - i.e. having no part that is part of the cuticle.

name: insect embryonic/larval sensillum
description: Any sensillum (UBERON:6007152) that is part of some larva (UBERON:6001727).

name: insect embryonic/larval head sensillum
description: Any sensillum (UBERON:6007152) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

name: insect chorionic specialization
description: Specialized structure of the chorion of the egg.

name: insect embryonic/larval head sense organ
description: Any sense organ (UBERON:6005155) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

name: insect region of integument
description: A region of cuticle and its underlying epidermis.

name: insect segmental subdivision of integument
description: A segmental subdivision of the integument of the whole animal.

name: insect segmental subdivision of organ system
description: The part of some organism that is part of some specified segment.

name: insect internal sense organ
description: Sense organ that is internal to the animal - i.e. having no part that is part of the cuticle.

name: insect epithelial furrow
description: A region of an epithelium that folds inwards from the epithelial plane to form a furrow.

name: insect non-connected developing system
description: The sum of all the anlagen and primordia that will develop into a single system.

name: insect synaptic neuropil
description: The part of the neuropil consisting largely of synapsing neuron projections.

name: insect synaptic neuropil domain
description: Region of synaptic neuropil whose boundaries are largely discontinuities in the density of presynaptic terminals: high density in the synaptic neuropil domain, lower or zero density outside this region. These boundaries often correspond to a boundary with glial sheath, tract neuropil or cortex.

name: insect synaptic neuropil block
description: A closely associated group of synaptic neuropil domains.

name: insect sensilla row
description: A row of sensilla.

name: insect adult cerebral ganglion
description: The pre-oral neuropils of the adult brain located above, around and partially below the esophagus, including the optic lobes. It excludes the gnathal ganglion. Developmentally, it comprises three fused neuromeres: protocerebrum, deutocerebrum, and tritocerebrum.

name: insect presumptive prothoracic metatarsus
description: Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic metatarsus.

name: insect presumptive arista
description: Region of the antennal disc that will develop into the arista.

name: distal-most point of medial condyle of femur
description: The distal-most point of the medial condyle of a femur.

name: distal-most point of trochlea of humerus
description: The distal-most point of the trochlea of a humerus.

name: tip of tail
description: Outermost point of a tail.

name: line from caundal-sacral region of the vertebral column to the last vertebra
description: An anatomical line along a tail that extends from the first caudal vertebra to the last cuadal vertebra.

name: line from helix of outer ear to intertragus incisure
description: An anatomical line of a ear that connects the helix of the outer ear to the intertragus incisure of an ear.

name: line from the distal-most end of the longest nail to the posterior-most part of the foot
description: An anatomical line of a hindfoot that connects the distal-most part of the longest nail to the posterior-most part of a foot.

name: posterior of pes
description: The posterior-most point of a foot.

name: tip of nail
description: The distal-most point of a cutaneous appendage.

name: tip of digit
description: The distal-most point of a digit.

name: line from the distal-most end of the longest phalax of the foot to the posterior-most part of the foot
description: An anatomical line of a hindfoot that connects the end of the longest digit to the posterior-most part of a foot.

name: line from tip of nose to the caudal-sacral region of the vertebral column
description: An anatomical line of a body that connects the tip of the nose to the posterior-most part of the sacrum.

name: line from tip of nose to the posterior-most part of the last caudal vertebra
description: An anatomical line of a body that connects the tip of the nose to the posterior-most part of a tail.

name: line of medial condyle of femur to greater trochanter
description: An anatomical line of a femur that connects the medial condyle to the greater trochanter.

name: proximal-most point of head of femur
description: The proximal-most point of the head of a femur.

name: proximal-most point of head of humerus
description: The proximal-most point of the head of a humerus.

name: proximal-most point of ventral tubercle of humerus
description: The proximal-most point of the ventral tubercle of a humerus.

name: proximal-most point of greater trochanter of femur
description: The proximal-most point of the greater trochanter of a femur.

name: line of medial condyle of femur to head of femur
description: An anatomical line of a femur that connects the medial condyle to the head of a femur.

name: line from trochlea of humerus to proximal head of humerus
description: An anatomical line of a humerus that connects the trochlea to the proximal head.

name: lower fourth secondary molar tooth
description: The molar tooth of the lower jaw that is phylogenetically number 4.

name: lower fourth secondary premolar tooth
description: The premolar tooth of the lower jaw that is phylogenetically number 4.

name: lower third secondary premolar tooth
description: The premolar tooth of the lower jaw that is phylogenetically number 3.

name: molar tooth 4
description: The molar tooth of the upper or lower jaw that is phylogenetically number 4.

name: premolar 3
description: The premolar tooth of the upper or lower jaw that is phylogenetically number 3.

name: upper fourth secondary molar tooth
description: The molar tooth of the upper jaw that is phylogenetically number 4.

name: upper fourth secondary premolar tooth
description: The premolar tooth of the upper jaw that is phylogenetically number 4.

name: upper third secondary premolar tooth
description: The premolar tooth of the upper jaw that is phylogenetically number 3.

name: line from trochlea of humerus to ventral tubercle of humerus
description: An anatomical line of a humerus that connects the trochlea to the ventral tubercle.

name: central retina
description: Region of retina around the fovea that extends approximately for 6 mm. Central retina is considerably thick due to increased density of photoreceptors, particularly cones and their associated bipolar and ganglion cells.

name: Henle's fiber layer
description: This layer contains bundles of unmyelinated cone and rod photoreceptor axons terminating in the pedicles and spherules that synapse in the retinal outer plexiform layer (OPL).
synonyms: ["Henle fiber layer","HFL","nerve fiber layer of Henle"]

name: left side of back
description: Left part of the organism dorsal to a horizontal plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane.

name: right side of back
description: Right part of the organism dorsal to a horizontal plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane.

name: Purkinje fiber network
description: A collection of Purkinje fibers that receives signals from the right and left bundle branches and innervates the ventricular cardiac muscle. The Purkinje fiber network creates synchronized contractions of the heart ventricles.

name: skin of scalp
description: A zone of skin that is part of a scalp.
synonyms: ["adult scalp zone of skin","scalp skin","scalp zone of skin","zone of skin of adult scalp","zone of skin of scalp"]

name: right forelimb
description: A forelimb that is on the right side of a pectoral complex.

name: left forelimb
description: A forelimb that is on the left side of a pectoral complex.

name: right hindlimb
description: A hindlimb that is on the right side of a pelvic complex.

name: left hindlimb
description: A hindlimb that is on the left side of a pelvic complex.

name: hepatic acinus zone 1
description: The region of the hepatic acinus that is closest to the arterial blood supply and has the highest oxygen concentration. Hepatocytes in this region are primarily involved in oxidative energy metabolism.

name: hepatic acinus zone 3
description: The region of the hepatic acinus immediately surrounding the central veins. This region has the lowest oxygen concentration in the acinus. Hepatocytes in this region are the primary location for the biotransformation of drugs.
synonyms: ["hepatic acinus centrilobular zone","hepatic acinus pericentral zone","hepatic acinus perivenous zone"]

name: hepatic acinus zone 2
description: The region of the hepatic acinus in between zones 1 and 3. Blood in this region has an intermediate oxygen concentration relative to the other two zones of the hepatic acinus. Hepatocytes in this region have mixed functionality in comparison with those in zones 1 and 3.

name: metabolic zone of liver
description: Any of the metabolic zones found in the hepatic acinus. Liver tissue is heterogenous at the level of morphometry and histochemistry. This heterogeneity is linked to the position of a cell within the functional unit of the tissue, which, in turn, is related to the blood supply: Cells located in the upstream zone differ from those in the downstream zone with respect to subcellular structures, key enzymes, translocators, and receptors and, therefore, have different metabolic capacities. This is the basis for \"metabolic zonation\", a concept first proposed for carbohydrate metabolism and later expanded to include amino acid and ammonia metabolism, xenobiotic metabolism, protective metabolism, and formation of plasma proteins.

name: liver lobule periportal region
description: The region of the liver lobule that is closest to the portal triad.

name: liver lobule centrilobular region
description: The region of the liver lobule that is closest to the central vein.

name: liver lobule midzonal region
description: The region of the liver lobule that is between the periportal and centrilobular regions.

name: liver serosa
description: Hepatic serous coat; peritoneal covering of the liver, enclosing almost all except for a triangular area on its posterior surface (the \"bare area of the liver\") and a smaller area where the liver and gallbladder are in direct contact.

name: liver subserosa
description: Subserosal tissue of liver. A zone of areolar connective tissue lying beneath the serous coat of the liver and distinguished with difficulty from the fibrous capsule of Glisson.
synonyms: ["hepatic subserosa","subserosal tissue of liver","subserous layer of liver","tela subserosa (hepar)","tela subserosa hepatis"]

name: subcapsular region of liver
description: Region of liver parenchyma immediately below the capsule. This region is frequently specified in pathology diagnoses.
synonyms: ["liver subcapsular region","liver subcapsular tissue","subcapsular tissue of liver"]

name: duodeno-jejunal junction
description: The anatomical junction between the duodenum and the jejunum.

name: fimbria of uterine tube
description: A fringe of tissue around the ostium of the fallopian tube, in the direction of the ovary.
synonyms: ["fimbria of fallopian tube","fimbriae of fallopian tube","fimbriae of uterine tube"]

name: descending sigmoid junction
description: The anatomical junction between the descending colon and the sigmoid colon.

name: left colic vein
description: A portal vein that drains the descending colon. It is a tributary of the inferior mesenteric vein, and follows the path of its corresponding artery, the left colic artery.

name: right colic vein
description: A portal vein that drains the ascending colon. It is a tributary of the superior mesenteric vein, and travels with its corresponding artery, the right colic artery.

name: jejuno-ileal junction
description: The area where the jejunum ends and the ileum part of the intestine begins. Although there is no clear distinct section, the ileum is narrower and has smaller villi than the jejunum.

name: inguinal region skin
description: The skin covering the inguinal region between the abdomen and the thigh on either side of the pubic bone.
synonyms: ["groin skin","inguinal skin","skin of groin","skin of inguinal region","zone of skin of groin","zone of skin of inguinal region"]

name: left colic artery
description: The first branch of the inferior mesenteric artery (IMA) is the left colic artery. The left colic artery supplies blood flow to the distal third of the transverse colon and the entirety of the descending colon. Once diverging from the IMA, the left colic artery runs anterior to the left ureter, left internal spermatic vessels (males), and psoas major before branching into its ascending and descending segments.

name: right colic artery
description: The right colic artery may arise directly from the superior mesenteric artery (SMA) but often arises from a common trunk with the ileocolic artery or middle colic artery. It supplies the ascending colon.

name: intestinal junction
description: An anatomical junction between two parts of the intestine.

name: transition zone of prostate
description: The region of the prostate gland anterior to the central and peripheral zones, surrounding the proximal urethra. It is the zone of the human prostate gland that grows the most throughout life, and is responsible for benign prostatic hypertrophy.

name: peripheral zone of prostate
description: The region of the prostate that is located posterior to the central and transition zones, surrounding the distal urethra. It is the zone of origin for the vast majority of human prostatic cancers.

name: central zone of prostate
description: The region of the prostate gland that is located between the peripheral and transition zones, surrounding the ejaculatory ducts. It gives rise to a very small percentage of human prostate cancers, often aggressive and invading the seminal vesicles.

name: lymph node vein
description: A vein where lymph node venules condense and which exits at the lymph node hilum. It is also called hilar vein.
synonyms: ["hilar vein of lymph node","vein of lymph node"]

name: lymph node artery
description: An artery that enters the lymph node at the hilum and branches into smaller arterioles.
synonyms: ["artery of lymph node","hilar artery of lymph node"]
